[(163, "'List<Future<Integer>> whenFileIsCopied100TimesConcurrently(final File file) throws InterruptedException {\\n        List<Callable<Integer>> r = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {\\n            r.add(() -> {\\n                class Sink extends OutputStream {\\n                    private Exception closed;\\n                    private final AtomicInteger count = new AtomicInteger();\\n\\n                    private void checkNotClosed() throws IOException {\\n                        if (closed != null)\\n                            throw new IOException(closed);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void write(int b) throws IOException {\\n                        count.incrementAndGet();\\n                        checkNotClosed();\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void write(byte[] b) throws IOException {\\n                        count.addAndGet(b.length);\\n                        checkNotClosed();\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void write(byte[] b, int off, int len) throws IOException {\\n                        count.addAndGet(len);\\n                        checkNotClosed();\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void close() {\\n                        closed = new Exception();\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                FilePath f = new FilePath(channels.french, file.getPath());\\n                Sink sink = new Sink();\\n                f.copyTo(sink);\\n                return sink.count.get();\\n            });\\n        }\\n\\n        ExecutorService es = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(100);\\n        try {\\n            return es.invokeAll(r);\\n        } finally {\\n            es.shutdown();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(510, "'R getByNumber(int n) {\\n        Index snapshot = index;\\n        if (snapshot.byNumber.containsKey(n)) {\\n            BuildReference<R> ref = snapshot.byNumber.get(n);\\n            if (ref == null)      return null;    // known failure\\n            R v = unwrap(ref);\\n            if (v != null)        return v;       // already in memory\\n            // otherwise fall through to load\\n        }\\n        synchronized (this) {\\n            if (index.byNumber.containsKey(n)) { // JENKINS-22767: recheck inside lock\\n                BuildReference<R> ref = index.byNumber.get(n);\\n                if (ref == null) {\\n                    return null;\\n                }\\n                R v = unwrap(ref);\\n                if (v != null) {\\n                    return v;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return load(n, null);\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(299, "'boolean isValidDomainSyntax(String domain) {\\n        if (domain == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        domain = unicodeToASCII(domain);\\n        // hosts must be equally reachable via punycode and Unicode;\\n        // Unicode is never shorter than punycode, so check punycode\\n        // if domain did not convert, then it will be caught by ASCII\\n        // checks in the regexes below\\n        if (domain.length() > MAX_DOMAIN_LENGTH) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        String[] groups = domainRegex.match(domain);\\n        return (groups != null && groups.length > 0)\\n                || hostnameRegex.isValid(domain);\\n    }'")]

[(879, "'HttpResponse doStopBuild(@CheckForNull @QueryParameter(fixEmpty = true) String runExtId) {\\n        lock.writeLock().lock(); // need write lock as interrupt will change the field\\n        try {\\n            if (executable != null) {\\n                if (runExtId == null || runExtId.isEmpty() || ! (executable instanceof Run)\\n                        || (runExtId.equals(((Run<?, ?>) executable).getExternalizableId()))) {\\n                    final Queue.Task ownerTask = getParentOf(executable).getOwnerTask();\\n                    boolean canAbort = ownerTask.hasAbortPermission();\\n                    if (canAbort && ownerTask instanceof AccessControlled) {\\n                        if (!((AccessControlled) ownerTask).hasPermission(Item.READ)) {\\n                            // pretend the build does not exist\\n                            return HttpResponses.forwardToPreviousPage();\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                    ownerTask.checkAbortPermission();\\n                    interrupt();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } finally {\\n            lock.writeLock().unlock();\\n        }\\n        return HttpResponses.forwardToPreviousPage();\\n    }'")]

[(1599, '\'Descriptor getDescriptor(String id) {\\n        // legacy descriptors that are registered manually doesn\\\'t show up in getExtensionList, so check them explicitly.\\n        Iterable<Descriptor> descriptors = Iterators.sequence(getExtensionList(Descriptor.class), DescriptorExtensionList.listLegacyInstances());\\n        for (Descriptor d : descriptors) {\\n            if (d.getId().equals(id)) {\\n                return d;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        Descriptor candidate = null;\\n        for (Descriptor d : descriptors) {\\n            String name = d.getId();\\n            if (name.substring(name.lastIndexOf(\\\'.\\\') + 1).equals(id)) {\\n                if (candidate == null) {\\n                    candidate = d;\\n                } else {\\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException(id + " is ambiguous; matches both " + name + " and " + candidate.getId());\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return candidate;\\n    }\'')]

[(185, '\'void doCreate(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp,\\n                                          @QueryParameter String name, @QueryParameter String mode,\\n                                          @QueryParameter String from) throws IOException, ServletException, Descriptor.FormException {\\n        final Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.get();\\n        jenkins.checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n\\n        if (mode != null && mode.equals("copy")) {\\n            name = checkName(name);\\n\\n            Cloud src = jenkins.getCloud(from);\\n            if (src == null) {\\n                if (Util.fixEmpty(from) == null) {\\n                    throw new Failure(Messages.CloudSet_SpecifyCloudToCopy());\\n                } else {\\n                    throw new Failure(Messages.CloudSet_NoSuchCloud(from));\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            // copy through XStream\\n            String xml = Jenkins.XSTREAM.toXML(src);\\n            // Not great, but cloud name is final\\n            xml = xml.replace("<name>" + src.name + "</name>", "<name>" + name + "</name>");\\n            Cloud result = (Cloud) Jenkins.XSTREAM.fromXML(xml);\\n            jenkins.clouds.add(result);\\n            // send the browser to the config page\\n            rsp.sendRedirect2(Functions.getNearestAncestorUrl(req, jenkins) + "/" + result.getUrl() + "configure");\\n        } else {\\n            // proceed to step 2\\n            if (mode == null) {\\n                throw new Failure("No mode given");\\n            }\\n\\n            Descriptor<Cloud> d = Cloud.all().findByName(mode);\\n            if (d == null) {\\n                throw new Failure("No node type ‘" + mode + "’ is known");\\n            }\\n            handleNewCloudPage(d, name, req, rsp);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(281, '\'boolean replaceActions(@NonNull Class<? extends Action> clazz, @NonNull Action a) {\\n        if (clazz == null) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Action type must be non-null");\\n        }\\n        if (a == null) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Action must be non-null");\\n        }\\n        // CopyOnWriteArrayList does not support Iterator.remove, so need to do it this way:\\n        List<Action> old = new ArrayList<>();\\n        List<Action> current = getActions();\\n        boolean found = false;\\n        for (Action a1 : current) {\\n            if (!found) {\\n                if (a.equals(a1)) {\\n                    found = true;\\n                } else if (clazz.isInstance(a1)) {\\n                    old.add(a1);\\n                }\\n            } else if (clazz.isInstance(a1) && !a.equals(a1)) {\\n                old.add(a1);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        current.removeAll(old);\\n        if (!found) {\\n            addAction(a);\\n        }\\n        return !(old.isEmpty() && found);\\n    }\'')]

[(375, '\'void checkTarUntarRoundTrip(String filePrefix, long fileSize) throws Exception {\\n        final File tmpDir = temp.newFolder(filePrefix);\\n        final File tempFile =  new File(tmpDir, filePrefix + ".log");\\n        RandomAccessFile file = new RandomAccessFile(tempFile, "rw");\\n        final File tarFile = new File(tmpDir, filePrefix + ".tar");\\n\\n        file.setLength(fileSize);\\n        assumeTrue(fileSize == file.length());\\n        file.close();\\n\\n        // Compress archive\\n        final FilePath tmpDirPath = new FilePath(tmpDir);\\n        int tar = tmpDirPath.tar(Files.newOutputStream(tarFile.toPath()), tempFile.getName());\\n        assertEquals("One file should have been compressed", 1, tar);\\n\\n        // Decompress\\n        FilePath outDir = new FilePath(temp.newFolder(filePrefix + "_out"));\\n        final FilePath outFile = outDir.child(tempFile.getName());\\n        tmpDirPath.child(tarFile.getName()).untar(outDir, TarCompression.NONE);\\n        assertEquals("Result file after the roundtrip differs from the initial file",\\n                new FilePath(tempFile).digest(), outFile.digest());\\n    }\'')]

[(1356, '\'PollingResult _poll(TaskListener listener, SCM scm) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        if (scm.requiresWorkspaceForPolling()) {\\n            R b = getSomeBuildWithExistingWorkspace();\\n            if (b == null) b = getLastBuild();\\n            // lock the workspace for the given build\\n            FilePath ws = b.getWorkspace();\\n\\n            WorkspaceOfflineReason workspaceOfflineReason = workspaceOffline(b);\\n            if (workspaceOfflineReason != null) {\\n                // workspace offline\\n                for (WorkspaceBrowser browser : ExtensionList.lookup(WorkspaceBrowser.class)) {\\n                    ws = browser.getWorkspace(this);\\n                    if (ws != null) {\\n                        return pollWithWorkspace(listener, scm, b, ws, browser.getWorkspaceList());\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                // At this point we start thinking about triggering a build just to get a workspace,\\n                // because otherwise there\\\'s no way we can detect changes.\\n                // However, first there are some conditions in which we do not want to do so.\\n                // give time for agents to come online if we are right after reconnection (JENKINS-8408)\\n                long running = Jenkins.get().getInjector().getInstance(Uptime.class).getUptime();\\n                long remaining = TimeUnit.MINUTES.toMillis(10) - running;\\n                if (remaining > 0 && /* this logic breaks tests of polling */!Functions.getIsUnitTest()) {\\n                    listener.getLogger().print(Messages.AbstractProject_AwaitingWorkspaceToComeOnline(remaining / 1000));\\n                    listener.getLogger().println(" (" + workspaceOfflineReason.name() + ")");\\n                    return NO_CHANGES;\\n                }\\n\\n                // Do not trigger build, if no suitable agent is online\\n                if (workspaceOfflineReason.equals(WorkspaceOfflineReason.all_suitable_nodes_are_offline)) {\\n                    // No suitable executor is online\\n                    listener.getLogger().print(Messages.AbstractProject_AwaitingWorkspaceToComeOnline(running / 1000));\\n                    listener.getLogger().println(" (" + workspaceOfflineReason.name() + ")");\\n                    return NO_CHANGES;\\n                }\\n\\n                Label label = getAssignedLabel();\\n                if (label != null && label.isSelfLabel()) {\\n                    // if the build is fixed on a node, then attempting a build will do us\\n                    // no good. We should just wait for the agent to come back.\\n                    listener.getLogger().print(Messages.AbstractProject_NoWorkspace());\\n                    listener.getLogger().println(" (" + workspaceOfflineReason.name() + ")");\\n                    return NO_CHANGES;\\n                }\\n\\n                listener.getLogger().println(ws == null\\n                    ? Messages.AbstractProject_WorkspaceOffline()\\n                    : Messages.AbstractProject_NoWorkspace());\\n                if (isInQueue()) {\\n                    listener.getLogger().println(Messages.AbstractProject_AwaitingBuildForWorkspace());\\n                    return NO_CHANGES;\\n                }\\n\\n                // build now, or nothing will ever be built\\n                listener.getLogger().print(Messages.AbstractProject_NewBuildForWorkspace());\\n                listener.getLogger().println(" (" + workspaceOfflineReason.name() + ")");\\n                return BUILD_NOW;\\n            } else {\\n                WorkspaceList l = b.getBuiltOn().toComputer().getWorkspaceList();\\n                return pollWithWorkspace(listener, scm, b, ws, l);\\n            }\\n\\n        } else {\\n            // polling without workspace\\n            LOGGER.fine("Polling SCM changes of " + getName());\\n            if (pollingBaseline == null) // see NOTE-NO-BASELINE above\\n                calcPollingBaseline(getLastBuild(), null, listener);\\n            PollingResult r = scm.poll(this, null, null, listener, pollingBaseline);\\n            pollingBaseline = r.remote;\\n            return r;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(159, '\'void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        LOGGER.entering(HudsonFilter.class.getName(), "doFilter");\\n\\n        // this is not the best place to do it, but doing it here makes the patch smaller.\\n        ((HttpServletResponse) response).setHeader("X-Content-Type-Options", "nosniff");\\n\\n        // to deal with concurrency, we need to capture the object.\\n        Filter f = filter;\\n\\n        if (f == null) {\\n            // Hudson is starting up.\\n            chain.doFilter(request, response);\\n        } else {\\n            f.doFilter(request, response, chain);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(109, '"boolean authenticationIsRequired(String username) {\\n        // Only reauthenticate if username doesn\'t match SecurityContextHolder and user isn\'t authenticated\\n        // (see SEC-53)\\n        Authentication existingAuth = SecurityContextHolder.getContext().getAuthentication();\\n\\n        if (existingAuth == null || !existingAuth.isAuthenticated()) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Limit username comparison to providers which use usernames (ie UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken)\\n        // (see SEC-348)\\n\\n        if (existingAuth instanceof UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken && !existingAuth.getName().equals(username)) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Handle unusual condition where an AnonymousAuthenticationToken is already present\\n        // This shouldn\'t happen very often, as BasicProcessingFilter is meant to be earlier in the filter\\n        // chain than AnonymousProcessingFilter. Nevertheless, presence of both an AnonymousAuthenticationToken\\n        // together with a BASIC authentication request header should indicate reauthentication using the\\n        // BASIC protocol is desirable. This behaviour is also consistent with that provided by form and digest,\\n        // both of which force re-authentication if the respective header is detected (and in doing so replace\\n        // any existing AnonymousAuthenticationToken). See SEC-610.\\n        return existingAuth instanceof AnonymousAuthenticationToken;\\n    }"')]

[(268, "'void removeNode(final @NonNull Node node) throws IOException {\\n        if (node == nodes.get(node.getNodeName())) {\\n            Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                @Override\\n                public void run() {\\n                    Computer c = node.toComputer();\\n                    if (c != null) {\\n                        c.recordTermination();\\n                        c.disconnect(OfflineCause.create(hudson.model.Messages._Hudson_NodeBeingRemoved()));\\n                    }\\n                    if (node == nodes.remove(node.getNodeName())) {\\n                        jenkins.updateComputerList();\\n                        jenkins.trimLabels(node);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            });\\n            // no need for a full save() so we just do the minimum\\n            Util.deleteRecursive(new File(getNodesDir(), node.getNodeName()));\\n\\n            NodeListener.fireOnDeleted(node);\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(597, '\'ScheduleResult scheduleInternal(Task p, int quietPeriod, List<Action> actions) {\\n        lock.lock();\\n        try { try {\\n            Calendar due = new GregorianCalendar();\\n            due.add(Calendar.SECOND, quietPeriod);\\n\\n            // Do we already have this task in the queue? Because if so, we won\\\'t schedule a new one.\\n            List<Item> duplicatesInQueue = new ArrayList<>();\\n            for (Item item : liveGetItems(p)) {\\n                boolean shouldScheduleItem = false;\\n                for (QueueAction action : item.getActions(QueueAction.class)) {\\n                    shouldScheduleItem |= action.shouldSchedule(actions);\\n                }\\n                for (QueueAction action : Util.filter(actions, QueueAction.class)) {\\n                    shouldScheduleItem |= action.shouldSchedule(new ArrayList<>(item.getAllActions()));\\n                }\\n                if (!shouldScheduleItem) {\\n                    duplicatesInQueue.add(item);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (duplicatesInQueue.isEmpty()) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "{0} added to queue", p);\\n\\n                // put the item in the queue\\n                WaitingItem added = new WaitingItem(due, p, actions);\\n                added.enter(this);\\n                scheduleMaintenance();   // let an executor know that a new item is in the queue.\\n                return ScheduleResult.created(added);\\n            }\\n\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "{0} is already in the queue", p);\\n\\n            // but let the actions affect the existing stuff.\\n            for (Item item : duplicatesInQueue) {\\n                for (FoldableAction a : Util.filter(actions, FoldableAction.class)) {\\n                    a.foldIntoExisting(item, p, actions);\\n                    if (LOGGER.isLoggable(Level.FINE)) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "after folding {0}, {1} includes {2}", new Object[] {a, item, item.getAllActions()});\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            boolean queueUpdated = false;\\n            for (WaitingItem wi : Util.filter(duplicatesInQueue, WaitingItem.class)) {\\n                // make sure to always use the shorter of the available due times\\n                if (wi.timestamp.before(due))\\n                    continue;\\n\\n                // waitingList is sorted, so when we change a timestamp we need to maintain order\\n                wi.leave(this);\\n                wi.timestamp = due;\\n                wi.enter(this);\\n                queueUpdated = true;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (queueUpdated) scheduleMaintenance();\\n\\n            // REVISIT: when there are multiple existing items in the queue that matches the incoming one,\\n            // whether the new one should affect all existing ones or not is debatable. I for myself\\n            // thought this would only affect one, so the code was bit of surprise, but I\\\'m keeping the current\\n            // behaviour.\\n            return ScheduleResult.existing(duplicatesInQueue.get(0));\\n        } finally { updateSnapshot(); } } finally {\\n            lock.unlock();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1318, '\'void doConfigSubmit(StaplerRequest req,\\n            StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException, FormException {\\n        checkPermission(CONFIGURE);\\n\\n        description = req.getParameter("description");\\n\\n        JSONObject json = req.getSubmittedForm();\\n\\n        try {\\n            try (BulkChange bc = new BulkChange(this)) {\\n                setDisplayName(json.optString("displayNameOrNull"));\\n\\n                logRotator = null;\\n\\n                DescribableList<JobProperty<?>, JobPropertyDescriptor> t = new DescribableList<>(NOOP, getAllProperties());\\n                JSONObject jsonProperties = json.optJSONObject("properties");\\n                if (jsonProperties != null) {\\n                  t.rebuild(req, jsonProperties, JobPropertyDescriptor.getPropertyDescriptors(Job.this.getClass()));\\n                } else {\\n                  t.clear();\\n                }\\n                properties.clear();\\n                for (JobProperty p : t) {\\n                    p.setOwner(this);\\n                    properties.add(p);\\n                }\\n\\n                submit(req, rsp);\\n                bc.commit();\\n            }\\n            ItemListener.fireOnUpdated(this);\\n\\n            final ProjectNamingStrategy namingStrategy = Jenkins.get().getProjectNamingStrategy();\\n                if (namingStrategy.isForceExistingJobs()) {\\n                    namingStrategy.checkName(getParent().getFullName(), name);\\n                }\\n                FormApply.success(".").generateResponse(req, rsp, null);\\n        } catch (JSONException e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "failed to parse " + json, e);\\n            sendError(e, req, rsp);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(106, '\'void readOperatingSystemList(String initialOperatingSystemJson) throws IOException {\\n        JSONArray systems = JSONArray.fromObject(initialOperatingSystemJson);\\n        if (systems.isEmpty()) {\\n            throw new IOException("Empty data set");\\n        }\\n        for (Object systemObj : systems) {\\n            if (!(systemObj instanceof JSONObject)) {\\n                throw new IOException("Wrong object type in data file");\\n            }\\n            JSONObject system = (JSONObject) systemObj;\\n\\n            if (!system.has("pattern")) {\\n                throw new IOException("Missing pattern in definition file");\\n            }\\n            String pattern = system.getString("pattern");\\n\\n            if (!system.has("endOfLife")) {\\n                throw new IOException("No end of life date for " + pattern);\\n            }\\n            LocalDate endOfLife = LocalDate.parse(system.getString("endOfLife"));\\n\\n            /* Start date defaults to 6 months before end of life */\\n            LocalDate startDate = system.has("start") ? LocalDate.parse(system.getString("start")) : endOfLife.minusMonths(6);\\n\\n            File dataFile = getDataFile(system);\\n\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, "Pattern {0} starts {1} and reaches end of life {2} from file {3}",\\n                    new Object[]{pattern, startDate, endOfLife, dataFile});\\n\\n            String name = readOperatingSystemName(dataFile, pattern);\\n            if (name.isEmpty()) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Pattern {0} did not match from file {1}",\\n                        new Object[]{pattern, dataFile});\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (startDate.isBefore(warningsStartDate)) {\\n                warningsStartDate = startDate;\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Warnings start date is now {0}", warningsStartDate);\\n            }\\n\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Matched operating system {0}", name);\\n            if (startDate.isBefore(LocalDate.now())) {\\n                this.operatingSystemName = name;\\n                this.documentationUrl = buildDocumentationUrl(this.operatingSystemName);\\n                this.endOfLifeDate = endOfLife.toString();\\n                if (endOfLife.isBefore(LocalDate.now())) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Operating system {0} is after end of life {1}",\\n                            new Object[]{name, endOfLife});\\n                    afterEndOfLifeDate = true;\\n                } else {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Operating system {0} started warnings {1} and reaches end of life {2}",\\n                            new Object[]{name, startDate, endOfLife});\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (lastLines != null) {\\n            // Discard the cached contents of the last read file\\n            lastLines.clear();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(372, '\'RunUrl decompose(StaplerRequest req) {\\n        List<Ancestor> ancestors = req.getAncestors();\\n\\n        // find the first and last Run instances\\n        Ancestor f = null, l = null;\\n        for (Ancestor anc : ancestors) {\\n            if (anc.getObject() instanceof Run) {\\n                if (f == null) f = anc;\\n                l = anc;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (l == null) return null;    // there was no Run object\\n\\n        String head = f.getPrev().getUrl() + \\\'/\\\';\\n        String base = l.getUrl();\\n\\n        String reqUri = req.getOriginalRequestURI();\\n        // Find "rest" or URI by removing N path components.\\n        // Not using reqUri.substring(f.getUrl().length()) to avoid mismatches due to\\n        // url-encoding or extra slashes.  Former may occur in Tomcat (despite the spec saying\\n        // this string is not decoded, Tomcat apparently decodes this string. You see \\\' \\\'\\n        // instead of \\\'%20\\\', which is what the browser has sent), latter may occur in some\\n        // proxy or URL-rewriting setups where extra slashes are inadvertently added.\\n        String furl = f.getUrl();\\n        int slashCount = 0;\\n        // Count components in ancestor URL\\n        for (int i = furl.indexOf(\\\'/\\\'); i >= 0; i = furl.indexOf(\\\'/\\\', i + 1)) slashCount++;\\n        // Remove that many from request URL, ignoring extra slashes\\n        String rest = reqUri.replaceFirst("(?:/+[^/]*){" + slashCount + "}", "");\\n\\n        return new RunUrl((Run) f.getObject(), head, base, rest);\\n    }\'')]

[(538, '\'HttpResponse doInstallStatus(StaplerRequest request) {\\n        try {\\n            String correlationId = request.getParameter("correlationId");\\n            Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\\n            response.put("state", Jenkins.get().getInstallState().name());\\n            List<Map<String, String>> installStates = new ArrayList<>();\\n            response.put("jobs", installStates);\\n            List<UpdateCenterJob> jobCopy = getJobs();\\n\\n            for (UpdateCenterJob job : jobCopy) {\\n                if (job instanceof InstallationJob) {\\n                    UUID jobCorrelationId = job.getCorrelationId();\\n                    if (correlationId == null || (jobCorrelationId != null && correlationId.equals(jobCorrelationId.toString()))) {\\n                        InstallationJob installationJob = (InstallationJob) job;\\n                        Map<String, String> pluginInfo = new LinkedHashMap<>();\\n                        pluginInfo.put("name", installationJob.plugin.name);\\n                        pluginInfo.put("version", installationJob.plugin.version);\\n                        pluginInfo.put("title", installationJob.plugin.title);\\n                        pluginInfo.put("installStatus", installationJob.status.getType());\\n                        pluginInfo.put("requiresRestart", Boolean.toString(installationJob.status.requiresRestart()));\\n                        if (jobCorrelationId != null) {\\n                            pluginInfo.put("correlationId", jobCorrelationId.toString());\\n                        }\\n                        installStates.add(pluginInfo);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return HttpResponses.okJSON(JSONObject.fromObject(response));\\n        } catch (RuntimeException e) {\\n            return HttpResponses.errorJSON(String.format("ERROR: %s", e.getMessage()));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(54, '\'String toHtml(MemoryUsage usage) {\\n        if (usage.availableSwapSpace == -1)\\n            return "N/A";\\n\\n       String humanReadableSpace = Functions.humanReadableByteSize(usage.availableSwapSpace);\\n\\n        long free = usage.availableSwapSpace;\\n        free /= 1024L;   // convert to KB\\n        free /= 1024L;   // convert to MB\\n        if (free > 256 || usage.totalSwapSpace < usage.availableSwapSpace * 5)\\n            return humanReadableSpace; // if we have more than 256MB free or less than 80% filled up, it\\\'s OK\\n\\n        // Otherwise considered dangerously low.\\n        return Util.wrapToErrorSpan(humanReadableSpace);\\n    }\'')]

[(111, "'void setNodes(final @NonNull Collection<? extends Node> nodes) throws IOException {\\n        Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n            @Override\\n            public void run() {\\n                Set<String> toRemove = new HashSet<>(Nodes.this.nodes.keySet());\\n                for (Node n : nodes) {\\n                    final String name = n.getNodeName();\\n                    toRemove.remove(name);\\n                    Nodes.this.nodes.put(name, n);\\n                }\\n                Nodes.this.nodes.keySet().removeAll(toRemove); // directory clean up will be handled by save\\n                jenkins.updateComputerList();\\n                jenkins.trimLabels();\\n            }\\n        });\\n        save();\\n    }'")]

[(1341, '\'Fingerprint load(@NonNull String id) throws IOException {\\n        long start = 0;\\n        if (logger.isLoggable(Level.FINE)) {\\n            start = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n        }\\n\\n        FingerprintStorage configuredFingerprintStorage = FingerprintStorage.get();\\n        FingerprintStorage fileFingerprintStorage = ExtensionList.lookupSingleton(FileFingerprintStorage.class);\\n\\n        Fingerprint loaded = configuredFingerprintStorage.load(id);\\n\\n        if (loaded == null && !(configuredFingerprintStorage instanceof FileFingerprintStorage) &&\\n                fileFingerprintStorage.isReady()) {\\n            loaded = fileFingerprintStorage.load(id);\\n            if (loaded != null) {\\n                initFacets(loaded);\\n                configuredFingerprintStorage.save(loaded);\\n                fileFingerprintStorage.delete(id);\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            initFacets(loaded);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (logger.isLoggable(Level.FINE)) {\\n            logger.fine("Loading fingerprint took " + (System.currentTimeMillis() - start) + "ms");\\n        }\\n\\n        return loaded;\\n    }\'')]

[(44, '\'void iteratePath(String exe, Helper helper) {\\n        exe = fixEmpty(exe);\\n        if (exe == null) {\\n            helper.ok(); // nothing entered yet\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (exe.indexOf(File.separatorChar) >= 0) {\\n            // this is full path\\n            if (checkPrefix(exe, helper))\\n                return;\\n\\n            helper.error("There\\\'s no such file: " + exe);\\n        } else {\\n            // look in PATH\\n            String path = EnvVars.masterEnvVars.get("PATH");\\n            String tokenizedPath;\\n            String delimiter = null;\\n            if (path != null) {\\n                StringBuilder tokenizedPathBuilder = new StringBuilder();\\n                for (String _dir : Util.tokenize(path.replace("\\\\\\\\", "\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), File.pathSeparator)) {\\n                    if (delimiter == null) {\\n                        delimiter = ", ";\\n                    }\\n                    else {\\n                        tokenizedPathBuilder.append(delimiter);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    tokenizedPathBuilder.append(_dir.replace(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', \\\'/\\\'));\\n\\n                    if (checkPrefix(_dir + File.separator + exe, helper))\\n                        return;\\n                }\\n                tokenizedPathBuilder.append(\\\'.\\\');\\n                tokenizedPath = tokenizedPathBuilder.toString();\\n            }\\n            else {\\n                tokenizedPath = "unavailable.";\\n            }\\n\\n            // didn\\\'t find it\\n            helper.error("There\\\'s no such executable " + exe + " in PATH: " + tokenizedPath);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(86, '\'Groovysh createShell(InputStream stdin, PrintStream stdout,\\n        PrintStream stderr) {\\n\\n        Binding binding = new Binding();\\n        // redirect "println" to the CLI\\n        Charset charset;\\n        try {\\n            charset = getClientCharset();\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new UncheckedIOException(e);\\n        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\\n        }\\n        binding.setProperty("out", new PrintWriter(new OutputStreamWriter(stdout, charset), true));\\n        binding.setProperty("hudson", Jenkins.get()); // backward compatibility\\n        binding.setProperty("jenkins", Jenkins.get());\\n\\n        IO io = new IO(new BufferedInputStream(stdin), stdout, stderr);\\n\\n        final ClassLoader cl = Jenkins.get().pluginManager.uberClassLoader;\\n        Closure registrar = new Closure(null, null) {\\n            private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\\n\\n            @SuppressWarnings("unused")\\n            @SuppressFBWarnings(value = "UMAC_UNCALLABLE_METHOD_OF_ANONYMOUS_CLASS", justification = "Closure invokes this via reflection")\\n            public Object doCall(Object[] args) {\\n                assert args.length == 1;\\n                assert args[0] instanceof Shell;\\n\\n                Shell shell = (Shell) args[0];\\n                XmlCommandRegistrar r = new XmlCommandRegistrar(shell, cl);\\n                r.register(GroovyshCommand.class.getResource("commands.xml"));\\n\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        };\\n        Groovysh shell = new Groovysh(cl, binding, io, registrar);\\n        shell.getImports().add("hudson.model.*");\\n        return shell;\\n    }\'')]

[(1701, '\'Runnable makeBuildable(final BuildableItem p) {\\n        if (p.task instanceof FlyweightTask) {\\n            String taskDisplayName = LOGGER.isLoggable(Level.FINEST) ? p.task.getFullDisplayName() : null;\\n            if (!isBlockedByShutdown(p.task)) {\\n\\n                Runnable runnable = makeFlyWeightTaskBuildable(p);\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, "Converting flyweight task: {0} into a BuildableRunnable", taskDisplayName);\\n                if (runnable != null) {\\n                    return runnable;\\n                }\\n\\n                //this is to solve JENKINS-30084: the task has to be buildable to force the provisioning of nodes.\\n                //if the execution gets here, it means the task could not be scheduled since the node\\n                //the task is supposed to run on is offline or not available.\\n                //Thus, the flyweighttask enters the buildables queue and will ask Jenkins to provision a node\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, "Flyweight task {0} is entering as buildable to provision a node.", taskDisplayName);\\n                return new BuildableRunnable(p);\\n            }\\n            // if the execution gets here, it means the task is blocked by shutdown and null is returned.\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, "Task {0} is blocked by shutdown.", taskDisplayName);\\n            return null;\\n        } else {\\n            // regular heavyweight task\\n            return new BuildableRunnable(p);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(852, '"String encode(@NonNull String s) {\\n        try {\\n            boolean escaped = false;\\n\\n            StringBuilder out = new StringBuilder(s.length());\\n\\n            ByteArrayOutputStream buf = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n            OutputStreamWriter w = new OutputStreamWriter(buf, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n\\n            for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {\\n                int c = s.charAt(i);\\n                if (c < 128 && c != \' \') {\\n                    out.append((char) c);\\n                } else {\\n                    // 1 char -> UTF8\\n                    w.write(c);\\n                    w.flush();\\n                    for (byte b : buf.toByteArray()) {\\n                        out.append(\'%\');\\n                        out.append(toDigit((b >> 4) & 0xF));\\n                        out.append(toDigit(b & 0xF));\\n                    }\\n                    buf.reset();\\n                    escaped = true;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            return escaped ? out.toString() : s;\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new Error(e); // impossible\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(116, '\'void onLoginSuccess(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response,\\n            Authentication successfulAuthentication) {\\n        // Exit if the principal hasn\\\'t asked to be remembered\\n        if (!rememberMeRequested(request, getParameter())) {\\n            if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {\\n                logger.debug("Did not send remember-me cookie (principal did not set parameter \\\'" +\\n                        getParameter() + "\\\')");\\n            }\\n\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n        if (j != null && j.isDisableRememberMe()) {\\n            if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {\\n                logger.debug("Did not send remember-me cookie because \\\'Remember Me\\\' is disabled in " +\\n                        "security configuration (principal did set parameter \\\'" + getParameter() + "\\\')");\\n            }\\n            // TODO log warning when receiving remember-me request despite the feature being disabled?\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        // TODO is it really still necessary to reimplement all of the below, or could we simply override rememberMeRequested?\\n\\n        long expiryTime = System.currentTimeMillis() + TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(getTokenValiditySeconds());\\n        String username = successfulAuthentication.getName();\\n\\n        String signatureValue = makeTokenSignature(expiryTime, username);\\n        int tokenLifetime = calculateLoginLifetime(request, successfulAuthentication);\\n        setCookie(new String[] { username, Long.toString(expiryTime), signatureValue },\\n                tokenLifetime, request, response);\\n\\n        if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {\\n            logger.debug("Added remember-me cookie for user \\\'" + username + "\\\', expiry: \\\'" + new Date(expiryTime)\\n                            + "\\\'");\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(174, '\'UserDetails processAutoLoginCookie(String[] cookieTokens, HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) {\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n        if (j == null) {\\n            // as this filter could be called during restart, this corrects at least the symptoms\\n            throw new InvalidCookieException("Jenkins is not yet running");\\n        }\\n        if (j.isDisableRememberMe()) {\\n            cancelCookie(request, response);\\n            throw new InvalidCookieException("rememberMe is disabled");\\n        }\\n        if (cookieTokens.length != 3) {\\n            throw new InvalidCookieException(\\n                    "Cookie token did not contain 3" + " tokens, but contained \\\'" + Arrays.asList(cookieTokens) + "\\\'");\\n        }\\n        long tokenExpiryTime = getTokenExpiryTime(cookieTokens);\\n        if (isTokenExpired(tokenExpiryTime)) {\\n            throw new InvalidCookieException("Cookie token[1] has expired (expired on \\\'" + new Date(tokenExpiryTime)\\n                    + "\\\'; current time is \\\'" + new Date() + "\\\')");\\n        }\\n        // Check the user exists. Defer lookup until after expiry time checked, to\\n        // possibly avoid expensive database call.\\n        UserDetails userDetails = getUserDetailsService().loadUserByUsername(cookieTokens[0]);\\n        Objects.requireNonNull(userDetails, "UserDetailsService " + getUserDetailsService()\\n                + " returned null for username " + cookieTokens[0] + ". " + "This is an interface contract violation");\\n        // Check signature of token matches remaining details. Must do this after user\\n        // lookup, as we need the DAO-derived password. If efficiency was a major issue,\\n        // just add in a UserCache implementation, but recall that this method is usually\\n        // only called once per HttpSession - if the token is valid, it will cause\\n        // SecurityContextHolder population, whilst if invalid, will cause the cookie to\\n        // be cancelled.\\n        String expectedTokenSignature = makeTokenSignature(tokenExpiryTime, userDetails.getUsername());\\n        if (!equals(expectedTokenSignature, cookieTokens[2])) {\\n            throw new InvalidCookieException("Cookie token[2] contained signature \\\'" + cookieTokens[2]\\n                    + "\\\' but expected \\\'" + expectedTokenSignature + "\\\'");\\n        }\\n        return userDetails;\\n    }\'')]

[(152, '\'PluginWrapper createPluginWrapper(File archive) throws IOException {\\n        final Manifest manifest;\\n\\n        URL baseResourceURL;\\n        File expandDir = null;\\n        // if .hpi, this is the directory where war is expanded\\n\\n        boolean isLinked = isLinked(archive);\\n        if (isLinked) {\\n            manifest = loadLinkedManifest(archive);\\n        } else {\\n            if (archive.isDirectory()) { // already expanded\\n                expandDir = archive;\\n            } else {\\n                File f = pluginManager.getWorkDir();\\n                expandDir =  new File(f == null ? archive.getParentFile() : f, getBaseName(archive.getName()));\\n                explode(archive, expandDir);\\n            }\\n\\n            File manifestFile = new File(expandDir, PluginWrapper.MANIFEST_FILENAME);\\n            if (!manifestFile.exists()) {\\n                throw new IOException(\\n                        "Plugin installation failed. No manifest at "\\n                                + manifestFile);\\n            }\\n            try (InputStream fin = Files.newInputStream(manifestFile.toPath())) {\\n                manifest = new Manifest(fin);\\n            } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n                throw new IOException(e);\\n            }\\n            String canonicalName = manifest.getMainAttributes().getValue("Short-Name") + ".jpi";\\n            if (!archive.getName().equals(canonicalName)) {\\n                LOGGER.warning(() -> "encountered " + archive + " under a nonstandard name; expected " + canonicalName);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        final Attributes atts = manifest.getMainAttributes();\\n\\n        // TODO: define a mechanism to hide classes\\n        // String export = manifest.getMainAttributes().getValue("Export");\\n\\n        List<File> paths = new ArrayList<>();\\n        if (isLinked) {\\n            parseClassPath(manifest, archive, paths, "Libraries", ",");\\n            parseClassPath(manifest, archive, paths, "Class-Path", " +"); // backward compatibility\\n\\n            baseResourceURL = resolve(archive, atts.getValue("Resource-Path")).toURI().toURL();\\n        } else {\\n            File classes = new File(expandDir, "WEB-INF/classes");\\n            if (classes.exists()) { // should not normally happen, due to createClassJarFromWebInfClasses\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Deprecated unpacked classes directory found in {0}", classes);\\n                paths.add(classes);\\n            }\\n            File lib = new File(expandDir, "WEB-INF/lib");\\n            File[] libs = lib.listFiles(JAR_FILTER);\\n            if (libs != null)\\n                paths.addAll(Arrays.asList(libs));\\n\\n            baseResourceURL = expandDir.toPath().toUri().toURL();\\n\\n        }\\n        File disableFile = new File(archive.getPath() + ".disabled");\\n        if (disableFile.exists()) {\\n            LOGGER.info("Plugin " + archive.getName() + " is disabled");\\n        }\\n        if (paths.isEmpty()) {\\n            LOGGER.info("No classpaths found for plugin " + archive.getName());\\n        }\\n\\n        // compute dependencies\\n        List<PluginWrapper.Dependency> dependencies = new ArrayList<>();\\n        List<PluginWrapper.Dependency> optionalDependencies = new ArrayList<>();\\n        String v = atts.getValue("Plugin-Dependencies");\\n        if (v != null) {\\n            for (String s : v.split(",")) {\\n                PluginWrapper.Dependency d = new PluginWrapper.Dependency(s);\\n                if (d.optional) {\\n                    optionalDependencies.add(d);\\n                } else {\\n                    dependencies.add(d);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        fix(atts, optionalDependencies);\\n\\n        // Register global classpath mask. This is useful for hiding JavaEE APIs that you might see from the container,\\n        // such as database plugin for JPA support. The Mask-Classes attribute is insufficient because those classes\\n        // also need to be masked by all the other plugins that depend on the database plugin.\\n        String masked = atts.getValue("Global-Mask-Classes");\\n        if (masked != null) {\\n            for (String pkg : masked.trim().split("[ \\\\t\\\\r\\\\n]+"))\\n                coreClassLoader.add(pkg);\\n        }\\n\\n        ClassLoader dependencyLoader = new DependencyClassLoader(coreClassLoader, archive, Util.join(dependencies, optionalDependencies), pluginManager);\\n        dependencyLoader = getBaseClassLoader(atts, dependencyLoader);\\n\\n        return new PluginWrapper(pluginManager, archive, manifest, baseResourceURL,\\n                createClassLoader(paths, dependencyLoader, atts), disableFile, dependencies, optionalDependencies);\\n    }\'')]

[(78, '\'Channel forProcess(String name, ExecutorService execService, InputStream in, OutputStream out, OutputStream header, final Proc proc) throws IOException {\\n        ChannelBuilder cb = new ChannelBuilder(name, execService) {\\n            @Override\\n            public Channel build(CommandTransport transport) throws IOException {\\n                return new Channel(this, transport) {\\n                    /**\\n                     * Kill the process when the channel is severed.\\n                     */\\n                    @Override\\n                    public synchronized void terminate(IOException e) {\\n                        super.terminate(e);\\n                        try {\\n                            proc.kill();\\n                        } catch (IOException x) {\\n                            // we are already in the error recovery mode, so just record it and move on\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Failed to terminate the severed connection", x);\\n                        } catch (InterruptedException x) {\\n                            // process the interrupt later\\n                            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public synchronized void join() throws InterruptedException {\\n                        super.join();\\n                        // wait for the child process to complete, too\\n                        try {\\n                            proc.join();\\n                        } catch (IOException e) {\\n                            throw new IOError(e);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                };\\n            }\\n        };\\n        cb.withHeaderStream(header);\\n\\n        Executor executor = Executor.currentExecutor();\\n        Object context = executor != null ? executor.getOwner() : proc;\\n        for (ChannelConfigurator cc : ChannelConfigurator.all()) {\\n            cc.onChannelBuilding(cb, context);\\n        }\\n\\n        return cb.build(in, out);\\n    }\'')]

[(1402, '\'String getRelativeNameFrom(@CheckForNull Item p, @CheckForNull ItemGroup g, boolean useDisplayName) {\\n        if (p == null) return null;\\n        if (g == null) return useDisplayName ? p.getFullDisplayName() : p.getFullName();\\n        String separationString = useDisplayName ? " » " : "/";\\n\\n        // first list up all the parents\\n        Map<ItemGroup, Integer> parents = new HashMap<>();\\n        int depth = 0;\\n        while (g != null) {\\n            parents.put(g, depth++);\\n            if (g instanceof Item)\\n                g = ((Item) g).getParent();\\n            else\\n                g = null;\\n        }\\n\\n        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n        Item i = p;\\n        while (true) {\\n            if (buf.length() > 0) buf.insert(0, separationString);\\n            buf.insert(0, useDisplayName ? i.getDisplayName() : i.getName());\\n            ItemGroup gr = i.getParent();\\n\\n            Integer d = parents.get(gr);\\n            if (d != null) {\\n                for (int j = d; j > 0; j--) {\\n                    buf.insert(0, separationString);\\n                    buf.insert(0, "..");\\n                }\\n                return buf.toString();\\n            }\\n\\n            if (gr instanceof Item)\\n                i = (Item) gr;\\n            else // Parent is a group, but not an item\\n                return null;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1355, '\'void createSymlink(@NonNull File baseDir, @NonNull String targetPath,\\n            @NonNull String symlinkPath, @NonNull TaskListener listener) throws InterruptedException {\\n        File fileForSymlink = new File(baseDir, symlinkPath);\\n        try {\\n            Path pathForSymlink = fileToPath(fileForSymlink);\\n            Path target = Paths.get(targetPath, MemoryReductionUtil.EMPTY_STRING_ARRAY);\\n\\n            if (createSymlinkAtomic(pathForSymlink, fileForSymlink, target, symlinkPath)) {\\n                return;\\n            }\\n\\n            final int maxNumberOfTries = 4;\\n            final int timeInMillis = 100;\\n            for (int tryNumber = 1; tryNumber <= maxNumberOfTries; tryNumber++) {\\n                Files.deleteIfExists(pathForSymlink);\\n                try {\\n                    Files.createSymbolicLink(pathForSymlink, target);\\n                    break;\\n                } catch (FileAlreadyExistsException fileAlreadyExistsException) {\\n                    if (tryNumber < maxNumberOfTries) {\\n                        TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.sleep(timeInMillis); //trying to defeat likely ongoing race condition\\n                        continue;\\n                    }\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "symlink FileAlreadyExistsException thrown {0} times => cannot createSymbolicLink", maxNumberOfTries);\\n                    throw fileAlreadyExistsException;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException e) {\\n            PrintStream log = listener.getLogger();\\n            log.print("Symbolic links are not supported on this platform");\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, log);\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            if (Functions.isWindows() && e instanceof FileSystemException) {\\n                warnWindowsSymlink();\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            PrintStream log = listener.getLogger();\\n            log.printf("ln %s %s failed%n", targetPath, fileForSymlink);\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, log);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1068, '\'void copyBundledPlugin(URL src, String fileName) throws IOException {\\n        LOGGER.log(FINE, "Copying {0}", src);\\n        fileName = fileName.replace(".hpi", ".jpi"); // normalize fileNames to have the correct suffix\\n        String legacyName = fileName.replace(".jpi", ".hpi");\\n        long lastModified = getModificationDate(src);\\n        File file = new File(rootDir, fileName);\\n\\n        // normalization first, if the old file exists.\\n        rename(new File(rootDir, legacyName), file);\\n\\n        // update file if:\\n        //  - no file exists today\\n        //  - bundled version and current version differs (by timestamp).\\n        if (!file.exists() || file.lastModified() != lastModified) {\\n            FileUtils.copyURLToFile(src, file);\\n            Files.setLastModifiedTime(Util.fileToPath(file), FileTime.fromMillis(getModificationDate(src)));\\n            // lastModified is set for two reasons:\\n            // - to avoid unpacking as much as possible, but still do it on both upgrade and downgrade\\n            // - to make sure the value is not changed after each restart, so we can avoid\\n            // unpacking the plugin itself in ClassicPluginStrategy.explode\\n        }\\n\\n        // Plugin pinning has been deprecated.\\n        // See https://groups.google.com/d/msg/jenkinsci-dev/kRobm-cxFw8/6V66uhibAwAJ\\n    }\'')]

[(5055, "'Future<DependencyGraph> scheduleCalculationOfFutureDependencyGraph(int delay, TimeUnit unit) {\\n        return Timer.get().schedule(() -> {\\n            // Wait for the currently running calculation to finish without blocking rebuildDependencyGraphAsync()\\n            Future<DependencyGraph> temp = null;\\n            synchronized (dependencyGraphLock) {\\n                if (calculatingFutureDependencyGraph != null) {\\n                    temp = calculatingFutureDependencyGraph;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (temp != null) {\\n                temp.get();\\n            }\\n\\n            synchronized (dependencyGraphLock) {\\n                // Scheduled future becomes the currently calculating future\\n                calculatingFutureDependencyGraph = scheduledFutureDependencyGraph;\\n                scheduledFutureDependencyGraph = null;\\n            }\\n\\n            rebuildDependencyGraph();\\n\\n            synchronized (dependencyGraphLock) {\\n                calculatingFutureDependencyGraph = null;\\n            }\\n\\n            return dependencyGraph;\\n        }, delay, unit);\\n    }'")]

[(346, '\'int webSocketConnection(String url, List<String> args, CLIConnectionFactory factory) throws Exception {\\n        LOGGER.fine(() -> "Trying to connect to " + url + " via plain protocol over WebSocket");\\n        class CLIEndpoint extends Endpoint {\\n            @Override\\n            public void onOpen(Session session, EndpointConfig config) {}\\n        }\\n\\n        class Authenticator extends ClientEndpointConfig.Configurator {\\n            @Override\\n            public void beforeRequest(Map<String, List<String>> headers) {\\n                if (factory.authorization != null) {\\n                    headers.put("Authorization", List.of(factory.authorization));\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        ClientManager client = ClientManager.createClient(JdkClientContainer.class.getName()); // ~ ContainerProvider.getWebSocketContainer()\\n        client.getProperties().put(ClientProperties.REDIRECT_ENABLED, true); // https://tyrus-project.github.io/documentation/1.13.1/index/tyrus-proprietary-config.html#d0e1775\\n        Session session = client.connectToServer(new CLIEndpoint(), ClientEndpointConfig.Builder.create().configurator(new Authenticator()).build(), URI.create(url.replaceFirst("^http", "ws") + "cli/ws"));\\n        PlainCLIProtocol.Output out = new PlainCLIProtocol.Output() {\\n            @Override\\n            public void send(byte[] data) throws IOException {\\n                session.getBasicRemote().sendBinary(ByteBuffer.wrap(data));\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public void close() throws IOException {\\n                session.close();\\n            }\\n        };\\n        try (ClientSideImpl connection = new ClientSideImpl(out)) {\\n            session.addMessageHandler(InputStream.class, is -> {\\n                try {\\n                    connection.handle(new DataInputStream(is));\\n                } catch (IOException x) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, null, x);\\n                }\\n            });\\n            connection.start(args);\\n            return connection.exit();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(254, "'void makeRemovable(@NonNull Path path) throws IOException {\\n        if (!Files.isWritable(path)) {\\n            makeWritable(path);\\n        }\\n        /*\\n         on Unix both the file and the directory that contains it has to be writable\\n         for a file deletion to be successful. (Confirmed on Solaris 9)\\n\\n         $ ls -la\\n         total 6\\n         dr-xr-sr-x   2 hudson   hudson       512 Apr 18 14:41 .\\n         dr-xr-sr-x   3 hudson   hudson       512 Apr 17 19:36 ..\\n         -r--r--r--   1 hudson   hudson       469 Apr 17 19:36 manager.xml\\n         -rw-r--r--   1 hudson   hudson         0 Apr 18 14:41 x\\n         $ rm x\\n         rm: x not removed: Permission denied\\n         */\\n        Optional<Path> maybeParent = Optional.ofNullable(path.getParent()).map(Path::normalize).filter(p -> !Files.isWritable(p));\\n        if (maybeParent.isPresent()) {\\n            makeWritable(maybeParent.get());\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(108, '\'void onLoad(ItemGroup<? extends Item> parent, String name) throws IOException {\\n        RunMap<RunT> _builds = createBuildRunMap();\\n        int max = _builds.maxNumberOnDisk();\\n        int next = asJob().getNextBuildNumber();\\n        if (next <= max) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "JENKINS-27530: improper nextBuildNumber {0} detected in {1} with highest build number {2}; adjusting", new Object[] {next, asJob(), max});\\n            asJob().updateNextBuildNumber(max + 1);\\n        }\\n        RunMap<RunT> currentBuilds = this.builds;\\n        if (parent != null) {\\n            // are we overwriting what currently exist?\\n            // this is primarily when Jenkins is getting reloaded\\n            Item current;\\n            try {\\n                current = parent.getItem(name);\\n            } catch (RuntimeException x) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "failed to look up " + name + " in " + parent, x);\\n                current = null;\\n            }\\n            if (current != null && current.getClass() == asJob().getClass()) {\\n                currentBuilds = (RunMap<RunT>) ((LazyLoadingJob) current).getLazyBuildMixIn().builds;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (currentBuilds != null) {\\n            // if we are reloading, keep all those that are still building intact\\n            for (RunT r : currentBuilds.getLoadedBuilds().values()) {\\n                if (r.isBuilding()) {\\n                    // Do not use RunMap.put(Run):\\n                    _builds.put(r.getNumber(), r);\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "keeping reloaded {0}", r);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        this.builds = _builds;\\n    }\'')]

[(179, "'void perform(Run<?, ?> build, FilePath workspace, EnvVars environment, Launcher launcher, TaskListener listener) throws InterruptedException {\\n        try {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(Messages.Fingerprinter_Recording());\\n\\n            Map<String, String> record = new HashMap<>();\\n\\n            if (targets.length() != 0) {\\n                String expandedTargets = targets;\\n                if (build instanceof AbstractBuild) { // no expansion for pipelines\\n                    expandedTargets = environment.expand(expandedTargets);\\n                }\\n                record(build, workspace, listener, record, expandedTargets);\\n            }\\n\\n            FingerprintAction fingerprintAction = build.getAction(FingerprintAction.class);\\n            if (fingerprintAction != null) {\\n                fingerprintAction.add(record);\\n            } else {\\n                build.addAction(new FingerprintAction(build, record));\\n            }\\n\\n            if (enableFingerprintsInDependencyGraph) {\\n                Jenkins.get().rebuildDependencyGraphAsync();\\n            }\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.error(Messages.Fingerprinter_Failed()));\\n            build.setResult(Result.FAILURE);\\n        }\\n\\n        // failing to record fingerprints is an error but not fatal\\n    }'")]

[(1331, '\'String getRelativeLinkTo(Item p) {\\n        Map<Object, String> ancestors = new HashMap<>();\\n        View view = null;\\n\\n        StaplerRequest request = Stapler.getCurrentRequest();\\n        for (Ancestor a : request.getAncestors()) {\\n            ancestors.put(a.getObject(), a.getRelativePath());\\n            if (a.getObject() instanceof View)\\n                view = (View) a.getObject();\\n        }\\n\\n        String path = ancestors.get(p);\\n        if (path != null) {\\n            return normalizeURI(path + \\\'/\\\');\\n        }\\n\\n        Item i = p;\\n        String url = "";\\n        while (true) {\\n            ItemGroup ig = i.getParent();\\n            url = i.getShortUrl() + url;\\n\\n            if (ig == Jenkins.get() || (view != null && ig == view.getOwner().getItemGroup())) {\\n                assert i instanceof TopLevelItem;\\n                if (view != null) {\\n                    // assume p and the current page belong to the same view, so return a relative path\\n                    // (even if they did not, View.getItem does not by default verify ownership)\\n                    return normalizeURI(ancestors.get(view) + \\\'/\\\' + url);\\n                } else {\\n                    // otherwise return a path from the root Hudson\\n                    return normalizeURI(request.getContextPath() + \\\'/\\\' + p.getUrl());\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            path = ancestors.get(ig);\\n            if (path != null) {\\n                return normalizeURI(path + \\\'/\\\' + url);\\n            }\\n\\n            assert ig instanceof Item; // if not, ig must have been the Hudson instance\\n            i = (Item) ig;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(222, '\'Channel newJVM(String displayName, TaskListener listener, JVMBuilder vmb, FilePath workDir, ClasspathBuilder classpath) throws IOException {\\n        ServerSocket serverSocket = new ServerSocket();\\n        serverSocket.bind(new InetSocketAddress("localhost", 0));\\n        serverSocket.setSoTimeout((int) TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(10));\\n\\n        // use -cp + FQCN instead of -jar since remoting.jar can be rebundled (like in the case of the swarm plugin.)\\n        vmb.classpath().addJarOf(Channel.class);\\n        vmb.mainClass(Launcher.class);\\n\\n        if (classpath != null)\\n            Arrays.stream(classpath.toString().split(File.pathSeparator)).forEach(arg -> vmb.classpath().add(arg));\\n        vmb.args().add("-connectTo", "localhost:" + serverSocket.getLocalPort());\\n\\n        listener.getLogger().println("Starting " + displayName);\\n        Proc p = vmb.launch(new LocalLauncher(listener)).stdout(listener).pwd(workDir).start();\\n\\n        Socket s = serverSocket.accept();\\n        serverSocket.close();\\n\\n        return forProcess("Channel to " + displayName, Computer.threadPoolForRemoting,\\n                new BufferedInputStream(SocketChannelStream.in(s)),\\n                new BufferedOutputStream(SocketChannelStream.out(s)), null, p);\\n    }\'')]

[(3045, '\'Item getItem(String pathName, ItemGroup context) {\\n        if (context == null)  context = this;\\n        if (pathName == null) return null;\\n\\n        if (pathName.startsWith("/"))   // absolute\\n            return getItemByFullName(pathName);\\n\\n        Object/*Item|ItemGroup*/ ctx = context;\\n\\n        StringTokenizer tokens = new StringTokenizer(pathName, "/");\\n        while (tokens.hasMoreTokens()) {\\n            String s = tokens.nextToken();\\n            if (s.equals("..")) {\\n                if (ctx instanceof Item) {\\n                    ctx = ((Item) ctx).getParent();\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n\\n                ctx = null;    // can\\\'t go up further\\n                break;\\n            }\\n            if (s.equals(".")) {\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (ctx instanceof ItemGroup) {\\n                ItemGroup g = (ItemGroup) ctx;\\n                Item i = g.getItem(s);\\n                if (i == null || !i.hasPermission(Item.READ)) { // TODO consider DISCOVER\\n                    ctx = null;    // can\\\'t go up further\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                ctx = i;\\n            } else {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (ctx instanceof Item)\\n            return (Item) ctx;\\n\\n        // fall back to the classic interpretation\\n        return getItemByFullName(pathName);\\n    }\'')]

[(1430, '\'PollingResult pollWithWorkspace(TaskListener listener, SCM scm, R lb, @NonNull FilePath ws, WorkspaceList l) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        // if doing non-concurrent build, acquire a workspace in a way that causes builds to block for this workspace.\\n        // this prevents multiple workspaces of the same job --- the behavior of Hudson < 1.319.\\n        //\\n        // OTOH, if a concurrent build is chosen, the user is willing to create a multiple workspace,\\n        // so better throughput is achieved over time (modulo the initial cost of creating that many workspaces)\\n        // by having multiple workspaces\\n        Node node = lb.getBuiltOn();\\n        Launcher launcher = ws.createLauncher(listener).decorateByEnv(getEnvironment(node, listener));\\n        WorkspaceList.Lease lease = l.acquire(ws, !concurrentBuild);\\n        try {\\n            String nodeName = node != null ? node.getSelfLabel().getName() : "[node_unavailable]";\\n            listener.getLogger().println("Polling SCM changes on " + nodeName);\\n            LOGGER.fine("Polling SCM changes of " + getName());\\n            if (pollingBaseline == null) // see NOTE-NO-BASELINE above\\n                calcPollingBaseline(lb, launcher, listener);\\n            PollingResult r = scm.poll(this, launcher, ws, listener, pollingBaseline);\\n            pollingBaseline = r.remote;\\n            return r;\\n        } finally {\\n            lease.release();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(57, '\'FormValidation verifySignature(JSONObject o) throws IOException {\\n        try {\\n            FormValidation warning = null;\\n\\n            JSONObject signature = o.getJSONObject("signature");\\n            if (signature.isNullObject()) {\\n                return FormValidation.error("No signature block found in " + name);\\n            }\\n            o.remove("signature");\\n\\n            List<X509Certificate> certs = new ArrayList<>();\\n            { // load and verify certificates\\n                CertificateFactory cf = CertificateFactory.getInstance("X509");\\n                for (Object cert : signature.getJSONArray("certificates")) {\\n                    try {\\n                        X509Certificate c = (X509Certificate) cf.generateCertificate(new ByteArrayInputStream(Base64.getDecoder().decode(cert.toString().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))));\\n                        try {\\n                            c.checkValidity();\\n                        } catch (CertificateExpiredException e) { // even if the certificate isn\\\'t valid yet, we\\\'ll proceed it anyway\\n                            warning = FormValidation.warning(e, String.format("Certificate %s has expired in %s", cert, name));\\n                        } catch (CertificateNotYetValidException e) {\\n                            warning = FormValidation.warning(e, String.format("Certificate %s is not yet valid in %s", cert, name));\\n                        }\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Add certificate found in JSON document:\\\\n\\\\tsubjectDN: {0}\\\\n\\\\tissuer: {1}\\\\n\\\\tnotBefore: {2}\\\\n\\\\tnotAfter: {3}",\\n                                new Object[] { c.getSubjectDN(), c.getIssuerDN(), c.getNotBefore(), c.getNotAfter() });\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, () -> "Certificate from JSON document: " + c);\\n                        certs.add(c);\\n                    } catch (IllegalArgumentException ex) {\\n                        throw new IOException("Could not decode certificate", ex);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                CertificateUtil.validatePath(certs, loadTrustAnchors(cf));\\n            }\\n\\n            if (certs.isEmpty()) {\\n                return FormValidation.error("No certificate found in %s. Cannot verify the signature", name);\\n            }\\n\\n            // check the better digest first\\n            FormValidation resultSha512 = null;\\n            try {\\n                MessageDigest digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-512");\\n                Signature sig = Signature.getInstance("SHA512withRSA");\\n                sig.initVerify(certs.get(0));\\n                resultSha512 = checkSpecificSignature(o, signature, digest, "correct_digest512", sig, "correct_signature512", "SHA-512");\\n                switch (resultSha512.kind) {\\n                    case ERROR:\\n                        return resultSha512;\\n                    case WARNING:\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "JSON data source \\\'" + name + "\\\' does not provide a SHA-512 content checksum or signature. Looking for SHA-1.");\\n                        break;\\n                    case OK:\\n                        break;\\n                    default:\\n                        throw new AssertionError("Unknown form validation kind: " + resultSha512.kind);\\n                }\\n            } catch (NoSuchAlgorithmException nsa) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to verify potential SHA-512 digest/signature, falling back to SHA-1", nsa);\\n            }\\n\\n            // if we get here, SHA-512 passed, wasn\\\'t provided, or the JRE is terrible.\\n\\n            MessageDigest digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA1");\\n            Signature sig = Signature.getInstance("SHA1withRSA");\\n            sig.initVerify(certs.get(0));\\n            FormValidation resultSha1 = checkSpecificSignature(o, signature, digest, "correct_digest", sig, "correct_signature", "SHA-1");\\n\\n            switch (resultSha1.kind) {\\n                case ERROR:\\n                    return resultSha1;\\n                case WARNING:\\n                    if (resultSha512.kind == FormValidation.Kind.WARNING) {\\n                        // neither signature provided\\n                        return FormValidation.error("No correct_signature or correct_signature512 entry found in \\\'" + name + "\\\'.");\\n                    }\\n                case OK:\\n                    break;\\n                default:\\n                    throw new AssertionError("Unknown form validation kind: " + resultSha1.kind);\\n            }\\n\\n            if (warning != null)  return warning;\\n            return FormValidation.ok();\\n        } catch (GeneralSecurityException e) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(e, "Signature verification failed in " + name);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(563, '\'String hashify(String spec) {\\n        if (spec.contains("H")) {\\n            // if someone is already using H, presumably he knows what it is, so a warning is likely false positive\\n            return null;\\n        } else if (spec.startsWith("*/")) { // "*/15 ...." (every N minutes) to hash\\n            return "H" + spec.substring(1);\\n        } else if (spec.matches("\\\\\\\\d+ .+")) { // "0 ..." (certain minute) to hash\\n            return "H " + spec.substring(spec.indexOf(\\\' \\\') + 1);\\n        } else {\\n            Matcher m = Pattern.compile("0(,(\\\\\\\\d+)(,\\\\\\\\d+)*)( .+)").matcher(spec);\\n            if (m.matches()) { // 0,15,30,45 to H/15\\n                int period = Integer.parseInt(m.group(2));\\n                if (period > 0) {\\n                    StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\\n                    for (int i = period; i < 60; i += period) {\\n                        b.append(\\\',\\\').append(i);\\n                    }\\n                    if (b.toString().equals(m.group(1))) {\\n                        return "H/" + period + m.group(4);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(86, '\'void eol(byte[] in, int sz) throws IOException {\\n        line.reset();\\n        final StringBuffer strBuf = line.getStringBuffer();\\n\\n        int next = ConsoleNote.findPreamble(in, 0, sz);\\n\\n        List<ConsoleAnnotator<T>> annotators = null;\\n\\n        { // perform byte[]->char[] while figuring out the char positions of the BLOBs\\n            int written = 0;\\n            while (next >= 0) {\\n                if (next > written) {\\n                    lineOut.write(in, written, next - written);\\n                    lineOut.flush();\\n                    written = next;\\n                } else {\\n                    assert next == written;\\n                }\\n\\n                // character position of this annotation in this line\\n                final int charPos = strBuf.length();\\n\\n                int rest = sz - next;\\n                ByteArrayInputStream b = new ByteArrayInputStream(in, next, rest);\\n\\n                try {\\n                    final ConsoleNote a = ConsoleNote.readFrom(new DataInputStream(b));\\n                    if (a != null) {\\n                        if (annotators == null)\\n                            annotators = new ArrayList<>();\\n                        annotators.add(new ConsoleAnnotator<>() {\\n                            @Override\\n                            public ConsoleAnnotator<T> annotate(T context, MarkupText text) {\\n                                return a.annotate(context, text, charPos);\\n                            }\\n                        });\\n                    }\\n                } catch (IOException | ClassNotFoundException e) {\\n                    // if we failed to resurrect an annotation, ignore it.\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Failed to resurrect annotation from \\\\"" + StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava(new String(in, next, rest, Charset.defaultCharset())) + "\\\\"", e);\\n                }\\n\\n                int bytesUsed = rest - b.available(); // bytes consumed by annotations\\n                written += bytesUsed;\\n\\n\\n                next = ConsoleNote.findPreamble(in, written, sz - written);\\n            }\\n            // finish the remaining bytes->chars conversion\\n            lineOut.write(in, written, sz - written);\\n\\n            if (annotators != null) {\\n                // aggregate newly retrieved ConsoleAnnotators into the current one.\\n                if (ann != null)      annotators.add(ann);\\n                ann = ConsoleAnnotator.combine(annotators);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        lineOut.flush();\\n        MarkupText mt = new MarkupText(strBuf.toString());\\n        if (ann != null)\\n            ann = ann.annotate(context, mt);\\n        out.write(mt.toString(true)); // this perform escapes\\n    }\'')]
