[(291, '\'boolean perform(AbstractBuild<?, ?> build, Launcher launcher, BuildListener listener) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        VariableResolver<String> vr = build.getBuildVariableResolver();\\n\\n        EnvVars env = build.getEnvironment(listener);\\n\\n        String targets = Util.replaceMacro(this.targets, vr);\\n        targets = env.expand(targets);\\n        String pom = env.expand(this.pom);\\n\\n        int startIndex = 0;\\n        int endIndex;\\n        do {\\n            // split targets into multiple invocations of maven separated by |\\n            endIndex = targets.indexOf(\\\'|\\\', startIndex);\\n            if (-1 == endIndex) {\\n                endIndex = targets.length();\\n            }\\n\\n            String normalizedTarget = targets\\n                    .substring(startIndex, endIndex)\\n                    .replaceAll("[\\\\t\\\\r\\\\n]+", " ");\\n\\n            ArgumentListBuilder args = new ArgumentListBuilder();\\n            MavenInstallation mi = getMaven();\\n            if (mi == null) {\\n                String execName = build.getWorkspace().act(new DecideDefaultMavenCommand(normalizedTarget));\\n                args.add(execName);\\n            } else {\\n                mi = mi.forNode(Computer.currentComputer().getNode(), listener);\\n                mi = mi.forEnvironment(env);\\n                String exec = mi.getExecutable(launcher);\\n                if (exec == null) {\\n                    listener.fatalError(Messages.Maven_NoExecutable(mi.getHome()));\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n                args.add(exec);\\n            }\\n            if (pom != null)\\n                args.add("-f", pom);\\n\\n\\n            if (!S_PATTERN.matcher(targets).find()) { // check the given target/goals do not contain settings parameter already\\n                String settingsPath = SettingsProvider.getSettingsRemotePath(getSettings(), build, listener);\\n                if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(settingsPath)) {\\n                    args.add("-s", settingsPath);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (!GS_PATTERN.matcher(targets).find()) {\\n                String settingsPath = GlobalSettingsProvider.getSettingsRemotePath(getGlobalSettings(), build, listener);\\n                if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(settingsPath)) {\\n                    args.add("-gs", settingsPath);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            Set<String> sensitiveVars = build.getSensitiveBuildVariables();\\n\\n            // Inject environment variables only if chosen to do so\\n            if (isInjectBuildVariables()) {\\n                args.addKeyValuePairs("-D", build.getBuildVariables(), sensitiveVars);\\n            }\\n\\n            // Add properties from builder configuration, AFTER the injected build variables.\\n            final VariableResolver<String> resolver = new Union<>(new ByMap<>(env), vr);\\n            args.addKeyValuePairsFromPropertyString("-D", this.properties, resolver, sensitiveVars);\\n\\n            if (usesPrivateRepository())\\n                args.add("-Dmaven.repo.local=" + build.getWorkspace().child(".repository"));\\n            args.addTokenized(normalizedTarget);\\n            wrapUpArguments(args, normalizedTarget, build, launcher, listener);\\n\\n            buildEnvVars(env, mi);\\n\\n            if (!launcher.isUnix()) {\\n                args = args.toWindowsCommand();\\n            }\\n\\n            try {\\n                MavenConsoleAnnotator mca = new MavenConsoleAnnotator(listener.getLogger(), build.getCharset());\\n                int r = launcher.launch().cmds(args).envs(env).stdout(mca).pwd(build.getModuleRoot()).join();\\n                if (0 != r) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                Util.displayIOException(e, listener);\\n                Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.Maven_ExecFailed()));\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n            startIndex = endIndex + 1;\\n        } while (startIndex < targets.length());\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(89, '\'int compareTo(ExtensionComponent<T> that) {\\n        double a = this.ordinal();\\n        double b = that.ordinal();\\n        if (Double.compare(a, b) > 0) return -1;\\n        if (Double.compare(a, b) < 0) return 1;\\n\\n        boolean thisIsDescriptor = false;\\n        String thisLabel = this.instance.getClass().getName();\\n        if (this.instance instanceof Descriptor) {\\n            try {\\n                thisLabel = Util.fixNull(((Descriptor) this.instance).getDisplayName());\\n                thisIsDescriptor = true;\\n            } catch (RuntimeException | LinkageError x) {\\n                LOG.log(Level.WARNING, "Failure during Descriptor#getDisplayName for " + this.instance.getClass().getName(), x);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        boolean thatIsDescriptor = false;\\n        String thatLabel = that.instance.getClass().getName();\\n        if (that.instance instanceof Descriptor) {\\n            try {\\n                thatLabel = Util.fixNull(((Descriptor) that.instance).getDisplayName());\\n                thatIsDescriptor = true;\\n            } catch (RuntimeException | LinkageError x) {\\n                LOG.log(Level.WARNING, "Failure during Descriptor#getDisplayName for " + that.instance.getClass().getName(), x);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (thisIsDescriptor) {\\n            if (thatIsDescriptor) {\\n                return thisLabel.compareTo(thatLabel);\\n            } else {\\n                return 1;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            if (thatIsDescriptor) {\\n                return -1;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return thisLabel.compareTo(thatLabel);\\n    }\'')]

[(5446, '\'void computeVersion(ServletContext context) {\\n        // set the version\\n        Properties props = new Properties();\\n        try (InputStream is = Jenkins.class.getResourceAsStream("jenkins-version.properties")) {\\n            if (is != null)\\n                props.load(is);\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            e.printStackTrace(); // if the version properties is missing, that\\\'s OK.\\n        }\\n        String ver = props.getProperty("version");\\n        if (ver == null)   ver = UNCOMPUTED_VERSION;\\n        if (Main.isDevelopmentMode && "${project.version}".equals(ver)) {\\n            // in dev mode, unable to get version (ahem Eclipse)\\n            try {\\n                File dir = new File(".").getAbsoluteFile();\\n                while (dir != null) {\\n                    File pom = new File(dir, "pom.xml");\\n                    if (pom.exists() && "pom".equals(XMLUtils.getValue("/project/artifactId", pom))) {\\n                        pom =  pom.getCanonicalFile();\\n                        LOGGER.info("Reading version from: " + pom.getAbsolutePath());\\n                        ver = XMLUtils.getValue("/project/version", pom);\\n                        break;\\n                    }\\n                    dir = dir.getParentFile();\\n                }\\n                LOGGER.info("Jenkins is in dev mode, using version: " + ver);\\n            } catch (Exception e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(WARNING, e, () -> "Unable to read Jenkins version: " + e.getMessage());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        VERSION = ver;\\n        context.setAttribute("version", ver);\\n\\n        CHANGELOG_URL = props.getProperty("changelog.url");\\n\\n        VERSION_HASH = Util.getDigestOf(ver).substring(0, 8);\\n        SESSION_HASH = Util.getDigestOf(ver + System.currentTimeMillis()).substring(0, 8);\\n\\n        if (ver.equals(UNCOMPUTED_VERSION) || SystemProperties.getBoolean("hudson.script.noCache"))\\n            RESOURCE_PATH = "";\\n        else\\n            RESOURCE_PATH = "/static/" + SESSION_HASH;\\n\\n        VIEW_RESOURCE_PATH = "/resources/" + SESSION_HASH;\\n    }\'')]

[(335, '\'void unmigrateJobsDir(File jobs) throws Exception {\\n        File[] jobDirs = jobs.listFiles();\\n        if (jobDirs == null) {\\n            System.err.println(jobs + " claimed to exist, but cannot be listed");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        for (File job : jobDirs) {\\n\\n            if (job.getName().equals("builds")) {\\n                // Might be maven modules, matrix builds, etc. which are direct children of job\\n                unmigrateBuildsDir(job);\\n            }\\n\\n            File[] kids = job.listFiles();\\n            if (kids == null) {\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            for (File kid : kids) {\\n                if (!kid.isDirectory()) {\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (kid.getName().equals("builds")) {\\n                    unmigrateBuildsDir(kid);\\n                } else {\\n                    // Might be jobs, modules, promotions, etc.; we assume an ItemGroup.getRootDirFor implementation\\n                    // returns grandchildren, unmigrateJobsDir(job) call above handles children.\\n                    unmigrateJobsDir(kid);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

plugins.size(), 1))\\n                .sorted((o1, o2) -> {\\n                    String o1DisplayName = o1.getDisplayName();\\n                    if (o1.name.equalsIgnoreCase(query) ||\\n  if (o2.name.equalsIgnoreCase(query) || o2DisplayName.equalsIgnoreCase(query)) {\\n                        return 1;\\n                    }\\n                    if (o1.name.equals(o2.name)) {\\n return pop; // highest popularity first\\n                    }\\n                    return o1DisplayName.compareTo(o2DisplayName);\\n                })\\n                .map(plugin -> {\\n                    JSONObject jsonObject = new JSONObject();\\n                    jsonObject.put("name", plugin.name);\\n                    jsonObject.put("sourceId", plugin.sourceId);\\n                    jsonObject.put("title", plugin.title);\\n                    jsonObject.put("displayName", plugin.getDisplayName());\\n                    if (plugin.wiki == null ||    jsonObject.put("wiki", plugin.wiki);\\n                    }\\n                    jsonObject.put("categories", plugin.getCategoriesStream()\\n                        .filter(PluginManager::isNonMetaLabel)\\n                        .map(UpdateCenter::getCategoryDisplayName)\\n                        .collect(toList())\\n                    );\\n\\n                    if (hasAdoptThisPluginLabel(plugin)) {\\n                        jsonObject.put("adoptMe", Messages.PluginManager_adoptThisPlugin());\\n                    }\\n                    if jsonObject.put("excerpt", plugin.excerpt);\\n                    jsonObject.put("version", plugin.version);\\n                    jsonObject.put("popularity", plugin.popularity);\\n                    if (plugin.isForNewerHudson()) {\\n                        jsonObject.put("newerCoreRequired", Messages.PluginManager_coreWarning(Util.xmlEscape(plugin.requiredCore)));\\n                    }\\n                    if (plugin.hasWarnings()) {\\n                        JSONObject unresolvedSecurityWarnings = new JSONObject();\\n                        unresolvedSecurityWarnings.put("text",                  throw new IllegalStateException("warnings cannot be null here");\\n                        }\\n                        List<JSONObject> warnings = pluginWarnings.stream()\\n                            .map(warning -> {\\n                                JSONObject jsonWarning = new JSONObject();\\n                                jsonWarning.put("url", warning.url);\\n                                jsonWarning.put("message", warning.message);\\n                                return jsonWarning;\\n                            }).collect(toList());\\n                        unresolvedSecurityWarnings.put("warnings", warnings);\\n                        jsonObject.put("unresolvedSecurityWarnings", unresolvedSecurityWarnings);\\n                    }\\n                    if (plugin.releaseTimestamp != null) {\\n                        JSONObject releaseTimestamp = new JSONObject();\\n                        releaseTimestamp.put("iso8601", Functions.iso8601DateTime(plugin.releaseTimestamp));\\n                        releaseTimestamp.put("displayValue", Messages.PluginManager_ago(Functions.getTimeSpanString(plugin.releaseTimestamp)));\\n                        jsonObject.put("releaseTimestamp", releaseTimestamp);\\n                    }\\n                    return jsonObject;\\n                })\\n                .collect(toList());\\n            plugins.addAll(sitePlugins);\\n            if (plugins.size() >= limit) {\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        JSONArray mappedPlugins = new JSONArray();\\n        mappedPlugins.addAll(plugins);\\n\\n        return [(34, '\'String convertEOL(String input, EOLType type) {\\n        if (null == input || input.isEmpty()) {\\n            return input;\\n        }\\n        // Convert line endings to Unix LF,\\n        // which also sets up the string for other conversions\\n        input = input.replace("\\\\r\\\\n", "\\\\n");\\n        input = input.replace(\\\'\\\\r\\\', \\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n        switch (type) {\\n            case CR:\\n            case Mac:\\n                // Convert line endings to CR\\n                input = input.replace(\\\'\\\\n\\\', \\\'\\\\r\\\');\\n                break;\\n            case CRLF:\\n            case Windows:\\n                // Convert line endings to Windows CR/LF\\n                input = input.replace("\\\\n", "\\\\r\\\\n");\\n                break;\\n            case LFCR:\\n                // Convert line endings to LF/CR\\n                input = input.replace("\\\\n", "\\\\n\\\\r");\\n                break;\\n            case LF:\\n            case Unix:\\n            default:\\n                // Conversion already completed\\n                return input;\\n        }\\n        return input;\\n    }\'')]

[(297, '\'String computeRelativeNamesAfterRenaming(String oldFullName, String newFullName, String relativeNames, ItemGroup context) {\\n\\n        StringTokenizer tokens = new StringTokenizer(relativeNames, ",");\\n        List<String> newValue = new ArrayList<>();\\n        while (tokens.hasMoreTokens()) {\\n            String relativeName = tokens.nextToken().trim();\\n            String canonicalName = getCanonicalName(context, relativeName);\\n            if (canonicalName.equals(oldFullName) || canonicalName.startsWith(oldFullName + \\\'/\\\')) {\\n                String newCanonicalName = newFullName + canonicalName.substring(oldFullName.length());\\n                if (relativeName.startsWith("/")) {\\n                    newValue.add("/" + newCanonicalName);\\n                } else {\\n                    newValue.add(getRelativeNameFrom(newCanonicalName, context.getFullName()));\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                newValue.add(relativeName);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return String.join(",", newValue);\\n    }\'')]

[(171, '\'HttpResponse doRevokeAllSelected(@JsonBody RevokeAllSelectedModel content) throws IOException {\\n        for (RevokeAllSelectedUserAndUuid value : content.values) {\\n            if (value.userId == null) {\\n                // special case not managed by JSONObject\\n                value.userId = "null";\\n            }\\n            User user = User.getById(value.userId, false);\\n            if (user == null) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "User not found id={0}", value.userId);\\n            } else {\\n                ApiTokenProperty apiTokenProperty = user.getProperty(ApiTokenProperty.class);\\n                if (apiTokenProperty == null) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "User without apiTokenProperty found id={0}", value.userId);\\n                } else {\\n                    ApiTokenStore.HashedToken revokedToken = apiTokenProperty.getTokenStore().revokeToken(value.uuid);\\n                    if (revokedToken == null) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "User without selected token id={0}, tokenUuid={1}", new Object[]{value.userId, value.uuid});\\n                    } else {\\n                        apiTokenProperty.deleteApiToken();\\n                        user.save();\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Revocation success for user id={0}, tokenUuid={1}", new Object[]{value.userId, value.uuid});\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return HttpResponses.ok();\\n    }\'')]

[(87, '\'String encodeTo(String url, String text, BiFunction<String, Integer, ConsoleNote> constructor) {\\n        // If text contains newlines, then its stored length will not match its length when being\\n        // displayed, since the display length will only include text up to the first newline,\\n        // which will cause an IndexOutOfBoundsException in MarkupText#rangeCheck when\\n        // ConsoleAnnotationOutputStream converts the note into markup. That stream treats \\\'\\\\n\\\' as\\n        // the sole end-of-line marker on all platforms, so we ignore \\\'\\\\r\\\' because it will not\\n        // break the conversion.\\n        text = text.replace(\\\'\\\\n\\\', \\\' \\\');\\n        try {\\n            return constructor.apply(url, text.length()).encode() + text;\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            // impossible, but don\\\'t make this a fatal problem\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to serialize " + HyperlinkNote.class, e);\\n            return text;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(102, '\'void init(FilterConfig filterConfig) throws ServletException {\\n        this.filterConfig = filterConfig;\\n        // this is how we make us available to the rest of Hudson.\\n        filterConfig.getServletContext().setAttribute(HudsonFilter.class.getName(), this);\\n        try {\\n            Jenkins hudson = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n            if (hudson != null) {\\n                // looks like we are initialized after Hudson came into being. initialize it now. See JENKINS-3069\\n                LOGGER.fine("Security wasn\\\'t initialized; Initializing it...");\\n                SecurityRealm securityRealm = hudson.getSecurityRealm();\\n                reset(securityRealm);\\n                LOGGER.fine("securityRealm is " + securityRealm);\\n                LOGGER.fine("Security initialized");\\n            }\\n        } catch (ExceptionInInitializerError e) {\\n            // see JENKINS-4592. In some containers this happens before\\n            // WebAppMain.contextInitialized kicks in, which makes\\n            // the whole thing fail hard before a nicer error check\\n            // in WebAppMain.contextInitialized. So for now,\\n            // just report it here, and let the WebAppMain handle the failure gracefully.\\n            LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to initialize Jenkins", e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(54, '\'void run(final InputStream upload, OutputStream download) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        channel = new Channel("HTTP full-duplex channel " + uuid,\\n                Computer.threadPoolForRemoting, Channel.Mode.BINARY, upload, download, null, restricted);\\n\\n        // so that we can detect dead clients, periodically send something\\n        PingThread ping = new PingThread(channel) {\\n            @Override\\n            protected void onDead(Throwable diagnosis) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Duplex-HTTP session " + uuid + " is terminated", diagnosis);\\n                // this will cause the channel to abort and subsequently clean up\\n                try {\\n                    upload.close();\\n                } catch (IOException e) {\\n                    // this can never happen\\n                    throw new AssertionError(e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            protected void onDead() {\\n                onDead(null);\\n            }\\n        };\\n        ping.start();\\n        main(channel);\\n        channel.join();\\n        ping.interrupt();\\n    }\'')]

[(175, "'TokenUuidAndPlainValue generateNewToken(@NonNull String name) {\\n        // 16x8=128bit worth of randomness, using brute-force you need on average 2^127 tries (~10^37)\\n        byte[] random = new byte[16];\\n        RANDOM.nextBytes(random);\\n        // 32-char in hex\\n        String secretValue = Util.toHexString(random);\\n        String tokenTheUserWillUse = HASH_VERSION + secretValue;\\n        assert tokenTheUserWillUse.length() == 2 + 32;\\n\\n        HashedToken token = prepareAndStoreToken(name, secretValue);\\n\\n        return new TokenUuidAndPlainValue(token.uuid, tokenTheUserWillUse);\\n    }'")]

[(182, '\'String createUtils(String cmd) throws BadCommandException {\\n        if (cmd == null || cmd.trim().isEmpty()) {\\n            throw new BadCommandException("Invalid command line");\\n        }\\n\\n        String[] cmds = {cmd};\\n\\n        try {\\n            ProcessBuilder processBuilder;\\n            processBuilder = new ProcessBuilder(cmds);\\n            Process process = null;\\n            try {\\n                process = processBuilder.start();\\n            } catch (IOException ignored) {\\n                // Ignored, but the sanitizer should still throw an exception.\\n            }\\n\\n            // Capture output\\n            if (process != null) {\\n                String output = captureOutput(process);\\n                // Print output for POV\\n                // System.out.println(output);\\n                Event event = new Event(Event.Status.SUCCESS, output, cmd);\\n                events.add(event);\\n\\n                // Wait for the process to complete\\n                int exitCode = process.waitFor();\\n                return cmd;\\n            } else {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        } catch (IOException | InterruptedException e) {\\n            e.printStackTrace();\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(159, "'void _loadSpike(JenkinsRule r) throws Exception {\\n        try (BulkChange bc = new BulkChange(r.jenkins)) {\\n            DummyCloudImpl cloud = initHudson(0, r);\\n\\n            verifySuccessfulCompletion(buildAll(create5SlowJobs(new Latch(5), r)), r);\\n\\n            // the time it takes to complete a job is eternally long compared to the time it takes to launch\\n            // a new slave, so in this scenario we end up allocating 5 slaves for 5 jobs.\\n            // sometimes we can end up allocating 6 due to the conservative estimation in StandardStrategyImpl#apply\\n            assertThat(cloud.numProvisioned, anyOf(equalTo(5), equalTo(6)));\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(93, "'void drawItem(Graphics2D g2,\\n                         CategoryItemRendererState state,\\n                         Rectangle2D dataArea,\\n                         CategoryPlot plot,\\n                         CategoryAxis domainAxis,\\n                         ValueAxis rangeAxis,\\n                         CategoryDataset dataset,\\n                         int row,\\n                         int column,\\n                         int pass) {\\n\\n        // plot non-null values...\\n        Number dataValue = dataset.getValue(row, column);\\n        if (dataValue == null) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        double value = dataValue.doubleValue();\\n\\n        // leave the y values (y1, y0) untranslated as it is going to be be\\n        // stacked up later by previous series values, after this it will be\\n        // translated.\\n        double xx1 = domainAxis.getCategoryMiddle(column, getColumnCount(),\\n                dataArea, plot.getDomainAxisEdge());\\n\\n        double previousHeightx1 = getPreviousHeight(dataset, row, column);\\n        double y1 = value + previousHeightx1;\\n        RectangleEdge location = plot.getRangeAxisEdge();\\n        double this information is being collected\\n        EntityCollection entities = state.getEntityCollection();\\n\\n        // in column zero, the only job to do is draw any visible item labels\\n        // and this is done in the second pass...\\n        if (column == 0) {\\n            if (pass == 1) {\\n                // draw item labels, if visible\\n                if (isItemLabelVisible(row, column)) {\\n                    drawItemLabel(g2, plot.getOrientation(), dataset, row, column,\\n                            xx1, yy1, y1 < 0.0);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            Number previousValue = dataset.getValue(row, column - 1);\\n            if (previousValue != null) {\\n\\n                double xx0 = domainAxis.getCategoryMiddle(column - 1,\\n                        getColumnCount(), dataArea, plot.getDomainAxisEdge());\\n                double y0 = previousValue.doubleValue();\\n\\n\\n                // Get the previous height, but this will be different for both\\n                // y0 and y1 as the previous series values could differ.\\n                double previousHeightx0 = getPreviousHeight(dataset, row,\\n                        column - 1);\\n\\n                // Now stack the current y values on top of the previous values.\\n                y0 += previousHeightx0;\\n\\n                // Now translate the previous heights\\n                double previousHeightxx0 = rangeAxis.valueToJava2D(\\n                        previousHeightx0, dataArea, location);\\n                double previousHeightxx1 = rangeAxis.valueToJava2D(\\n                        previousHeightx1, dataArea, location);\\n\\n                // Now translate the current y values.\\n                double yy0 = rangeAxis.valueToJava2D(y0, dataArea, location);\\n\\n                if (pass == 0) {\\n                    // left half\\n                    Polygon p = new Polygon();\\n                    p.addPoint((int) xx0, (int) yy0);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) (xx0 + xx1) / 2, (int) (yy0 + yy1) / 2);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) (xx0 + xx1) / 2, (int) (previousHeightxx0 + previousHeightxx1) / 2);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) xx0, (int) previousHeightxx0);\\n\\n                    g2.setPaint(getItemPaint(row, column - 1));\\n                    g2.setStroke(getItemStroke(row, column - 1));\\n                    g2.fill(p);\\n\\n                    if (entities != null)\\n                        addItemEntity(entities, dataset, row, column - 1, p);\\n\\n                    // right half\\n                    p = new Polygon();\\n                    p.addPoint((int) xx1, (int) yy1);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) (xx0 + xx1) / 2, (int) (yy0 + yy1) / 2);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) (xx0 + xx1) / 2, (int) (previousHeightxx0 + previousHeightxx1) / 2);\\n                    p.addPoint((int) xx1, (int) previousHeightxx1);\\n\\n                    g2.setPaint(getItemPaint(row, column));\\n                    g2.setStroke(getItemStroke(row, column));\\n                    g2.fill(p);\\n\\n                    if (entities != null)\\n                        addItemEntity(entities, dataset, row, column, p);\\n                } else {\\n                    if (isItemLabelVisible(row, column)) {\\n                        drawItemLabel(g2, plot.getOrientation(), dataset, row,\\n                                column, xx1, yy1, y1 < 0.0);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(692, '\'SecretKey toAes128Key(@NonNull String s) {\\n        try {\\n            // turn secretKey into 256 bit hash\\n            MessageDigest digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256");\\n            digest.reset();\\n            digest.update(s.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n\\n            // Due to the stupid US export restriction JDK only ships 128bit version.\\n            return new SecretKeySpec(digest.digest(), 0, 128 / 8, "AES");\\n        } catch (NoSuchAlgorithmException e) {\\n            throw new Error(e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(82, '"boolean rewrite(File f) throws InvalidKeyException, IOException {\\n\\n        AtomicFileWriter w = new AtomicFileWriter(f.toPath(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n        try {\\n            boolean modified = false; // did we actually change anything?\\n            try (PrintWriter out = new PrintWriter(new BufferedWriter(w));\\n                 InputStream fin = Files.newInputStream(Util.fileToPath(f));\\n                 BufferedReader r = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(fin, StandardCharsets.UTF_8))) {\\n                String line;\\n                StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n\\n                while ((line = r.readLine()) != null) {\\n                    int copied = 0;\\n                    buf.setLength(0);\\n                    while (true) {\\n                        int sidx = line.indexOf(\'>\', copied);\\n                        if (sidx < 0) break;\\n                        int eidx = line.indexOf(\'<\', sidx);\\n                        if (eidx < 0) break;\\n\\n                        String elementText = line.substring(sidx + 1, eidx);\\n                        String replacement = tryRewrite(elementText);\\n                        if (!replacement.equals(elementText))\\n                            modified = true;\\n\\n                        buf.append(line, copied, sidx + 1);\\n                        buf.append(replacement);\\n                        copied = eidx;\\n                    }\\n                    buf.append(line.substring(copied));\\n                    out.println(buf);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (modified) {\\n                w.commit();\\n            }\\n            return modified;\\n        } finally {\\n            w.abort();\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(66, '\'boolean hasInvalidSessionSeed(Authentication authentication, HttpSession session) {\\n        if (UserSeedProperty.DISABLE_USER_SEED || authentication instanceof AnonymousAuthenticationToken) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        User userFromSession;\\n        try {\\n            userFromSession = User.getById(authentication.getName(), false);\\n        } catch (IllegalStateException ise) {\\n            logger.warn("Encountered IllegalStateException trying to get a user. System init may not have completed yet. Invalidating user session.");\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        if (userFromSession == null) {\\n            // no requirement for further test as there is no user inside\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // for case like recovering backup or other corner cases when the session was not populated by this version\\n        Object userSessionSeedObject = session.getAttribute(UserSeedProperty.USER_SESSION_SEED);\\n        String actualUserSessionSeed;\\n        if (userSessionSeedObject instanceof String) {\\n            actualUserSessionSeed = (String) userSessionSeedObject;\\n        } else {\\n            // the seed must be present AND be a string in the session\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        UserSeedProperty userSeedProperty = userFromSession.getProperty(UserSeedProperty.class);\\n        if (userSeedProperty == null) {\\n            // if you want to filter out the user seed property, you should consider using the DISABLE_USER_SEED instead\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        // no need to do a time-constant test here because all the information come from the server\\n        // in other words, there is no way for a user to brute-force those values\\n        boolean validSeed = actualUserSessionSeed.equals(userSeedProperty.getSeed());\\n\\n        // if the authentication is no longer valid we need to remove it from the session\\n        return !validSeed;\\n    }\'')]

[(886, "'void setNumExecutors(int n) {\\n        this.numExecutors = n;\\n        final int diff = executors.size() - n;\\n\\n        if (diff > 0) {\\n            // we have too many executors\\n            // send signal to all idle executors to potentially kill them off\\n            // need the Queue maintenance lock held to prevent concurrent job assignment on the idle executors\\n            Queue.withLock(() -> {\\n                for (Executor e : executors) {\\n                    if (e.isIdle()) {\\n                        e.interrupt();\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            });\\n        }\\n\\n        if (diff < 0) {\\n            // if the number is increased, add new ones\\n            addNewExecutorIfNecessary();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

                }\\n                } catch (Exception x) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "problem checking " + loc, x);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (loc.endsWith("/target/classes/") || loc.matches(".+/build/classes/[^/]+/main/")) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "{0} seems to be current plugin classes, OK", loc);\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n            if (Main.isUnitTest) {\\n                if (loc.endsWith("/target/test-classes/") || loc.endsWith("-tests.jar") || [(90, '\'void ensureXssIsPrevented(TestRootAction testRootAction, String validationPart, String dangerousPart) throws Exception {\\n        JenkinsRule.WebClient wc = j.createWebClient();\\n\\n        AtomicBoolean alertTriggered = new AtomicBoolean(false);\\n        wc.setAlertHandler((p, s) -> alertTriggered.set(true));\\n\\n        HtmlPage page = wc.goTo(testRootAction.getUrlName());\\n\\n        // now it\\\'s a regular title, but without the correction, the tooltip will be triggered\\n\\n        // title field is modified by Yahoo tooltip, title attribute is set by the new code\\n        ScriptResult controlResult = page.executeJavaScript("var s = document.querySelector(\\\'#test-panel svg\\\'); s.title || s.getAttribute(\\\'title\\\');");\\n        Object jsControlResult = controlResult.getJavaScriptResult();\\n        assertThat(jsControlResult, instanceOf(String.class));\\n        String jsControlString = (String) jsControlResult;\\n        assertThat("The title attribute is not populated", jsControlString, containsString(validationPart));\\n\\n        page.executeJavaScript("document.querySelector(\\\'#test-panel svg\\\')._tippy.show()");\\n        wc.waitForBackgroundJavaScript(1000);\\n        ScriptResult result = page.executeJavaScript("document.querySelector(\\\'.tippy-content\\\').innerHTML;");\\n        Object jsResult = result.getJavaScriptResult();\\n        assertThat(jsResult, instanceOf(String.class));\\n        String jsResultString = (String) jsResult;\\n\\n        assertThat("XSS not prevented (content)", jsResultString, not(containsString(dangerousPart)));\\n        assertFalse("XSS not prevented (alert)", alertTriggered.get());\\n    }\'')]

[(384, "'boolean incrementTestPartsIndex(int[] testPartsIndex, Object[] testParts) {\\n      boolean carry = true;  //add 1 to lowest order part.\\n      boolean maxIndex = true;\\n      for (int testPartsIndexIndex = testPartsIndex.length - 1; testPartsIndexIndex >= 0; --testPartsIndexIndex) {\\n         int index = testPartsIndex[testPartsIndexIndex];\\n         ResultPair[] part = (ResultPair[]) testParts[testPartsIndexIndex];\\n         maxIndex &= (index == (part.length - 1));\\n         if (carry) {\\n            if (index < part.length - 1) {\\n               index++;\\n               testPartsIndex[testPartsIndexIndex] = index;\\n               carry = false;\\n            } else {\\n               testPartsIndex[testPartsIndexIndex] = 0;\\n               carry = true;\\n            }\\n         }\\n      }\\n\\n\\n      return !maxIndex;\\n   }'")]

[(115, '\'boolean cleanFingerprint(@NonNull Fingerprint fingerprint, TaskListener taskListener) {\\n        try {\\n            if (!fingerprint.isAlive() && fingerprint.getFacetBlockingDeletion() == null) {\\n                taskListener.getLogger().println("deleting obsolete " + fingerprint);\\n                Fingerprint.delete(fingerprint.getHashString());\\n                return true;\\n            } else {\\n                if (!fingerprint.isAlive()) {\\n                    FingerprintFacet deletionBlockerFacet = fingerprint.getFacetBlockingDeletion();\\n                    taskListener.getLogger().println(deletionBlockerFacet.getClass().getName() + " created on " +\\n                            new Date(deletionBlockerFacet.getTimestamp()) + " blocked deletion of " +\\n                            fingerprint.getHashString());\\n                }\\n                // get the fingerprint in the official map so have the changes visible to Jenkins\\n                // otherwise the mutation made in FingerprintMap can override our trimming.\\n                fingerprint = getFingerprint(fingerprint);\\n                return fingerprint.trim();\\n            }\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, taskListener.error("Failed to process " + fingerprint.getHashString()));\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(112, '"View getView(@CheckForNull String name) {\\n        if (name == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        //Top level views returned first if match\\n        List<View> views = views();\\n        for (View v : views) {\\n            if (v.getViewName().equals(name)) {\\n                return v;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        for (View v : views) {\\n            //getAllViews() cannot be used as it filters jobs by permission which is bad e.g. when trying to add a new job\\n            if (v instanceof ViewGroup) {\\n                View nestedView = ((ViewGroup) v).getView(name);\\n                if (nestedView != null) {\\n                    return nestedView;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (!name.equals(primaryView())) {\\n            // Fallback to subview of primary view if it is a ViewGroup\\n            View pv = getPrimaryView();\\n            if (pv instanceof ViewGroup)\\n                return ((ViewGroup) pv).getView(name);\\n            if (pv instanceof AllView && AllView.DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME.equals(pv.name)) {\\n                // JENKINS-38606: primary view is the default AllView, is somebody using an old link to localized form?\\n                for (Locale l : Locale.getAvailableLocales()) {\\n                    if (name.equals(Messages._Hudson_ViewName().toString(l))) {\\n                        // why yes they are, let\'s keep that link working\\n                        return pv;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }"')]

[(71, '\'Boolean _hasPermission(@NonNull Authentication a, Permission permission) {\\n        // ACL entries for this principal takes precedence\\n        Boolean b = hasPermission(new PrincipalSid(a), permission);\\n        if (LOGGER.isLoggable(FINER))\\n            LOGGER.finer("hasPermission(PrincipalSID:" + a.getPrincipal() + "," + permission + ")=>" + b);\\n        if (b != null)\\n            return b;\\n\\n        // after that, we check if the groups this principal belongs to\\n        // has any ACL entries.\\n        // here we are using GrantedAuthority as a group\\n        for (GrantedAuthority ga : a.getAuthorities()) {\\n            b = hasPermission(new GrantedAuthoritySid(ga), permission);\\n            if (LOGGER.isLoggable(FINER))\\n                LOGGER.finer("hasPermission(GroupSID:" + ga.getAuthority() + "," + permission + ")=>" + b);\\n            if (b != null)\\n                return b;\\n        }\\n\\n        // permissions granted to \\\'everyone\\\' and \\\'anonymous\\\' users are granted to everyone\\n        for (Sid sid : AUTOMATIC_SIDS) {\\n            b = hasPermission(sid, permission);\\n            if (LOGGER.isLoggable(FINER))\\n                LOGGER.finer("hasPermission(" + sid + "," + permission + ")=>" + b);\\n            if (b != null)\\n                return b;\\n        }\\n\\n        return null;\\n    }\'')]

[(194, '\'void compareDifferentSessions_tokenAreEqual(boolean areEqual) throws Exception {\\n        WebClient wc = r.createWebClient();\\n        wc.login("foo");\\n\\n        HtmlPage p = wc.goTo("configure");\\n        String crumb1 = p.getElementByName("Jenkins-Crumb").getAttribute("value");\\n        r.submit(p.getFormByName("config"));\\n\\n        wc.goTo("logout");\\n        wc.login("foo");\\n\\n        p = wc.goTo("configure");\\n        String crumb2 = p.getElementByName("Jenkins-Crumb").getAttribute("value");\\n        r.submit(p.getFormByName("config"));\\n\\n        assertEquals(crumb1.equals(crumb2), areEqual);\\n\\n        HtmlForm config = p.getFormByName("config");\\n        if (areEqual) {\\n            r.submit(config);\\n        } else {\\n            replaceAllCrumbInPageBy(p, crumb1);\\n            // submit the form with previous session crumb\\n            FailingHttpStatusCodeException e = assertThrows(FailingHttpStatusCodeException.class, () -> r.submit(config));\\n            assertEquals(HttpServletResponse.SC_FORBIDDEN, e.getStatusCode());\\n            assertThat(e.getResponse().getContentAsString(), containsString("No valid crumb"));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(258, '\'void checkArray(String label, String[] expect, String[] result) {\\n\\n        // Handle nulls\\n        if (expect == null || result == null) {\\n            if (expect == null && result == null) {\\n                return; // valid, both null\\n            } else {\\n                fail(label + " Null expect=" + Arrays.toString(expect) + " result=" + Arrays.toString(result));\\n            }\\n            return; // not strictly necessary, but prevents possible NPE below\\n        }\\n\\n        // Check Length\\n        if (expect.length != result.length) {\\n            fail(label + " Length expect=" + expect.length + " result=" + result.length);\\n        }\\n\\n        // Check Values\\n        for (int i = 0; i < expect.length; i++) {\\n            assertEquals(label + " value[" + i + "]", expect[i], result[i]);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(28, '"void write(int b) throws IOException {\\n        if (MBYTES[match] == b) { // another byte matched. Good. Keep going...\\n            match++;\\n            if (match == MBYTES.length) {\\n                // don\'t send MARK to the output, but instead notify the callback\\n                onMarkFound();\\n                match = 0;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            if (match > 0) {\\n                // only matched partially. send the partial match that we held off down the pipe\\n                base.write(MBYTES, 0, match);\\n                match = 0;\\n\\n                // this might match the first byte in MARK, so retry.\\n                write(b);\\n            } else {\\n                base.write(b);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(382, '\'EnvVars getEnvironment(@CheckForNull Node node, @NonNull TaskListener listener) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        EnvVars env = new EnvVars();\\n\\n        if (node != null) {\\n            final Computer computer = node.toComputer();\\n            if (computer != null) {\\n                // we need to get computer environment to inherit platform details\\n                env = computer.getEnvironment();\\n                env.putAll(computer.buildEnvironment(listener));\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        env.putAll(getCharacteristicEnvVars());\\n\\n        // servlet container may have set CLASSPATH in its launch script,\\n        // so don\\\'t let that inherit to the new child process.\\n        // see http://www.nabble.com/Run-Job-with-JDK-1.4.2-tf4468601.html\\n        env.put("CLASSPATH", "");\\n\\n        // apply them in a reverse order so that higher ordinal ones can modify values added by lower ordinal ones\\n        for (EnvironmentContributor ec : EnvironmentContributor.all().reverseView())\\n            ec.buildEnvironmentFor(this, env, listener);\\n\\n\\n        return env;\\n    }\'')]

[(956, '\'void doHelp(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        String path = req.getRestOfPath();\\n        if (path.contains("..")) throw new ServletException("Illegal path: " + path);\\n\\n        path = path.replace(\\\'/\\\', \\\'-\\\');\\n\\n        PluginWrapper pw = getPlugin();\\n        if (pw != null) {\\n            rsp.setHeader("X-Plugin-Short-Name", pw.getShortName());\\n            rsp.setHeader("X-Plugin-Long-Name", pw.getLongName());\\n            rsp.setHeader("X-Plugin-From", Messages.Descriptor_From(\\n                    pw.getLongName().replace("Hudson", "Jenkins").replace("hudson", "jenkins"), pw.getUrl()));\\n        }\\n\\n        for (Klass<?> c = getKlass(); c != null; c = c.getSuperClass()) {\\n            RequestDispatcher rd = Stapler.getCurrentRequest().getView(c, "help" + path);\\n            if (rd != null) { // template based help page\\n                rd.forward(req, rsp);\\n                return;\\n            }\\n\\n            URL url = getStaticHelpUrl(c, path);\\n            if (url != null) {\\n                // TODO: generalize macro expansion and perhaps even support JEXL\\n                rsp.setContentType("text/html;charset=UTF-8");\\n                try (InputStream in = url.openStream()) {\\n                    String literal = IOUtils.toString(in, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n                    rsp.getWriter().println(Util.replaceMacro(literal, Map.of("rootURL", req.getContextPath())));\\n                }\\n                return;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        rsp.sendError(SC_NOT_FOUND);\\n    }\'')]

[(618, '\'boolean isSortedLowerCase(String name, String [] array) {\\n        boolean sorted = true;\\n        boolean strictlySorted = true;\\n        final int length = array.length;\\n        boolean lowerCase = isLowerCase(array[length - 1]); // Check the last entry\\n        for (int i = 0; i < length - 1; i++) { // compare all but last entry with next\\n            final String entry = array[i];\\n            final String nextEntry = array[i + 1];\\n            final int cmp = entry.compareTo(nextEntry);\\n            if (cmp > 0) { // out of order\\n                System.out.println("Out of order entry: " + entry + " < " + nextEntry + " in " + name);\\n                sorted = false;\\n            } else if (cmp == 0) {\\n                strictlySorted = false;\\n                System.out.println("Duplicated entry: " + entry + " in " + name);\\n            }\\n            if (!isLowerCase(entry)) {\\n                System.out.println("Non lowerCase entry: " + entry + " in " + name);\\n                lowerCase = false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return sorted && strictlySorted && lowerCase;\\n    }\'')]

[(89, '\'boolean shouldSetCharacterEncoding(HttpServletRequest req) {\\n        String method = req.getMethod();\\n        if (!"POST".equalsIgnoreCase(method)) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // containers often implement RFCs incorrectly in that it doesn\\\'t interpret query parameter\\n        // decoding with UTF-8. This will ensure we get it right.\\n        // but doing this for config.xml submission could potentially overwrite valid\\n        // "text/xml;charset=xxx"\\n        String contentType = req.getContentType();\\n        if (contentType != null) {\\n            boolean isXmlSubmission = contentType.startsWith("application/xml") || contentType.startsWith("text/xml");\\n            if (isXmlSubmission) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return FORCE_ENCODING || req.getCharacterEncoding() == null;\\n    }\'')]

[(135, "'void addNode(final @NonNull Node node) throws IOException {\\n        if (ENFORCE_NAME_RESTRICTIONS) {\\n            Jenkins.checkGoodName(node.getNodeName());\\n        }\\n\\n        Node oldNode = nodes.get(node.getNodeName());\\n        if (node != oldNode) {\\n            AtomicReference<Node> old = new AtomicReference<>();\\n            old.set(nodes.put(node.getNodeName(), node));\\n            jenkins.updateNewComputer(node);\\n            jenkins.trimLabels(node, oldNode);\\n            // TODO there is a theoretical race whereby the node instance is updated/removed after lock release\\n            try {\\n                persistNode(node);\\n            } catch (IOException | RuntimeException e) {\\n                // JENKINS-50599: If persisting the node throws an exception, we need to remove the node from\\n                // memory before propagating the exception.\\n                Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void run() {\\n                        nodes.compute(node.getNodeName(), (ignoredNodeName, ignoredNode) -> oldNode);\\n                        jenkins.updateComputerList();\\n                        jenkins.trimLabels(node, oldNode);\\n                    }\\n                });\\n                throw e;\\n            }\\n            if (old.get() != null) {\\n                NodeListener.fireOnUpdated(old.get(), node);\\n            } else {\\n                NodeListener.fireOnCreated(node);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(298, '\'void persistInstallStatus(List<UpdateCenterJob> installingPlugins) {\\n        File installingPluginsFile = getInstallingPluginsFile();\\n        if (installingPlugins == null || installingPlugins.isEmpty()) {\\n            try {\\n                Files.deleteIfExists(installingPluginsFile.toPath());\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                throw new UncheckedIOException(e);\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        LOGGER.fine("Writing install state to: " + installingPluginsFile.getAbsolutePath());\\n        Map<String, String> statuses = new HashMap<>();\\n        for (UpdateCenterJob j : installingPlugins) {\\n            if (j instanceof InstallationJob && j.getCorrelationId() != null) { // only include install jobs with a correlation id (directly selected)\\n                InstallationJob ij = (InstallationJob) j;\\n                InstallationStatus status = ij.status;\\n                String statusText = status.getType();\\n                if (status instanceof Installing) { // flag currently installing plugins as pending\\n                    statusText = "Pending";\\n                }\\n                statuses.put(ij.plugin.name, statusText);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        try {\\n            String installingPluginXml = new XStream().toXML(statuses);\\n            Files.writeString(Util.fileToPath(installingPluginsFile), installingPluginXml, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to save " + installingPluginsFile.getAbsolutePath(), e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(100, "'long doHash(int s, int e, int step, int field) {\\n        rangeCheck(s, field);\\n        rangeCheck(e, field);\\n        if (step > e - s + 1) {\\n            error(Messages.BaseParser_OutOfRange(step, 1, e - s + 1));\\n            throw new AssertionError();\\n        } else if (step > 1) {\\n            long bits = 0;\\n            for (int i = hash.next(step) + s; i <= e; i += step) {\\n                bits |= 1L << i;\\n            }\\n            assert bits != 0;\\n            return bits;\\n        } else if (step <= 0) {\\n            error(Messages.BaseParser_MustBePositive(step));\\n            throw new AssertionError();\\n        } else {\\n            assert step == NO_STEP;\\n            // step=1 (i.e. omitted) in the case of hash is actually special; means pick one value, not step by 1\\n            return 1L << (s + hash.next(e + 1 - s));\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(910, '\'void checkCommonAssertionForList(VirtualFile virtualRoot, VirtualFile virtualFromA, VirtualFile virtualFromB) throws Exception {\\n        // outside link to folder is not returned\\n        assertThat(virtualFromA.listOnlyDescendants(), containsInAnyOrder(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("aa"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("ab")\\n        ));\\n\\n        // outside link to file is not returned\\n        assertThat(virtualFromB.listOnlyDescendants(), contains(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("ba")\\n        ));\\n\\n        assertThat(virtualFromA.child("_b").listOnlyDescendants(), hasSize(0));\\n\\n        assertThat(virtualFromA.child("aa").listOnlyDescendants(), containsInAnyOrder(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("aaa"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("aa.txt")\\n        ));\\n\\n        // only a outside link\\n        assertThat(virtualFromA.child("aa").child("aaa").listOnlyDescendants(), hasSize(0));\\n\\n        // as we start from the root, the a/_b linking to root/b is legal\\n        assertThat(virtualRoot.child("a").listOnlyDescendants(), containsInAnyOrder(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("aa"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("ab"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("_b")\\n        ));\\n\\n        assertThat(virtualRoot.child("a").child("_b").listOnlyDescendants(), containsInAnyOrder(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("_a"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("_aatxt"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("ba")\\n        ));\\n\\n        assertThat(virtualRoot.child("a").child("_b").child("_a").listOnlyDescendants(), containsInAnyOrder(\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("aa"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("ab"),\\n                VFMatcher.hasName("_b")\\n        ));\\n    }\'')]

[(48, "'void eol(byte[] b, int len) throws IOException {\\n        String line = charset.decode(ByteBuffer.wrap(b, 0, len)).toString();\\n\\n        // trim off CR/LF from the end\\n        line = trimEOL(line);\\n\\n        // TODO:\\n        // we need more support for conveniently putting annotations in the middle of the line, not just at the beginning\\n        // we also need the ability for an extension point to have notes hook into the processing\\n\\n        Matcher m = MavenMojoNote.PATTERN.matcher(line);\\n        if (m.matches())\\n            new MavenMojoNote().encodeTo(out);\\n\\n        m = Maven3MojoNote.PATTERN.matcher(line);\\n        if (m.matches())\\n            new Maven3MojoNote().encodeTo(out);\\n\\n        m = MavenWarningNote.PATTERN.matcher(line);\\n        if (m.find())\\n            new MavenWarningNote().encodeTo(out);\\n\\n        m = MavenErrorNote.PATTERN.matcher(line);\\n        if (m.find())\\n            new MavenErrorNote().encodeTo(out);\\n\\n        out.write(b, 0, len);\\n    }'")]

[(46, '\'String getToolHome(Node node, ToolInstallation tool, TaskListener log) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        if (node.getRootPath() == null) {\\n            log.error(node.getDisplayName() + " is offline; cannot locate " + tool.getName());\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        InstallSourceProperty isp = tool.getProperties().get(InstallSourceProperty.class);\\n        if (isp == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        ArrayList<String> inapplicableInstallersMessages = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        for (ToolInstaller installer : isp.installers) {\\n            if (installer.appliesTo(node)) {\\n                Semaphore semaphore;\\n                synchronized (mutexByNode) {\\n                    Map<ToolInstallation, Semaphore> mutexByTool = mutexByNode.computeIfAbsent(node, k -> new WeakHashMap<>());\\n                    semaphore = mutexByTool.get(tool);\\n                    if (semaphore == null) {\\n                        mutexByTool.put(tool, semaphore = new Semaphore(1));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                semaphore.acquire();\\n                try {\\n                    return installer.performInstallation(tool, node, log).getRemote();\\n                } finally {\\n                    semaphore.release();\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                inapplicableInstallersMessages.add(Messages.CannotBeInstalled(\\n                        installer.getDescriptor().getDisplayName(),\\n                        tool.getName(),\\n                        node.getDisplayName()));\\n            }\\n        }\\n        for (String message : inapplicableInstallersMessages) {\\n            log.getLogger().println(message);\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }\'')]

[(1705, "'void waitForCheckpoint(@NonNull CheckPoint id, @CheckForNull BuildListener listener, @CheckForNull String waiter) throws InterruptedException {\\n        while (true) {\\n            Run<?, ?>.RunExecution exec = RunnerStack.INSTANCE.peek();\\n            if (exec == null) {\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            Run b = exec.getBuild().getPreviousBuildInProgress();\\n            if (b == null)     return; // no pending earlier build\\n            Run.RunExecution runner = b.runner;\\n            if (runner == null) {\\n                // polled at the wrong moment. try again.\\n                Thread.sleep(0);\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            if (runner.checkpoints.waitForCheckPoint(id, listener, waiter))\\n                return; // confirmed that the previous build reached the check point\\n\\n            // the previous build finished without ever reaching the check point. try again.\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(2383, '\'InputStream readFromOffset(final long offset) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        if (channel == null) {\\n            final RandomAccessFile raf = new RandomAccessFile(new File(remote), "r");\\n            try {\\n                raf.seek(offset);\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                try {\\n                    raf.close();\\n                } catch (IOException e1) {\\n                    // ignore\\n                }\\n                throw e;\\n            }\\n            return new InputStream() {\\n                @Override\\n                public int read() throws IOException {\\n                    return raf.read();\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public void close() throws IOException {\\n                    raf.close();\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public int read(byte[] b, int off, int len) throws IOException {\\n                    return raf.read(b, off, len);\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public int read(byte[] b) throws IOException {\\n                    return raf.read(b);\\n                }\\n            };\\n        }\\n\\n        final Pipe p = Pipe.createRemoteToLocal();\\n        actAsync(new OffsetPipeSecureFileCallable(p, offset));\\n        return new java.util.zip.GZIPInputStream(p.getIn());\\n    }\'')]

[(89, '\'void download(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_OK);\\n\\n        // server->client channel.\\n        // this is created first, and this controls the lifespan of the channel\\n        rsp.addHeader("Transfer-Encoding", "chunked");\\n        OutputStream out = rsp.getOutputStream();\\n        if (DIY_CHUNKING) {\\n            out = new ChunkedOutputStream(out);\\n        }\\n\\n        // send something out so that the client will see the HTTP headers\\n        out.write(0);\\n        out.flush();\\n\\n        { // wait until we have the other channel\\n            long end = System.currentTimeMillis() + CONNECTION_TIMEOUT;\\n            while (upload == null && System.currentTimeMillis() < end) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Waiting for upload stream for {0}: {1}", new Object[] {uuid, this});\\n                wait(1000);\\n            }\\n\\n            if (upload == null) {\\n                throw new IOException("HTTP full-duplex channel timeout: " + uuid);\\n            }\\n\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Received upload stream {0} for {1}: {2}", new Object[] {upload, uuid, this});\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            run(upload, out);\\n        } finally {\\n            // publish that we are done\\n            completed = true;\\n            notify();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(219, '\'void writeMultipartFormDataBody(OutputStream os, String boundary, int files, int other, int fileSize) throws IOException {\\n        try (OutputStreamWriter osw = new OutputStreamWriter(os, StandardCharsets.UTF_8); PrintWriter pw = new PrintWriter(osw)) {\\n            final Random random = new Random();\\n            while (files + other > 0) {\\n                println(pw, "--" + boundary);\\n                if (files > other) {\\n                    println(pw, "Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\\\\"file" + files + "\\\\"; filename=\\\\"file" + files + "\\\\"");\\n                    println(pw, "Content-Type: application/octet-stream");\\n                    println(pw, "");\\n                    pw.flush();\\n                    byte[] content = new byte[fileSize];\\n                    random.nextBytes(content);\\n                    os.write(content);\\n                    os.flush();\\n                    println(pw, "");\\n                    files--;\\n                } else {\\n                    println(pw, "Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\\\\"field" + other + "\\\\"");\\n                    println(pw, "");\\n                    println(pw, "Value " + random.nextLong());\\n                    other--;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            println(pw, "--" + boundary + "--");\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(741, '\'String getTimeSpanString(long duration) {\\n        // Break the duration up in to units.\\n        long years = duration / ONE_YEAR_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_YEAR_MS;\\n        long months = duration / ONE_MONTH_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_MONTH_MS;\\n        long days = duration / ONE_DAY_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_DAY_MS;\\n        long hours = duration / ONE_HOUR_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_HOUR_MS;\\n        long minutes = duration / ONE_MINUTE_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_MINUTE_MS;\\n        long seconds = duration / ONE_SECOND_MS;\\n        duration %= ONE_SECOND_MS;\\n        long millisecs = duration;\\n\\n        if (years > 0)\\n            return makeTimeSpanString(years, Messages.Util_year(years), months, Messages.Util_month(months));\\n        else if (months > 0)\\n            return makeTimeSpanString(months, Messages.Util_month(months), days, Messages.Util_day(days));\\n        else if (days > 0)\\n            return makeTimeSpanString(days, Messages.Util_day(days), hours, Messages.Util_hour(hours));\\n        else if (hours > 0)\\n            return makeTimeSpanString(hours, Messages.Util_hour(hours), minutes, Messages.Util_minute(minutes));\\n        else if (minutes > 0)\\n            return makeTimeSpanString(minutes, Messages.Util_minute(minutes), seconds, Messages.Util_second(seconds));\\n        else if (seconds >= 10)\\n            return Messages.Util_second(seconds);\\n        else if (seconds >= 1)\\n            return Messages.Util_second(seconds + (float) (millisecs / 100) / 10); // render "1.2 sec"\\n        else if (millisecs >= 100)\\n            return Messages.Util_second((float) (millisecs / 10) / 100); // render "0.12 sec".\\n        else\\n            return Messages.Util_millisecond(millisecs);\\n    }\'')]

[(3038, '\'void readFromTar(String name, File baseDir, InputStream in) throws IOException {\\n\\n        // TarInputStream t = new TarInputStream(in);\\n        try (TarArchiveInputStream t = new TarArchiveInputStream(in)) {\\n            TarArchiveEntry te;\\n            while ((te = t.getNextTarEntry()) != null) {\\n                File f = new File(baseDir, te.getName());\\n                if (!f.toPath().normalize().startsWith(baseDir.toPath())) {\\n                    throw new IOException(\\n                            "Tar " + name + " contains illegal file name that breaks out of the target directory: " + te.getName());\\n                }\\n                if (te.isDirectory()) {\\n                    mkdirs(f);\\n                } else {\\n                    File parent = f.getParentFile();\\n                    if (parent != null) mkdirs(parent);\\n\\n                    if (te.isSymbolicLink()) {\\n                        new FilePath(f).symlinkTo(te.getLinkName(), TaskListener.NULL);\\n                    } else {\\n                        IOUtils.copy(t, f);\\n\\n                        Files.setLastModifiedTime(Util.fileToPath(f), FileTime.from(te.getModTime().toInstant()));\\n                        int mode = te.getMode() & 0777;\\n                        if (mode != 0 && !Functions.isWindows()) // be defensive\\n                            _chmod(f, mode);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to extract " + name, e);\\n        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n            Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); // process this later\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to extract " + name, e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1861, '\'HttpResponse doUploadPlugin(StaplerRequest req) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        try {\\n            Jenkins.get().checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n\\n            String fileName = "";\\n            PluginCopier copier;\\n            File tmpDir = Files.createTempDirectory("uploadDir").toFile();\\n            ServletFileUpload upload = new ServletFileUpload(new UrlPluginCopier(fileName);\\n            } else {\\n                // this is a file upload\\n                FileItem fileItem = items.get(0);\\n                fileName = HttpRedirect("advanced");\\n            }\\n            // we allow the upload of the new jpi\\\'s and the legacy hpi\\\'s\\n            if (!fileName.endsWith(".jpi") && !fileName.endsWith(".hpi")) {\\n                throw new Failure(hudson.model.Messages.Hudson_NotAPlugin(fileName));\\n            }\\n\\n            // first copy into a temporary file name\\n            File t = File.createTempFile("uploaded", ".jpi", tmpDir);\\n            tmpDir.deleteOnExit();\\n            t.deleteOnExit();\\n            // TODO Remove this workaround after FILEUPLOAD-293 is resolved.\\n            Files.delete(Util.fileToPath(t));\\n            try {\\n                copier.copy(t);\\n            } catch (Exception e) {\\n                // Exception thrown is too generic so at least limit the scope where it can occur\\n                throw new ServletException(e);\\n            }\\n            copier.cleanup();\\n\\n            final String baseName = identifyPluginShortName(t);\\n\\n            pluginUploaded = true;\\n\\n            JSONArray dependencies = new JSONArray();\\n            try {\\n                Manifest m;\\n                try (JarFile jarFile = new JarFile(t)) {\\n                    m = jarFile.getManifest();\\n                }\\n                String deps = m.getMainAttributes().getValue("Plugin-Dependencies");\\n\\n                if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(deps)) {\\n                    // now we get to parse it!\\n                    String[] plugins = deps.split(",");\\n                    for (String p : plugins) {\\n                        // should have name:version[;resolution:=optional]\\n                        String[] attrs = p.split("[:;]");\\n                        dependencies.add(new JSONObject()\\n                                .element("name", attrs[0])\\n                                .element("version", attrs[1])\\n                                .element("optional", p.contains("resolution:=optional")));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(WARNING, "Unable to setup dependency list for plugin upload", e);\\n            }\\n\\n            // Now create a dummy plugin that we can dynamically load (the InstallationJob will force a restart if one is needed):\\n            JSONObject cfg = new JSONObject().\\n                    element("name", baseName).\\n                    element("version", "0"). // unused but mandatory\\n                    element("url", t.toURI().toString()).\\n                    element("dependencies", dependencies);\\n            new UpdateSite(UpdateCenter.ID_UPLOAD, null).new Plugin(UpdateCenter.ID_UPLOAD, cfg).deploy(true);\\n            return new HttpRedirect("updates/");\\n        } catch (FileUploadException e) {\\n            throw new ServletException(e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(160, '\'boolean isModern(Class<? extends LoadStatistics> clazz) {\\n        // cannot use Util.isOverridden as these are protected methods.\\n        boolean hasGetNodes = false;\\n        boolean hasMatches = false;\\n        while (clazz != LoadStatistics.class && clazz != null && !(hasGetNodes && hasMatches)) {\\n            if (!hasGetNodes) {\\n                try {\\n                    final Method getNodes = clazz.getDeclaredMethod("getNodes");\\n                    hasGetNodes = !Modifier.isAbstract(getNodes.getModifiers());\\n                } catch (NoSuchMethodException e) {\\n                    // ignore\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (!hasMatches) {\\n                try {\\n                    final Method getNodes = clazz.getDeclaredMethod("matches", Queue.Item.class, SubTask.class);\\n                    hasMatches = !Modifier.isAbstract(getNodes.getModifiers());\\n                } catch (NoSuchMethodException e) {\\n                    // ignore\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (!(hasGetNodes && hasMatches) && LoadStatistics.class.isAssignableFrom(clazz.getSuperclass())) {\\n                clazz = (Class<? extends LoadStatistics>) clazz.getSuperclass();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return hasGetNodes && hasMatches;\\n    }\'')]

[(143, '\'void init(boolean newInstall) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.get();\\n\\n        if (newInstall) {\\n            // Create an admin user by default with a difficult password\\n            FilePath iapf = getInitialAdminPasswordFile();\\n            if (jenkins.getSecurityRealm() == null || jenkins.getSecurityRealm() == SecurityRealm.NO_AUTHENTICATION) { // this seems very fragile\\n                try (BulkChange bc = new BulkChange(jenkins)) {\\n                    HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm securityRealm = new HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm(false, false, null);\\n                    jenkins.setSecurityRealm(securityRealm);\\n                    String randomUUID = UUID.randomUUID().toString().replace("-", "").toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);\\n\\n                    // create an admin user\\n                    User initialAdmin = securityRealm.createAccount(SetupWizard.initialSetupAdminUserName, randomUUID);\\n\\n                    if (ADMIN_INITIAL_API_TOKEN != null) {\\n                        createInitialApiToken(initialAdmin);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    // JENKINS-33599 - write to a file in the jenkins home directory\\n                    // most native packages of Jenkins creates a machine user account \\\'jenkins\\\' to run Jenkins,\\n                    // and use group \\\'jenkins\\\' for admins. So we allow groups to read this file\\n                    iapf.touch(System.currentTimeMillis());\\n                    iapf.chmod(0640);\\n                    iapf.write(randomUUID + System.lineSeparator(), "UTF-8");\\n\\n\\n                    // Lock Jenkins down:\\n                    FullControlOnceLoggedInAuthorizationStrategy authStrategy = new FullControlOnceLoggedInAuthorizationStrategy();\\n                    authStrategy.setAllowAnonymousRead(false);\\n                    jenkins.setAuthorizationStrategy(authStrategy);\\n\\n                    // Disable jnlp by default, but honor system properties\\n                    jenkins.setSlaveAgentPort(SystemProperties.getInteger(Jenkins.class.getName() + ".slaveAgentPort", -1));\\n\\n                    // require a crumb issuer\\n                    jenkins.setCrumbIssuer(GlobalCrumbIssuerConfiguration.createDefaultCrumbIssuer());\\n\\n                    jenkins.save(); // TODO could probably be removed since some of the above setters already call save\\n                    bc.commit();\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (iapf.exists()) {\\n                String setupKey = iapf.readToString().trim();\\n                String ls = System.lineSeparator();\\n                LOGGER.info(ls + ls + "*************************************************************" + ls\\n                        + "*************************************************************" + ls\\n                        + "*************************************************************" + ls\\n                        + ls\\n                        + "Jenkins initial setup is required. An admin user has been created and "\\n                        + "a password generated." + ls\\n                        + "Please use the following password to proceed to installation:" + ls\\n                        + ls\\n                        + setupKey + ls\\n                        + ls\\n                        + "This may also be found at: " + iapf.getRemote() + ls\\n                        + ls\\n                        + "*************************************************************" + ls\\n                        + "*************************************************************" + ls\\n                        + "*************************************************************" + ls);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            // Make sure plugin metadata is up to date\\n            UpdateCenter.updateDefaultSite();\\n        } catch (RuntimeException e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, e.getMessage(), e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(2118, '\'String getPasswordValue(Object o) {\\n        if (o == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        /*\\n         Return plain value if it\\\'s the default value for PasswordParameterDefinition.\\n         This needs to work even when the user doesn\\\'t have CONFIGURE permission\\n         */\\n        if (o.equals(PasswordParameterDefinition.DEFAULT_VALUE)) {\\n            return o.toString();\\n        }\\n\\n        /* Mask from Extended Read */\\n        StaplerRequest req = Stapler.getCurrentRequest();\\n        if (o instanceof Secret || Secret.BLANK_NONSECRET_PASSWORD_FIELDS_WITHOUT_ITEM_CONFIGURE) {\\n            if (req != null) {\\n                Item item = req.findAncestorObject(Item.class);\\n                if (item != null && !item.hasPermission(Item.CONFIGURE)) {\\n                    return "********";\\n                }\\n                Computer computer = req.findAncestorObject(Computer.class);\\n                if (computer != null && !computer.hasPermission(Computer.CONFIGURE)) {\\n                    return "********";\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        /* Return encrypted value if it\\\'s a Secret */\\n        if (o instanceof Secret) {\\n            return ((Secret) o).getEncryptedValue();\\n        }\\n\\n        /* Log a warning if we\\\'re in development mode (core or plugin): There\\\'s an f:password backed by a non-Secret */\\n        if (req != null && (Boolean.getBoolean("hudson.hpi.run") || Boolean.getBoolean("hudson.Main.development"))) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, () -> "<f:password/> form control in " + getJellyViewsInformationForCurrentRequest() +\\n                    " is not backed by hudson.util.Secret. Learn more: https://www.jenkins.io/redirect/hudson.util.Secret");\\n        }\\n\\n        /* Return plain value if it\\\'s not a Secret and the escape hatch is set */\\n        if (!Secret.AUTO_ENCRYPT_PASSWORD_CONTROL) {\\n            return o.toString();\\n        }\\n\\n        /* Make it a Secret and return its encrypted value */\\n        return Secret.fromString(o.toString()).getEncryptedValue();\\n    }\'')]

[(160, '\'KeyAgreement diffieHellman(boolean side, int keySize) throws IOException, GeneralSecurityException {\\n        KeyPair keyPair;\\n        PublicKey otherHalf;\\n\\n        if (side) {\\n            AlgorithmParameterGenerator paramGen = AlgorithmParameterGenerator.getInstance("DH");\\n            paramGen.init(keySize);\\n\\n            KeyPairGenerator dh = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance("DH");\\n            dh.initialize(paramGen.generateParameters().getParameterSpec(DHParameterSpec.class));\\n            keyPair = dh.generateKeyPair();\\n\\n            // send a half and get a half\\n            writeKey(keyPair.getPublic());\\n            otherHalf = KeyFactory.getInstance("DH").generatePublic(readKey());\\n        } else {\\n            otherHalf = KeyFactory.getInstance("DH").generatePublic(readKey());\\n\\n            KeyPairGenerator keyPairGen = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance("DH");\\n            keyPairGen.initialize(((DHPublicKey) otherHalf).getParams());\\n            keyPair = keyPairGen.generateKeyPair();\\n\\n            // send a half and get a half\\n            writeKey(keyPair.getPublic());\\n        }\\n\\n        KeyAgreement ka = KeyAgreement.getInstance("DH");\\n        ka.init(keyPair.getPrivate());\\n        ka.doPhase(otherHalf, true);\\n\\n        return ka;\\n    }\'')]

[(442, '"Calendar floor(Calendar cal) {\\n        Calendar twoYearsAgo = (Calendar) cal.clone();\\n        twoYearsAgo.add(Calendar.YEAR, -2);\\n\\n        OUTER:\\n        while (true) {\\n            if (cal.compareTo(twoYearsAgo) < 0) {\\n                // we went too far into the past\\n                throw new RareOrImpossibleDateException();\\n            }\\n            for (CalendarField f : CalendarField.ADJUST_ORDER) {\\n                int cur = f.valueOf(cal);\\n                int next = f.floor(this, cur);\\n                if (cur == next)  continue;   // this field is already in a good shape. move on to next\\n\\n                // we are modifying this field, so clear all the lower level fields\\n                for (CalendarField l = f.lowerField; l != null; l = l.lowerField)\\n                    l.clear(cal);\\n\\n                if (next < 0) {\\n                    // we need to borrow from the next field.\\n                    f.rollUp(cal, -1);\\n                    // the problem here, in contrast with the ceil method, is that\\n                    // the maximum value of the field is not always a fixed value (that is, day of month)\\n                    // so we zero-clear all the lower fields, set the desired value +1,\\n                    f.setTo(cal, f.last(this));\\n                    f.addTo(cal, 1);\\n                    // then subtract a minute to achieve maximum values on all the lower fields,\\n                    // with the desired value in \'f\'\\n                    CalendarField.MINUTE.addTo(cal, -1);\\n                    // since higher order field is affected by this, we need to restart from all over\\n                    continue OUTER;\\n                } else {\\n                    f.setTo(cal, next);\\n                    f.addTo(cal, 1);\\n                    CalendarField.MINUTE.addTo(cal, -1);\\n                    if (f.redoAdjustmentIfModified)\\n                        continue OUTER; // when we modify DAY_OF_MONTH and DAY_OF_WEEK, do it all over from the top\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return cal; // all fields adjusted\\n        }\\n    }"')]
