[(359, '\'void renameTo(final String newName) throws IOException {\\n\\n        if (!isNameEditable()) {\\n            throw new IOException("Trying to rename an item that does not support this operation.");\\n        }\\n\\n        // always synchronize from bigger objects first\\n        final ItemGroup parent = getParent();\\n        String oldName = this.name;\\n        String oldFullName = getFullName();\\n        synchronized (parent) {\\n            synchronized (this) {\\n                // sanity check\\n                if (newName == null)\\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException("New name is not given");\\n\\n                // noop?\\n                if (this.name.equals(newName))\\n                    return;\\n\\n                // the lookup is case insensitive, so we should not fail if this item was the “existing” one\\n                // to allow people to rename "Foo" to "foo", for example.\\n                // see http://www.nabble.com/error-on-renaming-project-tt18061629.html\\n                Items.verifyItemDoesNotAlreadyExist(parent, newName, this);\\n\\n                File oldRoot = this.getRootDir();\\n\\n                doSetName(newName);\\n                File newRoot = this.getRootDir();\\n\\n                boolean success = false;\\n\\n                try { // rename data files\\n                    boolean interrupted = false;\\n                    boolean renamed = false;\\n\\n                    // try to rename the job directory.\\n                    // this may fail on Windows due to some other processes\\n                    // accessing a file.\\n                    // so retry few times before we fall back to copy.\\n                    for (int retry = 0; retry < 5; retry++) {\\n                        if (oldRoot.renameTo(newRoot)) {\\n                            renamed = true;\\n                            break; // succeeded\\n                        }\\n                        try {\\n                            Thread.sleep(500);\\n                        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n                            // process the interruption later\\n                            interrupted = true;\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    if (interrupted)\\n                        Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\\n\\n                    if (!renamed) {\\n                        // failed to rename. it must be that some lengthy\\n                        // process is going on\\n                        // to prevent a rename operation. So do a copy. Ideally\\n                        // we\\\'d like to\\n                        // later delete the old copy, but we can\\\'t reliably do\\n                        // so, as before the VM\\n                        // shuts down there might be a new job created under the\\n                        // old name.\\n                        Copy cp = new Copy();\\n                        cp.setProject(new Project());\\n                        cp.setTodir(newRoot);\\n                        FileSet src = new FileSet();\\n                        src.setDir(oldRoot);\\n                        cp.addFileset(src);\\n                        cp.setOverwrite(true);\\n                        cp.setPreserveLastModified(true);\\n                        cp.setFailOnError(false); // keep going even if\\n                                                    // there\\\'s an error\\n                        cp.execute();\\n\\n                        // try to delete as much as possible\\n                        try {\\n                            Util.deleteRecursive(oldRoot);\\n                        } catch (IOException e) {\\n                            // but ignore the error, since we expect that\\n                            e.printStackTrace();\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    success = true;\\n                } finally {\\n                    // if failed, back out the rename.\\n                    if (!success)\\n                        doSetName(oldName);\\n                }\\n\\n                parent.onRenamed(this, oldName, newName);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        ItemListener.fireLocationChange(this, oldFullName);\\n    }\'')]

[(217, '\'void buildDependencyGraph(AbstractProject owner, DependencyGraph graph) {\\n        if (enableFingerprintsInDependencyGraph) {\\n            RunList builds = owner.getBuilds();\\n            Set<String> seenUpstreamProjects = new HashSet<>();\\n\\n            for (Object build1 : builds) {\\n                Run build = (Run) build1;\\n                for (FingerprintAction action : build.getActions(FingerprintAction.class)) {\\n                    for (AbstractProject key : action.getDependencies().keySet()) {\\n                        if (key == owner) {\\n                            continue;   // Avoid self references\\n                        }\\n\\n                        AbstractProject p = key;\\n                        // TODO is this harmful to call unconditionally, so it would apply also to MavenModule for example?\\n                        if (key.getClass().getName().equals("hudson.matrix.MatrixConfiguration")) {\\n                            p = key.getRootProject();\\n                        }\\n\\n                        if (seenUpstreamProjects.contains(p.getName())) {\\n                            continue;\\n                        }\\n\\n                        seenUpstreamProjects.add(p.getName());\\n                        graph.addDependency(new Dependency(p, owner) {\\n                            @Override\\n                            public boolean shouldTriggerBuild(AbstractBuild build,\\n                                                              TaskListener listener,\\n                                                              List<Action> actions) {\\n                                // Fingerprints should not trigger builds.\\n                                return false;\\n                            }\\n                        });\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(235, '\'void doRss(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp, List<LogRecord> logs) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        // filter log records based on the log level\\n        String entryType = "all";\\n        String level = req.getParameter("level");\\n        if (level != null) {\\n            Level threshold = Level.parse(level);\\n            List<LogRecord> filtered = new ArrayList<>();\\n            for (LogRecord r : logs) {\\n                if (r.getLevel().intValue() >= threshold.intValue())\\n                    filtered.add(r);\\n            }\\n            logs = filtered;\\n            entryType = level;\\n        }\\n\\n        RSS.forwardToRss("Jenkins:log (" + entryType + " entries)", "", logs, new FeedAdapter<>() {\\n            @Override\\n            public String getEntryTitle(LogRecord entry) {\\n                return entry.getMessage();\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public String getEntryUrl(LogRecord entry) {\\n                return "log";   // TODO: one URL for one log entry?\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public String getEntryID(LogRecord entry) {\\n                return String.valueOf(entry.getSequenceNumber());\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public String getEntryDescription(LogRecord entry) {\\n                return Functions.printLogRecord(entry);\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public Calendar getEntryTimestamp(LogRecord entry) {\\n                GregorianCalendar cal = new GregorianCalendar();\\n                cal.setTimeInMillis(entry.getMillis());\\n                return cal;\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public String getEntryAuthor(LogRecord entry) {\\n                return JenkinsLocationConfiguration.get().getAdminAddress();\\n            }\\n        }, req, rsp);\\n    }\'')]

[(1718, '\'Set<PosixFilePermission> modeToPermissions(int mode) throws IOException {\\n         // Anything larger is a file type, not a permission.\\n        int PERMISSIONS_MASK = 07777;\\n        // setgid/setuid/sticky are not supported.\\n        int MAX_SUPPORTED_MODE = 0777;\\n        mode = mode & PERMISSIONS_MASK;\\n        if ((mode & MAX_SUPPORTED_MODE) != mode) {\\n            throw new IOException("Invalid mode: " + mode);\\n        }\\n        PosixFilePermission[] allPermissions = PosixFilePermission.values();\\n        Set<PosixFilePermission> result = EnumSet.noneOf(PosixFilePermission.class);\\n        for (int i = 0; i < allPermissions.length; i++) {\\n            if ((mode & 1) == 1) {\\n                result.add(allPermissions[allPermissions.length - i - 1]);\\n            }\\n            mode >>= 1;\\n        }\\n        return result;\\n    }\'')]

[(306, '\'boolean isValid(String value) {\\n        if (value == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        URI uri; // ensure value is a valid URI\\n        try {\\n            uri = new URI(value);\\n        } catch (URISyntaxException e) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        // OK, perfom additional validation\\n\\n        String scheme = uri.getScheme();\\n        if (!isValidScheme(scheme)) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        String authority = uri.getRawAuthority();\\n        if ("file".equals(scheme) && (authority == null || "".equals(authority))) { // Special case - file: allows an empty authority\\n            return true; // this is a local file - nothing more to do here\\n        } else if ("file".equals(scheme) && authority != null && authority.contains(":")) {\\n            return false;\\n        } else {\\n            // Validate the authority\\n            if (!isValidAuthority(authority)) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!isValidPath(uri.getRawPath())) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!isValidQuery(uri.getRawQuery())) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!isValidFragment(uri.getRawFragment())) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(107, '\'boolean perform(AbstractBuild<?, ?> build, Launcher launcher, TaskListener listener) throws InterruptedException {\\n        FilePath ws = build.getWorkspace();\\n        if (ws == null) {\\n            Node node = build.getBuiltOn();\\n            if (node == null) {\\n                throw new NullPointerException("no such build node: " + build.getBuiltOnStr());\\n            }\\n            throw new NullPointerException("no workspace from node " + node + " which is computer " + node.toComputer() + " and has channel " + node.getChannel());\\n        }\\n        FilePath script = null;\\n        int r = -1;\\n        try {\\n            try {\\n                script = createScriptFile(ws);\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                Util.displayIOException(e, listener);\\n                Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.CommandInterpreter_UnableToProduceScript()));\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            try {\\n                EnvVars envVars = build.getEnvironment(listener);\\n                // on Windows environment variables are converted to all upper case,\\n                // but no such conversions are done on Unix, so to make this cross-platform,\\n                // convert variables to all upper cases.\\n                for (Map.Entry<String, String> e : build.getBuildVariables().entrySet())\\n                    envVars.put(e.getKey(), e.getValue());\\n\\n                launcher.prepareFilterRules(build, this);\\n\\n                Launcher.ProcStarter procStarter = launcher.launch();\\n                procStarter.cmds(buildCommandLine(script))\\n                        .envs(envVars)\\n                        .stdout(listener)\\n                        .pwd(ws);\\n\\n                try {\\n                    Proc proc = procStarter.start();\\n                    r = join(proc);\\n                } catch (EnvVarsFilterException se) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Environment variable filtering failed", se);\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n\\n                if (isErrorlevelForUnstableBuild(r)) {\\n                    build.setResult(Result.UNSTABLE);\\n                    r = 0;\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                Util.displayIOException(e, listener);\\n                Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.CommandInterpreter_CommandFailed()));\\n            }\\n            return r == 0;\\n        } finally {\\n            try {\\n                if (script != null)\\n                    script.delete();\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                if (r == -1 && e.getCause() instanceof ChannelClosedException) {\\n                    // JENKINS-5073\\n                    // r==-1 only when the execution of the command resulted in IOException,\\n                    // and we\\\'ve already reported that error. A common error there is channel\\n                    // losing a connection, and in that case we don\\\'t want to confuse users\\n                    // by reporting the 2nd problem. Technically the 1st exception may not be\\n                    // a channel closed error, but that\\\'s rare enough, and JENKINS-5073 is common enough\\n                    // that this suppressing of the error would be justified\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Script deletion failed", e);\\n                } else {\\n                    Util.displayIOException(e, listener);\\n                    Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.CommandInterpreter_UnableToDelete(script)));\\n                }\\n            } catch (Exception e) {\\n                Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.CommandInterpreter_UnableToDelete(script)));\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(352, "'LoadStatisticsSnapshot computeSnapshot(Iterable<Queue.BuildableItem> queue) {\\n        final LoadStatisticsSnapshot.Builder builder = LoadStatisticsSnapshot.builder();\\n        final Iterable<Node> nodes = getNodes();\\n        if (nodes != null) {\\n            for (Node node : nodes) {\\n                builder.with(node);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        int q = 0;\\n        if (queue != null) {\\n            for (Queue.BuildableItem item : queue) {\\n\\n                for (SubTask st : item.task.getSubTasks()) {\\n                    if (matches(item, st))\\n                        q++;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return builder.withQueueLength(q).build();\\n    }'")]

[(105, '\'void assertExitCode(int code, boolean useApiToken, File jar, String... args) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        List<String> commands = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList("java", "-jar", jar.getAbsolutePath(), "-s", j.getURL().toString()));\\n        if (useApiToken) {\\n            commands.add("-auth");\\n            commands.add(ADMIN + ":" + User.getOrCreateByIdOrFullName(ADMIN).getProperty(ApiTokenProperty.class).getApiToken());\\n        }\\n        commands.addAll(Arrays.asList(args));\\n        final Launcher.LocalLauncher launcher = new Launcher.LocalLauncher(StreamTaskListener.fromStderr());\\n        final Proc proc = launcher.launch().cmds(commands).stdout(System.out).stderr(System.err).start();\\n        if (!Functions.isWindows()) {\\n            // Try to get a thread dump of the client if it hangs.\\n            Timer.get().schedule(() -> {\\n                try {\\n                    if (proc.isAlive()) {\\n                        Field procF = Proc.LocalProc.class.getDeclaredField("proc");\\n                        procF.setAccessible(true);\\n                        ProcessTree.OSProcess osp = ProcessTree.get().get((Process) procF.get(proc));\\n                        if (osp != null) {\\n                            launcher.launch().cmds("kill", "-QUIT", Integer.toString(osp.getPid())).stdout(System.out).stderr(System.err).join();\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                } catch (Exception x) {\\n                    throw new AssertionError(x);\\n                }\\n            }, 1, TimeUnit.MINUTES);\\n        }\\n        assertEquals(code, proc.join());\\n    }\'')]

[(1082, '\'void doRssChangelog(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        class FeedItem {\\n            ChangeLogSet.Entry e;\\n            int idx;\\n\\n            FeedItem(ChangeLogSet.Entry e, int idx) {\\n                this.e = e;\\n                this.idx = idx;\\n            }\\n\\n            Run<?, ?> getBuild() {\\n                return e.getParent().build;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        List<FeedItem> entries = new ArrayList<>();\\n        String scmDisplayName = "";\\n        if (this instanceof SCMTriggerItem) {\\n            SCMTriggerItem scmItem = (SCMTriggerItem) this;\\n            List<String> scmNames = new ArrayList<>();\\n            for (SCM s : scmItem.getSCMs()) {\\n                scmNames.add(s.getDescriptor().getDisplayName());\\n            }\\n            scmDisplayName = " " + String.join(", ", scmNames);\\n        }\\n\\n        for (RunT r = getLastBuild(); r != null; r = r.getPreviousBuild()) {\\n            int idx = 0;\\n            if (r instanceof RunWithSCM) {\\n                for (ChangeLogSet<? extends ChangeLogSet.Entry> c : ((RunWithSCM<?, ?>) r).getChangeSets()) {\\n                    for (ChangeLogSet.Entry e : c) {\\n                        entries.add(new FeedItem(e, idx++));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        RSS.forwardToRss(\\n                getDisplayName() + scmDisplayName + " changes",\\n                getUrl() + "changes",\\n                entries, new FeedAdapter<>() {\\n                    @Override\\n                    public String getEntryTitle(FeedItem item) {\\n                        return "#" + item.getBuild().number + \\\' \\\' + item.e.getMsg() + " (" + item.e.getAuthor() + ")";\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public String getEntryUrl(FeedItem item) {\\n                        return item.getBuild().getUrl() + "changes#detail" + item.idx;\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public String getEntryID(FeedItem item) {\\n                            return getEntryUrl(item);\\n                        }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public String getEntryDescription(FeedItem item) {\\n                        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n                        for (String path : item.e.getAffectedPaths())\\n                            buf.append(path).append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                        return buf.toString();\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public Calendar getEntryTimestamp(FeedItem item) {\\n                            return item.getBuild().getTimestamp();\\n                        }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public String getEntryAuthor(FeedItem entry) {\\n                        return JenkinsLocationConfiguration.get().getAdminAddress();\\n                    }\\n                },\\n                req, rsp);\\n    }\'')]

[(258, "'boolean execute(AbstractBuild build, BuildListener listener) {\\n        PrintStream logger = listener.getLogger();\\n        // Check all downstream Project of the project, not just those defined by BuildTrigger\\n\\n        DependencyGraph graphTemp;\\n        try {\\n            // Note: futureDependencyGraph can be null, if no asynchronous computation of the\\n            // dependency graph has been performed.\\n            Future<DependencyGraph> futureDependencyGraph = Jenkins.get().getFutureDependencyGraph();\\n            if (futureDependencyGraph != null) {\\n                graphTemp = futureDependencyGraph.get();\\n            } else {\\n                graphTemp = Jenkins.get().getDependencyGraph();\\n            }\\n        } catch (IllegalStateException | InterruptedException | ExecutionException e) {\\n            // Use old version of dependency graph instead\\n            graphTemp = Jenkins.get().getDependencyGraph();\\n        }\\n        DependencyGraph graph = graphTemp;\\n\\n        List<Dependency> downstreamProjects = new ArrayList<>(\\n                graph.getDownstreamDependencies(build.getProject()));\\n        // Sort topologically\\n        downstreamProjects.sort(new Comparator<>() {\\n            @Override\\n            public int compare(Dependency lhs, Dependency rhs) {\\n                // Swapping lhs/rhs to get reverse sort:\\n                return graph.compare(rhs.getDownstreamProject(), lhs.getDownstreamProject());\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        for (Dependency dep : downstreamProjects) {\\n            List<Action> buildActions = new ArrayList<>();\\n            if (dep.shouldTriggerBuild(build, listener, buildActions)) {\\n                AbstractProject p = dep.getDownstreamProject();\\n                // Allow shouldTriggerBuild to return false first, in case it is skipping because of a lack of Item.READ/DISCOVER permission:\\n                if (p.isDisabled()) {\\n                    logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_Disabled(ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(p)));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                boolean scheduled = p.scheduleBuild(p.getQuietPeriod(), new UpstreamCause((Run) build), buildActions.toArray(new Action[0]));\\n                if (Jenkins.get().getItemByFullName(p.getFullName()) == p) {\\n                    String name = ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(p);\\n                    if (scheduled) {\\n                        logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_Triggering(name));\\n                    } else {\\n                        logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_InQueue(name));\\n                    }\\n                } // otherwise upstream users should not know that it happened\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }'")]

[(223, '"boolean shouldSchedule(List<Action> actions) {\\n        List<ParametersAction> others = Util.filter(actions, ParametersAction.class);\\n        if (others.isEmpty()) {\\n            return !parameters.isEmpty();\\n        } else {\\n            // I don\'t think we need multiple ParametersActions, but let\'s be defensive\\n            Set<ParameterValue> params = new HashSet<>();\\n            for (ParametersAction other : others) {\\n                params.addAll(other.parameters);\\n            }\\n            return !params.equals(new HashSet<>(this.parameters));\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(2056, "'VerificationResult verifyChecksums(String expectedDigest, String actualDigest, boolean caseSensitive) {\\n        if (expectedDigest == null) {\\n            return VerificationResult.NOT_PROVIDED;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (actualDigest == null) {\\n            return VerificationResult.NOT_COMPUTED;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (caseSensitive) {\\n            if (MessageDigest.isEqual(expectedDigest.getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII), actualDigest.getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII))) {\\n                return VerificationResult.PASS;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            if (MessageDigest.isEqual(expectedDigest.toLowerCase().getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII), actualDigest.toLowerCase().getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII))) {\\n                return VerificationResult.PASS;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return VerificationResult.FAIL;\\n    }'")]

[(109, "'boolean isInstalled(int major, int minor, String targetMachine, IJIAuthInfo session) throws JIException, UnknownHostException {\\n        IJIWinReg registry = JIWinRegFactory.getSingleTon().getWinreg(session, targetMachine, true);\\n        JIPolicyHandle hklm = null;\\n        try {\\n            hklm = registry.winreg_OpenHKLM();\\n            if (major == 4 && minor >= 5) {\\n                return isV45PlusInstalled(minor, registry, hklm);\\n            } else if (major == 4 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV40Installed(registry, hklm);\\n            } else if (major == 3 && minor == 5) {\\n                return isV35Installed(registry, hklm);\\n            } else if (major == 3 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV35Installed(registry, hklm) || isV30Installed(registry, hklm);\\n            } else if (major == 2 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV35Installed(registry, hklm) || isV30Installed(registry, hklm) || isV20Installed(registry, hklm);\\n            } else {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        } catch (JIException e) {\\n            if (e.getErrorCode() == 2) {\\n                // not found\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n            throw e;\\n        } finally {\\n            if (hklm != null) {\\n                registry.winreg_CloseKey(hklm);\\n            }\\n            registry.closeConnection();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(32, '\'void _logRecordsArePresentOnController(JenkinsRule r) throws Throwable {\\n        List<LogRecord> logRecords = Jenkins.logRecords;\\n        assertThat(logRecords, not(empty()));\\n        assertThat("Records are displayed in reverse order",\\n            logRecords.stream().map(LogRecord::getMessage).collect(Collectors.toList()),\\n            containsInRelativeOrder("Completed initialization", "Started initialization"));\\n        VersionNumber javaVersion = new VersionNumber(JavaUtils.getCurrentRuntimeJavaVersion());\\n        if (javaVersion.isNewerThanOrEqualTo(new VersionNumber("17"))) { // TODO https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins-test-harness/issues/359\\n            Object x = new Object() {\\n                @Override\\n                public String toString() {\\n                    return "collect me";\\n                }\\n            };\\n            use(x);\\n            WeakReference<Object> ref = new WeakReference<>(x);\\n            x = null;\\n            MemoryAssert.assertGC(ref, true);\\n            assertThat("Record parameters formatted before collection",\\n                logRecords.stream().map(LogRecord::getMessage).collect(Collectors.toList()),\\n                hasItem("formatting collect me"));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(59, '\'List<Date> loadAttempts(File home) {\\n        List<Date> dates = new ArrayList<>();\\n        if (home != null) {\\n            File f = getBootFailureFile(home);\\n            try {\\n                if (f.exists()) {\\n                    try (BufferedReader failureFileReader = Files.newBufferedReader(f.toPath(), Charset.defaultCharset())) {\\n                        String line;\\n                        // WebAppMain.recordBootAttempt uses Date.toString when writing, so that is the format we must parse.\\n                        SimpleDateFormat df = new SimpleDateFormat("EEE MMM dd HH:mm:ss zzz yyyy");\\n                        while ((line = failureFileReader.readLine()) != null) {\\n                            try {\\n                                dates.add(df.parse(line));\\n                            } catch (Exception e) {\\n                                // ignore any parse error\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException | InvalidPathException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to parse " + f, e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return dates;\\n    }\'')]

[(4730, '\'HttpResponse doSafeExit(StaplerRequest req) throws IOException {\\n        checkPermission(ADMINISTER);\\n        quietDownInfo = new QuietDownInfo();\\n        final String exitUser = getAuthentication2().getName();\\n        final String exitAddr = req != null ? req.getRemoteAddr() : null;\\n        new Thread("safe-exit thread") {\\n            @Override\\n            @SuppressFBWarnings(value = "DM_EXIT", justification = "Exit is really intended.")\\n            public void run() {\\n                try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n                    getLifecycle().onStop(exitUser, exitAddr);\\n                    // Wait \\\'til we have no active executors.\\n                    doQuietDown(true, 0, null);\\n                    // Make sure isQuietingDown is still true.\\n                    if (isQuietingDown()) {\\n                        cleanUp();\\n                        System.exit(0);\\n                    }\\n                } catch (Exception e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to shut down Jenkins", e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }.start();\\n\\n        return HttpResponses.plainText("Shutting down as soon as all jobs are complete");\\n    }\'')]

[(430, '\'Map getHtmlInfo(final File f) throws IOException {\\n final Map info = new HashMap<>();\\n\\n// .ax\\n final Pattern domain = Pattern.compile(".*country-code\\n final Pattern type = Pattern.compile("\\\\\\\\s+([^<]+)");\\n// \\n// Ålands landskapsregering\\n final Pattern comment = Pattern.compile("\\\\\\\\s+([^<]+)");\\n\\n final BufferedReader br = Files.newBufferedReader(f.toPath(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n String line;\\n while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {\\n Matcher m = domain.matcher(line);\\n if (m.lookingAt()) {\\n String dom = m.group(1);\\n String typ = "??";\\n String com = "??";\\n line = br.readLine();\\n while (line.matches("^\\\\\\\\s*$")) { // extra blank lines introduced\\n line = br.readLine();\\n }\\n Matcher t = type.matcher(line);\\n if (t.lookingAt()) {\\n typ = t.group(1);\\n line = br.readLine();\\n if (line.matches("\\\\\\\\s+.*")) {\\n line = br.readLine();\\n }\\n line = br.readLine();\\n }\\n // Should have comment; is it wrapped?\\n while (!line.matches(".*.*")) {\\n line += " " + br.readLine();\\n }\\n Matcher n = comment.matcher(line);\\n if (n.lookingAt()) {\\n com = n.group(1);\\n }\\n // Don\\\'t save unused entries\\n if (com.contains("Not assigned") || com.contains("Retired") || typ.equals("test")) {\\n// System.out.println("Ignored: " + typ + " " + dom + " " +com);\\n } else {\\n info.put(dom.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH), new String[]{typ, com});\\n// System.out.println("Storing: " + typ + " " + dom + " " +com);\\n }\\n } else {\\n System.err.println("Unexpected type: " + line);\\n }\\n }\\n }\\n br.close();\\n return info;\\n }\'')]

[(69, '\'void execute(TaskListener listener) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        boolean due = false;\\n        for (UpdateSite site : Jenkins.get().getUpdateCenter().getSites()) {\\n            if (site.isDue()) {\\n                due = true;\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (!due) {\\n            // JENKINS-32886: downloadables like the tool installer data may have never been tried if the plugin\\n            // was installed "after a restart", so let\\\'s give them a try here.\\n            final long now = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n            for (DownloadService.Downloadable d : DownloadService.Downloadable.all()) {\\n                if (d.getDue() <= now) {\\n                    try {\\n                        d.updateNow();\\n                    } catch (Exception e) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, String.format("Unable to update downloadable [%s]", d.getId()), e);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        // This checks updates of the update sites and downloadables.\\n        HttpResponse rsp = Jenkins.get().getPluginManager().doCheckUpdatesServer();\\n        if (rsp instanceof FormValidation) {\\n            listener.error(((FormValidation) rsp).renderHtml());\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(435, '\'String unquote(String s)\\n    {\\n        if (s == null)\\n            return null;\\n        if (s.length() < 2)\\n            return s;\\n\\n        char first = s.charAt(0);\\n        char last = s.charAt(s.length() - 1);\\n        if (first != last || (first != \\\'"\\\' && first != \\\'\\\\\\\'\\\'))\\n            return s;\\n\\n        StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder(s.length() - 2);\\n        boolean escape = false;\\n        for (int i = 1; i < s.length() - 1; i++)\\n        {\\n            char c = s.charAt(i);\\n\\n            if (escape)\\n            {\\n                escape = false;\\n                switch (c)\\n                {\\n                    case \\\'n\\\':\\n                        b.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case \\\'r\\\':\\n                        b.append(\\\'\\\\r\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case \\\'t\\\':\\n                        b.append(\\\'\\\\t\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case \\\'f\\\':\\n                        b.append(\\\'\\\\f\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case \\\'b\\\':\\n                        b.append(\\\'\\\\b\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case \\\'u\\\':\\n                        b.append((char) (\\n                                (convertHexDigit((byte) s.charAt(i++)) << 24) +\\n                                (convertHexDigit((byte) s.charAt(i++)) << 16) +\\n                                (convertHexDigit((byte) s.charAt(i++)) << 8) +\\n                                convertHexDigit((byte) s.charAt(i++))\\n                                )\\n                        );\\n                        break;\\n                    default:\\n                        b.append(c);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            else if (c == \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\')\\n            {\\n                escape = true;\\n            }\\n            else\\n                b.append(c);\\n        }\\n\\n        return b.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(92, '"Run<?, ?> resolve(Job<?, ?> job) {\\n        Map<String, Integer> cache = cacheFor(job.getBuildDir());\\n        int n;\\n        synchronized (cache) {\\n            n = cache.getOrDefault(getId(), 0);\\n        }\\n        if (n == RESOLVES_TO_NONE) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        Run<?, ?> b;\\n        if (n > 0) {\\n            b = job.getBuildByNumber(n);\\n            if (b != null && apply(b)) {\\n                return b; // found it (in the most efficient way possible)\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            b = null;\\n        }\\n\\n        // the cache is stale. start the search\\n        if (b == null) {\\n            b = job.getNearestOldBuild(n);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (b == null) {\\n            // no cache\\n            b = job.getLastBuild();\\n        }\\n\\n        // start from the build \'b\' and locate the build that matches the criteria going back in time\\n        b = find(b);\\n\\n        updateCache(job, b);\\n        return b;\\n    }"')]

[(2254, '\'String unicodeToASCII(String input) {\\n        if (isOnlyASCII(input)) { // skip possibly expensive processing\\n            return input;\\n        }\\n        try {\\n            final String ascii = IDN.toASCII(input);\\n            if (DomainValidator.IDNBUGHOLDER.IDN_TOASCII_PRESERVES_TRAILING_DOTS) {\\n                return ascii;\\n            }\\n            final int length = input.length();\\n            if (length == 0) { // check there is a last character\\n                return input;\\n            }\\n            // RFC3490 3.1. 1)\\n            //            Whenever dots are used as label separators, the following\\n            //            characters MUST be recognized as dots: U+002E (full stop), U+3002\\n            //            (ideographic full stop), U+FF0E (fullwidth full stop), U+FF61\\n            //            (halfwidth ideographic full stop).\\n            char lastChar = input.charAt(length - 1); // fetch original last char\\n            switch (lastChar) {\\n                case \\\'\\\\u002E\\\': // "." full stop\\n                case \\\'\\\\u3002\\\': // ideographic full stop\\n                case \\\'\\\\uFF0E\\\': // fullwidth full stop\\n                case \\\'\\\\uFF61\\\': // halfwidth ideographic full stop\\n                    return ascii + "."; // restore the missing stop\\n                default:\\n                    return ascii;\\n            }\\n        } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) { // input is not valid\\n            return input;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(229, '"void sort(List<?> items) {\\n        // Queue items can start building out of order with how they got added to the queue. Sorting them\\n        // before adding to the page. They\'ll still get displayed before the building items coz they end\\n        // up in a different list in HistoryPageFilter.\\n        items.sort(new Comparator<Object>() {\\n            @Override\\n            public int compare(Object o1, Object o2) {\\n                long o1QID = HistoryPageEntry.getEntryId(o1);\\n                long o2QID = HistoryPageEntry.getEntryId(o2);\\n\\n                return Long.compare(o2QID, o1QID);\\n            }\\n        });\\n    }"')]

[(207, '\'void report(Saveable obj, Collection<Throwable> errors) {\\n        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n        int i = 0;\\n        for (Throwable e : errors) {\\n            if (e instanceof ReportException) {\\n                report(obj, ((ReportException) e).version);\\n            } else {\\n                if (Main.isUnitTest) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Trouble loading " + obj, e);\\n                }\\n                if (++i > 1) buf.append(", ");\\n                buf.append(e.getClass().getSimpleName()).append(": ").append(e.getMessage());\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (buf.length() == 0) return;\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n        if (j == null) { // Need this path, at least for unit tests, but also in case of very broken startup\\n            // Startup failed, something is very broken, so report what we can.\\n            for (Throwable t : errors) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "could not read " + obj + " (and Jenkins did not start up)", t);\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        OldDataMonitor odm = get(j);\\n        SaveableReference ref = referTo(obj);\\n        while (true) {\\n            VersionRange vr = odm.data.get(ref);\\n            if (vr != null && odm.data.replace(ref, vr, new VersionRange(vr, null, buf.toString()))) {\\n                break;\\n            } else if (odm.data.putIfAbsent(ref, new VersionRange(null, null, buf.toString())) == null) {\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1120, '\'InputStream getBundledJpiManifestStream(@NonNull URL url) throws IOException {\\n        URLConnection uc = url.openConnection();\\n        InputStream in = null;\\n        // Magic, which allows to avoid using stream generated for JarURLConnection.\\n        // It prevents getting into JENKINS-37332 due to the file descriptor leak\\n        if (uc instanceof JarURLConnection) {\\n            final JarURLConnection jarURLConnection = (JarURLConnection) uc;\\n            final String entryName = jarURLConnection.getEntryName();\\n\\n            try (JarFile jarFile = jarURLConnection.getJarFile()) {\\n                final JarEntry entry = entryName != null && jarFile != null ? jarFile.getJarEntry(entryName) : null;\\n                if (entry != null) {\\n                    try (InputStream i = jarFile.getInputStream(entry)) {\\n                        byte[] manifestBytes = i.readAllBytes();\\n                        in = new ByteArrayInputStream(manifestBytes);\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to locate the JAR file for {0}"\\n                            + "The default URLConnection stream access will be used, file descriptor may be leaked.",\\n                               url);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // If input stream is undefined, use the default implementation\\n        if (in == null) {\\n            in = url.openStream();\\n        }\\n\\n        return in;\\n    }\'')]

[(71, '\'boolean perform(AbstractBuild<?, ?> build, Launcher launcher, BuildListener listener) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        if (this instanceof SimpleBuildStep) {\\n            // delegate to the overloaded version defined in SimpleBuildStep\\n            final SimpleBuildStep step = (SimpleBuildStep) this;\\n            final FilePath workspace = build.getWorkspace();\\n            if (step.requiresWorkspace() && workspace == null) {\\n                throw new AbortException("no workspace for " + build);\\n            }\\n            if (workspace != null) { // if we have one, provide it regardless of whether it\\\'s _required_\\n                step.perform(build, workspace, build.getEnvironment(listener), launcher, listener);\\n            } else {\\n                step.perform(build, build.getEnvironment(listener), listener);\\n            }\\n            return true;\\n        } else if (build instanceof Build) {\\n            // delegate to the legacy signature deprecated in 1.312\\n            return perform((Build) build, launcher, listener);\\n        } else {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(2101, '\'void verifyChecksums(WithComputedChecksums job, UpdateSite.Entry entry, File file) throws IOException {\\n        VerificationResult result512 = verifyChecksums(entry.getSha512(), job.getComputedSHA512(), false);\\n        switch (result512) {\\n            case PASS:\\n                // this has passed so no reason to check the weaker checksums\\n                return;\\n            case FAIL:\\n                throwVerificationFailure(entry.getSha512(), job.getComputedSHA512(), file, "SHA-512");\\n                break;\\n            case NOT_COMPUTED:\\n                LOGGER.log(WARNING, "Attempt to verify a downloaded file (" + file.getName() + ") using SHA-512 failed since it could not be computed. Falling back to weaker algorithms. Update your JRE.");\\n                break;\\n            case NOT_PROVIDED:\\n                break;\\n            default:\\n                throw new IllegalStateException("Unexpected value: " + result512);\\n        }\\n\\n        VerificationResult result256 = verifyChecksums(entry.getSha256(), job.getComputedSHA256(), false);\\n        switch (result256) {\\n            case PASS:\\n                return;\\n            case FAIL:\\n                throwVerificationFailure(entry.getSha256(), job.getComputedSHA256(), file, "SHA-256");\\n                break;\\n            case NOT_COMPUTED:\\n            case NOT_PROVIDED:\\n                break;\\n            default:\\n                throw new IllegalStateException("Unexpected value: " + result256);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (result512 == VerificationResult.NOT_PROVIDED && result256 == VerificationResult.NOT_PROVIDED) {\\n            LOGGER.log(INFO, "Attempt to verify a downloaded file (" + file.getName() + ") using SHA-512 or SHA-256 failed since your configured update site does not provide either of those checksums. Falling back to SHA-1.");\\n        }\\n\\n        VerificationResult result1 = verifyChecksums(entry.getSha1(), job.getComputedSHA1(), true);\\n        switch (result1) {\\n            case PASS:\\n                return;\\n            case FAIL:\\n                throwVerificationFailure(entry.getSha1(), job.getComputedSHA1(), file, "SHA-1");\\n                break;\\n            case NOT_COMPUTED:\\n                throw new IOException("Failed to compute SHA-1 of downloaded file, refusing installation");\\n            case NOT_PROVIDED:\\n                throw new IOException("Unable to confirm integrity of downloaded file, refusing installation");\\n            default:\\n                throw new AssertionError("Unknown verification result: " + result1);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(567, "'ScheduleResult schedule2(Task p, int quietPeriod, List<Action> actions) {\\n        // remove nulls\\n        actions = new ArrayList<>(actions);\\n        actions.removeIf(Objects::isNull);\\n\\n        lock.lock();\\n        try { try {\\n            for (QueueDecisionHandler h : QueueDecisionHandler.all())\\n                if (!h.shouldSchedule(p, actions))\\n                    return ScheduleResult.refused();    // veto\\n\\n            return scheduleInternal(p, quietPeriod, actions);\\n        } finally { updateSnapshot(); } } finally {\\n            lock.unlock();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(220, "'JFreeChart createChart(CategoryDataset ds) {\\n        final JFreeChart chart = ChartFactory.createLineChart(null, // chart title\\n                null, // unused\\n                null, // range axis label\\n                ds, // data\\n                PlotOrientation.VERTICAL, // orientation\\n                true, // include legend\\n                true, // tooltips\\n                false // urls\\n                );\\n\\n        chart.setBackgroundPaint(Color.white);\\n\\n        final CategoryPlot plot = chart.getCategoryPlot();\\n        plot.setBackgroundPaint(Color.WHITE);\\n        plot.setOutlinePaint(null);\\n        plot.setRangeGridlinesVisible(true);\\n        plot.setRangeGridlinePaint(Color.black);\\n\\n        final LineAndShapeRenderer renderer = (LineAndShapeRenderer) plot.getRenderer();\\n        renderer.setBaseStroke(new BasicStroke(3));\\n        configureRenderer(renderer);\\n\\n        final CategoryAxis domainAxis = new NoOverlapCategoryAxis(null);\\n        plot.setDomainAxis(domainAxis);\\n        domainAxis.setCategoryLabelPositions(CategoryLabelPositions.UP_90);\\n        domainAxis.setLowerMargin(0.0);\\n        domainAxis.setUpperMargin(0.0);\\n        domainAxis.setCategoryMargin(0.0);\\n\\n        final NumberAxis rangeAxis = (NumberAxis) plot.getRangeAxis();\\n        rangeAxis.setStandardTickUnits(NumberAxis.createIntegerTickUnits());\\n\\n        // crop extra space around the graph\\n        plot.setInsets(new RectangleInsets(0, 0, 0, 5.0));\\n\\n        return chart;\\n    }'")]

[(1970, '\'FormValidation checkUpdateSiteURL(@CheckForNull String value) throws InterruptedException {\\n        value = Util.fixEmptyAndTrim(value);\\n\\n        if (value == null) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.PluginManager_emptyUpdateSiteUrl());\\n        }\\n\\n        final URI baseUri;\\n        try {\\n            baseUri = new URI(value);\\n        } catch (URISyntaxException ex) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(ex, Messages.PluginManager_invalidUrl());\\n        }\\n\\n        if ("file".equalsIgnoreCase(baseUri.getScheme())) {\\n            File f = new File(baseUri);\\n            if (f.isFile()) {\\n                return FormValidation.ok();\\n            }\\n            return     final URI uriWithQuery;\\n            try {\\n                if (baseUri.getRawQuery() == null) {\\n                    uriWithQuery = new URI(value + "?version=" + Jenkins.VERSION + "&uctest");\\n                } else {\\n                    uriWithQuery = new URI(value + "&version=" + Jenkins.VERSION + "&uctest");\\n                }\\n            } catch (URISyntaxException e) {\\n                return FormValidation.error(e, Messages.PluginManager_invalidUrl());\\n            }\\n            HttpClient httpClient = ProxyConfiguration.newHttpClientBuilder()\\n                    .connectTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))\\n                    .build();\\n            HttpRequest httpRequest;\\n            try {\\n                httpRequest = java.net.http.HttpResponse<Void> httpResponse = httpClient.send(\\n                        httpRequest, java.net.http.HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.discarding());\\n                if (100 <= httpResponse.statusCode() && httpResponse.statusCode() <= 399) {\\n                    return FormValidation.ok();\\n                }\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Obtained a non OK ({0}) FormValidation.error(Messages.PluginManager_connectionFailed());\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Failed to check update site", e);\\n                return FormValidation.error(e, Messages.PluginManager_connectionFailed());\\n            }\\n\\n        }\\n        // not a file or http(s) scheme\\n        return [(252, '\'String getCanonicalName(ItemGroup context, String path) {\\n        String[] c = context.getFullName().split("/");\\n        String[] p = path.split("/");\\n\\n        Stack<String> name = new Stack<>();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < c.length; i++) {\\n            if (i == 0 && c[i].isEmpty()) continue;\\n            name.push(c[i]);\\n        }\\n        for (int i = 0; i < p.length; i++) {\\n            if (i == 0 && p[i].isEmpty()) {\\n                // Absolute path starting with a "/"\\n                name.clear();\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            if (p[i].equals("..")) {\\n                if (name.isEmpty()) {\\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException(String.format(\\n                            "Illegal relative path \\\'%s\\\' within context \\\'%s\\\'", path, context.getFullName()\\n                    ));\\n                }\\n                name.pop();\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            if (p[i].equals(".")) {\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            name.push(p[i]);\\n        }\\n        return String.join("/", name);\\n    }\'')]

[(179, '\'void setUpPingForChannel(final Channel channel, final SlaveComputer computer, int timeoutSeconds, int intervalSeconds, final boolean analysis) {\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "setting up ping on {0} with a {1} seconds interval and {2} seconds timeout", new Object[] {channel.getName(), intervalSeconds, timeoutSeconds});\\n        final AtomicBoolean isInClosed = new AtomicBoolean(false);\\n        final PingThread t = new PingThread(channel, TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(timeoutSeconds), TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(intervalSeconds)) {\\n            @Override\\n            protected void onDead(Throwable cause) {\\n                    if (analysis) {\\n                        analyze(cause);\\n                    }\\n                    boolean inClosed = isInClosed.get();\\n                    // Disassociate computer channel before closing it\\n                    if (computer != null) {\\n                        Exception exception = cause instanceof Exception ? (Exception) cause : new IOException(cause);\\n                        computer.disconnect(new OfflineCause.ChannelTermination(exception));\\n                    }\\n                    if (inClosed) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Ping failed after the channel " + channel.getName() + " is already partially closed.", cause);\\n                    } else {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Ping failed. Terminating the channel " + channel.getName() + ".", cause);\\n                        if (computer == null) {\\n                            // Disconnect from agent side.\\n                            try {\\n                                channel.close(cause);\\n                            } catch (IOException x) {\\n                                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "could not disconnect " + channel.getName(), x);\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n            }\\n            /** Keep in a separate method so we do not even try to do class loading on {@link PingFailureAnalyzer} from an agent JVM. */\\n\\n            private void analyze(Throwable cause) {\\n                for (PingFailureAnalyzer pfa : PingFailureAnalyzer.all()) {\\n                    try {\\n                        pfa.onPingFailure(channel, cause);\\n                    } catch (IOException ex) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Ping failure analyzer " + pfa.getClass().getName() + " failed for " + channel.getName(), ex);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            @Deprecated\\n            @Override\\n            protected void onDead() {\\n                onDead(null);\\n            }\\n        };\\n\\n        channel.addListener(new Channel.Listener() {\\n            @Override\\n            public void onClosed(Channel channel, IOException cause) {\\n                LOGGER.fine("Terminating ping thread for " + channel.getName());\\n                isInClosed.set(true);\\n                t.interrupt();  // make sure the ping thread is terminated\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        t.start();\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Ping thread started for {0} with a {1} seconds interval and a {2} seconds timeout",\\n                   new Object[] { channel, intervalSeconds, timeoutSeconds });\\n    }\'')]

[(1309, "'Map<AbstractProject, DependencyChange> getDependencyChanges(AbstractBuild from) {\\n        if (from == null)             return Collections.emptyMap(); // make it easy to call this from views\\n        FingerprintAction n = this.getAction(FingerprintAction.class);\\n        FingerprintAction o = from.getAction(FingerprintAction.class);\\n        if (n == null || o == null)     return Collections.emptyMap();\\n\\n        Map<AbstractProject, Integer> ndep = n.getDependencies(true);\\n        Map<AbstractProject, Integer> odep = o.getDependencies(true);\\n\\n        Map<AbstractProject, DependencyChange> r = new HashMap<>();\\n\\n        for (Map.Entry<AbstractProject, Integer> entry : odep.entrySet()) {\\n            AbstractProject p = entry.getKey();\\n            Integer oldNumber = entry.getValue();\\n            Integer newNumber = ndep.get(p);\\n            if (newNumber != null && oldNumber.compareTo(newNumber) < 0) {\\n                r.put(p, new DependencyChange(p, oldNumber, newNumber));\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return r;\\n    }'")]

[(69, '\'int getWin32FileAttributes(File file) throws IOException {\\n        // allow lookup of paths longer than MAX_PATH\\n        // http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa365247(v=VS.85).aspx\\n        String canonicalPath = file.getCanonicalPath();\\n        String path;\\n        if (canonicalPath.length() < 260) {\\n            // path is short, use as-is\\n            path = canonicalPath;\\n        } else if (canonicalPath.startsWith("\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")) {\\n            // network share\\n            // \\\\\\\\server\\\\share --> \\\\\\\\?\\\\UNC\\\\server\\\\share\\n            path = "\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\?\\\\\\\\UNC\\\\\\\\" + canonicalPath.substring(2);\\n        } else {\\n            // prefix, canonical path should be normalized and absolute so this should work.\\n            path = "\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\?\\\\\\\\" + canonicalPath;\\n        }\\n        return Kernel32.INSTANCE.GetFileAttributesW(new WString(path));\\n    }\'')]

[(53, '\'boolean keep(@NonNull Function m) {\\n\\n        if (m.getAnnotation(StaplerNotDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (m.getAnnotation(StaplerDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        String methodName = m.getName();\\n        String signature = m.getSignature();\\n\\n        // check whitelist\\n        ExtensionList<RoutingDecisionProvider> whitelistProviders = ExtensionList.lookup(RoutingDecisionProvider.class);\\n        if (whitelistProviders.size() > 0) {\\n            for (RoutingDecisionProvider provider : whitelistProviders) {\\n                RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision methodDecision = provider.decide(signature);\\n                if (methodDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.ACCEPTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Action " + signature + " is acceptable because it is whitelisted by " + provider);\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n                if (methodDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.REJECTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Action " + signature + " is not acceptable because it is blacklisted by " + provider);\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (methodName.equals("doDynamic")) {\\n            // reject doDynamic because it\\\'s treated separately by Stapler.\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        for (Annotation a : m.getAnnotations()) {\\n            if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_ANNOTATION_NAMES.contains(a.annotationType().getName())) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n            if (a.annotationType().getAnnotation(InterceptorAnnotation.class) != null) {\\n                // This is a Stapler interceptor annotation like RequirePOST or JsonResponse\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // there is rarely more than two annotations in a method signature\\n        for (Annotation[] perParameterAnnotation : m.getParameterAnnotations()) {\\n            for (Annotation annotation : perParameterAnnotation) {\\n                if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_PARAMETER_ANNOTATION_NAMES.contains(annotation.annotationType().getName())) {\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!DO_METHOD_REGEX.matcher(methodName).matches()) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // after the method name check to avoid allowing methods that are meant to be used by routable ones\\n        // normally they should be private in such case\\n        for (Class<?> parameterType : m.getParameterTypes()) {\\n            if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_PARAMETERS_NAMES.contains(parameterType.getName())) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        Class<?> returnType = m.getReturnType();\\n        if (HttpResponse.class.isAssignableFrom(returnType)) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        // as HttpResponseException inherits from RuntimeException,\\n        // there is no requirement for the developer to explicitly checks it.\\n        Class<?>[] checkedExceptionTypes = m.getCheckedExceptionTypes();\\n        for (Class<?> checkedExceptionType : checkedExceptionTypes) {\\n            if (HttpResponse.class.isAssignableFrom(checkedExceptionType)) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return false;\\n    }\'')]

[(648, "'Collection<Method> getMethodAndInterfaceDeclarations(Method method, Collection<Class<?>> interfaces) {\\n        final List<Method> methods = new ArrayList<>();\\n        methods.add(method);\\n\\n        // we search for matching method by iteration and comparison vs getMethod to avoid repeated NoSuchMethodException\\n        // being thrown, while interface typically only define a few set of methods to check.\\n        interfaces.stream()\\n                .map(Class::getMethods)\\n                .flatMap(Arrays::stream)\\n                .filter(m -> m.getName().equals(method.getName()) && Arrays.equals(m.getParameterTypes(), method.getParameterTypes()))\\n                .findFirst()\\n                .ifPresent(methods::add);\\n\\n        return methods;\\n    }'")]

[(56, '\'void eol(byte[] in, int sz) throws IOException {\\n\\n        int next = ConsoleNote.findPreamble(in, 0, sz);\\n\\n        // perform byte[]->char[] while figuring out the char positions of the BLOBs\\n        int written = 0;\\n        while (next >= 0) {\\n            if (next > written) {\\n                out.write(in, written, next - written);\\n                written = next;\\n            } else {\\n                assert next == written;\\n            }\\n\\n            int rest = sz - next;\\n            ByteArrayInputStream b = new ByteArrayInputStream(in, next, rest);\\n\\n            try {\\n                ConsoleNote.skip(new DataInputStream(b));\\n            } catch (IOException x) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Failed to skip annotation from \\\\"" + StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava(new String(in, next, rest, Charset.defaultCharset())) + "\\\\"", x);\\n            }\\n\\n            int bytesUsed = rest - b.available(); // bytes consumed by annotations\\n            written += bytesUsed;\\n\\n\\n            next = ConsoleNote.findPreamble(in, written, sz - written);\\n        }\\n        // finish the remaining bytes->chars conversion\\n        out.write(in, written, sz - written);\\n    }\'')]

[(194, '\'void doBuild(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp, @QueryParameter TimeDuration delay) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        if (delay == null) {\\n            delay = new TimeDuration(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.convert(asJob().getQuietPeriod(), TimeUnit.SECONDS));\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!asJob().isBuildable()) {\\n            throw HttpResponses.error(SC_CONFLICT, new IOException(asJob().getFullName() + " is not buildable"));\\n        }\\n\\n        // if a build is parameterized, let that take over\\n        ParametersDefinitionProperty pp = asJob().getProperty(ParametersDefinitionProperty.class);\\n        if (pp != null && !req.getMethod().equals("POST")) {\\n            // show the parameter entry form.\\n            req.getView(pp, "index.jelly").forward(req, rsp);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        BuildAuthorizationToken.checkPermission(asJob(), asJob().getAuthToken(), req, rsp);\\n\\n        if (pp != null) {\\n            pp._doBuild(req, rsp, delay);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n\\n        Queue.Item item = Jenkins.get().getQueue().schedule2(asJob(), delay.getTimeInSeconds(), getBuildCause(asJob(), req)).getItem();\\n        if (item != null) {\\n            rsp.sendRedirect(SC_CREATED, req.getContextPath() + \\\'/\\\' + item.getUrl());\\n        } else {\\n            rsp.sendRedirect(".");\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(389, '\'int plainHttpConnection(String url, List<String> args, CLIConnectionFactory factory) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        LOGGER.log(FINE, "Trying to connect to {0} via plain protocol over HTTP", url);\\n        FullDuplexHttpStream streams = new FullDuplexHttpStream(new URL(url), "cli?remoting=false", factory.authorization);\\n        try (ClientSideImpl connection = new ClientSideImpl(new PlainCLIProtocol.FramedOutput(streams.getOutputStream()))) {\\n            connection.start(args);\\n            InputStream is = streams.getInputStream();\\n            if (is.read() != 0) { // cf. this.getCategoryLabelPositionOffset();\\n                    y0 = y1 - state.getMax();\\n                } else if (edge == RectangleEdge.BOTTOM) {\\n                    x0 = getCategoryStart(categoryIndex, ticks.size(),\\n                            dataArea, edge);\\n                    x1 = getCategoryEnd(categoryIndex, ticks.size(), dataArea,\\n                            edge);\\n                    y0 = state.getCursor() + this.getCategoryLabelPositionOffset();\\n                    y1 = y0 + state.getMax();\\n                } else if (edge == RectangleEdge.LEFT) {\\n                    y0 = getCategoryStart(categoryIndex, ticks.size(),\\n                            dataArea, edge);\\n                    y1 = getCategoryEnd(categoryIndex, ticks.size(), dataArea,\\n                            edge);\\n                    x1 = state.getCursor() - this.getCategoryLabelPositionOffset();\\n                    x0 = x1 - state.getMax();\\n                } else if (edge == RectangleEdge.RIGHT) {\\n                    y0 = getCategoryStart(categoryIndex, ticks.size(),\\n                            dataArea, edge);\\n                    y1 = getCategoryEnd(categoryIndex, ticks.size(), dataArea,\\n                            edge);\\n                    x0 = state.getCursor() + this.getCategoryLabelPositionOffset();\\n                    x1 = x0 - state.getMax();\\n                }\\n                Rectangle2D area = new Rectangle2D.Double(x0, y0, x1 - x0,\\n                        y1 - y0);\\n                if (r == null || !r.intersects(area)) {\\n                    Point2D anchorPoint = RectangleAnchor.coordinates(area,\\n                            position.getCategoryAnchor());\\n                    TextBlock block = tick.getLabel();\\n                    block.draw(g2, (float) anchorPoint.getX(),\\n                            (float) anchorPoint.getY(), position.getLabelAnchor(),\\n                            (float) anchorPoint.getX(), (float) anchorPoint.getY(),\\n                            position.getAngle());\\n                    Shape bounds = block.calculateBounds(g2,\\n                            (float) anchorPoint.getX(), (float) anchorPoint.getY(),\\n                            position.getLabelAnchor(), (float) anchorPoint.getX(),\\n                            (float) anchorPoint.getY(), position.getAngle());\\n                    if (plotState != null && plotState.getOwner() != null) {\\n                        EntityCollection entities\\n                                = plotState.getOwner().getEntityCollection();\\n                        if (entities != null) {\\n                            String tooltip = getCategoryLabelToolTip(\\n                                    tick.getCategory());\\n                            entities.add(new CategoryLabelEntity(tick.getCategory(),\\n                                    bounds, tooltip, null));\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                    r = bounds.getBounds2D();\\n                    // add margins in all directions\\n                    r.add(r.getMaxX() + r.getWidth() / 2, r.getCenterY());\\n                    r.add(r.getMinX() - r.getWidth() / 2, r.getCenterY());\\n                    r.add(r.getCenterX(), r.getMinY() - r.getHeight() / 2);\\n                    r.add(r.getCenterX(), r.getMaxX() + r.getHeight() / 2);\\n                }\\n\\n                categoryIndex++;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (edge.equals(RectangleEdge.TOP)) {\\n                double h = state.getMax();\\n                state.cursorUp(h);\\n            }\\n            else if (edge.equals(RectangleEdge.BOTTOM)) {\\n                double h = state.getMax();\\n                state.cursorDown(h);\\n            }\\n            else if (edge == RectangleEdge.LEFT) {\\n                double w = state.getMax();\\n                state.cursorLeft(w);\\n            }\\n            else if (edge == RectangleEdge.RIGHT) {\\n                double w = state.getMax();\\n                state.cursorRight(w);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return state;\\n    }\'')]

[(274, "'boolean hasIndirectDependencies(AbstractProject src, AbstractProject dst) {\\n        Set<AbstractProject> visited = new HashSet<>();\\n        Stack<AbstractProject> queue = new Stack<>();\\n\\n        queue.addAll(getDownstream(src));\\n        queue.remove(dst);\\n\\n        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {\\n            AbstractProject p = queue.pop();\\n            if (p == dst)\\n                return true;\\n            if (visited.add(p))\\n                queue.addAll(getDownstream(p));\\n        }\\n\\n        return false;\\n    }'")]

[(98, '\'void rewriteHudsonWar(File by) throws IOException {\\n        File dest = getHudsonWar();\\n        // this should be impossible given the canRewriteHudsonWar method,\\n        // but let\\\'s be defensive\\n        if (dest == null)  throw new IOException("jenkins.war location is not known.");\\n\\n        // backing up the old jenkins.war before its lost due to upgrading\\n        // unless we are trying to rewrite jenkins.war by a backup itself\\n        File bak = new File(dest.getPath() + ".bak");\\n        if (!by.equals(bak))\\n            FileUtils.copyFile(dest, bak);\\n\\n        String baseName = dest.getName();\\n        baseName = baseName.substring(0, baseName.indexOf(\\\'.\\\'));\\n\\n        File baseDir = getBaseDir();\\n        File copyFiles = new File(baseDir, baseName + ".copies");\\n\\n        try (Writer w = Files.newBufferedWriter(Util.fileToPath(copyFiles), Charset.defaultCharset(), StandardOpenOption.CREATE, StandardOpenOption.APPEND)) {\\n            w.write(by.getAbsolutePath() + \\\'>\\\' + getHudsonWar().getAbsolutePath() + \\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1218, '\'void updateByXml(Source source) throws IOException {\\n        checkPermission(CONFIGURE);\\n        StringWriter out = new StringWriter();\\n        try {\\n            // this allows us to use UTF-8 for storing data,\\n            // plus it checks any well-formedness issue in the submitted\\n            // data\\n            XMLUtils.safeTransform(source, new StreamResult(out));\\n            out.close();\\n        } catch (TransformerException | SAXException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to persist configuration.xml", e);\\n        }\\n\\n        // try to reflect the changes by reloading\\n        try (InputStream in = new BufferedInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(out.toString().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8)))) {\\n            // Do not allow overwriting view name as it might collide with another\\n            // view in same ViewGroup and might not satisfy Jenkins.checkGoodName.\\n            String oldname = name;\\n            ViewGroup oldOwner = owner; [(303, "'List<SuggestedItem> suggest(SearchIndex index, final String tokenList, SearchableModelObject searchContext) {\\n\\n        class Tag implements Comparable<Tag> {\\n            final SuggestedItem item;\\n            final int distance;\\n            /** If the path to this suggestion starts with the token list, 1. Otherwise 0. */\\n            final int prefixMatch;\\n\\n            Tag(SuggestedItem i) {\\n                item = i;\\n                distance = EditDistance.editDistance(i.getPath(), tokenList);\\n                prefixMatch = i.getPath().startsWith(tokenList) ? 1 : 0;\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public int compareTo(Tag that) {\\n                int r = this.prefixMatch - that.prefixMatch;\\n                if (r != 0)    return -r;  // ones with head match should show up earlier\\n                return this.distance - that.distance;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        List<Tag> buf = new ArrayList<>();\\n        List<SuggestedItem> items = find(Mode.SUGGEST, index, tokenList, searchContext);\\n\\n        // sort them\\n        for (SuggestedItem i : items)\\n            buf.add(new Tag(i));\\n        Collections.sort(buf);\\n        items.clear();\\n        for (Tag t : buf)\\n            items.add(t.item);\\n\\n        return items;\\n    }'")]

[(1734, "'Runnable makeFlyWeightTaskBuildable(final BuildableItem p) {\\n        //we double check if this is a flyweight task\\n        if (p.task instanceof FlyweightTask) {\\n            Jenkins h = Jenkins.get();\\n\\n            Label lbl = p.getAssignedLabel();\\n\\n            Computer masterComputer = h.toComputer();\\n            if (lbl != null && lbl.equals(h.getSelfLabel())) {\\n                // the flyweight task is bound to the master\\n                if (h.canTake(p) == null) {\\n                    return createFlyWeightTaskRunnable(p, masterComputer);\\n                } else {\\n                    return null;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (lbl == null && h.canTake(p) == null && masterComputer.isOnline() && masterComputer.isAcceptingTasks()) {\\n                // The flyweight task is not tied to a specific label, so execute on master if possible.\\n                // This will ensure that actual agent disconnects do not impact flyweight tasks randomly assigned to them.\\n                return createFlyWeightTaskRunnable(p, masterComputer);\\n            }\\n\\n            Map<Node, Integer> hashSource = new HashMap<>(h.getNodes().size());\\n\\n            for (Node n : h.getNodes()) {\\n                hashSource.put(n, n.getNumExecutors() * 100);\\n            }\\n\\n            ConsistentHash<Node> hash = new ConsistentHash<>(NODE_HASH);\\n            hash.addAll(hashSource);\\n\\n            String fullDisplayName = p.task.getFullDisplayName();\\n            for (Node n :     if (lbl != null && !lbl.contains(n)) {\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (n.canTake(p) != null) {\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n\\n                return createFlyWeightTaskRunnable(p, c);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }'")]

[(112, "'void addCriticalField(Class<?> clazz, String field) {\\n        // Lock the write lock\\n        criticalFieldsLock.writeLock().lock();\\n        try {\\n            // If the class already exists, then add a new field, otherwise\\n            // create the hash map field\\n            if (!criticalFields.containsKey(field)) {\\n                criticalFields.put(field, new HashSet<>());\\n            }\\n            criticalFields.get(field).add(clazz.getName());\\n        }\\n        finally {\\n            // Unlock\\n            criticalFieldsLock.writeLock().unlock();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

issue JENKINS-980.\\n                LOGGER.log(FINER, "moving into POST_PRODUCTION on {0}", this);\\n                state = State.POST_PRODUCTION;\\n\\n                if (listener != null) {\\n                    RunListener.fireCompleted(this, listener);\\n                    try {\\n                        job.cleanUp(listener);\\n                    } catch (Exception e) {\\n                        handleFatalBuildProblem(listener, e);\\n                        // too late to update the result now\\n                    }\\n                    listener.finished(result);\\n                    listener.closeQuietly();\\n                }\\n\\n                try {\\n                    save();\\n                } catch (IOException e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, "Failed to rotate log", e);\\n            }\\n        } finally {\\n            onEndBuilding();\\n            if (logger != null) {\\n                try {\\n [(172, '\'Secret decrypt(@CheckForNull String data) {\\n        if (!isValidData(data))      return null;\\n\\n        if (data.startsWith("{") && data.endsWith("}")) { //likely CBC encrypted/containing metadata but could be plain text\\n            byte[] payload;\\n            try {\\n                payload = Base64.getDecoder().decode(data.substring(1, data.length() - 1));\\n            } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            switch (payload[0]) {\\n                case PAYLOAD_V1:\\n                    // For PAYLOAD_V1 we use this byte shifting model, V2 probably will need DataOutput\\n                    int ivLength = ((payload[1] & 0xff) << 24)\\n                            | ((payload[2] & 0xff) << 16)\\n                            | ((payload[3] & 0xff) << 8)\\n                            | (payload[4] & 0xff);\\n                    int dataLength = ((payload[5] & 0xff) << 24)\\n                            | ((payload[6] & 0xff) << 16)\\n                            | ((payload[7] & 0xff) << 8)\\n                            | (payload[8] & 0xff);\\n                    if (payload.length != 1 + 8 + ivLength + dataLength) {\\n                        // not valid v1\\n                        return null;\\n                    }\\n                    byte[] iv = Arrays.copyOfRange(payload, 9, 9 + ivLength);\\n                    byte[] code = Arrays.copyOfRange(payload, 9 + ivLength, payload.length);\\n                    String text;\\n                    try {\\n                        text = new String(KEY.decrypt(iv).doFinal(code), UTF_8);\\n                    } catch (GeneralSecurityException e) {\\n                        // it\\\'s v1 which cannot be historical, but not decrypting\\n                        return null;\\n                    }\\n                    return new Secret(text, iv);\\n                default:\\n                    return null;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            try {\\n                return HistoricalSecrets.decrypt(data, KEY);\\n            } catch (UnsupportedEncodingException e) {\\n                throw new Error(e); // impossible\\n            } catch (GeneralSecurityException | IOException e) {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]
