[(92, '\'FormValidation checkUrl(String resourceRootUrlString, boolean allowOnlineIdentityCheck) {\\n        String jenkinsRootUrlString = JenkinsLocationConfiguration.get().getUrl();\\n        if (ExtensionList.lookupSingleton(RootUrlNotSetMonitor.class).isActivated() || jenkinsRootUrlString == null) {\\n            // This is needed to round-trip expired resource URLs through regular URLs to refresh them,\\n            // so while it\\\'s not required in the strictest sense, it is required.\\n            return FormValidation.warning(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_NeedsRootURL());\\n        }\\n\\n        resourceRootUrlString = Util.fixEmptyAndTrim(resourceRootUrlString);\\n        if (resourceRootUrlString == null) {\\n            return FormValidation.ok(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_Empty());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!UrlHelper.isValidRootUrl(resourceRootUrlString)) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_Invalid());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!resourceRootUrlString.endsWith("/")) {\\n            resourceRootUrlString += \\\'/\\\';\\n        }\\n\\n        URL resourceRootUrl;\\n        try {\\n            resourceRootUrl = new URL(resourceRootUrlString);\\n        } catch (MalformedURLException ex) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_Invalid());\\n        }\\n\\n        String resourceRootUrlHost = resourceRootUrl.getHost();\\n        try {\\n            String jenkinsRootUrlHost = new URL(jenkinsRootUrlString).getHost();\\n            if (jenkinsRootUrlHost.equals(resourceRootUrlHost)) {\\n                // We do not allow the same host for Jenkins and resource root URLs even if there\\\'s some other difference.\\n                // This is a conservative choice and prohibits same host/different proto/different port/different path:\\n                // - Different path still counts as the same origin for same-origin policy\\n                // - Cookies are shared across ports, and non-Secure cookies get sent to HTTPS sites\\n                return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_SameAsJenkinsRoot());\\n            }\\n        } catch (Exception ex) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Failed to create URL from the existing Jenkins URL", ex);\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_InvalidRootURL(ex.getMessage()));\\n        }\\n\\n        StaplerRequest currentRequest = Stapler.getCurrentRequest();\\n        if (currentRequest != null) {\\n            String currentRequestHost = currentRequest.getServerName();\\n\\n            if (currentRequestHost.equals(resourceRootUrlHost)) {\\n                return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_SameAsCurrent());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!allowOnlineIdentityCheck) {\\n            return FormValidation.ok();\\n        }\\n\\n        // Send a request to /instance-identity/ at the resource root URL and check whether it is this Jenkins\\n        try {\\n            URLConnection urlConnection = new URL(resourceRootUrlString + "instance-identity/").openConnection();\\n            if (urlConnection instanceof HttpURLConnection) {\\n                HttpURLConnection httpURLConnection = (HttpURLConnection) urlConnection;\\n                int responseCode = httpURLConnection.getResponseCode();\\n\\n                if (responseCode == 200) {\\n                    String identityHeader = urlConnection.getHeaderField("X-Instance-Identity");\\n                    if (identityHeader == null) {\\n                        return FormValidation.warning(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_NotJenkins());\\n                    }\\n                    // URL points to a Jenkins instance\\n                    RSAPublicKey publicKey = InstanceIdentityProvider.RSA.getPublicKey();\\n                    if (publicKey != null) {\\n                        String identity = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(publicKey.getEncoded());\\n                        if (identity.equals(identityHeader)) {\\n                            return FormValidation.ok(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_ThisJenkins());\\n                        }\\n                        return FormValidation.warning(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_OtherJenkins());\\n                    } // the current instance has no public key\\n                    return FormValidation.warning(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_SomeJenkins());\\n                }\\n                // response is error\\n                String responseMessage = httpURLConnection.getResponseMessage();\\n                if (responseCode == 404) {\\n                    String responseBody = String.join("", IOUtils.readLines(httpURLConnection.getErrorStream(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n                    if (responseMessage.contains(ERROR_RESPONSE) || responseBody.contains(ERROR_RESPONSE)) {\\n                        return FormValidation.ok(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_ResourceResponse());\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_FailedIdentityCheck(responseCode, responseMessage));\\n            }\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_Invalid()); // unlikely to ever be hit\\n        } catch (MalformedURLException ex) {\\n            // Not expected to be hit\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "MalformedURLException occurred during instance identity check for " + resourceRootUrlString, ex);\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.ResourceDomainConfiguration_Exception(ex.getMessage()));\\n        } catch (IOException ex) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "IOException occurred during instance [(15, '\'String toHex(byte[] buf, int start, int len) {\\n        StringBuilder r = new StringBuilder(len * 2);\\n        boolean inText = false;\\n        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {\\n            byte b = buf[start + i];\\n            if (b >= 0x20 && b <= 0x7e) {\\n                if (!inText) {\\n                    inText = true;\\n                    r.append(\\\'\\\\\\\'\\\');\\n                }\\n                r.append((char) b);\\n            } else {\\n                if (inText) {\\n                    r.append("\\\' ");\\n                    inText = false;\\n                }\\n                r.append("0x");\\n                r.append(CODE.charAt((b >> 4) & 15));\\n                r.append(CODE.charAt(b & 15));\\n                if (i < len - 1) {\\n                    if (b == 10) {\\n                        r.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                    } else {\\n                        r.append(\\\' \\\');\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (inText) {\\n            r.append(\\\'\\\\\\\'\\\');\\n        }\\n        return r.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(105, "'boolean isRoutableMethod(@NonNull Method m) {\\n        for (Annotation a : m.getDeclaredAnnotations()) {\\n            if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_ANNOTATION_NAMES.contains(a.annotationType().getName())) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n            if (a.annotationType().isAnnotationPresent(InterceptorAnnotation.class)) {\\n                // This is a Stapler interceptor annotation like RequirePOST or JsonResponse\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        for (Annotation[] set : m.getParameterAnnotations()) {\\n            for (Annotation a : set) {\\n                if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_PARAMETER_ANNOTATION_NAMES.contains(a.annotationType().getName())) {\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        for (Class<?> parameterType : m.getParameterTypes()) {\\n            if (WebMethodConstants.WEB_METHOD_PARAMETERS_NAMES.contains(parameterType.getName())) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return WebApp.getCurrent().getFilterForDoActions().keep(new Function.InstanceFunction(m));\\n    }'")]

[(3393, '\'void checkRawBuildsDir(String newBuildsDirValue) throws InvalidBuildsDir {\\n\\n        // do essentially what expandVariablesForDirectory does, without an Item\\n        String replacedValue = expandVariablesForDirectory(newBuildsDirValue,\\n                                                           "doCheckRawBuildsDir-Marker:foo",\\n                                                           Jenkins.get().getRootDir().getPath() + "/jobs/doCheckRawBuildsDir-Marker$foo");\\n\\n        File replacedFile = new File(replacedValue);\\n        if (!replacedFile.isAbsolute()) {\\n            throw new InvalidBuildsDir(newBuildsDirValue + " does not resolve to an absolute path");\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!replacedValue.contains("doCheckRawBuildsDir-Marker")) {\\n            throw new InvalidBuildsDir(newBuildsDirValue + " does not contain ${ITEM_FULL_NAME} or ${ITEM_ROOTDIR}, cannot distinguish between projects");\\n        }\\n\\n        if (replacedValue.contains("doCheckRawBuildsDir-Marker:foo")) {\\n            // make sure platform can handle colon\\n            try {\\n                File tmp = File.createTempFile("Jenkins-doCheckRawBuildsDir", "foo:bar");\\n                Files.delete(tmp.toPath());\\n            } catch (IOException | InvalidPathException e) {\\n                throw (InvalidBuildsDir) new InvalidBuildsDir(newBuildsDirValue +  " contains ${ITEM_FULLNAME} but your system does not support it (JENKINS-12251). Use ${ITEM_FULL_NAME} instead").initCause(e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        File d = new File(replacedValue);\\n        if (!d.isDirectory()) {\\n            // if dir does not exist (almost guaranteed) need to make sure nearest existing ancestor can be written to\\n            d = d.getParentFile();\\n            while (!d.exists()) {\\n                d = d.getParentFile();\\n            }\\n            if (!d.canWrite()) {\\n                throw new InvalidBuildsDir(newBuildsDirValue +  " does not exist and probably cannot be created");\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(56, '\'String tryRewrite(String s) throws InvalidKeyException {\\n        if (s.length() < 24)\\n            return s;   // Encrypting "" in Secret produces 24-letter characters, so this must be the minimum length\\n        if (!isBase64(s))\\n            return s;   // decode throws IOException if the input is not base64, and this is also a very quick way to filter\\n\\n        byte[] in;\\n        try {\\n            in = Base64.getDecoder().decode(s.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n        } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n            return s;   // not a valid base64\\n        }\\n        cipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, key);\\n        Secret sec = HistoricalSecrets.tryDecrypt(cipher, in);\\n        if (sec != null) // matched\\n            return sec.getEncryptedValue(); // replace by the new encrypted value\\n        else // not encrypted with the legacy key. leave it unmodified\\n            return s;\\n    }\'')]

[(247, '\'void doCreateItem(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp,\\n                                           @QueryParameter String name, @QueryParameter String mode,\\n                                           @QueryParameter String from) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        final Jenkins app = Jenkins.get();\\n        app.checkPermission(Computer.CREATE);\\n\\n        if (mode != null && mode.equals("copy")) {\\n            name = checkName(name);\\n\\n            Node src = app.getNode(from);\\n            if (src == null) {\\n                if (Util.fixEmpty(from) == null) {\\n                    throw new Failure(Messages.ComputerSet_SpecifySlaveToCopy());\\n                } else {\\n                    throw new Failure(Messages.ComputerSet_NoSuchSlave(from));\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            // copy through XStream\\n            String xml = Jenkins.XSTREAM.toXML(src);\\n            Node result = (Node) Jenkins.XSTREAM.fromXML(xml);\\n            result.setNodeName(name);\\n            result.holdOffLaunchUntilSave = true;\\n\\n            app.addNode(result);\\n\\n            // send the browser to the config page\\n            rsp.sendRedirect2(result.getNodeName() + "/configure");\\n        } else {\\n            // proceed to step 2\\n            if (mode == null) {\\n                throw new Failure("No mode given");\\n            }\\n\\n            NodeDescriptor d = NodeDescriptor.all().findByName(mode);\\n            if (d == null) {\\n                throw new Failure("No node type ‘" + mode + "’ is known");\\n            }\\n            d.handleNewNodePage(this, name, req, rsp);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1557, '\'String dumpThreadInfo(ThreadInfo ti, ThreadGroupMap map) {\\n        String grp = map.getThreadGroup(ti);\\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("\\\\"" + ti.getThreadName() + "\\\\"" +\\n                                             " Id=" + ti.getThreadId() + " Group=" +\\n                                             (grp != null ? grp : "?") + " " +\\n                                             ti.getThreadState());\\n        if (ti.getLockName() != null) {\\n            sb.append(" on " + ti.getLockName());\\n        }\\n        if (ti.getLockOwnerName() != null) {\\n            sb.append(" owned by \\\\"" + ti.getLockOwnerName() +\\n                      "\\\\" Id=" + ti.getLockOwnerId());\\n        }\\n        if (ti.isSuspended()) {\\n            sb.append(" (suspended)");\\n        }\\n        if (ti.isInNative()) {\\n            sb.append(" (in native)");\\n        }\\n        sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n        StackTraceElement[] stackTrace = ti.getStackTrace();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < stackTrace.length; i++) {\\n            StackTraceElement ste = stackTrace[i];\\n            sb.append("\\\\tat ").append(ste);\\n            sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n            if (i == 0 && ti.getLockInfo() != null) {\\n                Thread.State ts = ti.getThreadState();\\n                switch (ts) {\\n                    case BLOCKED:\\n                        sb.append("\\\\t-  blocked on ").append(ti.getLockInfo());\\n                        sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    case WAITING:\\n                    case TIMED_WAITING:\\n                        sb.append("\\\\t-  waiting on ").append(ti.getLockInfo());\\n                        sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                        break;\\n                    default:\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            for (MonitorInfo mi : ti.getLockedMonitors()) {\\n                if (mi.getLockedStackDepth() == i) {\\n                    sb.append("\\\\t-  locked ").append(mi);\\n                    sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                }\\n            }\\n       }\\n\\n       LockInfo[] locks = ti.getLockedSynchronizers();\\n       if (locks.length > 0) {\\n           sb.append("\\\\n\\\\tNumber of locked synchronizers = " + locks.length);\\n           sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n           for (LockInfo li : locks) {\\n               sb.append("\\\\t- ").append(li);\\n               sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n           }\\n       }\\n       sb.append(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n       return sb.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(923, '\'void doRssLatest(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        final List<Run> lastBuilds = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (Job<?, ?> p : Jenkins.get().allItems(Job.class)) {\\n            for (Run<?, ?> b = p.getLastBuild(); b != null; b = b.getPreviousBuild()) {\\n                if (relatedTo(b)) {\\n                    lastBuilds.add(b);\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        // historically these have been reported sorted by project name, we switched to the lazy iteration\\n        // so we only have to sort the sublist of runs rather than the full list of irrelevant projects\\n        lastBuilds.sort((o1, o2) -> Items.BY_FULL_NAME.compare(o1.getParent(), o2.getParent()));\\n        RSS.rss(req, rsp, "Jenkins:" + getDisplayName() + " (latest builds)", getUrl(), RunList.fromRuns(lastBuilds), Run.FEED_ADAPTER_LATEST);\\n    }\'')]

[(4148, '\'HttpRedirect doQuietDown(@QueryParameter boolean block,\\n                                    @QueryParameter int timeout,\\n                                    @QueryParameter @CheckForNull String message,\\n                                    @QueryParameter boolean safeRestart) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        synchronized (this) {\\n            checkPermission(MANAGE);\\n            quietDownInfo = new QuietDownInfo(message, safeRestart);\\n        }\\n        if (block) {\\n            long waitUntil = timeout;\\n            if (timeout > 0) waitUntil += System.currentTimeMillis();\\n            while (isQuietingDown()\\n                   && (timeout <= 0 || System.currentTimeMillis() < waitUntil)\\n                   && !RestartListener.isAllReady()) {\\n                TimeUnit.SECONDS.sleep(1);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return new HttpRedirect(".");\\n    }\'')]

[(2207, '\'JSONArray doPrevalidateConfig(StaplerRequest req) throws IOException {\\n        Jenkins.get().checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n\\n        JSONArray response = new JSONArray();\\n\\n        for (Map.Entry<String, VersionNumber> p : parseRequestedPlugins(req.getInputStream()).entrySet()) {\\n            PluginWrapper pw = getPlugin(p.getKey());\\n            JSONObject j = new JSONObject()\\n                    .accumulate("name", p.getKey())\\n                    .accumulate("version", p.getValue().toString());\\n            if (pw == null) { // install new\\n                response.add(j.accumulate("mode", "missing"));\\n            } else if (pw.isOlderThan(p.getValue())) { // upgrade\\n                response.add(j.accumulate("mode", "old"));\\n            } // else already good\\n        }\\n\\n        return response;\\n    }\'')]

[(30, '\'boolean isClassAcceptable(Class<?> clazz) {\\n        if (clazz.isArray()) {\\n            // special case to allow klass.isArray() dispatcher\\n            Class<?> elementClazz = clazz.getComponentType();\\n            // does not seem possible to fall in an infinite loop since array cannot be recursively defined\\n            if (isClassAcceptable(elementClazz)) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE,\\n                        "Class {0} is acceptable because it is an Array of acceptable elements {1}",\\n                        new Object[]{clazz.getName(), elementClazz.getName()}\\n                );\\n                return true;\\n            } else {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE,\\n                        "Class {0} is not acceptable because it is an Array of non-acceptable elements {1}",\\n                        new Object[]{clazz.getName(), elementClazz.getName()}\\n                );\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return SKIP_TYPE_CHECK || isStaplerRelevantCached(clazz);\\n    }\'')]

[(136, '\'String migrateLegacyPrimaryAllViewLocalizedName(@NonNull List<View> views,\\n                                                                  @NonNull String primaryView) {\\n        if (DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME.equals(primaryView)) {\\n            // modern name, we are safe\\n            return primaryView;\\n        }\\n        if (SystemProperties.getBoolean(AllView.class.getName() + ".JENKINS-38606", true)) {\\n            AllView allView = null;\\n            for (View v : views) {\\n                if (DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME.equals(v.getViewName())) {\\n                    // name conflict, we cannot rename the all view anyway\\n                    return primaryView;\\n                }\\n                if (Objects.equals(v.getViewName(), primaryView)) {\\n                    if (v instanceof AllView) {\\n                        allView = (AllView) v;\\n                    } else {\\n                        // none of our business fixing as we can only safely fix the primary view\\n                        return primaryView;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (allView != null) {\\n                // the primary view is an AllView but using a non-default name\\n                for (Locale l : Locale.getAvailableLocales()) {\\n                    if (primaryView.equals(Messages._Hudson_ViewName().toString(l))) {\\n                        // bingo JENKINS-38606 detected\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.INFO,\\n                                "JENKINS-38606 detected for AllView in {0}; renaming view from {1} to {2}",\\n                                new Object[] {allView.owner, primaryView, DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME});\\n                        allView.name = DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME;\\n                        return DEFAULT_VIEW_NAME;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return primaryView;\\n    }\'')]

[(218, '\'AutoCompletionCandidates doAutoCompleteLoggerName(@QueryParameter String value) {\\n        if (value == null) {\\n            return new AutoCompletionCandidates();\\n        }\\n\\n        // get names of all actual loggers known to Jenkins\\n        Set<String> candidateNames = new LinkedHashSet<>(getAutoCompletionCandidates(Collections.list(LogManager.getLogManager().getLoggerNames())));\\n\\n        for (String part : value.split("[ ]+")) {\\n            HashSet<String> partCandidates = new HashSet<>();\\n            String lowercaseValue = part.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);\\n            for (String loggerName : candidateNames) {\\n                if (loggerName.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH).contains(lowercaseValue)) {\\n                    partCandidates.add(loggerName);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            candidateNames.retainAll(partCandidates);\\n        }\\n        AutoCompletionCandidates candidates = new AutoCompletionCandidates();\\n        candidates.add(candidateNames.toArray(MemoryReductionUtil.EMPTY_STRING_ARRAY));\\n        return candidates;\\n    }\'')]

[(208, "'void adjustChebyshev(CategoryDataset dataset, NumberAxis yAxis) {\\n        // first compute E(X) and Var(X)\\n        double sum = 0, sum2 = 0;\\n\\n        final int nColumns = dataset.getColumnCount();\\n        final int nRows    = dataset.getRowCount();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < nRows; i++) {\\n            Comparable rowKey = dataset.getRowKey(i);\\n            for (int j = 0; j < nColumns; j++) {\\n                Comparable columnKey = dataset.getColumnKey(j);\\n\\n                double n = dataset.getValue(rowKey, columnKey).doubleValue();\\n                sum += n;\\n                sum2 += n * n;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        double average = sum / (nColumns * nRows);\\n        double stddev = Math.sqrt(sum2 / (nColumns * nRows) - average * average);\\n\\n        double rangeMin = average - stddev * CHEBYSHEV_N;\\n        double rangeMax = average + stddev * CHEBYSHEV_N;\\n\\n        // now see if there are any data points that fall outside (rangeMin,rangeMax)\\n        boolean found = false;\\n        double min = 0, max = 0;\\n        for (int i = 0; i < nRows; i++) {\\n            Comparable rowKey = dataset.getRowKey(i);\\n            for (int j = 0; j < nColumns; j++) {\\n                Comparable columnKey = dataset.getColumnKey(j);\\n\\n                double n = dataset.getValue(rowKey, columnKey).doubleValue();\\n                if (n < rangeMin || rangeMax < n) {\\n                    found = true;\\n                    continue;   // ignore this value\\n                }\\n\\n                min = Math.min(min, n);\\n                max = Math.max(max, n);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!found)\\n            return; // no adjustment was necessary\\n\\n        // some values fell outside the range, so adjust the Y-axis\\n\\n        // if we are ever to extend this method to handle negative value ranges correctly,\\n        // the code after this needs modifications\\n\\n        min = Math.min(0, min);  // always include 0 in the graph\\n        max += yAxis.getUpperMargin() * (max - min);\\n\\n        yAxis.setRange(min, max);\\n    }'")]

[(288, '\'void assertMultipleStdioCalls(String message, Node node, boolean emitStderr, ProcStarterCustomizer psCustomizer, boolean outputIn2) throws Exception {\\n        message = node.getDisplayName() + ": " + message;\\n        Launcher launcher = node.createLauncher(StreamTaskListener.fromStderr());\\n        Launcher.ProcStarter ps = launcher.launch();\\n        assumeFalse("should not be platform-dependent, not bothering for now", Functions.isWindows());\\n        if (emitStderr) {\\n            ps.cmds("sh", "-c", "echo hello >&2").quiet(true);\\n        } else {\\n            ps.cmds("echo", "hello");\\n        }\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream baos1 = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream baos2 = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        TaskListener listener = new StreamTaskListener(baos2, Charset.defaultCharset());\\n        psCustomizer.run(ps, baos1, baos2, listener);\\n        assertEquals(message, 0, ps.join());\\n        if (outputIn2) {\\n            assertThat(message, baos2.toString(Charset.defaultCharset()), containsString("hello"));\\n            assertThat(message, baos1.toString(Charset.defaultCharset()), is(emptyString()));\\n        } else {\\n            assertThat(message, baos1.toString(Charset.defaultCharset()), containsString("hello"));\\n            assertThat(message, baos2.toString(Charset.defaultCharset()), is(emptyString()));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(82, '\'String getDisplayNameOf(Method e, T i) {\\n        Class<?> c = e.getDeclaringClass();\\n        String key = displayNameOf(i);\\n        if (key.isEmpty())  return c.getSimpleName() + "." + e.getName();\\n        try {\\n            ResourceBundleHolder rb = ResourceBundleHolder.get(\\n                    c.getClassLoader().loadClass(c.getPackage().getName() + ".Messages"));\\n            return rb.format(key);\\n        } catch (ClassNotFoundException x) {\\n            LOGGER.log(WARNING, "Failed to load " + x.getMessage() + " for " + e, x);\\n            return key;\\n        } catch (MissingResourceException x) {\\n            LOGGER.log(WARNING, "Could not find key \\\'" + key + "\\\' in " + c.getPackage().getName() + ".Messages", x);\\n            return key;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(193, '\'boolean addOrReplaceAction(@NonNull Action a) {\\n        if (a == null) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Action must be non-null");\\n        }\\n        // CopyOnWriteArrayList does not support Iterator.remove, so need to do it this way:\\n        List<Action> old = new ArrayList<>(1);\\n        List<Action> current = getActions();\\n        boolean found = false;\\n        for (Action a2 : current) {\\n            if (!found && a.equals(a2)) {\\n                found = true;\\n            } else  if (a2.getClass() == a.getClass()) {\\n                old.add(a2);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        current.removeAll(old);\\n        if (!found) {\\n            addAction(a);\\n        }\\n        return !found || !old.isEmpty();\\n    }\'')]

[(145, "'boolean hasMoreRecentlyUsedToken(@NonNull User user, ApiTokenProperty.TokenInfoAndStats legacyStats) {\\n        if (legacyStats == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        ApiTokenProperty apiTokenProperty = user.getProperty(ApiTokenProperty.class);\\n\\n        return apiTokenProperty.getTokenList().stream()\\n                .filter(token -> !token.isLegacy)\\n                .anyMatch(token -> {\\n                    Date currentLastUseDate = token.lastUseDate;\\n                    Date legacyLastUseDate = legacyStats.lastUseDate;\\n                    if (legacyLastUseDate == null) {\\n                        legacyLastUseDate = legacyStats.creationDate;\\n                    }\\n                    return currentLastUseDate != null && legacyLastUseDate != null && currentLastUseDate.after(legacyLastUseDate);\\n                });\\n    }'")]

[(1149, '\'void executeReactor(final InitStrategy is, TaskBuilder... builders) throws IOException, InterruptedException, ReactorException {\\n        Reactor reactor = new Reactor(builders) {\\n            /**\\n             * Sets the thread name to the task for better diagnostics.\\n             */\\n            @Override\\n            protected void runTask(Task task) throws Exception {\\n                if (is != null && is.skipInitTask(task))  return;\\n\\n                String taskName = InitReactorRunner.getDisplayName(task);\\n\\n                Thread t = Thread.currentThread();\\n                String name = t.getName();\\n                if (taskName != null)\\n                    t.setName(taskName);\\n                try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) { // full access in the initialization thread\\n                    long start = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n                    super.runTask(task);\\n                    if (LOG_STARTUP_PERFORMANCE)\\n                        LOGGER.info(String.format("Took %dms for %s by %s",\\n                                System.currentTimeMillis() - start, taskName, name));\\n                } catch (Exception | Error x) {\\n                    if (containsLinkageError(x)) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, taskName + " failed perhaps due to plugin dependency issues", x);\\n                    } else {\\n                        throw x;\\n                    }\\n                } finally {\\n                    t.setName(name);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            private boolean containsLinkageError(Throwable x) {\\n                if (x instanceof LinkageError) {\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n                Throwable x2 = x.getCause();\\n                return x2 != null && containsLinkageError(x2);\\n            }\\n        };\\n\\n        new InitReactorRunner() {\\n            @Override\\n            protected void onInitMilestoneAttained(InitMilestone milestone) {\\n                initLevel = milestone;\\n                getLifecycle().onExtendTimeout(EXTEND_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n                if (milestone == PLUGINS_PREPARED) {\\n                    // set up Guice to enable injection as early as possible\\n                    // before this milestone, ExtensionList.ensureLoaded() won\\\'t actually try to locate instances\\n                    ExtensionList.lookup(ExtensionFinder.class).getComponents();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }.run(reactor);\\n    }\'')]

[(55, "'void putUserSeedInSession(String username, boolean overwriteSessionSeed) {\\n        StaplerRequest req = Stapler.getCurrentRequest();\\n        if (req == null) {\\n            // expected case: CLI\\n            // But also HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm because of a redirect from Spring Security, the request is not a Stapler one\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        HttpSession session = req.getSession(false);\\n        if (session == null) {\\n            // expected case: CLI through CLIRegisterer\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!UserSeedProperty.DISABLE_USER_SEED) {\\n            if (!overwriteSessionSeed && session.getAttribute(UserSeedProperty.USER_SESSION_SEED) != null) {\\n                return;\\n            }\\n\\n            User user = User.getById(username, true);\\n\\n            UserSeedProperty userSeed = user.getProperty(UserSeedProperty.class);\\n            if (userSeed == null) {\\n                // if you want to filter out the user seed property, you should consider using the DISABLE_USER_SEED instead\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            String sessionSeed = userSeed.getSeed();\\n            // normally invalidated before\\n            session.setAttribute(UserSeedProperty.USER_SESSION_SEED, sessionSeed);\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(332, '\'ArgumentListBuilder toWindowsCommand(boolean escapeVars) {\\n        ArgumentListBuilder windowsCommand = new ArgumentListBuilder().add("cmd.exe", "/C");\\n        boolean quoted, percent;\\n        for (int i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {\\n            StringBuilder quotedArgs = new StringBuilder();\\n            String arg = args.get(i);\\n            quoted = percent = false;\\n            for (int j = 0; j < arg.length(); j++) {\\n                char c = arg.charAt(j);\\n                if (!quoted && (c == \\\' \\\' || c == \\\'*\\\' || c == \\\'?\\\' || c == \\\',\\\' || c == \\\';\\\')) {\\n                    quoted = startQuoting(quotedArgs, arg, j);\\n                }\\n                else if (c == \\\'^\\\' || c == \\\'&\\\' || c == \\\'<\\\' || c == \\\'>\\\' || c == \\\'|\\\') {\\n                    if (!quoted) quoted = startQuoting(quotedArgs, arg, j);\\n                    // quotedArgs.append(\\\'^\\\'); See note in javadoc above\\n                }\\n                else if (c == \\\'"\\\') {\\n                    if (!quoted) quoted = startQuoting(quotedArgs, arg, j);\\n                    quotedArgs.append(\\\'"\\\');\\n                }\\n                else if (percent && escapeVars\\n                         && ((c >= \\\'A\\\' && c <= \\\'Z\\\') || (c >= \\\'a\\\' && c <= \\\'z\\\'))) {\\n                    if (!quoted) quoted = startQuoting(quotedArgs, arg, j);\\n                    quotedArgs.append(\\\'"\\\').append(c);\\n                    c = \\\'"\\\';\\n                }\\n                percent = c == \\\'%\\\';\\n                if (quoted) quotedArgs.append(c);\\n            }\\n            if (i == 0) {\\n                if (quoted) {\\n                    quotedArgs.insert(0, \\\'"\\\');\\n                } else {\\n                    quotedArgs.append(\\\'"\\\');\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (quoted) {\\n                quotedArgs.append(\\\'"\\\');\\n            } else {\\n                quotedArgs.append(arg);\\n            }\\n\\n            windowsCommand.add(quotedArgs, mask.get(i));\\n        }\\n        // (comment copied from old code in hudson.tasks.Ant)\\n        // on Windows, executing batch file can\\\'t return the correct error code,\\n        // so we need to wrap it into cmd.exe.\\n        // double %% is needed because we want ERRORLEVEL to be expanded after\\n        // batch file executed, not before. [(572, '\'void sendOneZipEntry(ZipOutputStream zos, VirtualFile vf, String relativePath) throws IOException {\\n        // In ZIP archives "All slashes MUST be forward slashes" (http://pkware.com/documents/casestudies/APPNOTE.TXT)\\n        // TODO On Linux file names can contain backslashes which should not treated as file separators.\\n        //      Unfortunately, only the file separator char of the controller is known (File.separatorChar)\\n        //      but not the file separator char of the (maybe remote) "dir".\\n        ZipEntry e = new ZipEntry(relativePath.replace(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', \\\'/\\\'));\\n\\n        e.setTime(vf.lastModified());\\n        zos.putNextEntry(e);\\n        try (InputStream in = vf.open()) {\\n            IOUtils.copy(in, zos);\\n        }\\n        finally {\\n            zos.closeEntry();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(54, "'Hash from(String seed) {\\n        try {\\n            MessageDigest md5 = getMd5();\\n            md5.update(seed.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n            byte[] digest = md5.digest();\\n\\n            for (int i = 8; i < digest.length; i++)\\n                digest[i % 8] ^= digest[i];\\n\\n            long l = 0;\\n            for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++)\\n                l = (l << 8) + (digest[i] & 0xFF);\\n\\n            final Random rnd = new Random(l);\\n            return new Hash() {\\n                @Override\\n                public int next(int n) {\\n                    return rnd.nextInt(n);\\n                }\\n            };\\n        } catch (NoSuchAlgorithmException e) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(e);    // MD5 is a part of JRE\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(433, '\'void parseClassPath(Manifest manifest, File archive, List<File> paths, String attributeName, String separator) throws IOException {\\n        String classPath = manifest.getMainAttributes().getValue(attributeName);\\n        if (classPath == null) return; // attribute not found\\n        for (String s : classPath.split(separator)) {\\n            File file = resolve(archive, s);\\n            if (file.getName().contains("*")) {\\n                // handle wildcard\\n                FileSet fs = new FileSet();\\n                File dir = file.getParentFile();\\n                fs.setDir(dir);\\n                fs.setIncludes(file.getName());\\n                for (String included : fs.getDirectoryScanner(new Project()).getIncludedFiles()) {\\n                    paths.add(new File(dir, included));\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                if (!file.exists())\\n                    throw new IOException("No such file: " + file);\\n                paths.add(file);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(75, "'String unprotect(String data) {\\n        if (data == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        try {\\n            final byte[] value = Base64.getDecoder().decode(data.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n            final byte[] iv = Arrays.copyOfRange(value, 0, IV_BYTES);\\n            final byte[] encrypted = Arrays.copyOfRange(value, IV_BYTES, value.length);\\n            Cipher cipher = Secret.getCipher(ALGORITHM_MODE);\\n            cipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, KEY, new IvParameterSpec(iv));\\n            String plainText = new String(cipher.doFinal(encrypted), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n            if (plainText.endsWith(MAGIC)) {\\n                return plainText.substring(0, plainText.length() - MAGIC.length());\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        } catch (GeneralSecurityException | RuntimeException e) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(201, '\'void doMarshal(final Object source, final HierarchicalStreamWriter writer, final MarshallingContext context) {\\n        final Set seenFields = new HashSet();\\n        final Set seenAsAttributes = new HashSet();\\n\\n        // Attributes might be preferred to child elements ...\\n         reflectionProvider.visitSerializableFields(source, new ReflectionProvider.Visitor() {\\n            @SuppressWarnings("deprecation") // deliberately calling deprecated methods?\\n            @Override\\n            public void visit(String fieldName, Class type, Class definedIn, Object value) {\\n                SingleValueConverter converter = mapper.getConverterFromItemType(fieldName, type, definedIn);\\n                if (converter == null) converter = mapper.getConverterFromItemType(fieldName, type);\\n                if (converter == null) converter = mapper.getConverterFromItemType(type);\\n                if (converter != null) {\\n                    if (value != null) {\\n                        final String str = converter.toString(value);\\n                        if (str != null) {\\n                            writer.addAttribute(mapper.aliasForAttribute(fieldName), str);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                    seenAsAttributes.add(fieldName);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        // Child elements not covered already processed as attributes ...\\n        reflectionProvider.visitSerializableFields(source, new ReflectionProvider.Visitor() {\\n            @Override\\n            public void visit(String fieldName, Class fieldType, Class definedIn, Object newObj) {\\n                if (!seenAsAttributes.contains(fieldName) && newObj != null) {\\n                    Mapper.ImplicitCollectionMapping mapping = mapper.getImplicitCollectionDefForFieldName(source.getClass(), fieldName);\\n                    if (mapping != null) {\\n                        if (mapping.getItemFieldName() != null) {\\n                            Collection list = (Collection) newObj;\\n                            for (Object obj : list) {\\n                                writeField(fieldName, mapping.getItemFieldName(), mapping.getItemType(), definedIn, obj);\\n                            }\\n                        } else {\\n                            context.convertAnother(newObj);\\n                        }\\n                    } else {\\n                        writeField(fieldName, fieldName, fieldType, definedIn, newObj);\\n                        seenFields.add(fieldName);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            @SuppressWarnings("deprecation") // TODO HierarchicalStreamWriter#startNode(String, Class) in 1.5.0\\n            private void writeField(String fieldName, String aliasName, Class fieldType, Class definedIn, Object newObj) {\\n                try {\\n                    if (!mapper.shouldSerializeMember(definedIn, aliasName)) {\\n                        return;\\n                    }\\n                    ExtendedHierarchicalStreamWriterHelper.startNode(writer, mapper.serializedMember(definedIn, aliasName), fieldType);\\n\\n                    Class actualType = newObj.getClass();\\n\\n                    Class defaultType = mapper.defaultImplementationOf(fieldType);\\n                    if (!actualType.equals(defaultType)) {\\n                        String serializedClassName = mapper.serializedClass(actualType);\\n                        if (!serializedClassName.equals(mapper.serializedClass(defaultType))) {\\n                            writer.addAttribute(mapper.aliasForSystemAttribute("class"), serializedClassName);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    if (seenFields.contains(aliasName)) {\\n                        writer.addAttribute(mapper.aliasForAttribute("defined-in"), mapper.serializedClass(definedIn));\\n                    }\\n\\n                    Field field = reflectionProvider.getField(definedIn, fieldName);\\n                    marshallField(context, newObj, field);\\n                    writer.endNode();\\n                } catch (RuntimeException e) {\\n                    // intercept an exception so that the stack trace shows how we end up marshalling the object in question\\n                    throw new RuntimeException("Failed to serialize " + definedIn.getName() + "#" + fieldName + " for " + source.getClass(), e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n        });\\n    }\'')]

[(150, "'boolean check(Calendar cal) {\\n\\n        Calendar checkCal = cal;\\n\\n        if (specTimezone != null && !specTimezone.isEmpty()) {\\n            Calendar tzCal = Calendar.getInstance(TimeZone.getTimeZone(specTimezone));\\n            tzCal.setTime(cal.getTime());\\n            checkCal = tzCal;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!checkBits(bits[0], checkCal.get(MINUTE)))\\n            return false;\\n        if (!checkBits(bits[1], checkCal.get(HOUR_OF_DAY)))\\n            return false;\\n        if (!checkBits(bits[2], checkCal.get(DAY_OF_MONTH)))\\n            return false;\\n        if (!checkBits(bits[3], checkCal.get(MONTH) + 1))\\n            return false;\\n        if (!checkBits(dayOfWeek, checkCal.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK) - 1))\\n            return false;\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }'")]

[(182, '\'void doRestart(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        Jenkins.get().checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n\\n        if (installationDir == null) {\\n            // if the user reloads the page after Hudson has restarted,\\n            // it comes back here. In such a case, don\\\'t let this restart Hudson.\\n            // so just send them back to the top page\\n            rsp.sendRedirect(req.getContextPath() + "/");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        rsp.forward(this, "_restart", req);\\n        final File oldRoot = Jenkins.get().getRootDir();\\n\\n        // initiate an orderly shutdown after we finished serving this request\\n        new Thread("terminator") {\\n            @SuppressFBWarnings(value = "DM_EXIT", justification = "Exit is really intended.")\\n            @Override\\n            public void run() {\\n                try {\\n                    Thread.sleep(1000);\\n\\n                    // let the service start after we close our sockets, to avoid conflicts\\n                    Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread("service starter") {\\n                        @Override\\n                        public void run() {\\n                            try {\\n                                if (!oldRoot.equals(installationDir)) {\\n                                    LOGGER.info("Moving data");\\n                                    Move mv = new Move();\\n                                    Project p = new Project();\\n                                    p.addBuildListener(createLogger());\\n                                    mv.setProject(p);\\n                                    FileSet fs = new FileSet();\\n                                    fs.setDir(oldRoot);\\n                                    fs.setExcludes("war/**"); // we can\\\'t really move the exploded war.\\n                                    mv.addFileset(fs);\\n                                    mv.setTodir(installationDir);\\n                                    mv.setFailOnError(false); // plugins can also fail to move\\n                                    mv.execute();\\n                                }\\n                                LOGGER.info("Starting a Windows service");\\n                                StreamTaskListener task = StreamTaskListener.fromStdout();\\n                                int r = runElevated(\\n                                        new File(installationDir, "jenkins.exe"), "start", task, installationDir);\\n                                task.getLogger().println(r == 0 ? "Successfully started" : "start service failed. Exit code=" + r);\\n                            } catch (IOException | InterruptedException e) {\\n                                e.printStackTrace();\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n\\n                        private DefaultLogger createLogger() {\\n                            DefaultLogger logger = new DefaultLogger();\\n                            logger.setOutputPrintStream(System.out);\\n                            logger.setErrorPrintStream(System.err);\\n                            return logger;\\n                        }\\n                    });\\n\\n                    Jenkins.get().cleanUp();\\n                    System.exit(0);\\n                } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n                    e.printStackTrace();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }.start();\\n    }\'')]

[(965, '\'void start(List<PluginWrapper> plugins) throws Exception {\\n      try (ACLContext context = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n        Map<String, PluginWrapper> pluginsByName = plugins.stream().collect(Collectors.toMap(PluginWrapper::getShortName, p -> p));\\n\\n        // recalculate dependencies of plugins optionally depending the newly deployed ones.\\n        for (PluginWrapper depender : this.plugins) {\\n            if (plugins.contains(depender)) {\\n                // skip itself.\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            for (Dependency d : depender.getOptionalDependencies()) {\\n                PluginWrapper dependee = pluginsByName.get(d.shortName);\\n                if (dependee != null) {\\n                    // this plugin depends on the newly loaded one!\\n                    // recalculate dependencies!\\n                    getPluginStrategy().updateDependency(depender, dependee);\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Redo who depends on who.\\n        resolveDependentPlugins();\\n\\n        try {\\n            Jenkins.get().refreshExtensions();\\n        } catch (ExtensionRefreshException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to refresh extensions after installing some plugins", e);\\n        }\\n        for (PluginWrapper p : plugins) {\\n            //TODO:According to the postInitialize() documentation, one may expect that\\n            //p.getPluginOrFail() NPE will continue the initialization. Keeping the original behavior ATM\\n          p.getPluginOrFail().postInitialize();\\n        }\\n\\n        // run initializers in the added plugins\\n        Reactor r = new Reactor(InitMilestone.ordering());\\n        Set<ClassLoader> loaders = plugins.stream().map(p -> p.classLoader).collect(Collectors.toSet());\\n        r.addAll(new InitializerFinder(uberClassLoader) {\\n          @Override\\n          protected boolean filter(Method e) {\\n            return !loaders.contains(e.getDeclaringClass().getClassLoader()) || super.filter(e);\\n          }\\n        }.discoverTasks(r));\\n        new InitReactorRunner().run(r);\\n      }\\n    }\'')]

[(54, '\'TagScript createTagScript(final String tagName, Attributes attributes) throws JellyException {\\n        return new TagScript() {\\n            private Object evalAttribute(String name, JellyContext context) {\\n                ExpressionAttribute e = attributes.get(name);\\n                if (e == null)    return null;\\n                return e.exp.evaluate(context);\\n            }\\n\\n            private Collection<?> getExclusions(JellyContext context) {\\n                Object exclusion = evalAttribute(EXCEPT_ATTRIBUTES, context);\\n                if (exclusion == null)\\n                    return Collections.emptySet();\\n                if (exclusion instanceof String)\\n                    return Arrays.asList(exclusion.toString().split("\\\\\\\\s+")); // split by whitespace\\n                if (exclusion instanceof Collection)\\n                    return (Collection) exclusion;\\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException("Expected collection for exclusion but found :" + exclusion);\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public void run(JellyContext context, XMLOutput output) throws JellyTagException {\\n                AttributesImpl actual = new AttributesImpl();\\n\\n                Collection<?> exclusions = getExclusions(context);\\n\\n                Map<String, ?> meta = (Map) evalAttribute(META_ATTRIBUTES, context);\\n                if (meta != null) {\\n                    for (Map.Entry<String, ?> e : meta.entrySet()) {\\n                        String key = e.getKey();\\n                        // @see jelly.impl.DynamicTag.setAttribute() -- ${attrs} has duplicates with "Attr" suffix\\n                        if (key.endsWith("Attr") && meta.containsKey(key.substring(0, key.length() - 4))) continue;\\n                        // @see http://github.com/jenkinsci/jelly/commit/4ae67d15957b5b4d32751619997a3cb2a6ad56ed\\n                        if (key.equals("ownerTag")) continue;\\n                        if (!exclusions.contains(key)) {\\n                            Object v = e.getValue();\\n                            if (v != null)\\n                                actual.addAttribute("", key, key, "CDATA", v.toString());\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    meta = Collections.emptyMap();\\n                }\\n\\n                for (Map.Entry<String, ExpressionAttribute> e : attributes.entrySet()) {\\n                    String name = e.getKey();\\n                    if (name.equals(META_ATTRIBUTES) || name.equals(EXCEPT_ATTRIBUTES))     continue;   // already handled\\n                    if (meta.containsKey(name)) {\\n                        // if the explicit value is also generated by a map, delete it first.\\n                        // this is O(N) operation, but we don\\\'t expect there to be a lot of collisions.\\n                        int idx = actual.getIndex(name);\\n                        if (idx >= 0)  actual.removeAttribute(idx);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    Expression expression = e.getValue().exp;\\n                    actual.addAttribute("", name, name, "CDATA", expression.evaluateAsString(context));\\n                }\\n\\n                try {\\n                    output.startElement(tagName, actual);\\n                    getTagBody().run(context, output);\\n                    output.endElement(tagName);\\n                } catch (SAXException x) {\\n                    throw new JellyTagException(x);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        };\\n    }\'')]

[(219, '"boolean isResourceRequest(HttpServletRequest req) {\\n        if (!isResourceDomainConfigured()) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        String resourceRootUrl = get().getUrl();\\n        try {\\n            URL url = new URL(resourceRootUrl);\\n\\n            String resourceRootHost = url.getHost();\\n            if (!resourceRootHost.equalsIgnoreCase(req.getServerName())) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            int resourceRootPort = url.getPort();\\n            if (resourceRootPort == -1) {\\n                resourceRootPort = url.getDefaultPort();\\n            }\\n\\n            // let\'s hope this gives the default port if the Host header exists but doesn\'t specify a port\\n            int requestedPort = req.getServerPort();\\n\\n            if (requestedPort != resourceRootPort) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        } catch (MalformedURLException ex) {\\n            // the URL here cannot be so broken that we cannot call `new URL(String)` on it...\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        return true;\\n    }"')]

[(384, '\'List<SuggestedItem> find(Mode m, SearchIndex index, String tokenList, SearchableModelObject searchContext) {\\n        TokenList tokens = new TokenList(tokenList);\\n        if (tokens.length() == 0) return Collections.emptyList();   // no tokens given\\n\\n        List<SuggestedItem>[] paths = new List[tokens.length() + 1]; // we won\\\'t use [0].\\n        for (int i = 1; i <= tokens.length(); i++)\\n            paths[i] = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        List<SearchItem> items = new ArrayList<>(); // items found in 1 step\\n\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "tokens={0}", tokens);\\n\\n        // first token\\n        int w = 1;    // width of token\\n        for (String token : tokens.subSequence(0)) {\\n            items.clear();\\n            m.find(index, token, items);\\n            for (SearchItem si : items) {\\n                paths[w].add(SuggestedItem.build(searchContext, si));\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "found search item: {0}", si.getSearchName());\\n            }\\n            w++;\\n        }\\n\\n        // successive tokens\\n        for (int j = 1; j < tokens.length(); j++) {\\n            // for each length\\n            w = 1;\\n            for (String token : tokens.subSequence(j)) {\\n                // for each candidate\\n                for (SuggestedItem r : paths[j]) {\\n                    items.clear();\\n                    m.find(r.item.getSearchIndex(), token, items);\\n                    for (SearchItem i : items)\\n                        paths[j + w].add(new SuggestedItem(r, i));\\n                }\\n                w++;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return paths[tokens.length()];\\n    }\'')]

        if (a.isEmpty()) {\\n                    LabelAtom nearest = LabelAtom.findNearest(a.getName());\\n                    return [(130, '\'void filter(@NonNull EnvVars envVars, @NonNull EnvVarsFilterRuleContext context) {\\n        Map<String, String> systemEnvVars = EnvVars.masterEnvVars;\\n\\n        final List<String> variablesRemoved = new ArrayList<>();\\n        final List<String> variablesReset = new ArrayList<>();\\n        final List<String> variables = variablesToRetain();\\n        for (Iterator<Map.Entry<String, String>> iterator = envVars.entrySet().iterator(); iterator.hasNext(); ) {\\n            Map.Entry<String, String> entry = iterator.next();\\n            String variableName = entry.getKey();\\n            String variableValue = entry.getValue();\\n\\n            if (!variables.contains(variableName.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH))) {\\n                // systemEnvVars\\\'s keys are case insensitive\\n                String systemValue = systemEnvVars.get(variableName);\\n\\n                if (systemValue == null) {\\n                    variablesRemoved.add(variableName);\\n                    iterator.remove();\\n                } else {\\n                    switch (processVariablesHandling) {\\n                        case RESET:\\n                            if (!systemValue.equals(variableValue)) {\\n                                variablesReset.add(variableName);\\n                            }\\n                            break;\\n                        case REMOVE:\\n                            variablesRemoved.add(variableName);\\n                            iterator.remove();\\n                            break;\\n                        default:\\n                            throw new AssertionError("Unknown process variables handling: " + processVariablesHandling);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!variablesRemoved.isEmpty()) {\\n            context.getTaskListener().getLogger().println(Messages.RetainVariablesLocalRule_RemovalMessage(getDescriptor().getDisplayName(), String.join(", ", variablesRemoved)));\\n        }\\n        if (!variablesReset.isEmpty()) {\\n            // reset the variables using the initial value from System\\n            variablesReset.forEach(variableName -> envVars.put(variableName, systemEnvVars.get(variableName)));\\n            context.getTaskListener().getLogger().println(Messages.RetainVariablesLocalRule_ResetMessage(getDescriptor().getDisplayName(), String.join(", ", variablesReset)));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

Level.FINE : Level.INFO, "Waiting for node disconnection completion");\\n        }\\n        for (Future<?> f : pending) {\\n            try {\\n                f.get(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS);    // if clean up operation didn\\\'t complete in time, we fail the test\\n            } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n                Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\\n                break;  // someone wants us to die now. quick!\\n            } catch (ExecutionException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to shut down remote computer connection cleanly", e);\\n            } catch (TimeoutException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to shut down remote computer connection within 10 seconds", e);\\n            } catch (OutOfMemoryError e) {\\n                // we should just propagate this, no point trying to log\\n                throw e;\\n            } catch (LinkageError e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to shut down remote computer connection", e);\\n            } catch (Throwable e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, "Unexpected error while waiting for remote computer connection disconnect", e);\\n                errors.add(e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1291, '\'PollingResult poll(TaskListener listener) {\\n        SCM scm = getScm();\\n        if (scm == null) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(Messages.AbstractProject_NoSCM());\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        }\\n        if (!isBuildable()) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(Messages.AbstractProject_Disabled());\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        }\\n        SCMDecisionHandler veto = SCMDecisionHandler.firstShouldPollVeto(this);\\n        if (veto != null) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(Messages.AbstractProject_PollingVetoed(veto));\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        }\\n\\n        R lb = getLastBuild();\\n        if (lb == null) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(Messages.AbstractProject_NoBuilds());\\n            return isInQueue() ? NO_CHANGES : BUILD_NOW;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (pollingBaseline == null) {\\n            R success = getLastSuccessfulBuild(); // if we have a persisted baseline, we\\\'ll find it by this\\n            for (R r = lb; r != null; r = r.getPreviousBuild()) {\\n                SCMRevisionState s = r.getAction(SCMRevisionState.class);\\n                if (s != null) {\\n                    pollingBaseline = s;\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                if (r == success) break;  // searched far enough\\n            }\\n            // NOTE-NO-BASELINE:\\n            // if we don\\\'t have baseline yet, it means the data is built by old Hudson that doesn\\\'t set the baseline\\n            // as action, so we need to compute it. This happens later.\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            SCMPollListener.fireBeforePolling(this, listener);\\n            PollingResult r = _poll(listener, scm);\\n            SCMPollListener.firePollingSuccess(this, listener, r);\\n            return r;\\n        } catch (AbortException e) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println(e.getMessage());\\n            listener.fatalError(Messages.AbstractProject_Aborted());\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Polling " + this + " aborted", e);\\n            SCMPollListener.firePollingFailed(this, listener, e);\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(e.getMessage()));\\n            SCMPollListener.firePollingFailed(this, listener, e);\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n            Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.fatalError(Messages.AbstractProject_PollingABorted()));\\n            SCMPollListener.firePollingFailed(this, listener, e);\\n            return NO_CHANGES;\\n        } catch (RuntimeException | Error e) {\\n            SCMPollListener.firePollingFailed(this, listener, e);\\n            throw e;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(63, '\'int sshConnection(String jenkinsUrl, String user, List<String> args, PrivateKeyProvider provider, final boolean strictHostKey) throws IOException {\\n        Logger.getLogger(SecurityUtils.class.getName()).setLevel(Level.WARNING); // suppress: BouncyCastle not registered, using the default JCE provider\\n        URL url = new URL(jenkinsUrl + "login");\\n        URLConnection conn = openConnection(url);\\n        CLI.verifyJenkinsConnection(conn);\\n        String endpointDescription = conn.getHeaderField("X-SSH-Endpoint");\\n\\n        if (endpointDescription == null) {\\n            CLI.LOGGER.warning("No header \\\'X-SSH-Endpoint\\\' returned by Jenkins");\\n            return -1;\\n        }\\n\\n        CLI.LOGGER.log(FINE, "Connecting via SSH to: {0}", endpointDescription);\\n\\n        int sshPort = Integer.parseInt(endpointDescription.split(":")[1]);\\n        String sshHost = endpointDescription.split(":")[0];\\n\\n        StringBuilder command = new StringBuilder();\\n\\n        for (String arg : args) {\\n            command.append(QuotedStringTokenizer.quote(arg));\\n            command.append(\\\' \\\');\\n        }\\n\\n        try (SshClient client = SshClient.setUpDefaultClient()) {\\n\\n            KnownHostsServerKeyVerifier verifier = new DefaultKnownHostsServerKeyVerifier(new ServerKeyVerifier() {\\n                @Override\\n                public boolean verifyServerKey(ClientSession clientSession, SocketAddress remoteAddress, PublicKey serverKey) {\\n                    CLI.LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Unknown host key for {0}", remoteAddress.toString());\\n                    return !strictHostKey;\\n                }\\n            }, true);\\n\\n            client.setServerKeyVerifier(verifier);\\n            client.start();\\n\\n            ConnectFuture cf = client.connect(user, sshHost, sshPort);\\n            cf.await();\\n            try (ClientSession session = cf.getSession()) {\\n                for (KeyPair pair : provider.getKeys()) {\\n                    CLI.LOGGER.log(FINE, "Offering {0} private key", pair.getPrivate().getAlgorithm());\\n                    session.addPublicKeyIdentity(pair);\\n                }\\n                session.auth().verify(10000L);\\n\\n                try (ClientChannel channel = session.createExecChannel(command.toString())) {\\n                    channel.setIn(new NoCloseInputStream(System.in));\\n                    channel.setOut(new NoCloseOutputStream(System.out));\\n                    channel.setErr(new NoCloseOutputStream(System.err));\\n                    WaitableFuture wf = channel.open();\\n                    wf.await();\\n\\n                    Set<ClientChannelEvent> waitMask = channel.waitFor(List.of(ClientChannelEvent.CLOSED), 0L);\\n\\n                    if (waitMask.contains(ClientChannelEvent.TIMEOUT)) {\\n                        throw new SocketTimeoutException("Failed to retrieve command result in time: " + command);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    Integer exitStatus = channel.getExitStatus();\\n                    return exitStatus;\\n\\n                }\\n            } finally {\\n                client.stop();\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(2292, "'void trimLabels(@CheckForNull Set<LabelAtom> includedLabels) {\\n        Set<Set<LabelAtom>> nodeLabels = new HashSet<>();\\n        nodeLabels.add(this.getAssignedLabels());\\n        this.getNodes().forEach(n -> nodeLabels.add(n.getAssignedLabels()));\\n        for (Iterator<Label> itr = labels.values().iterator(); itr.hasNext();) {\\n            Label l = itr.next();\\n            if (includedLabels == null || includedLabels.contains(l) || l.matches(includedLabels)) {\\n                if (nodeLabels.stream().anyMatch(l::matches) || !l.getClouds().isEmpty()) {\\n                    // there is at least one static agent or one cloud that currently claims it can handle the label.\\n                    // if the cloud has been removed, or its labels updated such that it can not handle this, this is handle in later calls\\n                    // resetLabel will remove the agents, and clouds from the label, and they will be repopulated later.\\n                    // not checking `cloud.canProvision()` here prevents a potential call that will only be repeated later\\n                    resetLabel(l);\\n                } else {\\n                    itr.remove();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(4635, '\'void safeRestart(String message) throws RestartNotSupportedException {\\n        final Lifecycle lifecycle = restartableLifecycle();\\n        // Quiet down so that we won\\\'t launch new builds.\\n        quietDownInfo = new QuietDownInfo(message, true);\\n\\n        new Thread("safe-restart thread") {\\n            final String exitUser = getAuthentication2().getName();\\n            @Override\\n            public void run() {\\n                try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n\\n                    // Wait \\\'til we have no active executors.\\n                    doQuietDown(true, 0, message, true);\\n                    // Make sure isQuietingDown is still true.\\n                    if (isQuietingDown()) {\\n                        servletContext.setAttribute("app", new HudsonIsRestarting(true));\\n                        // give some time for the browser to load the "reloading" page\\n                        lifecycle.onStatusUpdate("Restart in 10 seconds");\\n                        Thread.sleep(TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(10));\\n                        lifecycle.onStop(exitUser, null);\\n                        Listeners.notify(RestartListener.class, true, RestartListener::onRestart);\\n                        lifecycle.restart();\\n                    } else {\\n                        lifecycle.onStatusUpdate("Safe-restart mode cancelled");\\n                    }\\n                } catch (Throwable e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to restart Jenkins", e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }.start();\\n    }\'')]

[(160, '\'FormValidation checkSpecificSignature(JSONObject json, JSONObject signatureJson, MessageDigest digest, String digestEntry, Signature signature, String signatureEntry, String digestName) throws IOException {\\n        // this is for computing a digest to check sanity\\n        OutputStream nos = OutputStream.nullOutputStream();\\n        DigestOutputStream dos = new DigestOutputStream(nos, digest);\\n        SignatureOutputStream sos = new SignatureOutputStream(signature);\\n\\n        String providedDigest = signatureJson.optString(digestEntry, null);\\n        if (providedDigest == null) {\\n            return FormValidation.warning("No \\\'" + digestEntry + "\\\' found");\\n        }\\n\\n        String providedSignature = signatureJson.optString(signatureEntry, null);\\n        if (providedSignature == null) {\\n            return FormValidation.warning("No \\\'" + signatureEntry + "\\\' found");\\n        }\\n\\n        // until JENKINS-11110 fix, UC used to serve invalid digest (and therefore unverifiable signature)\\n        // that only covers the earlier portion of the file. This was caused by the lack of close() call\\n        // in the canonical writing, which apparently leave some bytes somewhere that\\\'s not flushed to\\n        // the digest output stream. This affects Jenkins [1.424,1,431].\\n        // Jenkins 1.432 shipped with the "fix" (1eb0c64abb3794edce29cbb1de50c93fa03a8229) that made it\\n        // compute the correct digest, but it breaks all the existing UC json metadata out there. We then\\n        // quickly discovered ourselves in the catch-22 situation. If we generate UC with the correct signature,\\n        // it\\\'ll cut off [1.424,1.431] from the UC. But if we don\\\'t, we\\\'ll cut off [1.432,*).\\n        //\\n        // In 1.433, we revisited 1eb0c64abb3794edce29cbb1de50c93fa03a8229 so that the original "digest"/"signature"\\n        // pair continues to be generated in a buggy form, while "correct_digest"/"correct_signature" are generated\\n        // correctly.\\n        //\\n        // Jenkins should ignore "digest"/"signature" pair. [(1563, '"Method getMethod(@NonNull Class<?> clazz, @Nullable Class<?> base, @NonNull String methodName, @NonNull Class<?>... types) {\\n        try {\\n            final Method res = clazz.getDeclaredMethod(methodName, types);\\n            final int mod = res.getModifiers();\\n            // private and static methods are never ok, and end the search\\n            if (Modifier.isPrivate(mod) || Modifier.isStatic(mod)) {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            // when looking for the base/declaring method, final is not ok\\n            if (base == null && Modifier.isFinal(mod)) {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            // when looking for the overriding method, abstract is not ok\\n            if (base != null && Modifier.isAbstract(mod)) {\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            return res;\\n        } catch (NoSuchMethodException e) {\\n            // If the base is an interface, the implementation may come from a default implementation on a derived\\n            // interface. So look at interfaces too.\\n            if (base != null && Modifier.isInterface(base.getModifiers())) {\\n                for (Class<?> iface : clazz.getInterfaces()) {\\n                    if (base.equals(iface) || !base.isAssignableFrom(iface)) {\\n                        continue;\\n                    }\\n                    final Method defaultImpl = Util.getMethod(iface, base, methodName, types);\\n                    if (defaultImpl != null) {\\n                        return defaultImpl;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            // Method not found in clazz, let\'s search in superclasses\\n            Class<?> superclass = clazz.getSuperclass();\\n            if (superclass != null) {\\n                // if the superclass doesn\'t derive from base anymore (or IS base), stop looking\\n                if (base != null && (base.equals(superclass) || !base.isAssignableFrom(superclass))) {\\n                    return null;\\n                }\\n                return getMethod(superclass, base, methodName, types);\\n            }\\n            return null;\\n        } catch (SecurityException e) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(e);\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(230, '\'void doAjax(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp,\\n          @Header("n") String n) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n\\n        rsp.setContentType("text/html;charset=UTF-8");\\n\\n        // pick up builds to send back\\n        List<T> items = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        if (n != null) {\\n            String nn = null; // we\\\'ll compute next n here\\n\\n            // list up all builds >=n.\\n            for (T t : baseList) {\\n                if (adapter.compare(t, n) >= 0) {\\n                    items.add(t);\\n                    if (adapter.isBuilding(t))\\n                    nn = adapter.getKey(t); // the next fetch should start from youngest build in progress\\n                } else\\n                    break;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (nn == null) {\\n                if (items.isEmpty()) {\\n                    // nothing to report back. next fetch should retry the same \\\'n\\\'\\n                    nn = n;\\n                } else {\\n                    // every record fetched this time is frozen. next fetch should start from the next build\\n                    nn = adapter.getNextKey(adapter.getKey(items.get(0)));\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            baseList = items;\\n\\n            rsp.setHeader("n", nn);\\n            firstTransientBuildKey = nn; // all builds >= nn should be marked transient\\n        }\\n\\n        HistoryPageFilter page = getHistoryPageFilter();\\n        req.getView(page, "ajaxBuildHistory.jelly").forward(req, rsp);\\n    }\'')]

[(63, '\'void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        HttpServletRequest req = (HttpServletRequest) request;\\n        HttpServletResponse rsp = (HttpServletResponse) response;\\n        String authorization = req.getHeader("Authorization");\\n\\n        if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCase(authorization, "Basic ")) {\\n            // authenticate the user\\n            String uidpassword = Scrambler.descramble(authorization.substring(6));\\n            int idx = uidpassword.indexOf(\\\':\\\');\\n            if (idx >= 0) {\\n                String username = uidpassword.substring(0, idx);\\n                String password = uidpassword.substring(idx + 1);\\n\\n                if (!authenticationIsRequired(username)) {\\n                    chain.doFilter(request, response);\\n                    return;\\n                }\\n\\n                for (BasicHeaderAuthenticator a : all()) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINER, "Attempting to authenticate with {0}", a);\\n                    Authentication auth = a.authenticate2(req, rsp, username, password);\\n                    if (auth != null) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(FINE, "Request authenticated as {0} by {1}", new Object[]{auth, a});\\n                        success(req, rsp, chain, auth);\\n                        return;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                fail(req, rsp, new BadCredentialsException("Invalid password/token for user: " + username));\\n            } else {\\n                fail(req, rsp, new BadCredentialsException("Malformed HTTP basic Authorization header"));\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            // not something we care\\n            chain.doFilter(request, response);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1160, '\'long getModificationDate(@NonNull URL url) throws IOException {\\n        URLConnection uc = url.openConnection();\\n\\n        // It prevents file descriptor leak if the URL references a file within JAR\\n        // See JENKINS-37332  for more info\\n        // The code idea is taken from https://github.com/jknack/handlebars.java/pull/394\\n        if (uc instanceof JarURLConnection) {\\n            final JarURLConnection connection = (JarURLConnection) uc;\\n            final URL jarURL = connection.getJarFileURL();\\n            if (jarURL.getProtocol().equals("file")) {\\n                String file = jarURL.getFile();\\n                return new File(file).lastModified();\\n            } else {\\n                // We access the data without file protocol\\n                if (connection.getEntryName() != null) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "Accessing modification date of {0} file, which is an entry in JAR file. "\\n                        + "The access protocol is not file:, falling back to the default logic (risk of file descriptor leak).",\\n                            url);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Fallbak to the default implementation\\n        return uc.getLastModified();\\n    }\'')]
