[(134, '\'boolean isValidInet6Address(String inet6Address) {\\n        String[] parts;\\n        // remove prefix size. This will appear after the zone id (if any)\\n        parts = inet6Address.split("/", -1);\\n        if (parts.length > 2) {\\n            return false; // can only have one prefix specifier\\n        }\\n        if (parts.length == 2) {\\n            if (parts[1].matches("\\\\\\\\d{1,3}")) { // Need to eliminate signs\\n                int bits = Integer.parseInt(parts[1]); // cannot fail because of RE check\\n                if (bits < 0 || bits > 128) {\\n                    return false; // out of range\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                return false; // not a valid number\\n            }\\n        }\\n        // remove zone-id\\n        parts = parts[0].split("%", -1);\\n        if (parts.length > 2) {\\n            return false;\\n        } else if (parts.length == 2) {\\n            // The id syntax is implemenatation independent, but it presumably cannot allow:\\n            // whitespace, \\\'/\\\' or \\\'%\\\'\\n            if (!parts[1].matches("[^\\\\\\\\s/%]+")) {\\n                return false; // invalid id\\n            }\\n        }\\n        inet6Address = parts[0];\\n        boolean containsCompressedZeroes = inet6Address.contains("::");\\n        if (containsCompressedZeroes && (inet6Address.indexOf("::") != inet6Address.lastIndexOf("::"))) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        if ((inet6Address.startsWith(":") && !inet6Address.startsWith("::"))\\n                || (inet6Address.endsWith(":") && !inet6Address.endsWith("::"))) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        String[] octets = inet6Address.split(":");\\n        if (containsCompressedZeroes) {\\n            List<String> octetList = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(octets));\\n            if (inet6Address.endsWith("::")) {\\n                // String.split() drops ending empty segments\\n                octetList.add("");\\n            } else if (inet6Address.startsWith("::") && !octetList.isEmpty()) {\\n                octetList.remove(0);\\n            }\\n            octets = octetList.toArray(new String[0]);\\n        }\\n        if (octets.length > IPV6_MAX_HEX_GROUPS) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        int validOctets = 0;\\n        int emptyOctets = 0; // consecutive empty chunks\\n        for (int index = 0; index < octets.length; index++) {\\n            String octet = octets[index];\\n            if (octet.isEmpty()) {\\n                emptyOctets++;\\n                if (emptyOctets > 1) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                emptyOctets = 0;\\n                // Is last chunk an IPv4 address?\\n                if (index == octets.length - 1 && octet.contains(".")) {\\n                    if (!isValidInet4Address(octet)) {\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                    validOctets += 2;\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (octet.length() > IPV6_MAX_HEX_DIGITS_PER_GROUP) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n                int octetInt;\\n                try {\\n                    octetInt = Integer.parseInt(octet, BASE_16);\\n                } catch (NumberFormatException e) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n                if (octetInt < 0 || octetInt > MAX_UNSIGNED_SHORT) {\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            validOctets++;\\n        }\\n        if (validOctets > IPV6_MAX_HEX_GROUPS || (validOctets < IPV6_MAX_HEX_GROUPS && !containsCompressedZeroes)) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(272, '\'String toNormalizedCSSSelector(String classNames) {\\n        if (classNames == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        String[] classNameTokA = classNames.split(" ");\\n        List<String> classNameTokL = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        // Trim all tokens first\\n        for (String classNameTok : classNameTokA) {\\n            String trimmedToken = classNameTok.trim();\\n            if (trimmedToken.length() > 0) {\\n                classNameTokL.add(trimmedToken);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Refill classNameTokA\\n        classNameTokA = new String[classNameTokL.size()];\\n        classNameTokL.toArray(classNameTokA);\\n\\n        // Sort classNameTokA\\n        Arrays.sort(classNameTokA, Comparator.comparing(String::toString));\\n\\n        // Build the compound name\\n        StringBuilder stringBuilder = new StringBuilder();\\n        for (String classNameTok : classNameTokA) {\\n            stringBuilder.append(".").append(classNameTok);\\n        }\\n\\n        return stringBuilder.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(219, '\'FormValidation doFieldCheck(@QueryParameter(fixEmpty = true) String value,\\n                                       @QueryParameter(fixEmpty = true) String type,\\n                                       @QueryParameter(fixEmpty = true) String errorText,\\n                                       @QueryParameter(fixEmpty = true) String warningText) {\\n        if (value == null) {\\n            if (errorText != null)\\n                return FormValidation.error(errorText);\\n            if (warningText != null)\\n                return FormValidation.warning(warningText);\\n            return FormValidation.error("No error or warning text was set for fieldCheck().");\\n        }\\n\\n        if (type != null) {\\n            try {\\n                if (type.equalsIgnoreCase("number")) {\\n                    NumberFormat.getInstance().parse(value);\\n                } else if (type.equalsIgnoreCase("number-positive")) {\\n                    if (NumberFormat.getInstance().parse(value).floatValue() <= 0)\\n                        return FormValidation.error(Messages.Hudson_NotAPositiveNumber());\\n                } else if (type.equalsIgnoreCase("number-negative")) {\\n                    if (NumberFormat.getInstance().parse(value).floatValue() >= 0)\\n                        return FormValidation.error(Messages.Hudson_NotANegativeNumber());\\n                }\\n            } catch (ParseException e) {\\n                return FormValidation.error(Messages.Hudson_NotANumber());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return FormValidation.ok();\\n    }\'')]

[(83, '\'void populateCollection(HierarchicalStreamReader reader, UnmarshallingContext context, Collection collection) {\\n        while (reader.hasMoreChildren()) {\\n            reader.moveDown();\\n            try {\\n                Object item = readBareItem(reader, context, collection);\\n                long nanoNow = System.nanoTime();\\n                collection.add(item);\\n                XStream2SecurityUtils.checkForCollectionDoSAttack(context, nanoNow);\\n            } catch (CriticalXStreamException e) {\\n                throw e;\\n            } catch (InputManipulationException e) {\\n                Logger.getLogger(RobustCollectionConverter.class.getName()).warning(\\n                        "DoS detected and prevented. If the heuristic was too aggressive, " +\\n                                "you can customize the behavior by setting the hudson.util.XStream2.collectionUpdateLimit system property. " +\\n                                "See https://www.jenkins.io/redirect/xstream-dos-prevention for more information.");\\n                throw new CriticalXStreamException(e);\\n            } catch (XStreamException | LinkageError e) {\\n                RobustReflectionConverter.addErrorInContext(context, e);\\n            }\\n            reader.moveUp();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(712, '\'void unzip(File dir, File zipFile) throws IOException {\\n        dir = dir.getAbsoluteFile();    // without absolutization, getParentFile below seems to fail\\n\\n        try (ZipFile zip = new ZipFile(zipFile)) {\\n            Enumeration<ZipEntry> entries = zip.getEntries();\\n            while (entries.hasMoreElements()) {\\n                ZipEntry e = entries.nextElement();\\n                File f = new File(dir, e.getName());\\n                if (!f.getCanonicalFile().toPath().startsWith(dir.getCanonicalPath())) {\\n                    throw new IOException(\\n                        "Zip " + zipFile.getPath() + " contains illegal file name that breaks out of the target directory: " + e.getName());\\n                }\\n                if (e.isDirectory()) {\\n                    mkdirs(f);\\n                } else {\\n                    File p = f.getParentFile();\\n                    if (p != null) {\\n                        mkdirs(p);\\n                    }\\n                    try (InputStream input = zip.getInputStream(e)) {\\n                        IOUtils.copy(input, f);\\n                    }\\n                    try {\\n                        FilePath target = new FilePath(f);\\n                        int mode = e.getUnixMode();\\n                        if (mode != 0)    // Ant returns 0 if the archive doesn\\\'t record the access mode\\n                            target.chmod(mode);\\n                    } catch (InterruptedException ex) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "unable to set permissions", ex);\\n                    }\\n                    Files.setLastModifiedTime(Util.fileToPath(f), e.getLastModifiedTime());\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(320, '\'void main(String[] a) throws Exception {\\n        // Check the arrays first as this affects later checks\\n        // Doing this here makes it easier when updating the lists\\n        boolean OK = true;\\n        for (String list : new String[]{"INFRASTRUCTURE_TLDS", "COUNTRY_CODE_TLDS", "GENERIC_TLDS", "LOCAL_TLDS"}) {\\n            OK &= isSortedLowerCase(list);\\n        }\\n        if (!OK) {\\n            System.out.println("Fix arrays before retrying; cannot continue");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        Set<String> ianaTlds = new HashSet<>(); // keep for comparison with array contents\\n        DomainValidator dv = DomainValidator.getInstance();\\n        File txtFile = new File("target/tlds-alpha-by-domain.txt");\\n        long timestamp = download(txtFile, "https://data.iana.org/TLD/tlds-alpha-by-domain.txt", 0L);\\n        final File htmlFile = new File("target/tlds-alpha-by-domain.html");\\n        // N.B. sometimes the html file may be updated a day or so after the txt file\\n        // if the txt file contains entries not found in the html file, try again in a day or two\\n        download(htmlFile, "https://www.iana.org/domains/root/db", timestamp);\\n\\n        BufferedReader br = Files.newBufferedReader(txtFile.toPath(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n        String line;\\n        final String header;\\n        line = br.readLine(); // header\\n        if (line.startsWith("# Version ")) {\\n            header = line.substring(2);\\n        } else {\\n            br.close();\\n            throw new IOException("File does not have expected Version header");\\n        }\\n        final boolean generateUnicodeTlds = false; // Change this to generate Unicode TLDs as well\\n\\n        // Parse html page to get entries\\n        Map<String, String[]> htmlInfo = getHtmlInfo(htmlFile);\\n        Map<String, String> missingTLD = new TreeMap<>(); // stores entry and comments as String[]\\n        Map<String, String> missingCC = new TreeMap<>();\\n        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {\\n            if (!line.startsWith("#")) {\\n                final String unicodeTld; // only different from asciiTld if that was punycode\\n                final String asciiTld = line.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);\\n                if (line.startsWith("XN--")) {\\n                    unicodeTld = IDN.toUnicode(line);\\n                } else {\\n                    unicodeTld = asciiTld;\\n                }\\n                if (!dv.isValidTld(asciiTld)) {\\n                    String [] info = htmlInfo.get(asciiTld);\\n                    if (info != null) {\\n                        String type = info[0];\\n                        String comment = info[1];\\n                        if ("country-code".equals(type)) { // Which list to use?\\n                            missingCC.put(asciiTld, unicodeTld + " " + comment);\\n                            if (generateUnicodeTlds) {\\n                                missingCC.put(unicodeTld, asciiTld + " " + comment);\\n                            }\\n                        } else {\\n                            missingTLD.put(asciiTld, unicodeTld + " " + comment);\\n                            if (generateUnicodeTlds) {\\n                                missingTLD.put(unicodeTld, asciiTld + " " + comment);\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    } else {\\n                        System.err.println("Expected to find HTML info for " + asciiTld);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                ianaTlds.add(asciiTld);\\n                // Don\\\'t merge these conditions; generateUnicodeTlds is final so needs to be separate to avoid a warning\\n                if (generateUnicodeTlds) {\\n                    if (!unicodeTld.equals(asciiTld)) {\\n                        ianaTlds.add(unicodeTld);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        br.close();\\n        // List html entries not in TLD text list\\n        for (String key : new TreeMap<>(htmlInfo).keySet()) {\\n            if (!ianaTlds.contains(key)) {\\n                if (isNotInRootZone(key)) {\\n                    System.out.println("INFO: HTML entry not yet in root zone: " + key);\\n                } else {\\n                    System.err.println("WARN: Expected to find text entry for html: " + key);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (!missingTLD.isEmpty()) {\\n            printMap(header, missingTLD, "TLD");\\n        }\\n        if (!missingCC.isEmpty()) {\\n            printMap(header, missingCC, "CC");\\n        }\\n        // Check if internal tables contain any additional entries\\n        isInIanaList("INFRASTRUCTURE_TLDS", ianaTlds);\\n        isInIanaList("COUNTRY_CODE_TLDS", ianaTlds);\\n        isInIanaList("GENERIC_TLDS", ianaTlds);\\n        // Don\\\'t check local TLDS isInIanaList("LOCAL_TLDS", ianaTlds);\\n        System.out.println("Finished checks");\\n    }\'')]

[(243, "'ParametersAction createUpdated(Collection<? extends ParameterValue> overrides) {\\n        if (overrides == null) {\\n            ParametersAction parametersAction = new ParametersAction(parameters);\\n            parametersAction.safeParameters = this.safeParameters;\\n            return parametersAction;\\n        }\\n        List<ParameterValue> combinedParameters = new ArrayList<>(overrides);\\n        Set<String> names = new HashSet<>();\\n\\n        for (ParameterValue v : overrides) {\\n            if (v == null) continue;\\n            names.add(v.getName());\\n        }\\n\\n        for (ParameterValue v : parameters) {\\n            if (v == null) continue;\\n            if (!names.contains(v.getName())) {\\n                combinedParameters.add(v);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return new ParametersAction(combinedParameters, this.safeParameters);\\n    }'")]

[(141, "'List<MarkupText.SubText> findTokens(Pattern pattern) {\\n        String text = getText();\\n        Matcher m = pattern.matcher(text);\\n        List<SubText> r = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        while (m.find()) {\\n            int idx = m.start();\\n            if (idx > 0) {\\n                char ch = text.charAt(idx - 1);\\n                if (Character.isLetter(ch) || Character.isDigit(ch))\\n                    continue;   // not at a word boundary\\n            }\\n            idx = m.end();\\n            if (idx < text.length()) {\\n                char ch = text.charAt(idx);\\n                if (Character.isLetter(ch) || Character.isDigit(ch))\\n                    continue;   // not at a word boundary\\n            }\\n            r.add(createSubText(m));\\n        }\\n\\n        return r;\\n    }'")]

[(772, '"PluginDisableResult disable(@NonNull PluginDisableStrategy strategy) {\\n        PluginDisableResult result = new PluginDisableResult(shortName);\\n\\n        if (!this.isEnabled()) {\\n            result.setMessage(Messages.PluginWrapper_Already_Disabled(shortName));\\n            result.setStatus(ALREADY_DISABLED);\\n            return result;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Act as a flag indicating if this plugin, finally, can be disabled. If there is a not-disabled-dependent\\n        // plugin, this one couldn\'t be disabled.\\n        String aDependentNotDisabled = null;\\n\\n        // List of dependents plugins to \'check\'. \'Check\' means disable for mandatory or all strategies, or review if\\n        // this dependent-mandatory plugin is enabled in order to return an error for the NONE strategy.\\n        Set<String> dependentsToCheck = dependentsToCheck(strategy);\\n\\n        // Review all the dependents and add to the plugin result what happened with its dependents\\n        for (String dependent : dependentsToCheck) {\\n            PluginWrapper dependentPlugin = parent.getPlugin(dependent);\\n\\n            // The dependent plugin doesn\'t exist, add an error to the report\\n            if (dependentPlugin == null) {\\n                PluginDisableResult dependentStatus = new PluginDisableResult(dependent, NO_SUCH_PLUGIN, Messages.PluginWrapper_NoSuchPlugin(dependent));\\n                result.addDependentDisableStatus(dependentStatus);\\n\\n            // If the strategy is none and there is some enabled dependent plugin, the plugin cannot be disabled. If\\n            // this dependent plugin is not enabled, continue searching for one enabled.\\n            } else if (strategy.equals(PluginDisableStrategy.NONE)) {\\n                if (dependentPlugin.isEnabled()) {\\n                    aDependentNotDisabled = dependent;\\n                    break; // in this case, we don\'t need to continue with the rest of its dependents\\n                }\\n\\n            // If the strategy is not none and this dependent plugin is not enabled, add it as already disabled\\n            } else if (!dependentPlugin.isEnabled()) {\\n                PluginDisableResult dependentStatus = new PluginDisableResult(dependent, ALREADY_DISABLED, Messages.PluginWrapper_Already_Disabled(dependent));\\n                result.addDependentDisableStatus(dependentStatus);\\n\\n            // If the strategy is not none and this dependent plugin is enabled, disable it\\n            } else {\\n                // As there is no cycles in the plugin dependencies, the recursion shouldn\'t be infinite. The\\n                // strategy used is the same for its dependents plugins\\n                PluginDisableResult dependentResult = dependentPlugin.disable(strategy);\\n                PluginDisableStatus dependentStatus = dependentResult.status;\\n\\n                // If something wrong happened, flag this dependent plugin to set the plugin later as not-disabled due\\n                // to its dependents plugins.\\n                if (ERROR_DISABLING.equals(dependentStatus) || NOT_DISABLED_DEPENDANTS.equals(dependentStatus)) {\\n                    aDependentNotDisabled = dependent;\\n                    break; // we found a dependent plugin enabled, stop looking for dependent plugins to disable.\\n                }\\n                result.addDependentDisableStatus(dependentResult);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // If there is no enabled-dependent plugin, disable this plugin and add it to the result\\n        if (aDependentNotDisabled == null) {\\n            try {\\n                this.disableWithoutCheck();\\n                result.setMessage(Messages.PluginWrapper_Plugin_Disabled(shortName));\\n                result.setStatus(DISABLED);\\n            } catch (IOException io) {\\n                result.setMessage(Messages.PluginWrapper_Error_Disabling(shortName, io.toString()));\\n                result.setStatus(ERROR_DISABLING);\\n            }\\n        // if there is yet some not disabled dependent plugin (only possible with none strategy), this plugin cannot\\n        // be disabled.\\n        } else {\\n            result.setMessage(Messages.PluginWrapper_Plugin_Has_Dependent(shortName, aDependentNotDisabled, strategy));\\n            result.setStatus(NOT_DISABLED_DEPENDANTS);\\n        }\\n\\n        return result;\\n    }"')]

[(492, '\'long download(File f, String tldurl, long timestamp) throws IOException {\\n        final int HOUR = 60 * 60 * 1000; // an hour in ms\\n        final long modTime;\\n        // For testing purposes, don\\\'t download files more than once an hour\\n        if (f.canRead()) {\\n            modTime = f.lastModified();\\n            if (modTime > System.currentTimeMillis() - HOUR) {\\n                System.out.println("Skipping download - found recent " + f);\\n                return modTime;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            modTime = 0;\\n        }\\n        HttpURLConnection hc = (HttpURLConnection) new URL(tldurl).openConnection();\\n        if (modTime > 0) {\\n            SimpleDateFormat sdf = new SimpleDateFormat("EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss z"); //Sun, 06 Nov 1994 08:49:37 GMT\\n            String since = sdf.format(new Date(modTime));\\n            hc.addRequestProperty("If-Modified-Since", since);\\n            System.out.println("Found " + f + " with date " + since);\\n        }\\n        if (hc.getResponseCode() == 304) {\\n            System.out.println("Already have most recent " + tldurl);\\n        } else {\\n            System.out.println("Downloading " + tldurl);\\n            byte[] buff = new byte[1024];\\n            InputStream is = hc.getInputStream();\\n\\n            FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(f);\\n            int len;\\n            while ((len = is.read(buff)) != -1) {\\n                fos.write(buff, 0, len);\\n            }\\n            fos.close();\\n            is.close();\\n            System.out.println("Done");\\n        }\\n        return f.lastModified();\\n    }\'')]

[(448, '\'boolean isValidPath(String path) {\\n        if (path == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!PATH_PATTERN.matcher(path).matches()) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            // Don\\\'t omit host otherwise leading path may be taken as host if it starts with //\\n            URI uri = new URI(null, "localhost", path, null);\\n            String norm = uri.normalize().getPath();\\n            if (norm.startsWith("/../") // Trying to go via the parent dir\\n                    || norm.equals("/..")) {   // Trying to go to the parent dir\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        } catch (URISyntaxException e) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        int slash2Count = countToken("//", path);\\n        if (isOff(ALLOW_2_SLASHES) && slash2Count > 0) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(78, '\'URL findResource(@NonNull String path) throws IOException {\\n        if (StringUtils.isBlank(path)) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (path.contains("..")) // crude avoidance of directory traversal attack\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(path);\\n\\n        String name;\\n        if (path.charAt(0) == \\\'/\\\') {\\n            name = "assets" + path;\\n        } else {\\n            name = "assets/" + path;\\n        }\\n\\n        ClassLoader cl = Jenkins.class.getClassLoader();\\n        URL url = ClassLoaderReflectionToolkit._findResource(cl, name);\\n        if (url == null) {\\n            // pick the last one, which is the one closest to the leaf of the classloader tree.\\n            Enumeration<URL> e = cl.getResources(name);\\n            while (e.hasMoreElements()) {\\n                url = e.nextElement();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return url;\\n    }\'')]

[(50, '\'void doDynamic(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        String path = req.getRestOfPath();\\n        URL resource = findResource(path);\\n\\n        if (resource == null) {\\n            rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_NOT_FOUND);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Stapler routes requests like the "/static/.../foo/bar/zot" to be treated like "/foo/bar/zot"\\n        // and this is used to serve long expiration header, by using Jenkins.VERSION_HASH as "..."\\n        // to create unique URLs. Recognize that and set a long expiration header.\\n        String requestPath = req.getRequestURI().substring(req.getContextPath().length());\\n        boolean staticLink = requestPath.startsWith("/static/");\\n        long expires = staticLink ? TimeUnit.DAYS.toMillis(365) : -1;\\n\\n        // use serveLocalizedFile to support automatic locale selection\\n        rsp.serveLocalizedFile(req, resource, expires);\\n    }\'')]

[(368, '\'int zip(OutputStream outputStream, String includes, String excludes, boolean useDefaultExcludes,\\n                   String prefix, OpenOption... openOptions) throws IOException {\\n        String correctPrefix;\\n        if (StringUtils.isBlank(prefix)) {\\n            correctPrefix = "";\\n        } else {\\n            correctPrefix = Util.ensureEndsWith(prefix, "/");\\n        }\\n\\n        Collection<String> files = list(includes, excludes, useDefaultExcludes, openOptions);\\n        try (ZipOutputStream zos = new ZipOutputStream(outputStream)) {\\n            zos.setEncoding(System.getProperty("file.encoding")); // TODO JENKINS-20663 make this overridable via query parameter\\n\\n            for (String relativePath : files) {\\n                VirtualFile virtualFile = this.child(relativePath);\\n                sendOneZipEntry(zos, virtualFile, relativePath, correctPrefix, openOptions);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return files.size();\\n    }\'')]

[(45, '\'SubTask getParentOf(@NonNull Executable e)\\n            throws Error, RuntimeException {\\n        try {\\n            return e.getParent();\\n        } catch (AbstractMethodError ignored) { // will fallback to a private implementation\\n            try {\\n                Method m = e.getClass().getMethod("getParent");\\n                m.setAccessible(true);\\n                return (SubTask) m.invoke(e);\\n            } catch (IllegalAccessException x) {\\n                throw (Error) new IllegalAccessError().initCause(x);\\n            } catch (NoSuchMethodException x) {\\n                throw (Error) new NoSuchMethodError().initCause(x);\\n            } catch (InvocationTargetException x) {\\n                Throwable y = x.getTargetException();\\n                if (y instanceof Error)     throw (Error) y;\\n                if (y instanceof RuntimeException)     throw (RuntimeException) y;\\n                throw new Error(x);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(136, "'void reset(SecurityRealm securityRealm) throws ServletException {\\n        if (securityRealm != null) {\\n            SecurityRealm.SecurityComponents sc = securityRealm.getSecurityComponents();\\n            AUTHENTICATION_MANAGER.setDelegate(sc.manager2);\\n            USER_DETAILS_SERVICE_PROXY.setDelegate(sc.userDetails2);\\n            REMEMBER_ME_SERVICES_PROXY.setDelegate(sc.rememberMe2);\\n            // make sure this.filter is always a valid filter.\\n            Filter oldf = this.filter;\\n            Filter newf = securityRealm.createFilter(this.filterConfig);\\n            newf.init(this.filterConfig);\\n            this.filter = newf;\\n            if (oldf != null)\\n                oldf.destroy();\\n        } else {\\n            // no security related filter needed.\\n            AUTHENTICATION_MANAGER.setDelegate(null);\\n            USER_DETAILS_SERVICE_PROXY.setDelegate(null);\\n            REMEMBER_ME_SERVICES_PROXY.setDelegate(null);\\n            filter = null;\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(383, '"SortedMap<Integer, R> subMap(Integer fromKey, Integer toKey) {\\n        // TODO: if this method can produce a lazy map, that\'d be wonderful\\n        // because due to the lack of floor/ceil/higher/lower kind of methods\\n        // to look up keys in SortedMap, various places of Jenkins rely on\\n        // subMap+firstKey/lastKey combo.\\n\\n        R start = search(fromKey, DESC);\\n        if (start == null)    return EMPTY_SORTED_MAP;\\n\\n        R end = search(toKey, ASC);\\n        if (end == null)      return EMPTY_SORTED_MAP;\\n\\n        for (R i = start; i != end; ) {\\n            i = search(getNumberOf(i) - 1, DESC);\\n            assert i != null;\\n        }\\n\\n        return Collections.unmodifiableSortedMap(new BuildReferenceMapAdapter<>(this, index.byNumber.subMap(fromKey, toKey)));\\n    }"')]

[(217, "'List<IOException> tryRemoveDirectoryContents(@NonNull Path path) {\\n        Path normalized = path.normalize();\\n        List<IOException> accumulatedErrors = new ArrayList<>();\\n        if (!Files.isDirectory(normalized)) return accumulatedErrors;\\n        try (DirectoryStream<Path> children = Files.newDirectoryStream(normalized)) {\\n            for (Path child : children) {\\n                accumulatedErrors.addAll(tryRemoveRecursive(child));\\n            }\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            accumulatedErrors.add(e);\\n        }\\n        return accumulatedErrors;\\n    }'")]

[(219, '"void fireLocationChange(final Item rootItem, final String oldFullName) {\\n        String prefix = rootItem.getParent().getFullName();\\n        if (!prefix.isEmpty()) {\\n            prefix += \'/\';\\n        }\\n        final String newFullName = rootItem.getFullName();\\n        assert newFullName.startsWith(prefix);\\n        int prefixS = prefix.length();\\n        if (oldFullName.startsWith(prefix) && oldFullName.indexOf(\'/\', prefixS) == -1) {\\n            final String oldName = oldFullName.substring(prefixS);\\n            final String newName = rootItem.getName();\\n            assert newName.equals(newFullName.substring(prefixS));\\n            Listeners.notify(ItemListener.class, false, l -> l.onRenamed(rootItem, oldName, newName));\\n        }\\n        Listeners.notify(ItemListener.class, false, l -> l.onLocationChanged(rootItem, oldFullName, newFullName));\\n        if (rootItem instanceof ItemGroup) {\\n            for (final Item child : Items.allItems2(ACL.SYSTEM2, (ItemGroup) rootItem, Item.class)) {\\n                final String childNew = child.getFullName();\\n                assert childNew.startsWith(newFullName);\\n                assert childNew.charAt(newFullName.length()) == \'/\';\\n                final String childOld = oldFullName + childNew.substring(newFullName.length());\\n                Listeners.notify(ItemListener.class, false, l -> l.onLocationChanged(child, childOld, childNew));\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(341, '\'FormValidation validateExecutable(String exe, FileValidator exeValidator) {\\n        // insufficient permission to perform validation?\\n        if (!Jenkins.get().hasPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER)) return ok();\\n        final FormValidation[] result = {null};\\n\\n        try {\\n            DOSToUnixPathHelper.iteratePath(exe, new DOSToUnixPathHelper.Helper() {\\n                @Override\\n                public void ok() {\\n                    result[0] = FormValidation.ok();\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public void checkExecutable(File fexe) {\\n                    result[0] = exeValidator.validate(fexe);\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public void error(String string) {\\n                    result[0] = FormValidation.error(string);\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override\\n                public void validate(File fexe) {\\n                    result[0] = exeValidator.validate(fexe);\\n                }\\n            });\\n            return result[0];\\n        } catch (RuntimeException e) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(e, "Unexpected error");\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1445, "'boolean canDiscoverItem(@NonNull final String fullName) {\\n        final Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.get();\\n\\n        // Fast check to avoid security context switches\\n        Item item = null;\\n        try {\\n            item = jenkins.getItemByFullName(fullName);\\n        } catch (AccessDeniedException ex) {\\n            // ignore, we will fall-back later\\n        }\\n        if (item != null) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Probably it failed due to the missing Item.DISCOVER\\n        // We try to retrieve the job using SYSTEM2 user and to check permissions manually.\\n        final Authentication userAuth = Jenkins.getAuthentication2();\\n        try (ACLContext acl = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n            final Item itemBySystemUser = jenkins.getItemByFullName(fullName);\\n            if (itemBySystemUser == null) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            // To get the item existence fact, a user needs Item.DISCOVER for the item\\n            // and Item.READ for all container folders.\\n            boolean canDiscoverTheItem = itemBySystemUser.hasPermission2(userAuth, Item.DISCOVER);\\n            if (canDiscoverTheItem) {\\n                ItemGroup<?> current = itemBySystemUser.getParent();\\n                do {\\n                    if (current instanceof Item) {\\n                        final Item i = (Item) current;\\n                        current = i.getParent();\\n                        if (!i.hasPermission2(userAuth, Item.READ)) {\\n                            canDiscoverTheItem = false;\\n                        }\\n                    } else {\\n                        current = null;\\n                    }\\n                } while (canDiscoverTheItem && current != null);\\n            }\\n            return canDiscoverTheItem;\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(1522, '\'boolean isOverridden(@NonNull Class<?> base, @NonNull Class<?> derived, @NonNull String methodName, @NonNull Class<?>... types) {\\n        // If derived is not a subclass or implementor of base, it can\\\'t override any method\\n        // Technically this should also be triggered when base == derived, because it can\\\'t override its own method, but\\n        // the unit tests explicitly test for that as working.\\n        if (!base.isAssignableFrom(derived)) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException("The specified derived class (" + derived.getCanonicalName() + ") does not derive from the specified base class (" + base.getCanonicalName() + ").");\\n        }\\n        final Method baseMethod = Util.getMethod(base, null, methodName, types);\\n        if (baseMethod == null) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException("The specified method is not declared by the specified base class (" + base.getCanonicalName() + "), or it is private, static or final.");\\n        }\\n        final Method derivedMethod = Util.getMethod(derived, base, methodName, types);\\n        // the lookup will either return null or the base method when no override has been found (depending on whether\\n        // the base is an interface)\\n        return derivedMethod != null && derivedMethod != baseMethod;\\n    }\'')]

[(84, '\'boolean isApplicable(Class<? extends Job> jobType) {\\n        Type parameterization = Types.getBaseClass(clazz, JobProperty.class);\\n        if (parameterization instanceof ParameterizedType) {\\n            ParameterizedType pt = (ParameterizedType) parameterization;\\n            Class applicable = Types.erasure(Types.getTypeArgument(pt, 0));\\n            return applicable.isAssignableFrom(jobType);\\n        } else {\\n            throw new AssertionError(clazz + " doesn\\\'t properly parameterize JobProperty. The isApplicable() method must be overridden.");\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(394, '\'CauseOfBlockage canTake(Queue.BuildableItem item) {\\n        Label l = item.getAssignedLabel();\\n        if (l != null && !l.contains(this))\\n            return CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Node_LabelMissing(getDisplayName(), l));   // the task needs to be executed on label that this node doesn\\\'t have.\\n\\n        if (l == null && getMode() == Mode.EXCLUSIVE) {\\n            // flyweight tasks need to get executed somewhere, if every node\\n            if (!(item.task instanceof Queue.FlyweightTask && (\\n                    this instanceof Jenkins\\n                            // TODO Why is the next operator a \\\'||\\\' instead of a \\\'&&\\\'?\\n                            || Jenkins.get().getNumExecutors() < 1\\n                            || Jenkins.get().getMode() == Mode.EXCLUSIVE)\\n            )) {\\n                return CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Node_BecauseNodeIsReserved(getDisplayName()));   // this node is reserved for tasks that are tied to it\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        Authentication identity = item.authenticate2();\\n        if (!(SKIP_BUILD_CHECK_ON_FLYWEIGHTS && item.task instanceof Queue.FlyweightTask) && !hasPermission2(identity, Computer.BUILD)) {\\n            // doesn\\\'t have a permission\\n            return CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Node_LackingBuildPermission(identity.getName(), getDisplayName()));\\n        }\\n\\n        // Check each NodeProperty to see whether they object to this node\\n        // taking the task\\n        for (NodeProperty prop : getNodeProperties()) {\\n            CauseOfBlockage c;\\n            try {\\n                c = prop.canTake(item);\\n            } catch (Throwable t) {\\n                // We cannot guarantee the task can be taken by this node because something wrong happened\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, t, () -> String.format("Exception evaluating if the node \\\'%s\\\' can take the task \\\'%s\\\'", getNodeName(), item.task.getName()));\\n                c = CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Queue_ExceptionCanTake());\\n            }\\n            if (c != null)    return c;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!isAcceptingTasks()) {\\n            return new CauseOfBlockage.BecauseNodeIsNotAcceptingTasks(this);\\n        }\\n\\n        // Looks like we can take the task\\n        return null;\\n    }\'')]

[(72, '\'JSONObject getBundle(@NonNull String baseName, @NonNull Locale locale) throws MissingResourceException {\\n        String bundleKey = baseName + ":" + locale;\\n        JSONObject bundleJSON = bundles.get(bundleKey);\\n\\n        if (bundleJSON != null) {\\n            return bundleJSON;\\n        }\\n\\n        ResourceBundle bundle = getBundle(baseName, locale, Jenkins.class.getClassLoader());\\n        if (bundle == null) {\\n            // Not in Jenkins core. Check the plugins.\\n            Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n            if (jenkins != null) {\\n                for (PluginWrapper plugin : jenkins.getPluginManager().getPlugins()) {\\n                    bundle = getBundle(baseName, locale, plugin.classLoader);\\n                    if (bundle != null) {\\n                        break;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (bundle == null) {\\n            throw new MissingResourceException("Can\\\'t find bundle for base name "\\n                    + baseName + ", locale " + locale, baseName + "_" + locale, "");\\n        }\\n\\n        bundleJSON = toJSONObject(bundle);\\n        bundles.put(bundleKey, bundleJSON);\\n\\n        return bundleJSON;\\n    }\'')]

[(205, '\'void _labels(JenkinsRule r) throws Exception {\\n        try (BulkChange bc = new BulkChange(r.jenkins)) {\\n            DummyCloudImpl cloud = initHudson(0, r);\\n            Label blue = r.jenkins.getLabel("blue");\\n            Label red = r.jenkins.getLabel("red");\\n            cloud.label = red;\\n\\n            // red jobs\\n            List<FreeStyleProject> redJobs = create5SlowJobs(new Latch(5), r);\\n            for (FreeStyleProject p : redJobs)\\n                p.setAssignedLabel(red);\\n\\n            // blue jobs\\n            List<FreeStyleProject> blueJobs = create5SlowJobs(new Latch(5), r);\\n            for (FreeStyleProject p : blueJobs)\\n                p.setAssignedLabel(blue);\\n\\n            // build all\\n            List<Future<FreeStyleBuild>> blueBuilds = buildAll(blueJobs);\\n            verifySuccessfulCompletion(buildAll(redJobs), r);\\n\\n            // cloud should only give us 5 nodes for 5 red jobs\\n            // sometimes we can end up allocating 6 due to the conservative estimation in StandardStrategyImpl#apply\\n            assertThat(cloud.numProvisioned, anyOf(equalTo(5), equalTo(6)));\\n\\n            // and all blue jobs should be still stuck in the queue\\n            for (Future<FreeStyleBuild> bb : blueBuilds)\\n                assertFalse(bb.isDone());\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(163, "'void synchronizeEnd(Executor e, Queue.Executable executable, Throwable problems, long duration) throws InterruptedException {\\n        // Let code waiting for the build to finish (future.get()) finishes when there is a faulty SubTask by setting\\n        // the future always.\\n        try {\\n            endLatch.synchronize();\\n        } finally {\\n            // the main thread will send a notification\\n            WorkUnit wu = e.getCurrentWorkUnit();\\n            if (wu.isMainWork()) {\\n                if (problems == null) {\\n                    future.set(executable);\\n                    e.getOwner().taskCompleted(e, task, duration);\\n                    for (ExecutorListener listener : ExtensionList.lookup(ExecutorListener.class)) {\\n                        try {\\n                            listener.taskCompleted(e, task, duration);\\n                        } catch (RuntimeException x) {\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, null, x);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    future.set(problems);\\n                    e.getOwner().taskCompletedWithProblems(e, task, duration, problems);\\n                    for (ExecutorListener listener : ExtensionList.lookup(ExecutorListener.class)) {\\n                        try {\\n                            listener.taskCompletedWithProblems(e, task, duration, problems);\\n                        } catch (RuntimeException x) {\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, null, x);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(414, '\'SignupInfo validateAccountCreationForm(StaplerRequest req, boolean validateCaptcha) {\\n        // form field validation\\n        // this pattern needs to be generalized and moved to stapler\\n        SignupInfo si = new SignupInfo(req);\\n\\n        if (validateCaptcha && !validateCaptcha(si.captcha)) {\\n            si.errors.put("captcha", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_TextNotMatchWordInImage());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (si.username == null || si.username.isEmpty()) {\\n            si.errors.put("username", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_UserNameRequired());\\n        } else if (!containsOnlyAcceptableCharacters(si.username)) {\\n            if (ID_REGEX == null) {\\n                si.errors.put("username", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_UserNameInvalidCharacters());\\n            } else {\\n                si.errors.put("username", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_UserNameInvalidCharactersCustom(ID_REGEX));\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            // do not create the user - we just want to check if the user already exists but is not a "login" user.\\n            User user = User.getById(si.username, false);\\n            if (null != user)\\n                // Allow sign up. SCM people has no such property.\\n                if (user.getProperty(Details.class) != null)\\n                    si.errors.put("username", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_UserNameAlreadyTaken());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (si.password1 != null && !si.password1.equals(si.password2)) {\\n            si.errors.put("password1", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_PasswordNotMatch());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!(si.password1 != null && si.password1.length() != 0)) {\\n            si.errors.put("password1", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_PasswordRequired());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (si.fullname == null || si.fullname.isEmpty()) {\\n            si.fullname = si.username;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (isMailerPluginPresent() && (si.email == null || !si.email.contains("@"))) {\\n            si.errors.put("email", Messages.HudsonPrivateSecurityRealm_CreateAccount_InvalidEmailAddress());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!User.isIdOrFullnameAllowed(si.username)) {\\n            si.errors.put("username", hudson.model.Messages.User_IllegalUsername(si.username));\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!User.isIdOrFullnameAllowed(si.fullname)) {\\n            si.errors.put("fullname", hudson.model.Messages.User_IllegalFullname(si.fullname));\\n        }\\n        req.setAttribute("data", si); // for error messages in the view\\n        return si;\\n    }\'')]

[(46, "'int waitForExitProcess(Pointer hProcess) throws InterruptedException {\\n        while (true) {\\n            if (Thread.interrupted())\\n                throw new InterruptedException();\\n\\n            Kernel32.INSTANCE.WaitForSingleObject(hProcess, 1000);\\n            IntByReference exitCode = new IntByReference();\\n            exitCode.setValue(-1);\\n            Kernel32.INSTANCE.GetExitCodeProcess(hProcess, exitCode);\\n\\n            int v = exitCode.getValue();\\n            if (v != Kernel32.STILL_ACTIVE) {\\n                return v;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

List<File> kidsList = new ArrayList<>(Arrays.asList(kids));\\n        Iterator<File> it = kidsList.iterator();\\n        while (it.hasNext()) {\\n            File kid = it.next();\\n            String name = kid.getName();\\n            try {\\n                Integer.parseInt(name);\\n            } catch (NumberFormatException x) {\\n                LOGGER.log(FINE, "ignoring nonnumeric entry {0}", name);\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            try {\\n                if (Util.isSymlink(kid)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINE, "deleting build number symlink {0} → {1}", new Object[] {name, Util.resolveSymlink(kid)});\\n                } else if (kid.isDirectory()) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINE, "ignoring build directory {0}", name);\\n Integer.parseInt(name);\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINE, "skipping new build dir {0}", name);\\n                    continue;\\n                } catch (NumberFormatException x) {\\n legacyIdFormatter.parse(name).getTime();\\n                    }\\n                } catch (ParseException x) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "found unexpected dir {0}", name);\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                File buildXml = new File(kid, "build.xml");\\n                if (!buildXml.isFile()) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "found no build.xml in {0}", name);\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                String xml = Files.readString(Util.fileToPath(buildXml), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n                Matcher m = NUMBER_ELT.matcher(xml);\\n                if (!m.find()) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "could not find <number> in {0}/build.xml", name);\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                int number = Integer.parseInt(m.group(1));\\n                String nl = m.group(2);\\n                xml = m.replaceFirst("  <id>" + name + "</id>" + nl + "  <timestamp>" + timestamp + "</timestamp>" + nl);\\n                File newKid = new File(dir, Integer.toString(number));\\n                move(kid, newKid);\\n [(3743, '\'Set<Future<?>> _cleanUpDisconnectComputers(final List<Throwable> errors) {\\n        LOGGER.log(Main.isUnitTest ? Level.FINE : Level.INFO, "Starting node disconnection");\\n        final Set<Future<?>> pending = new HashSet<>();\\n        // JENKINS-28840 we know we will be interrupting all the Computers so get the Queue lock once for all\\n        Queue.withLock(() -> {\\n            for (Computer c : computers.values()) {\\n                try {\\n                    c.interrupt();\\n                    killComputer(c);\\n                    pending.add(c.disconnect(null));\\n                } catch (OutOfMemoryError e) {\\n                    // we should just propagate this, no point trying to log\\n                    throw e;\\n                } catch (LinkageError e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, e, () -> "Could not disconnect " + c + ": " + e.getMessage());\\n                    // safe to ignore and continue for this one\\n                } catch (Throwable e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, e, () -> "Could not disconnect " + c + ": " + e.getMessage());\\n                    // save for later\\n                    errors.add(e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        });\\n        return pending;\\n    }\'')]

[(883, '\'void updateByXml(Source source) throws IOException {\\n        checkPermission(CONFIGURE);\\n        XmlFile configXmlFile = getConfigFile();\\n        final AtomicFileWriter out = new AtomicFileWriter(configXmlFile.getFile());\\n        try {\\n            try {\\n                XMLUtils.safeTransform(source, new StreamResult(out));\\n                out.close();\\n            } catch (TransformerException | SAXException e) {\\n                throw new IOException("Failed to persist config.xml", e);\\n            }\\n\\n            // try to reflect the changes by reloading\\n            Object o = new XmlFile(Items.XSTREAM, out.getTemporaryPath().toFile()).unmarshalNullingOut(this);\\n            if (o != this) {\\n                // ensure that we\\\'ve got the same job type. extending this code to support updating\\n                // to different job type requires destroying & creating a new job type\\n                throw new IOException("Expecting " + this.getClass() + " but got " + o.getClass() + " instead");\\n            }\\n\\n            Items.whileUpdatingByXml(new NotReallyRoleSensitiveCallable<Void, IOException>() {\\n                @Override public Void call() throws IOException {\\n                    onLoad(getParent(), getRootDir().getName());\\n                    return null;\\n                }\\n            });\\n            Jenkins.get().rebuildDependencyGraphAsync();\\n\\n            // if everything went well, commit this new version\\n            out.commit();\\n            SaveableListener.fireOnChange(this, getConfigFile());\\n\\n        } finally {\\n            out.abort(); // don\\\'t leave anything behind\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(72, '\'void onRenamed(Item item, String oldName, String newName) {\\n        // bug 5077308 - Display name field should be cleared when you rename a job.\\n        if (item instanceof AbstractItem) {\\n            AbstractItem abstractItem = (AbstractItem) item;\\n            if (oldName.equals(abstractItem.getDisplayName())) {\\n                // the user renamed the job, but the old project name which is shown as the\\n                // displayname if no displayname was set, has been set into the displayname field.\\n                // This means that the displayname was never set, so we want to set it\\n                // to null as it was before\\n                try {\\n                    LOGGER.info(String.format("onRenamed():Setting displayname to null for item.name=%s", item.getName()));\\n                    abstractItem.setDisplayName(null);\\n                }\\n                catch (IOException ioe) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, String.format("onRenamed():Exception while trying to clear the displayName for Item.name:%s",\\n                            item.getName()), ioe);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(77, '"void visit(final File f, final String _relativePath) throws IOException {\\n        int mode = IOUtils.mode(f);\\n\\n        // On Windows, the elements of relativePath are separated by\\n        // back-slashes (\\\\), but Zip files need to have their path elements separated\\n        // by forward-slashes (/)\\n        String relativePath = _relativePath.replace(\'\\\\\\\\\', \'/\');\\n\\n        BasicFileAttributes basicFileAttributes = Files.readAttributes(Util.fileToPath(f), BasicFileAttributes.class);\\n        if (basicFileAttributes.isDirectory()) {\\n            ZipEntry dirZipEntry = new ZipEntry(this.prefix + relativePath + \'/\');\\n            // Setting this bit explicitly is needed by some unzipping applications (see JENKINS-3294).\\n            dirZipEntry.setExternalAttributes(BITMASK_IS_DIRECTORY);\\n            if (mode != -1)   dirZipEntry.setUnixMode(mode);\\n            dirZipEntry.setTime(basicFileAttributes.lastModifiedTime().toMillis());\\n            zip.putNextEntry(dirZipEntry);\\n            zip.closeEntry();\\n        } else {\\n            ZipEntry fileZipEntry = new ZipEntry(this.prefix + relativePath);\\n            if (mode != -1)   fileZipEntry.setUnixMode(mode);\\n            fileZipEntry.setTime(basicFileAttributes.lastModifiedTime().toMillis());\\n            fileZipEntry.setSize(basicFileAttributes.size());\\n            zip.putNextEntry(fileZipEntry);\\n            try (InputStream in = FilePath.openInputStream(f, openOptions)) {\\n                int len;\\n                while ((len = in.read(buf)) >= 0)\\n                    zip.write(buf, 0, len);\\n            } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n                throw new IOException(e);\\n            }\\n            zip.closeEntry();\\n        }\\n        entriesWritten++;\\n    }"')]

[(191, '\'boolean keep(@NonNull Function function) {\\n\\n        if (function.getAnnotation(StaplerNotDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            // explicitly marked as an invalid getter\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (function.getAnnotation(StaplerDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            // explicitly marked as a valid getter\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        String signature = function.getSignature();\\n\\n        // check whitelist\\n        ExtensionList<RoutingDecisionProvider> decision = ExtensionList.lookup(RoutingDecisionProvider.class);\\n        if (decision.size() > 0) {\\n            for (RoutingDecisionProvider provider : decision) {\\n                RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision methodDecision = provider.decide(signature);\\n                if (methodDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.ACCEPTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Function {0} is acceptable because it is whitelisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n                if (methodDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.REJECTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Function {0} is not acceptable because it is blacklisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n\\n                Class<?> type = function.getReturnType();\\n                if (type != null) {\\n                    String typeSignature = "class " + type.getCanonicalName();\\n                    RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision returnTypeDecision = provider.decide(typeSignature);\\n                    if (returnTypeDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.ACCEPTED) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Function {0} is acceptable because its type is whitelisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                        return true;\\n                    }\\n                    if (returnTypeDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.REJECTED) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Function {0} is not acceptable because its type is blacklisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (PROHIBIT_STATIC_ACCESS && function.isStatic()) {\\n            // unless whitelisted or marked as routable, reject static methods\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (function.getName().equals("getDynamic")) {\\n            Class[] parameterTypes = function.getParameterTypes();\\n            if (parameterTypes.length > 0 && parameterTypes[0] == String.class) {\\n                // While this is more general than what Stapler can invoke on these types,\\n                // The above is the only criterion for Stapler to attempt dispatch.\\n                // Therefore prohibit this as a regular getter.\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (function.getName().equals("getStaplerFallback") && function.getParameterTypes().length == 0) {\\n            // A parameter-less #getStaplerFallback() implements special fallback behavior for the\\n            // StaplerFallback interface. We do not check for the presence of the interface on the current\\n            // class, or the return type, as that could change since the implementing component was last built.\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (function.getName().equals("getTarget") && function.getParameterTypes().length == 0) {\\n            // A parameter-less #getTarget() implements special redirection behavior for the\\n            // StaplerProxy interface. We do not check for the presence of the interface on the current\\n            // class, or the return type, as that could change since the implementing component was last built.\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        Class<?> returnType = function.getReturnType();\\n\\n        boolean isOk = isClassAcceptable(returnType);\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Function analyzed: {0} => {1}", new Object[]{signature, isOk});\\n        return isOk;\\n    }\'')]

[(89, "'void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse resp, FilterChain chain) throws IOException,\\n            ServletException {\\n        HttpServletResponse httpResp = (HttpServletResponse) resp;\\n\\n        Enumeration e = config.getInitParameterNames();\\n\\n        // for each configuration element...\\n        while (e.hasMoreElements()) {\\n            String headerName = (String) e.nextElement();\\n            String headerValue = config.getInitParameter(headerName);\\n            // set the header with the given name and value\\n            httpResp.setHeader(headerName, headerValue);\\n        }\\n        chain.doFilter(req, resp);\\n    }'")]

[(106, "'InstallState getNextInstallState(InstallState current) {\\n        List<Function<Provider<InstallState>, InstallState>> installStateFilterChain = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (InstallStateFilter setupExtension : InstallStateFilter.all()) {\\n            installStateFilterChain.add(next -> setupExtension.getNextInstallState(current, next));\\n        }\\n        // Terminal condition: getNextState() on the current install state\\n        installStateFilterChain.add(input -> {\\n            // Initially, install state is unknown and\\n            // needs to be determined\\n            if (current == null || InstallState.UNKNOWN.equals(current)) {\\n                return getDefaultInstallState();\\n            }\\n            Map<InstallState, InstallState> states = new HashMap<>();\\n            {\\n                states.put(InstallState.CONFIGURE_INSTANCE, InstallState.INITIAL_SETUP_COMPLETED);\\n                states.put(InstallState.CREATE_ADMIN_USER, InstallState.CONFIGURE_INSTANCE);\\n                states.put(InstallState.INITIAL_PLUGINS_INSTALLING, InstallState.CREATE_ADMIN_USER);\\n                states.put(InstallState.INITIAL_SECURITY_SETUP, InstallState.NEW);\\n                states.put(InstallState.RESTART, InstallState.RUNNING);\\n                states.put(InstallState.UPGRADE, InstallState.INITIAL_SETUP_COMPLETED);\\n                states.put(InstallState.DOWNGRADE, InstallState.INITIAL_SETUP_COMPLETED);\\n                states.put(InstallState.INITIAL_SETUP_COMPLETED, InstallState.RUNNING);\\n            }\\n            return states.get(current);\\n        });\\n\\n        ProviderChain<InstallState> chain = new ProviderChain<>(installStateFilterChain.iterator());\\n        return chain.get();\\n    }'")]

[(2357, '\'Icon tryGetIcon(String iconGuess) {\\n        // Jenkins Symbols don\\\'t have metadata so return null\\n        if (iconGuess == null || iconGuess.startsWith("symbol-")) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        Icon iconMetadata = IconSet.icons.getIconByClassSpec(iconGuess);\\n\\n        // `iconGuess` must be class names if it contains a whitespace.\\n        //  It may contains extra css classes unrelated to icons.\\n        // Filter classes with `icon-` prefix.\\n        if (iconMetadata == null && iconGuess.contains(" ")) {\\n            iconMetadata = IconSet.icons.getIconByClassSpec(filterIconNameClasses(iconGuess));\\n        }\\n\\n        if (iconMetadata == null) {\\n            // Icon could be provided as a simple iconFileName e.g. "help.svg"\\n            iconMetadata = IconSet.icons.getIconByClassSpec(IconSet.toNormalizedIconNameClass(iconGuess) + " icon-md");\\n        }\\n\\n        if (iconMetadata == null) {\\n            // Icon could be provided as an absolute iconFileName e.g. "/plugin/foo/abc.png"\\n            iconMetadata = IconSet.icons.getIconByUrl(iconGuess);\\n        }\\n\\n        return iconMetadata;\\n    }\'')]

[(277, '\'FormValidation doCheckNewName(@QueryParameter String newName) {\\n\\n        if (!isNameEditable()) {\\n            return FormValidation.error("Trying to rename an item that does not support this operation.");\\n        }\\n\\n        // TODO: Create an Item.RENAME permission to use here, see JENKINS-18649.\\n        if (!hasPermission(Item.CONFIGURE)) {\\n            if (parent instanceof AccessControlled) {\\n                ((AccessControlled) parent).checkPermission(Item.CREATE);\\n            }\\n            checkPermission(Item.DELETE);\\n        }\\n\\n        newName = newName == null ? null : newName.trim();\\n        try {\\n            Jenkins.checkGoodName(newName);\\n            assert newName != null; // Would have thrown Failure\\n            if (newName.equals(name)) {\\n                return FormValidation.warning(Messages.AbstractItem_NewNameUnchanged());\\n            }\\n            Jenkins.get().getProjectNamingStrategy().checkName(getParent().getFullName(), newName);\\n            checkIfNameIsUsed(newName);\\n            checkRename(newName);\\n        } catch (Failure e) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(e.getMessage());\\n        }\\n        return FormValidation.ok();\\n    }\'')]

[(159, '\'String fastTail(int numChars, Charset cs) throws IOException {\\n\\n        try (RandomAccessFile raf = new RandomAccessFile(file, "r")) {\\n            long len = raf.length();\\n            // err on the safe side and assume each char occupies 4 bytes\\n            // additional 1024 byte margin is to bring us back in sync in case we started reading from non-char boundary.\\n            long pos = Math.max(0, len - (numChars * 4 + 1024));\\n            raf.seek(pos);\\n\\n            byte[] tail = new byte[(int) (len - pos)];\\n            raf.readFully(tail);\\n\\n            String tails = cs.decode(java.nio.ByteBuffer.wrap(tail)).toString();\\n\\n            return tails.substring(Math.max(0, tails.length() - numChars));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(871, "'Launcher decorateByPrefix(final String... prefix) {\\n        final Launcher outer = this;\\n        return new Launcher(outer) {\\n            @Override\\n            public boolean isUnix() {\\n                return outer.isUnix();\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public Proc launch(ProcStarter starter) throws IOException {\\n                starter.commands.addAll(0, Arrays.asList(prefix));\\n                boolean[] masks = starter.masks;\\n                if (masks != null) {\\n                    starter.masks = prefix(masks);\\n                }\\n                return outer.launch(starter);\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public Channel launchChannel(String[] cmd, OutputStream out, FilePath workDir, Map<String, String> envVars) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n                return outer.launchChannel(prefix(cmd), out, workDir, envVars);\\n            }\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public void kill(Map<String, String> modelEnvVars) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n                outer.kill(modelEnvVars);\\n            }\\n\\n            private String[] prefix(@NonNull String[] args) {\\n                String[] newArgs = new String[args.length + prefix.length];\\n                System.arraycopy(prefix, 0, newArgs, 0, prefix.length);\\n                System.arraycopy(args, 0, newArgs, prefix.length, args.length);\\n                return newArgs;\\n            }\\n\\n            private boolean[] prefix(@NonNull boolean[] args) {\\n                boolean[] newArgs = new boolean[args.length + prefix.length];\\n                System.arraycopy(args, 0, newArgs, prefix.length, args.length);\\n                return newArgs;\\n            }\\n        };\\n    }'")]

[(200, "'void abort(Throwable cause) {\\n        if (cause == null)        throw new IllegalArgumentException();\\n        if (aborted != null)      return; // already aborted\\n        aborted = cause;\\n        startLatch.abort(cause);\\n        endLatch.abort(cause);\\n\\n        Thread c = Thread.currentThread();\\n        for (WorkUnit wu : workUnits) {\\n            Executor e = wu.getExecutor();\\n            if (e != null && e != c)\\n                e.interrupt();\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(123, '\'Manifest loadLinkedManifest(File archive) throws IOException {\\n            // resolve the .hpl file to the location of the manifest file\\n            try {\\n                // Locate the manifest\\n                String firstLine;\\n                try (InputStream manifestHeaderInput = Files.newInputStream(archive.toPath())) {\\n                    firstLine = IOUtils.readFirstLine(manifestHeaderInput, "UTF-8");\\n                } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n                    throw new IOException(e);\\n                }\\n                //noinspection StatementWithEmptyBody\\n                if (firstLine.startsWith("Manifest-Version:")) {\\n                    // this is the manifest already\\n                } else {\\n                    // indirection\\n                    archive = resolve(archive, firstLine);\\n                }\\n\\n                // Read the manifest\\n                try (InputStream manifestInput = Files.newInputStream(archive.toPath())) {\\n                    return new Manifest(manifestInput);\\n                } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n                    throw new IOException(e);\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                throw new IOException("Failed to load " + archive, e);\\n            }\\n    }\'')]

[(983, '\'boolean installIfNecessaryFrom(@NonNull URL archive, @NonNull TaskListener listener, @NonNull String message, int maxRedirects) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        try {\\n            FilePath timestamp = this.child(".timestamp");\\n            long lastModified = timestamp.lastModified();\\n            URLConnection con;\\n            try {\\n                con = ProxyConfiguration.open(archive);\\n                if (lastModified != 0) {\\n                    con.setIfModifiedSince(lastModified);\\n                }\\n                con.connect();\\n            } catch (IOException x) {\\n                if (this.exists()) {\\n                    // Cannot connect now, so assume whatever was last unpacked is still OK.\\n                    listener.getLogger().println("Skipping installation of " + archive + " to " + remote + ": " + x);\\n                    return false;\\n                } else {\\n                    throw x;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (con instanceof HttpURLConnection) {\\n                HttpURLConnection httpCon = (HttpURLConnection) con;\\n                int responseCode = httpCon.getResponseCode();\\n                if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_PERM\\n                        || responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_TEMP) {\\n                    // follows redirect\\n                    if (maxRedirects > 0) {\\n                        String location = httpCon.getHeaderField("Location");\\n                        listener.getLogger().println("Following redirect " + archive.toExternalForm() + " -> " + location);\\n                        return installIfNecessaryFrom(getUrlFactory().newURL(location), listener, message, maxRedirects - 1);\\n                    } else {\\n                        listener.getLogger().println("Skipping installation of " + archive + " to " + remote + " due to too many redirects.");\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                if (lastModified != 0) {\\n                    if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_NOT_MODIFIED) {\\n                        return false;\\n                    } else if (responseCode != HttpURLConnection.HTTP_OK) {\\n                        listener.getLogger().println("Skipping installation of " + archive + " to " + remote + " due to server error: " + responseCode + " " + httpCon.getResponseMessage());\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            long sourceTimestamp = con.getLastModified();\\n\\n            if (this.exists()) {\\n                if (lastModified != 0 && sourceTimestamp == lastModified)\\n                    return false;   // already up to date\\n                this.deleteContents();\\n            } else {\\n                this.mkdirs();\\n            }\\n\\n            listener.getLogger().println(message);\\n\\n            if (isRemote()) {\\n                // First try to download from the agent machine.\\n                try {\\n                    act(new Unpack(archive));\\n                    timestamp.touch(sourceTimestamp);\\n                    return true;\\n                } catch (IOException x) {\\n                    Functions.printStackTrace(x, listener.error("Failed to download " + archive + " from agent; will retry from controller"));\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            // for HTTP downloads, enable automatic retry for added resilience\\n            InputStream in = archive.getProtocol().startsWith("http") ? ProxyConfiguration.getInputStream(archive) : con.getInputStream();\\n            CountingInputStream cis = new CountingInputStream(in);\\n            try {\\n                if (archive.toExternalForm().endsWith(".zip"))\\n                    unzipFrom(cis);\\n                else\\n                    untarFrom(cis, TarCompression.GZIP);\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                throw new IOException(String.format("Failed to unpack %s (%d bytes read of total %d)",\\n                        archive, cis.getByteCount(), con.getContentLength()), e);\\n            }\\n            timestamp.touch(sourceTimestamp);\\n            return true;\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to install " + archive + " to " + remote, e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(266, '\'TopLevelItem createProjectFromXML(String name, InputStream xml) throws IOException {\\n        acl.checkPermission(Item.CREATE);\\n\\n        Jenkins.get().getProjectNamingStrategy().checkName(parent.getFullName(), name);\\n        Items.verifyItemDoesNotAlreadyExist(parent, name, null);\\n        Jenkins.checkGoodName(name);\\n\\n        // place it as config.xml\\n        File configXml = Items.getConfigFile(getRootDirFor(name)).getFile();\\n        final File dir = configXml.getParentFile();\\n        boolean success = false;\\n        try {\\n            Util.createDirectories(dir.toPath());\\n            XMLUtils.safeTransform(new StreamSource(xml), new StreamResult(configXml));\\n\\n            // load it\\n            TopLevelItem result = Items.whileUpdatingByXml(new NotReallyRoleSensitiveCallable<TopLevelItem, IOException>() {\\n                @Override public TopLevelItem call() throws IOException {\\n                    return (TopLevelItem) Items.load(parent, dir);\\n                }\\n            });\\n\\n            success = acl.getACL().hasCreatePermission2(Jenkins.getAuthentication2(), parent, result.getDescriptor())\\n                && result.getDescriptor().isApplicableIn(parent);\\n\\n            add(result);\\n\\n            ItemListener.fireOnCreated(result);\\n            Jenkins.get().rebuildDependencyGraphAsync();\\n\\n            return result;\\n        } catch (TransformerException | SAXException e) {\\n            success = false;\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to persist config.xml", e);\\n        } catch (IOException | RuntimeException e) {\\n            success = false;\\n            throw e;\\n        } finally {\\n            if (!success) {\\n                // if anything fails, delete the config file to avoid further confusion\\n                Util.deleteRecursive(dir);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(315, '\'String normalize(@NonNull String path) {\\n        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n        // Check for prefix designating absolute path\\n        Matcher m = ABSOLUTE_PREFIX_PATTERN.matcher(path);\\n        if (m.find()) {\\n            buf.append(m.group(1));\\n            path = path.substring(m.end());\\n        }\\n        boolean isAbsolute = buf.length() > 0;\\n        // Split remaining path into tokens, trimming any duplicate or trailing separators\\n        List<String> tokens = new ArrayList<>();\\n        int s = 0, end = path.length();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < end; i++) {\\n            char c = path.charAt(i);\\n            if (c == \\\'/\\\' || c == \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\') {\\n                tokens.add(path.substring(s, i));\\n                s = i;\\n                // Skip any extra separator chars\\n                //noinspection StatementWithEmptyBody\\n                while (++i < end && ((c = path.charAt(i)) == \\\'/\\\' || c == \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\'))\\n                    ;\\n                // Add token for separator unless we reached the end\\n                if (i < end) tokens.add(path.substring(s, s + 1));\\n                s = i;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (s < end) tokens.add(path.substring(s));\\n        // Look through tokens for "." or ".."\\n        for (int i = 0; i < tokens.size();) {\\n            String token = tokens.get(i);\\n            if (token.equals(".")) {\\n                tokens.remove(i);\\n                if (tokens.size() > 0)\\n                    tokens.remove(i > 0 ? i - 1 : i);\\n            } else if (token.equals("..")) {\\n                if (i == 0) {\\n                    // If absolute path, just remove: /../something\\n                    // If relative path, not collapsible so leave as-is\\n                    tokens.remove(0);\\n                    if (tokens.size() > 0) token += tokens.remove(0);\\n                    if (!isAbsolute) buf.append(token);\\n                } else {\\n                    // Normalize: remove something/.. plus separator before/after\\n                    i -= 2;\\n                    for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) tokens.remove(i);\\n                    if (i > 0) tokens.remove(i - 1);\\n                    else if (tokens.size() > 0) tokens.remove(0);\\n                }\\n            } else\\n                i += 2;\\n        }\\n        // Recombine tokens\\n        for (String token : tokens) buf.append(token);\\n        if (buf.length() == 0) buf.append(\\\'.\\\');\\n        return buf.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(58, '\'void execute(TaskListener listener) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        if (!enabled)   return;\\n\\n        long now = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n        for (Computer c : Jenkins.get().getComputers()) {\\n            VirtualChannel ch = c.getChannel();\\n            if (ch instanceof Channel) {\\n                Channel channel = (Channel) ch;\\n                if (now - channel.getLastHeard() > TIME_TILL_PING) {\\n                    // haven\\\'t heard from this agent for a while.\\n                    Long lastPing = (Long) channel.getProperty(ConnectionActivityMonitor.class);\\n\\n                    if (lastPing != null && now - lastPing > TIMEOUT) {\\n                        LOGGER.info("Repeated ping attempts failed on " + c.getName() + ". Disconnecting");\\n                        c.disconnect(OfflineCause.create(Messages._ConnectionActivityMonitor_OfflineCause()));\\n                    } else {\\n                        // send a ping. if we receive a reply, it will be reflected in the next getLastHeard() call.\\n                        channel.callAsync(PING_COMMAND);\\n                        if (lastPing == null)\\n                            channel.setProperty(ConnectionActivityMonitor.class, now);\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    // we are receiving data nicely\\n                    channel.setProperty(ConnectionActivityMonitor.class, null);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(386, '\'boolean isRelativePath(String path) {\\n        if (path.startsWith("/"))\\n            return false;\\n        if (path.startsWith("\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") && path.length() > 3 && path.indexOf(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', 3) != -1)\\n            return false; // a UNC path which is the most absolute you can get on windows\\n        if (path.length() >= 3 && \\\':\\\' == path.charAt(1)) {\\n            // never mind that the drive mappings can be changed between sessions, we just want to\\n            // know if the 3rd character is a `\\\\` (or a \\\'/\\\' is acceptable too)\\n            char p = path.charAt(0);\\n            if ((\\\'A\\\' <= p && p <= \\\'Z\\\') || (\\\'a\\\' <= p && p <= \\\'z\\\')) {\\n                return path.charAt(2) != \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\' && path.charAt(2) != \\\'/\\\';\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(44, "'void visit(N p) throws CycleDetectedException {\\n        if (!visited.add(p))    return;\\n\\n        visiting.add(p);\\n        path.push(p);\\n        for (N q : getEdges(p)) {\\n            if (q == null)        continue;   // ignore unresolved references\\n            if (visiting.contains(q))\\n                detectedCycle(q);\\n            visit(q);\\n        }\\n        visiting.remove(p);\\n        path.pop();\\n        topologicalOrder.add(p);\\n    }'")]
