[(51, '"void write(byte[] b, int off, int len) throws IOException {\\n        final int start = off;\\n        final int end = off + len;\\n        for (int i = off; i < end; ) {\\n            if (MBYTES[match] == b[i]) { // another byte matched. Good. Keep going...\\n                match++;\\n                i++;\\n                if (match == MBYTES.length) {\\n                    base.write(b, off, i - off - MBYTES.length);    // flush the portion up to MARK\\n                    // don\'t send MARK to the output, but instead notify the callback\\n                    onMarkFound();\\n                    match = 0;\\n                    off = i;\\n                    len = end - i;\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                if (match > 0) {\\n                    // only matched partially.\\n                    // if a part of the partial match spans into the previous write, we need to fake that write.\\n                    int extra = match - (i - start);\\n                    if (extra > 0) {\\n                        base.write(MBYTES, 0, extra);\\n                    }\\n                    match = 0;\\n\\n                    // this b[i] might be a fast byte in MARK, so we\'ll retry\\n                } else {\\n                    // irrelevant byte.\\n                    i++;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n        }\\n\\n        // if we are partially matching, can\'t send that portion yet.\\n        if (len - match > 0)\\n            base.write(b, off, len - match);\\n    }"')]

[(2116, '\'List<String> getLog(int maxLines) throws IOException {\\n        if (maxLines == 0) {\\n            return Collections.emptyList();\\n        }\\n\\n        int lines = 0;\\n        long filePointer;\\n        final List<String> lastLines = new ArrayList<>(Math.min(maxLines, 128));\\n        final List<Byte> bytes = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        try (RandomAccessFile fileHandler = new RandomAccessFile(getLogFile(), "r")) {\\n            long fileLength = fileHandler.length() - 1;\\n\\n            for (filePointer = fileLength; filePointer != -1 && maxLines != lines; filePointer--) {\\n                fileHandler.seek(filePointer);\\n                byte readByte = fileHandler.readByte();\\n\\n                if (readByte == 0x0A) {\\n                    if (filePointer < fileLength) {\\n                        lines = lines + 1;\\n                        lastLines.add(convertBytesToString(bytes));\\n                        bytes.clear();\\n                    }\\n                } else if (readByte != 0xD) {\\n                    bytes.add(readByte);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (lines != maxLines) {\\n            lastLines.add(convertBytesToString(bytes));\\n        }\\n\\n        Collections.reverse(lastLines);\\n\\n        // If the log has been truncated, include that information.\\n        // Use set (replaces the first element) rather than add so that\\n        // the list doesn\\\'t grow beyond the specified maximum number of lines.\\n        if (lines == maxLines) {\\n            lastLines.set(0, "[...truncated " + Functions.humanReadableByteSize(filePointer) + "...]");\\n        }\\n\\n        return ConsoleNote.removeNotes(lastLines);\\n    }\'')]

[(650, '\'Set<String> loadPluginsFromWar(@NonNull String fromPath, @CheckForNull FilenameFilter filter) {\\n        Set<String> names = new HashSet<>();\\n\\n        ServletContext context = Jenkins.get().servletContext;\\n        Set<String> plugins = Util.fixNull(context.getResourcePaths(fromPath));\\n        Set<URL> copiedPlugins = new HashSet<>();\\n        Set<URL> dependencies = new HashSet<>();\\n\\n        for (String pluginPath : plugins) {\\n            String fileName = pluginPath.substring(pluginPath.lastIndexOf(\\\'/\\\') + 1);\\n            if (fileName.isEmpty()) {\\n                // see http://www.nabble.com/404-Not-Found-error-when-clicking-on-help-td24508544.html\\n                // I suspect some containers are returning directory names.\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            try {\\n                URL url = context.getResource(pluginPath);\\n                if (filter != null && url != null) {\\n                    if (!filter.accept(new File(url.getFile()).getParentFile(), fileName)) {\\n                        continue;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                names.add(fileName);\\n                copyBundledPlugin(Objects.requireNonNull(url), fileName);\\n                copiedPlugins.add(url);\\n                try {\\n                    addDependencies(url, fromPath, dependencies);\\n                } catch (Exception e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, "Failed to resolve dependencies for the bundled plugin " + fileName, e);\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, "Failed to extract the bundled plugin " + fileName, e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Copy dependencies. These are not detached plugins, but are required by them.\\n        for (URL dependency : dependencies) {\\n            if (copiedPlugins.contains(dependency)) {\\n                // Ignore. Already copied.\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n\\n            String fileName = new File(dependency.getFile()).getName();\\n            try {\\n                names.add(fileName);\\n                copyBundledPlugin(dependency, fileName);\\n                copiedPlugins.add(dependency);\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.SEVERE, "Failed to extract the bundled dependency plugin " + fileName, e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return names;\\n    }\'')]

[(1203, '\'int addArtifacts(@NonNull VirtualFile dir,\\n            @NonNull String path, @NonNull String pathHref,\\n            @NonNull SerializableArtifactList r, @CheckForNull SerializableArtifact parent, int upTo) throws IOException {\\n        VirtualFile[] kids = dir.list();\\n        Arrays.sort(kids);\\n\\n        int n = 0;\\n        for (VirtualFile sub : kids) {\\n            String child = sub.getName();\\n            String childPath = path + child;\\n            String childHref = pathHref + Util.rawEncode(child);\\n            String length = sub.isFile() ? String.valueOf(sub.length()) : "";\\n            boolean collapsed = kids.length == 1 && parent != null;\\n            SerializableArtifact a;\\n            if (collapsed) {\\n                // Collapse single items into parent node where possible:\\n                a = new SerializableArtifact(parent.name + \\\'/\\\' + child, childPath,\\n                                 sub.isDirectory() ? null : childHref, length,\\n                                 parent.treeNodeId);\\n                r.tree.put(a, r.tree.remove(parent));\\n            } else {\\n                // Use null href for a directory:\\n                a = new SerializableArtifact(child, childPath,\\n                                 sub.isDirectory() ? null : childHref, length,\\n                                 "n" + ++r.idSeq);\\n                r.tree.put(a, parent != null ? parent.treeNodeId : null);\\n            }\\n            if (sub.isDirectory()) {\\n                n += addArtifacts(sub, childPath + \\\'/\\\', childHref + \\\'/\\\', r, a, upTo - n);\\n                if (n >= upTo) break;\\n            } else {\\n                // Don\\\'t store collapsed path in ArrayList (for correct data in external API)\\n                r.add(collapsed ? new SerializableArtifact(child, a.relativePath, a.href, length, a.treeNodeId) : a);\\n                if (++n >= upTo) break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return n;\\n    }\'')]

[(96, '\'Fingerprint load(@NonNull File file) throws IOException {\\n        XmlFile configFile = getConfigFile(file);\\n        if (!configFile.exists()) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            Object loaded = configFile.read();\\n            if (!(loaded instanceof Fingerprint)) {\\n                throw new IOException("Unexpected Fingerprint type. Expected " + Fingerprint.class + " or subclass but got "\\n                        + (loaded != null ? loaded.getClass() : "null"));\\n            }\\n            Fingerprint f = (Fingerprint) loaded;\\n            if (f.getPersistedFacets() == null) {\\n                logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Malformed fingerprint {0}: Missing facets", configFile);\\n                Files.deleteIfExists(Util.fileToPath(file));\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            return f;\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            if (Files.exists(Util.fileToPath(file)) && Files.size(Util.fileToPath(file)) == 0) {\\n                // Despite the use of AtomicFile, there are reports indicating that people often see\\n                // empty XML file, presumably either due to file system corruption (perhaps by sudden\\n                // power loss, etc.) or abnormal program termination.\\n                // generally we don\\\'t want to wipe out user data just because we can\\\'t load it,\\n                // but if the file size is 0, which is what\\\'s reported in JENKINS-2012, then it seems\\n                // like recovering it silently by deleting the file is not a bad idea.\\n                logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Size zero fingerprint. Disk corruption? {0}", configFile);\\n                Files.delete(Util.fileToPath(file));\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            String parseError = messageOfParseException(e);\\n            if (parseError != null) {\\n                logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Malformed XML in {0}: {1}", new Object[] {configFile, parseError});\\n                Files.deleteIfExists(Util.fileToPath(file));\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Failed to load " + configFile, e);\\n            throw e;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(95, "'String getToolHome(Node node, ToolInstallation installation, TaskListener log) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        String result = null;\\n\\n        // node-specific configuration takes precedence\\n        ToolLocationNodeProperty property = node.getNodeProperties().get(ToolLocationNodeProperty.class);\\n        if (property != null) {\\n            result = property.getHome(installation);\\n        }\\n        if (result != null) {\\n            return result;\\n        }\\n\\n        // consult translators\\n        for (ToolLocationTranslator t : ToolLocationTranslator.all()) {\\n            result = t.getToolHome(node, installation, log);\\n            if (result != null) {\\n                return result;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // fall back is no-op\\n        return installation.getHome();\\n    }'")]

[(341, "'int findPreamble(byte[] buf, int start, int len) {\\n        int e = start + len - PREAMBLE.length + 1;\\n\\n        OUTER:\\n        for (int i = start; i < e; i++) {\\n            if (buf[i] == PREAMBLE[0]) {\\n                // check for the rest of the match\\n                for (int j = 1; j < PREAMBLE.length; j++) {\\n                    if (buf[i + j] != PREAMBLE[j])\\n                        continue OUTER;\\n                }\\n                return i; // found it\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return -1; // not found\\n    }'")]

[(101, '\'List> discover(@NonNull final Jenkins jenkins) {\\n LOGGER.fine("Listing up @CLIMethod");\\n List> r = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n try {\\n for (final Method m : Util.filter(Index.list(CLIMethod.class, jenkins.getPluginManager().uberClassLoader), Method.class)) {\\n try {\\n // command name\\n final String name = m.getAnnotation(CLIMethod.class).name();\\n\\n final ResourceBundleHolder res = loadMessageBundle(m);\\n res.format("CLI." + name + ".shortDescription"); // make sure we have the resource, to fail early\\n\\n r.add(new ExtensionComponent<>(new CloneableCLICommand() {\\n @Override\\n public String getName() {\\n return name;\\n }\\n\\n @Override\\n public String getShortDescription() {\\n // format by using the right locale\\n return res.format("CLI." + name + ".shortDescription");\\n }\\n\\n @Override\\n protected CmdLineParser getCmdLineParser() {\\n return bindMethod(new ArrayList<>());\\n }\\n\\n private CmdLineParser bindMethod(List binders) {\\n\\n registerOptionHandlers();\\n CmdLineParser parser = new CmdLineParser(null);\\n\\n // build up the call sequence\\n Stack chains = new Stack<>();\\n Method method = m;\\n while (true) {\\n chains.push(method);\\n if (Modifier.isStatic(method.getModifiers()))\\n break; // the chain is complete.\\n\\n // the method in question is an instance method, so we need to resolve the instance by using another resolver\\n Class type = method.getDeclaringClass();\\n try {\\n method = findResolver(type);\\n } catch (IOException ex) {\\n throw new RuntimeException("Unable to find the resolver method annotated with @CLIResolver for " + type, ex);\\n }\\n if (method == null) {\\n throw new RuntimeException("Unable to find the resolver method annotated with @CLIResolver for " + type);\\n }\\n }\\n\\n while (!chains.isEmpty())\\n binders.add(new MethodBinder(chains.pop(), this, parser));\\n\\n return parser;\\n }\\n\\n /**\\n * Envelope an annotated CLI command\\n *\\n * @param args\\n * Arguments to the sub command. For example, if the CLI is invoked like "java -jar cli.jar foo bar zot",\\n * then "foo" is the sub-command and the argument list is ["bar","zot"].\\n * @param locale\\n * Locale of the client (which can be different from that of the server.) Good behaving command implementation\\n * would use this locale for formatting messages.\\n * @param stdin\\n * Connected to the stdin of the CLI client.\\n * @param stdout\\n * Connected to the stdout of the CLI client.\\n * @param stderr\\n * Connected to the stderr of the CLI client.\\n * @return\\n * Exit code from the CLI command execution\\n *\\n *

\\n * Jenkins standard exit codes from CLI:\\n * 0 means everything went well.\\n * 1 means further unspecified exception is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 2 means CmdLineException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 3 means IllegalArgumentException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 4 mean IllegalStateException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 5 means AbortException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 6 means AccessDeniedException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 7 means BadCredentialsException is thrown while performing the command.\\n * 8-15 are reserved for future usage\\n * 16+ mean a custom CLI exit error code (meaning defined by the CLI command itself)\\n *\\n *

\\n * Note: For details - see JENKINS-32273\\n */\\n @Override\\n public int main(List args, Locale locale, InputStream stdin, PrintStream stdout, PrintStream stderr) {\\n this.stdout = stdout;\\n this.stderr = stderr;\\n this.locale = locale;\\n\\n List binders = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n CmdLineParser parser = bindMethod(binders);\\n try {\\n // TODO this could probably use ACL.as; why is it calling SecurityContext.setAuthentication rather than SecurityContextHolder.setContext?\\n SecurityContext sc = SecurityContextHolder.getContext();\\n Authentication old = sc.getAuthentication();\\n try {\\n // fill up all the binders\\n parser.parseArgument(args);\\n\\n Authentication auth = getTransportAuthentication2();\\n sc.setAuthentication(auth); // run the CLI with the right credential\\n jenkins.checkPermission(Jenkins.READ);\\n\\n // resolve them\\n Object instance = null;\\n for (MethodBinder binder : binders)\\n instance = binder.call(instance);\\n\\n if (instance instanceof Integer)\\n return (Integer) instance;\\n else\\n return 0;\\n } catch (InvocationTargetException e) {\\n Throwable t = e.getTargetException();\\n if (t instanceof Exception)\\n throw (Exception) t;\\n throw e;\\n } finally {\\n sc.setAuthentication(old); // restore\\n }\\n } catch (CmdLineException e) {\\n printError(e.getMessage());\\n printUsage(stderr, parser);\\n return 2;\\n } catch (IllegalStateException e) {\\n printError(e.getMessage());\\n return 4;\\n } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n printError(e.getMessage());\\n return 3;\\n } catch (AbortException e) {\\n printError(e.getMessage());\\n return 5;\\n } catch (AccessDeniedException e) {\\n printError(e.getMessage());\\n return 6;\\n } catch (BadCredentialsException e) {\\n // to the caller, we can\\\'t reveal whether the user didn\\\'t exist or the password didn\\\'t match.\\n // do that to the server log instead\\n String id = UUID.randomUUID().toString();\\n logAndPrintError(e, "Bad Credentials. Search the server log for " + id + " for more details.",\\n "CLI login attempt failed: " + id, Level.INFO);\\n return 7;\\n } catch (Throwable e) {\\n final String errorMsg = "Unexpected exception occurred while performing " + getName() + " command.";\\n logAndPrintError(e, errorMsg, errorMsg, Level.WARNING);\\n Functions.printStackTrace(e, stderr);\\n return 1;\\n }\\n }\\n\\n private void printError(String errorMessage) {\\n this.stderr.println();\\n this.stderr.println("ERROR: " + errorMessage);\\n }\\n\\n private void logAndPrintError(Throwable e, String errorMessage, String logMessage, Level logLevel) {\\n LOGGER.log(logLevel, logMessage, e);\\n printError(errorMessage);\\n }\\n\\n @Override\\n protected int run() throws Exception {\\n throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\\n }\\n }));\\n } catch (ClassNotFoundException | MissingResourceException e) {\\n LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to process @CLIMethod: " + m, e);\\n }\\n }\\n } catch (IOException e) {\\n LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to discover @CLIMethod", e);\\n }\\n\\n return r;\\n }\'')]

[(389, '\'void sendOneZipEntry(ZipOutputStream zos, VirtualFile vf, String relativePath, String prefix, OpenOption... openOptions) throws IOException {\\n        // In ZIP archives "All slashes MUST be forward slashes" (http://pkware.com/documents/casestudies/APPNOTE.TXT)\\n        // TODO On Linux file names can contain backslashes which should not treated as file separators.\\n        //      Unfortunately, only the file separator char of the master is known (File.separatorChar)\\n        //      but not the file separator char of the (maybe remote) "dir".\\n        String onlyForwardRelativePath = relativePath.replace(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', \\\'/\\\');\\n        String zipEntryName = prefix + onlyForwardRelativePath;\\n        ZipEntry e = new ZipEntry(zipEntryName);\\n\\n        e.setTime(vf.lastModified());\\n        zos.putNextEntry(e);\\n        try (InputStream in = vf.open(openOptions)) {\\n            // hudson.util.IOUtils is already present\\n            org.apache.commons.io.IOUtils.copy(in, zos);\\n        }\\n        finally {\\n            zos.closeEntry();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(57, '\'Set<String> retrieveRedactedKeys(JSONObject jsonObject) {\\n        Set<String> redactedKeySet = new HashSet<>();\\n        if (jsonObject.has(REDACT_KEY)) {\\n            Object value = jsonObject.get(REDACT_KEY);\\n            if (value instanceof JSONArray) {\\n                for (Object o : jsonObject.getJSONArray(REDACT_KEY)) {\\n                    if (o instanceof String) {\\n                        redactedKeySet.add((String) o);\\n                    } else {\\n                        // array, object, null, number, boolean\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Unsupported type " + o.getClass().getName() + " for " + REDACT_KEY + ", please use either a single String value or an Array");\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            } else if (value instanceof String) {\\n                redactedKeySet.add((String) value);\\n            } else {\\n                // object, null, number, boolean\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Unsupported type " + value.getClass().getName() + " for " + REDACT_KEY + ", please use either a single String value or an Array");\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return redactedKeySet;\\n    }\'')]

[(103, '"Long fit(long start, long duration, int n) {\\n        OUTER:\\n        while (true) {\\n            long t = start;\\n            // check if \'start\' satisfies the two conditions by moving t across [start,start+duration)\\n            while (t - start < duration) {\\n                if (at(t) > n) {\\n                    // value too big. what\'s the next t that\'s worth trying?\\n                    Long nxt = next(t);\\n                    if (nxt == null)  return null;\\n                    start = nxt;\\n                    continue OUTER;\\n                } else {\\n                    Long nxt = next(t);\\n                    if (nxt == null) t = Long.MAX_VALUE;\\n                    else           t = nxt;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            // q(t) looks good at the entire [start,start+duration)\\n            return start;\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(1731, '\'void doPrintStackTrace(@NonNull StringBuilder s, @NonNull Throwable t, @CheckForNull Throwable higher, @NonNull String prefix, @NonNull Set<Throwable> encountered) {\\n        if (!encountered.add(t)) {\\n            s.append("<cycle to ").append(t).append(">\\\\n");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        if (Util.isOverridden(Throwable.class, t.getClass(), "printStackTrace", PrintWriter.class)) {\\n            StringWriter sw = new StringWriter();\\n            t.printStackTrace(new PrintWriter(sw));\\n            s.append(sw);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        Throwable lower = t.getCause();\\n        if (lower != null) {\\n            doPrintStackTrace(s, lower, t, prefix, encountered);\\n        }\\n        for (Throwable suppressed : t.getSuppressed()) {\\n            s.append(prefix).append("Also:   ");\\n            doPrintStackTrace(s, suppressed, t, prefix + "\\\\t", encountered);\\n        }\\n        if (lower != null) {\\n            s.append(prefix).append("Caused: ");\\n        }\\n        String summary = t.toString();\\n        if (lower != null) {\\n            String suffix = ": " + lower;\\n            if (summary.endsWith(suffix)) {\\n                summary = summary.substring(0, summary.length() - suffix.length());\\n            }\\n        }\\n        s.append(summary).append(System.lineSeparator());\\n        StackTraceElement[] trace = t.getStackTrace();\\n        int end = trace.length;\\n        if (higher != null) {\\n            StackTraceElement[] higherTrace = higher.getStackTrace();\\n            while (end > 0) {\\n                int higherEnd = end + higherTrace.length - trace.length;\\n                if (higherEnd <= 0 || !higherTrace[higherEnd - 1].equals(trace[end - 1])) {\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                end--;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        for (int i = 0; i < end; i++) {\\n            s.append(prefix).append("\\\\tat ").append(trace[i]).append(System.lineSeparator());\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(216, "'List<TopLevelItem> getItems(boolean recurse) {\\n        SortedSet<String> names;\\n        List<TopLevelItem> items = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        synchronized (this) {\\n            names = new TreeSet<>(jobNames);\\n        }\\n\\n        ItemGroup<? extends TopLevelItem> parent = getOwner().getItemGroup();\\n\\n        if (recurse) {\\n            if (!names.isEmpty() || includePattern != null) {\\n                items.addAll(parent.getAllItems(TopLevelItem.class, item -> {\\n                    String itemName = item.getRelativeNameFrom(parent);\\n                    if (names.contains(itemName)) {\\n                        return true;\\n                    }\\n                    if (includePattern != null) {\\n                        return includePattern.matcher(itemName).matches();\\n                    }\\n                    return false;\\n                }));\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            for (String name : names) {\\n                try {\\n                    TopLevelItem i = parent.getItem(name);\\n                    if (i != null) {\\n                        items.add(i);\\n                    }\\n                } catch (AccessDeniedException e) {\\n                    //Ignore\\n                }\\n            }\\n            if (includePattern != null) {\\n                items.addAll(parent.getItems(item -> {\\n                    String itemName = item.getRelativeNameFrom(parent);\\n                    return includePattern.matcher(itemName).matches();\\n                }));\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        Collection<ViewJobFilter> jobFilters = getJobFilters();\\n        if (!jobFilters.isEmpty()) {\\n            List<TopLevelItem> candidates = recurse ? parent.getAllItems(TopLevelItem.class) : new ArrayList<>(parent.getItems());\\n            // check the filters\\n            for (ViewJobFilter jobFilter : jobFilters) {\\n                items = jobFilter.filter(items, candidates, this);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        // for sanity, trim off duplicates\\n        items = new ArrayList<>(new LinkedHashSet<>(items));\\n\\n        return items;\\n    }'")]

[(420, '\'File whoAmI(File directory) {\\n        // JNLP returns the URL where the jar was originally placed (like http://jenkins-ci.org/...)\\n        // not the local cached file. So we need a rather round about approach to get to\\n        // the local file name.\\n        // There is no portable way to find where the locally cached copy\\n        // of jenkins.war/jar is; JDK 6 is too smart. (See JENKINS-2326.)\\n        try {\\n            URL classFile = Main.class.getClassLoader().getResource("executable/Main.class");\\n            JarFile jf = ((JarURLConnection) classFile.openConnection()).getJarFile();\\n            return new File(jf.getName());\\n        } catch (Exception x) {\\n            System.err.println("ZipFile.name trick did not work, using fallback: " + x);\\n        }\\n        File myself;\\n        try {\\n            myself = File.createTempFile("jenkins", ".jar", directory);\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new UncheckedIOException(e);\\n        }\\n        myself.deleteOnExit();\\n        try (InputStream is = Main.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation().openStream();\\n             OutputStream os = new FileOutputStream(myself)) {\\n            copyStream(is, os);\\n        } catch (IOException e) {\\n            throw new UncheckedIOException(e);\\n        }\\n        return myself;\\n    }\'')]

[(112, "'List<Class<?>> calcExceptionHierarchy(Throwable t) {\\n        List<Class<?>> hierarchy = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (; t != null; t = t.getCause()) {\\n            hierarchy.add(t.getClass());\\n            // with a composite exception, we might be hiding some other causes\\n            if (t instanceof CompositeIOException) {\\n                CompositeIOException e = (CompositeIOException) t;\\n                e.getExceptions().forEach(ex -> hierarchy.addAll(calcExceptionHierarchy(ex)));\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return hierarchy;\\n    }'")]

SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(new ContainerAuthentication(req));\\n            }\\n            try {\\n                chain.doFilter(request, response);\\n            } finally {\\n                SecurityContextHolder.clearContext();\\n            }\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        // authenticate the user\\n        String username = null;\\n        String password = null;\\n        String uidpassword = Scrambler.descramble(authorization.substring(6));\\n        int idx = uidpassword.indexOf(\\\':\\\');\\n        if (idx >= 0) {\\n            username = uidpassword.substring(0, idx);\\n            password = uidpassword.substring(idx + 1);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (username == null) {\\n            rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_UNAUTHORIZED);\\n            rsp.setHeader("WWW-Authenticate", "Basic realm=\\\\"Jenkins user\\\\"");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        {\\n            User u = BasicApiTokenHelper.isConnectingUsingApiToken(username, password);\\n            if (u != null) {\\n                UserDetails userDetails = u.getUserDetailsForImpersonation2();\\n [(482, '\'boolean filterQueueItemTest(Queue.Item item, Collection<TopLevelItem> viewItems) {\\n        // Check if the task of parent tasks are in the list of viewItems.\\n        // Pipeline jobs and other jobs which allow parts require us to\\n        // check owner tasks as well.\\n        Queue.Task currentTask = item.task;\\n        for (int count = 1;; count++) {\\n            if (viewItems.contains(currentTask)) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n            Queue.Task next = currentTask.getOwnerTask();\\n            if (next == currentTask) {\\n                break;\\n            } else {\\n                currentTask = next;\\n            }\\n            if (count == FILTER_LOOP_MAX_COUNT) {\\n                LOGGER.warning(String.format(\\n                        "Failed to find root task for queue item \\\'%s\\\' for " +\\n                        "view \\\'%s\\\' in under %d iterations, aborting!",\\n                        item.getDisplayName(), getDisplayName(),\\n                        FILTER_LOOP_MAX_COUNT));\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        // Check root project for sub-job projects (e.g. matrix jobs).\\n        if (item.task instanceof AbstractProject<?, ?>) {\\n            AbstractProject<?, ?> project = (AbstractProject<?, ?>) item.task;\\n            return viewItems.contains(project.getRootProject());\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\'')]

[(2804, '"int copyRecursiveTo(final DirScanner scanner, final FilePath target, final String description, @NonNull TarCompression compression) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        if (this.channel == target.channel) {\\n            // local to local copy.\\n            return act(new CopyRecursiveLocal(target, scanner));\\n        } else\\n        if (this.channel == null) {\\n            // local -> remote copy\\n            final Pipe pipe = Pipe.createLocalToRemote();\\n\\n            Future<Void> future = target.actAsync(new ReadFromTar(target, pipe, description, compression));\\n            Future<Integer> future2 = actAsync(new WriteToTar(scanner, pipe, compression));\\n            try {\\n                // JENKINS-9540 in case the reading side failed, report that error first\\n                future.get();\\n                return future2.get();\\n            } catch (ExecutionException e) {\\n                throw ioWithCause(e);\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            // remote -> local copy\\n            final Pipe pipe = Pipe.createRemoteToLocal();\\n\\n            Future<Integer> future = actAsync(new CopyRecursiveRemoteToLocal(pipe, scanner, compression));\\n            try {\\n                readFromTar(remote + \'/\' + description, new File(target.remote), compression.extract(pipe.getIn()));\\n            } catch (IOException e) { // BuildException or IOException\\n                try {\\n                    future.get(3, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n                    throw e;    // the remote side completed successfully, so the error must be local\\n                } catch (ExecutionException x) {\\n                    // report both errors\\n                    e.addSuppressed(x);\\n                    throw e;\\n                } catch (TimeoutException ignored) {\\n                    // remote is hanging, just throw the original exception\\n                    throw e;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            try {\\n                return future.get();\\n            } catch (ExecutionException e) {\\n                throw ioWithCause(e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(161, '\'Computer createNewComputerForNode(Node n, boolean automaticAgentLaunch) {\\n        Computer c = null;\\n        ConcurrentMap<Node, Computer> computers = getComputerMap();\\n        // we always need Computer for the built-in node as a fallback in case there\\\'s no other Computer.\\n        if (n.getNumExecutors() > 0 || n == Jenkins.get()) {\\n            // The start/connect of a new computer is potentially costly, so we don\\\'t want to perform it inside\\n            // computeIfAbsent. Instead, we use this creationWasAttempted flag to signal if start/connect is needed or\\n            // not.\\n            final AtomicBoolean creationWasAttempted = new AtomicBoolean(false);\\n            try {\\n                c = computers.computeIfAbsent(n, node -> {\\n                    creationWasAttempted.set(true);\\n                    return node.createComputer();\\n                });\\n            } catch (RuntimeException ex) { // Just in case there is a bogus extension\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Error retrieving computer for node " + n.getNodeName() + ", continuing", ex);\\n            }\\n            if (!creationWasAttempted.get()) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Node {0} is not a new node skipping", n.getNodeName());\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n            if (c == null) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Cannot create computer for node {0}, the {1}#createComputer() method returned null. Skipping this node",\\n                        new Object[]{n.getNodeName(), n.getClass().getName()});\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (!n.isHoldOffLaunchUntilSave() && automaticAgentLaunch) {\\n                RetentionStrategy retentionStrategy = c.getRetentionStrategy();\\n                if (retentionStrategy != null) {\\n                    // if there is a retention strategy, it is responsible for deciding to start the computer\\n                    retentionStrategy.start(c);\\n                } else {\\n                    // we should never get here, but just in case, we\\\'ll fall back to the legacy behaviour\\n                    c.connect(true);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return c;\\n        } else {\\n            // TODO: Maybe it should be allowed, but we would just get NPE in the original logic before JENKINS-43496\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Node {0} has no executors. Cannot update the Computer instance of it", n.getNodeName());\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(318, '\'List<? extends ParameterValue> filter(List<ParameterValue> parameters) {\\n        if (this.run == null) {\\n            return parameters;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (this.parameterDefinitionNames == null) {\\n            return parameters;\\n        }\\n\\n        Boolean shouldKeepFlag = SystemProperties.optBoolean(KEEP_UNDEFINED_PARAMETERS_SYSTEM_PROPERTY_NAME);\\n        if (shouldKeepFlag != null && shouldKeepFlag) {\\n            return parameters;\\n        }\\n\\n        List<ParameterValue> filteredParameters = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        for (ParameterValue v : this.parameters) {\\n            if (this.parameterDefinitionNames.contains(v.getName()) || isSafeParameter(v.getName())) {\\n                filteredParameters.add(v);\\n            } else if (shouldKeepFlag == null) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Skipped parameter `{0}` as it is undefined on `{1}` (#{2}). Set `-D{3}=true` to allow "\\n                        + "undefined parameters to be injected as environment variables or `-D{4}=[comma-separated list]` to whitelist specific parameter names, "\\n                        + "even though it represents a security breach or `-D{3}=false` to no longer show this message.",\\n                        new Object [] { v.getName(), run.getParent().getFullName(), run.getNumber(),\\n                                KEEP_UNDEFINED_PARAMETERS_SYSTEM_PROPERTY_NAME, SAFE_PARAMETERS_SYSTEM_PROPERTY_NAME });\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return filteredParameters;\\n    }\'')]

[(91, '\'void testIsValid(Object[] testObjects, long options) {\\n      UrlValidator urlVal = new UrlValidator(null, null, options);\\n      assertTrue(urlVal.isValid("http://www.google.com"));\\n      assertTrue(urlVal.isValid("http://www.google.com/"));\\n      int statusPerLine = 60;\\n      int printed = 0;\\n      if (printIndex)  {\\n         statusPerLine = 6;\\n      }\\n      do {\\n          StringBuilder testBuffer = new StringBuilder();\\n         boolean expected = true;\\n         for (int testPartsIndexIndex = 0; testPartsIndexIndex < testPartsIndex.length; ++testPartsIndexIndex) {\\n            int index = testPartsIndex[testPartsIndexIndex];\\n            ResultPair[] part = (ResultPair[]) testObjects[testPartsIndexIndex];\\n            testBuffer.append(part[index].item);\\n            expected &= part[index].valid;\\n         }\\n         String url = testBuffer.toString();\\n         boolean result = urlVal.isValid(url);\\n         assertEquals(url, expected, result);\\n         if (printStatus) {\\n            if (printIndex) {\\n               System.out.print(testPartsIndextoString());\\n            } else {\\n               if (result == expected) {\\n                  System.out.print(\\\'.\\\');\\n               } else {\\n                  System.out.print(\\\'X\\\');\\n               }\\n            }\\n            printed++;\\n            if (printed == statusPerLine) {\\n               System.out.println();\\n               printed = 0;\\n            }\\n         }\\n      } while (incrementTestPartsIndex(testPartsIndex, testObjects));\\n      if (printStatus) {\\n         System.out.println();\\n      }\\n   }\'')]

[(196, '\'boolean perform(AbstractBuild build, Launcher launcher, BuildListener listener) {\\n        List<Job<?, ?>> jobs = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (Job<?, ?> job : getChildJobs(build.getProject())) {\\n            if (job instanceof AbstractProject) {\\n                continue; // taken care of by DependencyGraph\\n            }\\n            jobs.add(job);\\n        }\\n        if (!jobs.isEmpty() && build.getResult().isBetterOrEqualTo(threshold)) {\\n            PrintStream logger = listener.getLogger();\\n            for (Job<?, ?> downstream : jobs) {\\n                if (Jenkins.get().getItemByFullName(downstream.getFullName()) != downstream) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Running as {0} cannot even see {1} for trigger from {2}", new Object[] {Jenkins.getAuthentication2().getName(), downstream, build.getParent()});\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (!downstream.hasPermission(Item.BUILD)) {\\n                    listener.getLogger().println(Messages.BuildTrigger_you_have_no_permission_to_build_(ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(downstream)));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (!(downstream instanceof ParameterizedJobMixIn.ParameterizedJob)) {\\n                    logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_NotBuildable(ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(downstream)));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                ParameterizedJobMixIn.ParameterizedJob<?, ?> pj = (ParameterizedJobMixIn.ParameterizedJob) downstream;\\n                if (pj.isDisabled()) {\\n                    logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_Disabled(ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(downstream)));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (!downstream.isBuildable()) { // some other reason; no API to retrieve cause\\n                    logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_NotBuildable(ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(downstream)));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                boolean scheduled = pj.scheduleBuild(pj.getQuietPeriod(), new UpstreamCause((Run) build));\\n                if (Jenkins.get().getItemByFullName(downstream.getFullName()) == downstream) {\\n                    String name = ModelHyperlinkNote.encodeTo(downstream);\\n                    if (scheduled) {\\n                        logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_Triggering(name));\\n                    } else {\\n                        logger.println(Messages.BuildTrigger_InQueue(name));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(139, '\'int rewriteRecursive(File dir, String relative, TaskListener listener) throws InvalidKeyException {\\n        String canonical;\\n        try {\\n            canonical = dir.toPath().toRealPath().toString();\\n        } catch (IOException | InvalidPathException e) {\\n            canonical = dir.getAbsolutePath(); //\\n        }\\n        if (!callstack.add(canonical)) {\\n            listener.getLogger().println("Cycle detected: " + dir);\\n            return 0;\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            File[] children = dir.listFiles();\\n            if (children == null)     return 0;\\n\\n            int rewritten = 0;\\n            for (File child : children) {\\n                String cn = child.getName();\\n                if (cn.endsWith(".xml")) {\\n                    if (count++ % 100 == 0)\\n                        listener.getLogger().println("Scanning " + child);\\n                    try {\\n                        if (rewrite(child)) {\\n                            listener.getLogger().println("Rewritten " + child);\\n                            rewritten++;\\n                        }\\n                    } catch (IOException e) {\\n                        Functions.printStackTrace(e, listener.error("Failed to rewrite " + child));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                if (child.isDirectory()) {\\n                    if (!isIgnoredDir(child))\\n                        rewritten += rewriteRecursive(child,\\n                                relative.isEmpty() ? cn : relative + \\\'/\\\' + cn,\\n                                listener);\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return rewritten;\\n        } finally {\\n            callstack.remove(canonical);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1333, '\'PluginWrapper whichPlugin(Class c) {\\n        PluginWrapper oneAndOnly = null;\\n        ClassLoader cl = c.getClassLoader();\\n        for (PluginWrapper p : activePlugins) {\\n            if (p.classLoader == cl) {\\n                if (oneAndOnly != null)\\n                    return null;    // ambiguous\\n                oneAndOnly = p;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        if (oneAndOnly == null && Main.isUnitTest) {\\n            // compare jenkins.security.ClassFilterImpl\\n            CodeSource cs = c.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\\n            if (cs != null) {\\n                URL loc = cs.getLocation();\\n                if (loc != null) {\\n                    if ("file".equals(loc.getProtocol())) {\\n                        File file;\\n                        try {\\n                            file = Paths.get(loc.toURI()).toFile();\\n                        } catch (InvalidPathException | URISyntaxException e) {\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "could not inspect " + loc, e);\\n                            return null;\\n                        }\\n                        if (file.isFile()) { // ignore directories\\n                            try (JarFile jf = new JarFile(file)) {\\n                                Manifest mf = jf.getManifest();\\n                                if (mf != null) {\\n                                    java.util.jar.Attributes attr = mf.getMainAttributes();\\n                                    if (attr.getValue("Plugin-Version") != null) {\\n                                        String shortName = attr.getValue("Short-Name");\\n                                        LOGGER.fine(() -> "found " + shortName + " for " + c);\\n                                        return getPlugin(shortName);\\n                                    }\\n                                }\\n                            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "could not inspect " + loc, e);\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return oneAndOnly;\\n    }\'')]

[(103, '\'boolean shouldBeDeleted(@NonNull TopLevelItem item, FilePath dir, @NonNull Node n) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        // TODO: the use of remoting is not optimal.\\n        // One remoting can execute "exists", "lastModified", and "delete" all at once.\\n        // (Could even invert master loop so that one FileCallable takes care of all known items.)\\n        if (!dir.exists()) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Directory {0} does not exist", dir);\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // if younger than a month, keep it\\n        long now = new Date().getTime();\\n        if (dir.lastModified() + retainForDays * DAY > now) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Directory {0} is only {1} old, so not deleting", new Object[] {dir, Util.getTimeSpanString(now - dir.lastModified())});\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // TODO could also be good to add checkbox that lets users configure a workspace to never be auto-cleaned.\\n\\n        // TODO check instead for SCMTriggerItem:\\n        if (item instanceof AbstractProject<?, ?>) {\\n            AbstractProject<?, ?> p = (AbstractProject<?, ?>) item;\\n            Node lb = p.getLastBuiltOn();\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINER, "Directory {0} is last built on {1}", new Object[] {dir, lb});\\n            if (lb != null && lb.equals(n)) {\\n                // this is the active workspace. keep it.\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Directory {0} is the last workspace for {1}", new Object[] {dir, p});\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (!p.getScm().processWorkspaceBeforeDeletion((Job<?, ?>) p, dir, n)) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Directory deletion of {0} is vetoed by SCM", dir);\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // TODO this may only check the last build in fact:\\n        if (item instanceof Job<?, ?>) {\\n            Job<?, ?> j = (Job<?, ?>) item;\\n            if (j.isBuilding()) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Job {0} is building, so not deleting", item.getFullDisplayName());\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINER, "Going to delete directory {0}", dir);\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(174, '\'long check(final SlaveComputer c) {\\n        boolean shouldBeOnline = isOnlineScheduled();\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Checking computer {0} against schedule. online = {1}, shouldBeOnline = {2}",\\n                new Object[]{c.getName(), c.isOnline(), shouldBeOnline});\\n        if (shouldBeOnline && c.isOffline()) {\\n            LOGGER.log(INFO, "Trying to launch computer {0} as schedule says it should be on-line at "\\n                    + "this point in time", new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n            if (c.isLaunchSupported()) {\\n                Computer.threadPoolForRemoting.submit(new Runnable() {\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void run() {\\n                        try {\\n                            c.connect(true).get();\\n                            if (c.isOnline()) {\\n                                LOGGER.log(INFO, "Launched computer {0} per schedule", new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n         "Enabling new jobs for computer {0} as it has started its scheduled uptime",\\n                                        new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n                                c.setAcceptingTasks(true);\\n                            }\\n                        } catch (InterruptedException | ExecutionException e) {\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                });\\n            }\\n        } else if (!shouldBeOnline && c.isOnline()) {\\n            if (keepUpWhenActive) {\\n                if (!c.isIdle() && c.isAcceptingTasks()) {\\n            new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n                    return 1;\\n                } else if (c.isIdle() && c.isAcceptingTasks()) {\\n                    Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                        @Override\\n                        public void run() {\\n                            if (c.isIdle()) {\\n                                LOGGER.log(INFO, "Disconnecting computer {0} as it has finished its scheduled uptime",\\n                                        new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n                                c.disconnect(OfflineCause\\n                                        .create(Messages._SimpleScheduledRetentionStrategy_FinishedUpTime()));\\n                            } else {\\n                                c.setAcceptingTasks(false);\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    });\\n                } else if (c.isIdle() && !c.isAcceptingTasks()) {\\n                    Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                        @Override\\n                        public void run() {\\n                            if (c.isIdle()) {\\n                                LOGGER.log(INFO, "Disconnecting computer {0} as it has finished all jobs running when "\\n                                        + "it completed its scheduled uptime", new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n                                c.disconnect(OfflineCause\\n                                        .create(Messages._SimpleScheduledRetentionStrategy_FinishedUpTime()));\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    });\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                // no need to get the queue lock as the user has selected the break builds option!\\n                LOGGER.log(INFO, "Disconnecting computer {0} as it has finished its scheduled uptime",\\n                        new Object[]{c.getName()});\\n                c.disconnect(OfflineCause.create(Messages._SimpleScheduledRetentionStrategy_FinishedUpTime()));\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return 1;\\n    }\'')]

[(180, '\'void updateCache(@NonNull Job<?, ?> job, @CheckForNull Run<?, ?> b) {\\n        File buildDir = job.getBuildDir();\\n        Map<String, Integer> cache = cacheFor(buildDir);\\n        synchronized (cache) {\\n            cache.put(getId(), b == null ? RESOLVES_TO_NONE : b.getNumber());\\n            File storage = storageFor(buildDir);\\n            LOGGER.fine(() -> "saving to " + storage + ": " + cache);\\n            try (AtomicFileWriter cw = new AtomicFileWriter(storage)) {\\n                try {\\n                    for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : cache.entrySet()) {\\n                        cw.write(entry.getKey());\\n                        cw.write(\\\' \\\');\\n                        cw.write(Integer.toString(entry.getValue()));\\n                        cw.write(\\\'\\\\n\\\');\\n                    }\\n                    cw.commit();\\n                } finally {\\n                    cw.abort();\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException x) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "failed to update " + storage, x);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1197, '\'CauseOfBlockage getCauseOfBlockageForItem(Item i) {\\n        CauseOfBlockage causeOfBlockage = getCauseOfBlockageForTask(i.task);\\n        if (causeOfBlockage != null) {\\n            return causeOfBlockage;\\n        }\\n\\n        for (QueueTaskDispatcher d : QueueTaskDispatcher.all()) {\\n            try {\\n                causeOfBlockage = d.canRun(i);\\n            } catch (Throwable t) {\\n                // We cannot guarantee the task can be run because something wrong happened\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, t, () -> String.format("Exception evaluating if the queue can run the task \\\'%s\\\'", i.task.getName()));\\n                causeOfBlockage = CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Queue_ExceptionCanRun());\\n            }\\n            if (causeOfBlockage != null)\\n                return causeOfBlockage;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!(i instanceof BuildableItem)) {\\n            // Make sure we don\\\'t queue two tasks of the same project to be built\\n            // unless that project allows concurrent builds. Once item is buildable it\\\'s ok.\\n            //\\n            // This check should never pass. And must be remove once we can completely rely on `getCauseOfBlockage`.\\n            // If `task.isConcurrentBuild` returns `false`,\\n            // it should also return non-null value for `task.getCauseOfBlockage` in case of on-going execution.\\n            // But both are public non-final methods, so, we need to keep backward compatibility here.\\n            // And check one more time across all `buildables` and `pendings` for O(N) each.\\n            if (!i.task.isConcurrentBuild() && (buildables.containsKey(i.task) || pendings.containsKey(i.task))) {\\n                return CauseOfBlockage.fromMessage(Messages._Queue_InProgress());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return null;\\n    }\'')]

[(134, '\'boolean keep(@NonNull FieldRef fieldRef) {\\n\\n        if (fieldRef.getAnnotation(StaplerNotDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            // explicitly marked as an invalid field\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (fieldRef.getAnnotation(StaplerDispatchable.class) != null) {\\n            // explicitly marked as a valid field\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n\\n        String signature = fieldRef.getSignature();\\n\\n        // check whitelist\\n        ExtensionList<RoutingDecisionProvider> decisionProviders = ExtensionList.lookup(RoutingDecisionProvider.class);\\n        if (decisionProviders.size() > 0) {\\n            for (RoutingDecisionProvider provider : decisionProviders) {\\n                RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision fieldDecision = provider.decide(signature);\\n                if (fieldDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.ACCEPTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Field {0} is acceptable because it is whitelisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                    return true;\\n                }\\n                if (fieldDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.REJECTED) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Field {0} is not acceptable because it is blacklisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n                Class<?> type = fieldRef.getReturnType();\\n                if (type != null) {\\n                    String typeSignature = "class " + type.getCanonicalName();\\n                    RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision fieldTypeDecision = provider.decide(typeSignature);\\n                    if (fieldTypeDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.ACCEPTED) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Field {0} is acceptable because its type is whitelisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                        return true;\\n                    }\\n                    if (fieldTypeDecision == RoutingDecisionProvider.Decision.REJECTED) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "Field {0} is not acceptable because its type is blacklisted by {1}", new Object[]{signature, provider});\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (PROHIBIT_STATIC_ACCESS && fieldRef.isStatic()) {\\n            // unless whitelisted or marked as routable, reject static fields\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n\\n        Class<?> returnType = fieldRef.getReturnType();\\n\\n        boolean isOk = isClassAcceptable(returnType);\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Field analyzed: {0} => {1}", new Object[]{fieldRef.getName(), isOk});\\n        return isOk;\\n    }\'')]

[(282, '"Collection<String> list(@NonNull String includes, @CheckForNull String excludes, boolean useDefaultExcludes,\\n                                            OpenOption... openOptions) throws IOException {\\n        Collection<String> r = run(new CollectFiles(this));\\n        List<TokenizedPattern> includePatterns = patterns(includes);\\n        List<TokenizedPattern> excludePatterns = patterns(excludes);\\n        if (useDefaultExcludes) {\\n            for (String patt : DirectoryScanner.getDefaultExcludes()) {\\n                excludePatterns.add(new TokenizedPattern(patt.replace(\'/\', File.separatorChar)));\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return r.stream().filter(p -> {\\n            TokenizedPath path = new TokenizedPath(p.replace(\'/\', File.separatorChar));\\n            return includePatterns.stream().anyMatch(patt -> patt.matchPath(path, true)) && excludePatterns.stream().noneMatch(patt -> patt.matchPath(path, true));\\n        }).collect(Collectors.toSet());\\n    }"')]

version: " + slaveVersion);\\n        VersionNumber agentVersion = new VersionNumber(slaveVersion);\\n        if (agentVersion.isOlderThan(RemotingVersionInfo.getMinimumSupportedVersion())) {\\n            if (!ALLOW_UNSUPPORTED_REMOTING_VERSIONS) {\\n                taskListener.fatalError(\\n                        "Rejecting the connection because the Remoting version is older than the"\\n                            + " minimum required version (%s). To allow the connection anyway, set"\\n                            + " the hudson.slaves.SlaveComputer.allowUnsupportedRemotingVersions"\\n                            + " system property to true.",\\n                        RemotingVersionInfo.getMinimumSupportedVersion());\\n                disconnect(new OfflineCause.LaunchFailed());\\n                return;\\n            } else {\\n                taskListener.error(\\n                        "The Remoting version is older than the minimum required version (%s)."\\n                            + " The connection will be allowed, but compatibility is NOT"\\n                            + " guaranteed.",\\n                        RemotingVersionInfo.getMinimumSupportedVersion());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        log.println("Launcher: " + getLauncher().getClass().getSimpleName());\\n\\n        String communicationProtocol = channel.call(new CommunicationProtocol());\\n        if (communicationProtocol != null) {\\n            log.println("Communication Protocol: " + communicationProtocol);\\n        }\\n\\n        boolean _isUnix = channel.call(new DetectOS());\\n        log.println(_isUnix ? hudson.model.Messages.Slave_UnixSlave() : hudson.model.Messages.Slave_WindowsSlave());\\n\\n        String defaultCharsetName = channel.call(new DetectDefaultCharset());\\n\\n        Slave node = getNode();\\n        if (node == null) { // Node has been disabled/removed during the connection\\n            throw new IOException("Node " + nodeName + " has been deleted during the channel setup");\\n        }\\n\\n        String remoteFS = node.getRemoteFS();\\n        if (Util.isRelativePath(remoteFS)) {\\n            remoteFS = channel.call(new AbsolutePath(remoteFS));\\n            log.println("NOTE: Relative remote path resolved to: " + remoteFS);\\n        }\\n        if (_isUnix && !remoteFS.contains("/") && remoteFS.contains("\\\\\\\\"))\\n            log.println("WARNING: " + remoteFS\\n                    + " looks suspiciously like Windows path. Maybe you meant " + remoteFS.replace(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', \\\'/\\\') + "?");\\n        FilePath root = new FilePath(channel, remoteFS);\\n\\n        // reference counting problem is known to happen, such as JENKINS-9017, and so as a preventive measure\\n        // we pin the base classloader so that it\\\'ll never get GCed. When this classloader gets released,\\n        // it\\\'ll have a catastrophic impact on the communication.\\n        channel.pinClassLoader(getClass().getClassLoader());\\n\\n        channel.call(new SlaveInitializer(DEFAULT_RING_BUFFER_SIZE));\\n        try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n            for (ComputerListener cl : ComputerListener.all()) {\\n                cl.preOnline(this, channel, root, taskListener);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        offlineCause = null;\\n\\n        // update the data structure atomically to prevent others from seeing a channel that\\\'s not properly initialized yet\\n        synchronized (channelLock) {\\n            if (this.channel != null) {\\n                // check again. we used to have this entire method in a big synchronization block,\\n                // but Channel constructor blocks for an external process to do the connection\\n                // if CommandLauncher is used, and that cannot be interrupted because it blocks at InputStream.\\n                // so if the process hangs, it hangs the thread in a lock, and since Hudson will try to relaunch,\\n                // we\\\'ll end up queuing the lot of threads in a pseudo deadlock.\\n                // This implementation prevents that by avoiding a lock. JENKINS-1705 is likely a manifestation of this.\\n                channel.close();\\n                throw new IllegalStateException("Already connected");\\n            }\\n            isUnix = _isUnix;\\n            numRetryAttempt = 0;\\n            this.channel = channel;\\n            this.absoluteRemoteFs = remoteFS;\\n            defaultCharset = Charset.forName(defaultCharsetName);\\n\\n            synchronized (statusChangeLock) {\\n                statusChangeLock.notifyAll();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(ACL.SYSTEM2)) {\\n            for (ComputerListener cl : ComputerListener.all()) {\\n                try {\\n                    cl.onOnline(this, taskListener);\\n                } catch (AbortException e) {\\n                    taskListener.error(e.getMessage());\\n                } catch (Exception e) {\\n                    // Per Javadoc log exceptions but still go online.\\n                    // NOTE: this does not include Errors, which indicate a fatal problem\\n                    Functions.printStackTrace(e, taskListener.error(Messages.ComputerLauncher_unexpectedError()));\\n                } catch (Throwable e) {\\n                    closeChannel();\\n                    throw e;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        log.println("Agent successfully connected and online");\\n        Jenkins.get().getQueue().scheduleMaintenance();\\n    }\'')]

[(90, '\'void afterProperties(@NonNull JnlpConnectionState event) {\\n        String clientName = event.getProperty(JnlpConnectionState.CLIENT_NAME_KEY);\\n        SlaveComputer computer = (SlaveComputer) Jenkins.get().getComputer(clientName);\\n        if (computer == null) {\\n            event.reject(new ConnectionRefusalException(String.format("%s is not an inbound agent", clientName)));\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        ComputerLauncher launcher = computer.getLauncher();\\n        while (!(launcher instanceof JNLPLauncher)) {\\n            ComputerLauncher l;\\n            if (launcher instanceof DelegatingComputerLauncher) {\\n                launcher = ((DelegatingComputerLauncher) launcher).getLauncher();\\n            } else if (launcher instanceof ComputerLauncherFilter) {\\n                launcher = ((ComputerLauncherFilter) launcher).getCore();\\n            } else if (null != (l = getDelegate(launcher))) {  // TODO remove when all plugins are fixed\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Connecting {0} as an inbound agent where the launcher {1} does not mark "\\n                                + "itself correctly as being an inbound agent",\\n                        new Object[]{clientName, computer.getLauncher().getClass()});\\n                launcher = l;\\n            } else {\\n                if (disableStrictVerification) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Connecting {0} as an inbound agent where the launcher {1} does not mark "\\n                            + "itself correctly as being an inbound agent",\\n                            new Object[]{clientName, computer.getLauncher().getClass()});\\n                    break;\\n                } else {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Rejecting connection to {0} from {1} as an inbound agent as the launcher "\\n                                    + "{2} does not extend JNLPLauncher or does not implement "\\n                                    + "DelegatingComputerLauncher with a delegation chain leading to a JNLPLauncher. "\\n                                    + "Set system property "\\n                                    + "jenkins.slaves.DefaultJnlpSlaveReceiver.disableStrictVerification=true to allow"\\n                                    + "connections until the plugin has been fixed.",\\n                            new Object[]{clientName, event.getRemoteEndpointDescription(), computer.getLauncher().getClass()});\\n                    event.reject(new ConnectionRefusalException(String.format("%s is not an inbound agent", clientName)));\\n                    return;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        Channel ch = computer.getChannel();\\n        if (ch != null) {\\n            String cookie = event.getProperty(JnlpConnectionState.COOKIE_KEY);\\n            String channelCookie = (String) ch.getProperty(JnlpConnectionState.COOKIE_KEY);\\n            if (cookie != null && channelCookie != null && MessageDigest.isEqual(cookie.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8), channelCookie.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))) {\\n                // we think we are currently connected, but this request proves that it\\\'s from the party\\n                // we are supposed to be communicating to. so let the current one get disconnected\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Disconnecting {0} as we are reconnected from the current peer", clientName);\\n                try {\\n                    computer.disconnect(new ConnectionFromCurrentPeer()).get(15, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n                } catch (ExecutionException | TimeoutException | InterruptedException e) {\\n                    event.reject(new ConnectionRefusalException("Failed to disconnect the current client", e));\\n                    return;\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                event.reject(new ConnectionRefusalException(String.format(\\n                        "%s is already connected to this controller. Rejecting this connection.", clientName)));\\n                return;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        event.approve();\\n        event.setStash(new State(computer));\\n    }\'')]

[(847, '\'void writeConfigDotXml(OutputStream os) throws IOException {\\n        checkPermission(EXTENDED_READ);\\n        XmlFile configFile = getConfigFile();\\n        if (hasPermission(CONFIGURE)) {\\n            IOUtils.copy(configFile.getFile(), os);\\n        } else {\\n            String encoding = configFile.sniffEncoding();\\n            String xml = Files.readString(Util.fileToPath(configFile.getFile()), Charset.forName(encoding));\\n            Matcher matcher = SECRET_PATTERN.matcher(xml);\\n            StringBuilder cleanXml = new StringBuilder();\\n            while (matcher.find()) {\\n                if (Secret.decrypt(matcher.group(1)) != null) {\\n                    matcher.appendReplacement(cleanXml, ">********<");\\n                }\\n            }\\n            matcher.appendTail(cleanXml);\\n            org.apache.commons.io.IOUtils.write(cleanXml.toString(), os, encoding);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(277, '"void makeWritable(@NonNull Path path) throws IOException {\\n        if (!Functions.isWindows()) {\\n            try {\\n                PosixFileAttributes attrs = Files.readAttributes(path, PosixFileAttributes.class);\\n                Set<PosixFilePermission> newPermissions = attrs.permissions();\\n                newPermissions.add(PosixFilePermission.OWNER_WRITE);\\n                Files.setPosixFilePermissions(path, newPermissions);\\n            } catch (NoSuchFileException ignored) {\\n                return;\\n            } catch (UnsupportedOperationException ignored) {\\n                // PosixFileAttributes not supported, fall back to old IO.\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n          /*\\n           * If on Windows a folder has a read only attribute set, the file.setWritable(true) doesn\'t work (JENKINS-57855)\\n           */\\n          DosFileAttributeView dos = Files.getFileAttributeView(path, DosFileAttributeView.class, LinkOption.NOFOLLOW_LINKS);\\n          if (dos != null) {\\n            dos.setReadOnly(false);\\n          }\\n        }\\n\\n        /*\\n         * We intentionally do not check the return code of setWritable, because if it\\n         * is false we prefer to rethrow the exception thrown by Files.deleteIfExists,\\n         * which will have a more useful message than something we make up here.\\n         */\\n        path.toFile().setWritable(true);\\n    }"')]

[(77, '\'HttpResponse doResourceBundle(StaplerRequest request) {\\n        String baseName = request.getParameter("baseName");\\n\\n        if (baseName == null) {\\n            return HttpResponses.errorJSON("Mandatory parameter \\\'baseName\\\' not specified.");\\n        }\\n\\n        String language = request.getParameter("language");\\n        String country = request.getParameter("country");\\n        String variant = request.getParameter("variant");\\n        // https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-lang-priorities\\n        // in case we have regions/countries in the language query parameter\\n        if (language != null) {\\n            String[] languageTokens = language.split("-|_");\\n            language = languageTokens[0];\\n            if (country == null && languageTokens.length > 1) {\\n                country = languageTokens[1];\\n                if (variant == null && languageTokens.length > 2) {\\n                    variant = languageTokens[2];\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        try {\\n            Locale locale = request.getLocale();\\n\\n            if (language != null && country != null && variant != null) {\\n                locale = new Locale(language, country, variant);\\n            } else if (language != null && country != null) {\\n                locale = new Locale(language, country);\\n            } else if (language != null) {\\n                locale = new Locale(language);\\n            }\\n\\n            return HttpResponses.okJSON(ResourceBundleUtil.getBundle(baseName, locale));\\n        } catch (RuntimeException e) {\\n            return HttpResponses.errorJSON(e.getMessage());\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(52, '\'String quoteArgument(@NonNull String argument) {\\n        if (!NEEDS_QUOTING.matcher(argument).find()) return argument;\\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\\n        sb.append(\\\'"\\\');\\n        int end = argument.length();\\n        for (int i = 0; i < end; i++) {\\n            int nrBackslashes = 0;\\n            while (i < end && argument.charAt(i) == \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\') {\\n                i++;\\n                nrBackslashes++;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (i == end) {\\n                // backslashes at the end of the argument must be escaped so the terminate quote isn\\\'t\\n                nrBackslashes = nrBackslashes * 2;\\n            } else if (argument.charAt(i) == \\\'"\\\') {\\n                // backslashes preceding a quote all need to be escaped along with the quote\\n                nrBackslashes = nrBackslashes * 2 + 1;\\n            }\\n            // else backslashes have no special meaning and don\\\'t need to be escaped here\\n\\n            sb.append("\\\\\\\\".repeat(Math.max(0, nrBackslashes)));\\n\\n            if (i < end) {\\n                sb.append(argument.charAt(i));\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return sb.append(\\\'"\\\').toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(92, "'byte[] getValue(String valueName) {\\n        IntByReference pType, lpcbData;\\n        byte[] lpData = new byte[1];\\n\\n        pType = new IntByReference();\\n        lpcbData = new IntByReference();\\n\\n        OUTER:\\n        while (true) {\\n            int r = Advapi32.INSTANCE.RegQueryValueEx(handle, valueName, null, pType, lpData, lpcbData);\\n            switch (r) {\\n            case WINERROR.ERROR_MORE_DATA:\\n                lpData = new byte[lpcbData.getValue()];\\n                continue OUTER;\\n\\n            case WINERROR.ERROR_SUCCESS:\\n                return lpData;\\n\\n            default:\\n                throw new JnaException(r);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(94, '\'BufferedImage render(StaplerRequest req, ChartRenderingInfo info) {\\n        String w = req.getParameter("width");\\n        if (w == null) {\\n            w = String.valueOf(defaultWidth);\\n        }\\n\\n        String h = req.getParameter("height");\\n        if (h == null) {\\n            h = String.valueOf(defaultHeight);\\n        }\\n\\n        String s = req.getParameter("scale");\\n        if (s == null) {\\n            s = String.valueOf(defaultScale);\\n        }\\n\\n        Color graphBg = stringToColor(req.getParameter("graphBg"));\\n        Color plotBg = stringToColor(req.getParameter("plotBg"));\\n\\n        if (graph == null)    graph = createGraph();\\n        graph.setBackgroundPaint(graphBg);\\n        Plot p = graph.getPlot();\\n        p.setBackgroundPaint(plotBg);\\n\\n        int width = Math.min(Integer.parseInt(w), 2560);\\n        int height = Math.min(Integer.parseInt(h), 1440);\\n        int scale = Math.min(Integer.parseInt(s), 3);\\n        Dimension safeDimension = safeDimension(width, height, defaultWidth, defaultHeight);\\n        return graph.createBufferedImage(safeDimension.width * scale, safeDimension.height * scale,\\n                safeDimension.width, safeDimension.height, info);\\n    }\'')]

[(114, '\'void checkUpdateSite(String urlUpdateSite, String message, boolean isSuccess) throws IOException, SAXException {\\n        // Capture log messages in the plugin manager and the retrier without changing the level of each logger\\n        logging.record(PluginManager.class, Logger.getLogger(PluginManager.class.getName()).getLevel());\\n        logging.record(Retrier.class, Logger.getLogger(Retrier.class.getName()).getLevel()).capture(50);\\n\\n\\n        Jenkins.get().getUpdateCenter().getSites().clear();\\n        UpdateSite us = new UpdateSite("CustomUpdateSite", urlUpdateSite);\\n        Jenkins.get().getUpdateCenter().getSites().add(us);\\n\\n        JenkinsRule.WebClient wc = j.createWebClient();\\n        wc.getOptions().setThrowExceptionOnFailingStatusCode(false);\\n        HtmlPage p = wc.goTo("pluginManager");\\n        Page pageAfterClick = PluginManagerUtil.getCheckForUpdatesButton(p).click();\\n        String page = pageAfterClick.getWebResponse().getContentAsString();\\n\\n        // Check what is shown in the web page\\n        Assert.assertNotEquals(isSuccess, page.contains(Messages.PluginManager_CheckUpdateServerError(message)));\\n\\n        // Check the logs (attempted CHECK_UPDATE_ATTEMPTS times). The second argument, the exception does\\\'t matter to test the message in the log\\n        Assert.assertNotEquals(isSuccess, logging.getMessages().stream().anyMatch(m -> m.contains(Messages.PluginManager_UpdateSiteError(PluginManager.CHECK_UPDATE_ATTEMPTS, ""))));\\n    }\'')]

[(60, '\'void doData(String location) throws Exception {\\n        URL url = new URL(location);\\n        String jsonp = DownloadService.loadJSON(url);\\n        JSONObject json = JSONObject.fromObject(jsonp);\\n\\n        UpdateSite us = new UpdateSite("default", url.toExternalForm());\\n        UpdateSite.Data data = us.new Data(json);\\n        assertThat(requireNonNull(data.core).url, startsWith("https://updates.jenkins.io/"));\\n        assertTrue(data.plugins.containsKey("rake"));\\n        System.out.println(data.core.url);\\n\\n        // make sure the certificate is valid for a while more\\n        CertificateFactory cf = CertificateFactory.getInstance("X509");\\n        JSONObject signature = json.getJSONObject("signature");\\n        for (Object cert : signature.getJSONArray("certificates")) {\\n            X509Certificate c = (X509Certificate) cf.generateCertificate(new ByteArrayInputStream(Base64.getDecoder().decode(cert.toString().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))));\\n            c.checkValidity(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + TimeUnit.DAYS.toMillis(30)));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(390, '\'void createUserWithToken(boolean legacy, boolean fresh, boolean recent) throws Exception {\\n        User user = User.getById(String.format("user %b %b %b %d", legacy, fresh, recent, nextId++), true);\\n        if (!legacy) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        ApiTokenProperty apiTokenProperty = user.getProperty(ApiTokenProperty.class);\\n        apiTokenProperty.changeApiToken();\\n\\n        if (fresh) {\\n            if (recent) {\\n                simulateUseOfLegacyToken(user);\\n                Thread.sleep(1);\\n\\n                TokenUuidAndPlainValue tokenInfo = apiTokenProperty.getTokenStore().generateNewToken("Fresh and recent token");\\n                simulateUseOfToken(user, tokenInfo.plainValue);\\n            } else {\\n                simulateUseOfLegacyToken(user);\\n                Thread.sleep(1);\\n\\n                apiTokenProperty.getTokenStore().generateNewToken("Fresh token");\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            if (recent) {\\n                TokenUuidAndPlainValue tokenInfo = apiTokenProperty.getTokenStore().generateNewToken("Recent token");\\n                Thread.sleep(1);\\n\\n                simulateUseOfLegacyToken(user);\\n                Thread.sleep(1);\\n\\n                simulateUseOfToken(user, tokenInfo.plainValue);\\n            }\\n            //else: no other token to generate\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(231, '\'void doDynamic(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        String path = req.getRestOfPath();\\n\\n        String pathUC = path.toUpperCase(Locale.ENGLISH);\\n        if (path.isEmpty() || path.contains("..") || path.startsWith(".") || path.contains("%")\\n                || pathUC.contains("META-INF") || pathUC.contains("WEB-INF")\\n                // ClassicPluginStrategy#explode produce that file to know if a new explosion is required or not\\n                || pathUC.equals("/.TIMESTAMP2")\\n        ) {\\n            LOGGER.warning("rejecting possibly malicious " + req.getRequestURIWithQueryString());\\n            rsp.sendError(HttpServletResponse.SC_BAD_REQUEST);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        // Stapler routes requests like the "/static/.../foo/bar/zot" to be treated like "/foo/bar/zot"\\n        // and this is used to serve long expiration header, by using Jenkins.VERSION_HASH as "..."\\n        // to create unique URLs. Recognize that and set a long expiration header.\\n        String requestPath = req.getRequestURI().substring(req.getContextPath().length());\\n        boolean staticLink = requestPath.startsWith("/static/");\\n\\n        long expires = staticLink ?
