[(64, '\'void execute(TaskListener listener) throws InterruptedException, IOException {\\n        if (disabled) {\\n            LOGGER.fine("Disabled. Skipping execution");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        List<Node> nodes = new ArrayList<>();\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.get();\\n        nodes.add(j);\\n        nodes.addAll(j.getNodes());\\n        for (TopLevelItem item : j.allItems(TopLevelItem.class)) {\\n            if (item instanceof ModifiableTopLevelItemGroup) { // no such thing as TopLevelItemGroup, and ItemGroup offers no access to its type parameter\\n                continue; // children will typically have their own workspaces as subdirectories; probably no real workspace of its own\\n            }\\n            listener.getLogger().println("Checking " + item.getFullDisplayName());\\n            for (Node node : nodes) {\\n                FilePath ws = node.getWorkspaceFor(item);\\n                if (ws == null) {\\n                    continue; // offline, fine\\n                }\\n                boolean check;\\n                try {\\n                    check = shouldBeDeleted(item, ws, node);\\n                } catch (IOException | InterruptedException x) {\\n                    Functions.printStackTrace(x, listener.error("Failed to check " + node.getDisplayName()));\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (check) {\\n                    listener.getLogger().println("Deleting " + ws + " on " + node.getDisplayName());\\n                    try {\\n                        ws.deleteSuffixesRecursive();\\n                        ws.deleteRecursive();\\n                    } catch (IOException | InterruptedException x) {\\n                        Functions.printStackTrace(x, listener.error("Failed to delete " + ws + " on " + node.getDisplayName()));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(51, '\'DiagnosedStreamCorruptionException analyzeCrash(Exception problem, String diagnosisName) {\\n        final ByteArrayOutputStream readAhead = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        final IOException[] error = new IOException[1];\\n\\n        Thread diagnosisThread = new Thread(diagnosisName + " stream corruption diagnosis thread") {\\n            @Override\\n            public void run() {\\n                int b;\\n                try {\\n                    // not all InputStream will look for the thread interrupt flag, so check that explicitly to be defensive\\n                    while (!Thread.interrupted() && (b = source.read()) != -1) {\\n                        readAhead.write(b);\\n                    }\\n                } catch (IOException e) {\\n                    error[0] = e;\\n                }\\n            }\\n        };\\n\\n        // wait up to 1 sec to grab as much data as possible\\n        diagnosisThread.start();\\n        try {\\n            diagnosisThread.join(1000);\\n        } catch (InterruptedException ignored) {\\n            // we are only waiting for a fixed amount of time, so we\\\'ll pretend like we were in a busy loop\\n            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\\n            // fall through\\n        }\\n\\n        IOException diagnosisProblem = error[0]; // capture the error, if any, before we kill the thread\\n        if (diagnosisThread.isAlive())\\n            diagnosisThread.interrupt();    // if it\\\'s not dead, kill\\n\\n        return new DiagnosedStreamCorruptionException(problem, diagnosisProblem, getRecord(), readAhead.toByteArray());\\n\\n    }\'')]

(!jenkins.getInstallState().isSetupComplete()) {\\n            jenkins.setInstallState(InstallState.INITIAL_PLUGINS_INSTALLING);\\n            updateCenter.persistInstallStatus();\\n            new for (Future<UpdateCenter.UpdateCenterJob> jobFuture : installJobs) {\\n                                if (!jobFuture.isDone() && !jobFuture.isCancelled()) {\\n                                    continue INSTALLING;\\n                                }\\n                                UpdateCenter.UpdateCenterJob job = jobFuture.get();\\n                                if (job instanceof (ACLContext acl = ACL.as2(currentAuth)) {\\n                            InstallUtil.proceedToNextStateFrom(InstallState.INITIAL_PLUGINS_INSTALLING);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }.start();\\n        }\\n\\n        return installJobs;\\n    }\'')]

[(346, '\'void clearStaleSessionCookies(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp, String contextPath) {\\n        /* While "executableWar.jetty.sessionIdCookieName" and\\n         * "executableWar.jetty.disableCustomSessionIdCookieName"\\n         * <https://github.com/jenkinsci/extras-executable-war/blob/6558df699d1366b18d045d2ffda3e970df377873/src/main/java/Main.java#L79-L97>\\n         * can influence the current running behavior of the generated session cookie, we aren\\\'t interested\\n         * in either of them at all.\\n         *\\n         * What matters to us are any stale cookies.\\n         * Those cookies would have been created by this jenkins in a different incarnation, when it\\n         * could, perhaps, have had different configuration flags, including for those configurables.\\n         *\\n         * Thus, we unconditionally zap all JSESSIONID. cookies.\\n         * a new cookie will be generated by sendRedirect2(...)\\n         *\\n         * We don\\\'t care about JSESSIONID cookies outside our path because it\\\'s the browser\\\'s\\n         * responsibility not to send them to us in the first place.\\n         */\\n        final String cookieName = "JSESSIONID.";\\n        Cookie[] cookies = req.getCookies();\\n        if (cookies != null) {\\n            for (Cookie cookie : cookies) {\\n                if (cookie.getName().startsWith(cookieName)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Removing cookie {0} during logout", cookie.getName());\\n                    // one reason users log out is to clear their session(s)\\n                    // so tell the browser to drop all old sessions\\n                    cookie.setMaxAge(0);\\n                    cookie.setValue("");\\n                    rsp.addCookie(cookie);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(259, '\'void callPageAndCheckIfResultContainsExpected(String url, String bodyContainsExpected, String valueContainsExpected, boolean checkExactCharacters) throws Exception {\\n        HtmlPage page = (HtmlPage) j.createWebClient().goTo(url, null);\\n        String responseContent = page.getWebResponse().getContentAsString();\\n\\n        if (checkExactCharacters) {\\n            // in this mode, we check the data directly received by the response,\\n            // without any un-escaping done by HtmlElement\\n\\n            // first value shown as value\\n            int indexOfValue = responseContent.indexOf(valueContainsExpected);\\n            assertNotEquals(-1, indexOfValue);\\n\\n            // second as body\\n            int indexOfBody = responseContent.indexOf(bodyContainsExpected, indexOfValue + 1);\\n\\n            assertNotEquals(-1, indexOfBody);\\n\\n            // also check there is no "<script>" present in the answer\\n            int indexOfScript = responseContent.indexOf("<script>");\\n            assertEquals(-1, indexOfScript);\\n        } else {\\n            // in this mode, we check the content as displayed to the user, converting all the escaped characters to\\n            // their un-escaped equivalent, done by org.htmlunit.html.HtmlSerializer#cleanUp(String)\\n\\n            HtmlElement document = page.getDocumentElement();\\n            DomNodeList<HtmlElement> elements = document.getElementsByTagName("option");\\n            assertEquals(1, elements.size());\\n\\n            HtmlOption option = (HtmlOption) elements.get(0);\\n\\n            // without that check, the getValue could return getText if the value is not present\\n            assertNotEquals(DomElement.ATTRIBUTE_NOT_DEFINED, option.getAttribute("value"));\\n\\n            assertTrue(\\n                    "Value attribute does not contain the expected value",\\n                    option.getValueAttribute().contains(valueContainsExpected)\\n            );\\n            assertTrue(\\n                    "Body content of the option does not contain the expected value",\\n                    option.getText().contains(bodyContainsExpected)\\n            );\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(161, '\'Set<String> getAutoCompletionCandidates(List<String> loggerNamesList) {\\n        Set<String> loggerNames = new HashSet<>(loggerNamesList);\\n\\n        // now look for package prefixes that make sense to offer for autocompletion:\\n        // Only prefixes that match multiple loggers will be shown.\\n        // Example: \\\'org\\\' will show \\\'org\\\', because there\\\'s org.apache, org.jenkinsci, etc.\\n        // \\\'io\\\' might only show \\\'io.jenkins.plugins\\\' rather than \\\'io\\\' if all loggers starting with \\\'io\\\' start with \\\'io.jenkins.plugins\\\'.\\n        HashMap<String, Integer> seenPrefixes = new HashMap<>();\\n        SortedSet<String> relevantPrefixes = new TreeSet<>();\\n        for (String loggerName : loggerNames) {\\n            String[] loggerNameParts = loggerName.split("[.]");\\n\\n            String longerPrefix = null;\\n            for (int i = loggerNameParts.length; i > 0; i--) {\\n                String loggerNamePrefix = String.join(".", Arrays.copyOf(loggerNameParts, i));\\n                seenPrefixes.put(loggerNamePrefix, seenPrefixes.getOrDefault(loggerNamePrefix, 0) + 1);\\n                if (longerPrefix == null) {\\n                    relevantPrefixes.add(loggerNamePrefix); // actual logger name\\n                    longerPrefix = loggerNamePrefix;\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n\\n                if (seenPrefixes.get(loggerNamePrefix) > seenPrefixes.get(longerPrefix)) {\\n                    relevantPrefixes.add(loggerNamePrefix);\\n                }\\n                longerPrefix = loggerNamePrefix;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return relevantPrefixes;\\n    }\'')]

[(301, "'String toString(boolean preEscape) {\\n        if (tags.isEmpty())\\n            return preEscape ? Util.xmlEscape(text) : Util.escape(text);  // the most common case\\n\\n        Collections.sort(tags);\\n\\n        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();\\n        int copied = 0; // # of chars already copied from text to buf\\n\\n        for (Tag tag : tags) {\\n            if (copied < tag.pos) {\\n                String portion = text.substring(copied, tag.pos);\\n                buf.append(preEscape ? Util.xmlEscape(portion) : Util.escape(portion));\\n                copied = tag.pos;\\n            }\\n            buf.append(tag.markup);\\n        }\\n        if (copied < text.length()) {\\n            String portion = text.substring(copied);\\n            buf.append(preEscape ? Util.xmlEscape(portion) : Util.escape(portion));\\n        }\\n\\n        return buf.toString();\\n    }'")]

[(215, '\'void delete(String id) throws IOException {\\n        File file = getFingerprintFile(id);\\n        if (!file.exists()) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!file.delete()) {\\n            throw new IOException("Error occurred in deleting Fingerprint " + id);\\n        }\\n\\n        File inner = new File(Jenkins.get().getRootDir(), "fingerprints/" + id.substring(0, 2) + "/" + id.substring(2, 4));\\n        String[] innerFiles = inner.list();\\n        if (innerFiles != null && innerFiles.length == 0) {\\n            if (!inner.delete()) {\\n                throw new IOException("Error occurred in deleting inner directory of Fingerprint " + id);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        File outer = new File(Jenkins.get().getRootDir(), "fingerprints/" + id.substring(0, 2));\\n        String[] outerFiles = outer.list();\\n        if (outerFiles != null && outerFiles.length == 0) {\\n            if (!outer.delete()) {\\n                throw new IOException("Error occurred in deleting outer directory of Fingerprint " + id);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(73, '\'void generateResponse(StaplerRequest req, final StaplerResponse res, Object node) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        RequestDispatcher view = req.getView(it, viewName);\\n        if ("true".equals(req.getParameter("encrypt"))) {\\n            final CapturingServletOutputStream csos = new CapturingServletOutputStream();\\n            StaplerResponse temp = new ResponseImpl(req.getStapler(), new HttpServletResponseWrapper(res) {\\n                @Override public ServletOutputStream getOutputStream() {\\n                    return csos;\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override public PrintWriter getWriter() {\\n                    throw new IllegalStateException();\\n                }\\n            });\\n            view.forward(req, temp);\\n\\n            byte[] iv = new byte[128 / 8];\\n            RANDOM.nextBytes(iv);\\n\\n            byte[] jnlpMac;\\n            if (it instanceof SlaveComputer) {\\n                jnlpMac = Util.fromHexString(((SlaveComputer) it).getJnlpMac());\\n            } else {\\n                jnlpMac = JnlpAgentReceiver.SLAVE_SECRET.mac(slaveName.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n            }\\n            SecretKey key = new SecretKeySpec(jnlpMac, 0, /* export restrictions */ 128 / 8, "AES");\\n            byte[] encrypted;\\n            try {\\n                Cipher c = Secret.getCipher("AES/CFB8/NoPadding");\\n                c.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, key, new IvParameterSpec(iv));\\n                encrypted = c.doFinal(csos.getBytes());\\n            } catch (GeneralSecurityException x) {\\n                throw new IOException(x);\\n            }\\n            res.setContentType("application/octet-stream");\\n            res.getOutputStream().write(iv);\\n            res.getOutputStream().write(encrypted);\\n        } else {\\n            it.checkPermission(connectPermission);\\n            view.forward(req, res);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(129, '\'boolean shouldTrigger(Run upstreamBuild, TaskListener listener) {\\n        Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.get();\\n        if (job == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        boolean downstreamVisible = false;\\n        boolean downstreamDiscoverable = false;\\n\\n        // This checks Item.READ also on parent folders; note we are checking as the upstream auth currently:\\n        try {\\n            downstreamVisible = jenkins.getItemByFullName(job.getFullName()) == job;\\n        } catch (AccessDeniedException ex) {\\n            // Fails because of missing Item.READ but upstream user has Item.DISCOVER\\n            downstreamDiscoverable = true;\\n        }\\n\\n        Authentication originalAuth = Jenkins.getAuthentication2();\\n        Job upstream = upstreamBuild.getParent();\\n        Authentication auth = Tasks.getAuthenticationOf2((Queue.Task) job);\\n\\n        Item authUpstream = null;\\n        try (ACLContext ctx = ACL.as2(auth)) {\\n            authUpstream = jenkins.getItemByFullName(upstream.getFullName());\\n            // No need to check Item.BUILD on downstream, because the downstream project’s configurer has asked for this.\\n        } catch (AccessDeniedException ade) {\\n            // Fails because of missing Item.READ but downstream user has Item.DISCOVER\\n        }\\n\\n        if (authUpstream != upstream) {\\n            if (downstreamVisible) {\\n                // TODO ModelHyperlink\\n                listener.getLogger().println(Messages.ReverseBuildTrigger_running_as_cannot_even_see_for_trigger_f(auth.getName(),\\n                        upstream.getFullName(), job.getFullName()));\\n            } else  {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "Running as {0} cannot even {1} {2} for trigger from {3}, (but cannot tell {4} that)",\\n                        new Object [] { auth.getName(), downstreamDiscoverable ? "READ" : "DISCOVER", upstream, job, originalAuth.getName()});\\n            }\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        Result result = upstreamBuild.getResult();\\n        return result != null && result.isBetterOrEqualTo(threshold);\\n    }\'')]

[(450, '\'List<List<Path>> keepReadabilityOnlyOnDescendants(VirtualFile root, boolean patternUsed, List<List<Path>> pathFragmentsList) {\\n        Stream<List<Path>> pathFragmentsStream = pathFragmentsList.stream().map((List<Path> pathFragments) -> {\\n            List<Path> mappedFragments = new ArrayList<>(pathFragments.size());\\n            String relativePath = "";\\n            for (int i = 0; i < pathFragments.size(); i++) {\\n                Path current = pathFragments.get(i);\\n                if (i == 0) {\\n                    relativePath = current.title;\\n                } else {\\n                    relativePath += "/" + current.title;\\n                }\\n\\n                if (!current.isReadable) {\\n                    if (patternUsed) {\\n                        // we do not want to leak information about existence of folders / files satisfying the pattern inside that folder\\n                        return null;\\n                    }\\n                    mappedFragments.add(current);\\n                    return mappedFragments;\\n                } else {\\n                    if (isDescendant(root, relativePath)) {\\n                        mappedFragments.add(current);\\n                    } else {\\n                        if (patternUsed) {\\n                            // we do not want to leak information about existence of folders / files satisfying the pattern inside that folder\\n                            return null;\\n                        }\\n                        mappedFragments.add(Path.createNotReadableVersionOf(current));\\n                        return mappedFragments;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return mappedFragments;\\n        });\\n\\n        if (patternUsed) {\\n            pathFragmentsStream = pathFragmentsStream.filter(Objects::nonNull);\\n        }\\n\\n        return pathFragmentsStream.collect(Collectors.toList());\\n    }\'')]

[(100, '\'void scan(String pattern) {\\n        LOGGER.fine("Scanning " + pattern + " for hs_err_pid files");\\n\\n        pattern = pattern.replace("%p", "*").replace("%%", "%");\\n        File f = new File(pattern).getAbsoluteFile();\\n        if (!pattern.contains("*"))\\n            scanFile(f);\\n        else { // GLOB\\n            File commonParent = f;\\n            while (commonParent != null && commonParent.getPath().contains("*")) {\\n                commonParent = commonParent.getParentFile();\\n            }\\n            if (commonParent == null) {\\n                LOGGER.warning("Failed to process " + f);\\n                return; // huh?\\n            }\\n\\n            FileSet fs = Util.createFileSet(commonParent, f.getPath().substring(commonParent.getPath().length() + 1), null);\\n            DirectoryScanner ds = fs.getDirectoryScanner(new Project());\\n            for (String child : ds.getIncludedFiles()) {\\n                scanFile(new File(commonParent, child));\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1466, "'boolean isAllSuitableNodesOffline(R build) {\\n        Label label = getAssignedLabel();\\n\\n        if (label != null) {\\n            //Invalid label. Put in queue to make administrator fix\\n            if (label.getNodes().isEmpty()) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n            //Returns true, if all suitable nodes are offline\\n            return label.isOffline();\\n        } else {\\n            if (canRoam) {\\n                for (Node n : Jenkins.get().getNodes()) {\\n                    Computer c = n.toComputer();\\n                    if (c != null && c.isOnline() && c.isAcceptingTasks() && n.getMode() == Mode.NORMAL) {\\n                        // Some executor is online that  is ready and this job can run anywhere\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                //We can roam, check that the master is set to be used as much as possible, and not tied jobs only.\\n                return Jenkins.get().getMode() == Mode.EXCLUSIVE;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return true;\\n    }'")]

[(456, '\'void jenkins48775workaround(Proxy proxy, URL url) {\\n        if ("https".equals(url.getProtocol()) && !authCacheSeeded && proxy != Proxy.NO_PROXY) {\\n            HttpURLConnection preAuth = null;\\n            try {\\n                // We do not care if there is anything at this URL, all we care is that it is using the proxy\\n                preAuth = (HttpURLConnection) new URL("http", url.getHost(), -1, "/").openConnection(proxy);\\n                preAuth.setRequestMethod("HEAD");\\n                preAuth.connect();\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                // ignore, this is just a probe we don\\\'t care at all\\n            } finally {\\n                if (preAuth != null) {\\n                    preAuth.disconnect();\\n                }\\n            }\\n            authCacheSeeded = true;\\n        } else if ("https".equals(url.getProtocol())) {\\n            // if we access any http url using a proxy then the auth cache will have been seeded\\n            authCacheSeeded = authCacheSeeded || proxy != Proxy.NO_PROXY;\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(97, '\'byte[] load(ConfidentialKey key) throws IOException {\\n        try {\\n            File f = getFileFor(key);\\n            if (!f.exists())    return null;\\n\\n            Cipher sym = Secret.getCipher("AES");\\n            sym.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, masterKey);\\n            try (InputStream fis = Files.newInputStream(f.toPath());\\n                 CipherInputStream cis = new CipherInputStream(fis, sym)) {\\n                byte[] bytes = cis.readAllBytes();\\n                return verifyMagic(bytes);\\n            }\\n        } catch (GeneralSecurityException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to load the key: " + key.getId(), e);\\n        } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n            throw new IOException(e);\\n        } catch (IOException x) {\\n            if (x.getCause() instanceof BadPaddingException) {\\n                return null; // broken somehow\\n            } else {\\n                throw x;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(300, "'void skip(DataInputStream in) throws IOException {\\n        byte[] preamble = new byte[PREAMBLE.length];\\n        in.readFully(preamble);\\n        if (!Arrays.equals(preamble, PREAMBLE))\\n            return;    // not a valid preamble\\n\\n        DataInputStream decoded = new DataInputStream(Base64.getDecoder().wrap(in));\\n        int macSz = - decoded.readInt();\\n        if (macSz > 0) { // new format\\n            IOUtils.skipFully(decoded, macSz);\\n            int sz = decoded.readInt();\\n            IOUtils.skipFully(decoded, sz);\\n        } else { // old format\\n            int sz = -macSz;\\n            IOUtils.skipFully(decoded, sz);\\n        }\\n\\n        byte[] postamble = new byte[POSTAMBLE.length];\\n        in.readFully(postamble);\\n    }'")]

[(250, '\'Set<TrustAnchor> loadTrustAnchors(CertificateFactory cf) throws IOException {\\n        // if we trust default root CAs, we end up trusting anyone who has a valid certificate,\\n        // which isn\\\'t useful at all\\n        Set<TrustAnchor> anchors = new HashSet<>(); // CertificateUtil.getDefaultRootCAs();\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.get();\\n        for (String cert : j.servletContext.getResourcePaths("/WEB-INF/update-center-rootCAs")) {\\n            if (cert.endsWith("/") || cert.endsWith(".txt"))  {\\n                continue;       // skip directories also any text files that are meant to be documentation\\n            }\\n            Certificate certificate;\\n            try (InputStream in = j.servletContext.getResourceAsStream(cert)) {\\n                if (in == null) continue; // our test for paths ending in / should prevent this from happening\\n                certificate = cf.generateCertificate(in);\\n                if (certificate instanceof X509Certificate) {\\n                    X509Certificate c = (X509Certificate) certificate;\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Add CA certificate found in webapp resources:\\\\n\\\\tsubjectDN: {0}\\\\n\\\\tissuer: {1}\\\\n\\\\tnotBefore: {2}\\\\n\\\\tnotAfter: {3}",\\n                            new Object[] { c.getSubjectDN(), c.getIssuerDN(), c.getNotBefore(), c.getNotAfter() });\\n                }\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, () -> "CA certificate from webapp resource " + cert + ": " + certificate);\\n            } catch (CertificateException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, String.format("Webapp resources in /WEB-INF/update-center-rootCAs are "\\n                                + "expected to be either certificates or .txt files documenting the "\\n                                + "certificates, but %s did not parse as a certificate. Skipping this "\\n                                + "resource for now.",\\n                        cert), e);\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            try {\\n                TrustAnchor certificateAuthority = new TrustAnchor((X509Certificate) certificate, null);\\n                anchors.add(certificateAuthority);\\n            } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING,\\n                        String.format("The name constraints in the certificate resource %s could not be "\\n                                        + "decoded. Skipping this resource for now.",\\n                        cert), e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        File[] cas = new File(j.root, "update-center-rootCAs").listFiles();\\n        if (cas != null) {\\n            for (File cert : cas) {\\n                if (cert.isDirectory() || cert.getName().endsWith(".txt"))  {\\n                    continue;       // skip directories also any text files that are meant to be documentation\\n                }\\n                Certificate certificate;\\n                try (InputStream in = Files.newInputStream(cert.toPath())) {\\n                    certificate = cf.generateCertificate(in);\\n                    if (certificate instanceof X509Certificate) {\\n                        X509Certificate c = (X509Certificate) certificate;\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Add CA certificate found in Jenkins home:\\\\n\\\\tsubjectDN: {0}\\\\n\\\\tissuer: {1}\\\\n\\\\tnotBefore: {2}\\\\n\\\\tnotAfter: {3}",\\n                                new Object[] { c.getSubjectDN(), c.getIssuerDN(), c.getNotBefore(), c.getNotAfter() });\\n                    }\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINEST, () -> "CA certificate from Jenkins home " + cert + ": " + certificate);\\n                } catch (InvalidPathException e) {\\n                    throw new IOException(e);\\n                } catch (CertificateException e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, String.format("Files in %s are expected to be either "\\n                                    + "certificates or .txt files documenting the certificates, "\\n                                    + "but %s did not parse as a certificate. Skipping this file for now.",\\n                            cert.getParentFile().getAbsolutePath(),\\n                            cert.getAbsolutePath()), e);\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                try {\\n                    TrustAnchor certificateAuthority = new TrustAnchor((X509Certificate) certificate, null);\\n                    anchors.add(certificateAuthority);\\n                } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING,\\n                            String.format("The name constraints in the certificate file %s could not be "\\n                                            + "decoded. Skipping this file for now.",\\n                            cert.getAbsolutePath()), e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return anchors;\\n    }\'')]

[(195, "'String validate(String value) {\\n        if (value == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        for (Pattern pattern : patterns) {\\n            Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(value);\\n            if (matcher.matches()) {\\n                int count = matcher.groupCount();\\n                if (count == 1) {\\n                    return matcher.group(1);\\n                }\\n                StringBuilder buffer = new StringBuilder();\\n                for (int j = 0; j < count; j++) {\\n                    String component = matcher.group(j + 1);\\n                    if (component != null) {\\n                        buffer.append(component);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                return buffer.toString();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }'")]

[(4273, '\'void checkGoodName(String name) throws Failure {\\n        if (name == null || name.isEmpty())\\n            throw new Failure(Messages.Hudson_NoName());\\n\\n        if (".".equals(name.trim()))\\n            throw new Failure(Messages.Jenkins_NotAllowedName("."));\\n        if ("..".equals(name.trim()))\\n            throw new Failure(Messages.Jenkins_NotAllowedName(".."));\\n        for (int i = 0; i < name.length(); i++) {\\n            char ch = name.charAt(i);\\n            if (Character.isISOControl(ch)) {\\n                throw new Failure(Messages.Hudson_ControlCodeNotAllowed(toPrintableName(name)));\\n            }\\n            if ("?*/\\\\\\\\%!@#$^&|<>[]:;".indexOf(ch) != -1)\\n                throw new Failure(Messages.Hudson_UnsafeChar(ch));\\n        }\\n\\n        if (SystemProperties.getBoolean(NAME_VALIDATION_REJECTS_TRAILING_DOT_PROP, true)) {\\n            // SECURITY-2424 on Windows the trailing dot can be used to create ambiguity\\n            if (name.trim().endsWith(".")) {\\n                throw new Failure(Messages.Hudson_TrailingDot());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // looks good\\n    }\'')]

[(256, '\'void sameCrumbUsedOnDifferentAnonymousRequest_tokenAreEqual(boolean areEqual, String namePrefix) throws Exception {\\n        String responseForCrumb = r.createWebClient().goTo("crumbIssuer/api/xml?xpath=concat(//crumbRequestField,\\\'=\\\',//crumb)", "text/plain")\\n                .getWebResponse().getContentAsString();\\n        // responseForCrumb = Jenkins-Crumb=xxxx\\n        String crumb1 = responseForCrumb.substring(CrumbIssuer.DEFAULT_CRUMB_NAME.length() + "=".length());\\n\\n        String jobName1 = namePrefix + "-test1";\\n        String jobName2 = namePrefix + "-test2";\\n\\n        WebRequest request1 = createRequestForJobCreation(jobName1);\\n        FailingHttpStatusCodeException e = assertThrows(FailingHttpStatusCodeException.class, () -> r.createWebClient().getPage(request1));\\n        assertEquals(HttpServletResponse.SC_FORBIDDEN, e.getStatusCode());\\n        assertThat(e.getResponse().getContentAsString(), containsString("No valid crumb"));\\n        // cannot create new job due to missing crumb\\n        assertNull(r.jenkins.getItem(jobName1));\\n\\n        WebRequest request2 = createRequestForJobCreation(jobName2);\\n        request2.setAdditionalHeader(CrumbIssuer.DEFAULT_CRUMB_NAME, crumb1);\\n        if (areEqual) {\\n            r.createWebClient().getPage(request2);\\n\\n            assertNotNull(r.jenkins.getItem(jobName2));\\n        } else {\\n            e = assertThrows(\\n                    "Should have failed due to invalid crumb",\\n                    FailingHttpStatusCodeException.class,\\n                    () -> r.createWebClient().getPage(request2));\\n            assertEquals(HttpURLConnection.HTTP_FORBIDDEN, e.getStatusCode());\\n            // cannot create new job due to invalid crumb\\n            assertNull(r.jenkins.getItem(jobName2));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(1066, "'FormValidation doCheckJobName(@QueryParameter String value) {\\n        // this method can be used to check if a file exists anywhere in the file system,\\n        // so it should be protected.\\n        getOwner().checkPermission(Item.CREATE);\\n\\n        if (Util.fixEmpty(value) == null) {\\n            return FormValidation.ok();\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            Jenkins.checkGoodName(value);\\n            value = value.trim(); // why trim *after* checkGoodName? not sure, but ItemGroupMixIn.createTopLevelItem does the same\\n            ItemGroup<?> parent = getOwner().getItemGroup();\\n            Jenkins.get().getProjectNamingStrategy().checkName(parent.getFullName(), value);\\n        } catch (Failure e) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(e.getMessage());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (getOwner().getItemGroup().getItem(value) != null) {\\n            return FormValidation.error(Messages.Hudson_JobAlreadyExists(value));\\n        }\\n\\n        // looks good\\n        return FormValidation.ok();\\n    }'")]

[(357, "'boolean isSymlink(@NonNull Path path) {\\n        /*\\n         *  Windows Directory Junctions are effectively the same as Linux symlinks to directories.\\n         *  Unfortunately, the Java 7 NIO2 API function isSymbolicLink does not treat them as such.\\n         *  It thinks of them as normal directories.  To use the NIO2 API & treat it like a symlink,\\n         *  you have to go through BasicFileAttributes and do the following check:\\n         *     isSymbolicLink() || isOther()\\n         *  The isOther() call will include Windows reparse points, of which a directory junction is.\\n         *  It also includes includes devices, but reading the attributes of a device with NIO fails\\n         *  or returns false for isOther(). (i.e. named pipes such as \\\\\\\\.\\\\pipe\\\\JenkinsTestPipe return\\n         *  false for isOther(), and drives such as \\\\\\\\.\\\\PhysicalDrive0 throw an exception when\\n         *  calling readAttributes.\\n         */\\n        try {\\n            BasicFileAttributes attrs = Files.readAttributes(path, BasicFileAttributes.class, LinkOption.NOFOLLOW_LINKS);\\n            return attrs.isSymbolicLink() || (attrs instanceof DosFileAttributes && attrs.isOther());\\n        } catch (IOException ignored) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(842, '\'String htmlAttributeEscape(String text) {\\n        StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder(text.length() + 64);\\n        for (int i = 0; i < text.length(); i++) {\\n            char ch = text.charAt(i);\\n            if (ch == \\\'<\\\')\\n                buf.append("<");\\n            else\\n            if (ch == \\\'>\\\')\\n                buf.append(">");\\n            else\\n            if (ch == \\\'&\\\')\\n                buf.append("&");\\n            else\\n            if (ch == \\\'"\\\')\\n                buf.append(""");\\n            else\\n            if (ch == \\\'\\\\\\\'\\\')\\n                buf.append("'");\\n            else\\n                buf.append(ch);\\n        }\\n        return buf.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(83, "'void execute(@NonNull Runnable task, final ResourceActivity activity) throws InterruptedException {\\n        final ResourceList resources = activity.getResourceList();\\n        _withLock(new NotReallyRoleSensitiveCallable<Void, InterruptedException>() {\\n            @Override\\n            public Void call() throws InterruptedException {\\n                while (inUse.isCollidingWith(resources)) {\\n                    // TODO revalidate the resource list after re-acquiring lock, for now we just let the build fail\\n                    _await();\\n                }\\n\\n                // we have a go\\n                inProgress.add(activity);\\n                inUse = ResourceList.union(inUse, resources);\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        });\\n\\n        try {\\n            task.run();\\n        } finally {\\n           // TODO if AsynchronousExecution, do that later\\n            _withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                @Override\\n                public void run() {\\n                    inProgress.remove(activity);\\n                    inUse = ResourceList.union(resourceView);\\n                    _signalAll();\\n                }\\n            });\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(128, '\'boolean configure(StaplerRequest req, JSONObject json) throws FormException {\\n        // for compatibility reasons, the actual value is stored in Jenkins\\n        Jenkins j = Jenkins.get();\\n        j.checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n\\n        j.setDisableRememberMe(json.optBoolean("disableRememberMe", false));\\n        // TODO probably clearer to configure such things with @DataBoundSetter\\n        j.setSecurityRealm(Descriptor.bindJSON(req, SecurityRealm.class, json.getJSONObject("securityRealm")));\\n        j.setAuthorizationStrategy(Descriptor.bindJSON(req, AuthorizationStrategy.class, json.getJSONObject("authorizationStrategy")));\\n\\n        if (json.has("markupFormatter")) {\\n            j.setMarkupFormatter(req.bindJSON(MarkupFormatter.class, json.getJSONObject("markupFormatter")));\\n        } else {\\n            j.setMarkupFormatter(null);\\n        }\\n\\n        // Agent settings\\n        if (!isSlaveAgentPortEnforced()) {\\n            try {\\n                j.setSlaveAgentPort(new ServerTcpPort(json.getJSONObject("slaveAgentPort")).getPort());\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                throw new FormException(e, "slaveAgentPortType");\\n            }\\n        }\\n        Set<String> agentProtocols = new TreeSet<>();\\n        if (json.has("agentProtocol")) {\\n            Object protocols = json.get("agentProtocol");\\n            if (protocols instanceof JSONArray) {\\n                for (int i = 0; i < ((JSONArray) protocols).size(); i++) {\\n                    agentProtocols.add(((JSONArray) protocols).getString(i));\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                agentProtocols.add(protocols.toString());\\n            }\\n        }\\n        j.setAgentProtocols(agentProtocols);\\n\\n        // persist all the additional security configs\\n        boolean result = true;\\n        for (Descriptor<?> d : Functions.getSortedDescriptorsForGlobalConfigByDescriptor(FILTER)) {\\n            result &= configureDescriptor(req, json, d);\\n        }\\n\\n        return result;\\n    }\'')]

[(97, '"long seek(Run<?, ?> run) throws IOException {\\n        class RingBuffer {\\n            long[] lastNlines = new long[n];\\n            int ptr = 0;\\n\\n            RingBuffer() {\\n                for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)\\n                    lastNlines[i] = -1;\\n            }\\n\\n            void add(long pos) {\\n                lastNlines[ptr] = pos;\\n                ptr = (ptr + 1) % lastNlines.length;\\n            }\\n\\n            long get() {\\n                long v = lastNlines[ptr];\\n                if (v < 0)    return lastNlines[0];   // didn\'t even wrap around\\n                return v;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        RingBuffer rb = new RingBuffer();\\n\\n        try (InputStream in = run.getLogInputStream()) {\\n            byte[] buf = new byte[4096];\\n            int len;\\n            byte prev = 0;\\n            long pos = 0;\\n            boolean prevIsNL = false;\\n            while ((len = in.read(buf)) >= 0) {\\n                for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {\\n                    byte ch = buf[i];\\n                    boolean isNL = ch == \'\\\\r\' || ch == \'\\\\n\';\\n                    if (!isNL && prevIsNL)  rb.add(pos);\\n                    if (isNL && prevIsNL && !(prev == \'\\\\r\' && ch == \'\\\\n\'))  rb.add(pos);\\n                    pos++;\\n                    prev = ch;\\n                    prevIsNL = isNL;\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            return rb.get();\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(3789, '\'void _cleanUpShutdownTriggers(List<Throwable> errors) {\\n        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Shutting down triggers");\\n        try {\\n            final java.util.Timer timer = Trigger.timer;\\n            if (timer != null) {\\n                final CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(1);\\n                timer.schedule(new TimerTask() {\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void run() {\\n                        timer.cancel();\\n                        latch.countDown();\\n                    }\\n                }, 0);\\n                if (latch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Triggers shut down successfully");\\n                } else {\\n                    timer.cancel();\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.INFO, "Gave up waiting for triggers to finish running");\\n                }\\n            }\\n            Trigger.timer = null;\\n        } catch (OutOfMemoryError e) {\\n            // we should just propagate this, no point trying to log\\n            throw e;\\n        } catch (LinkageError e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to shut down triggers", e);\\n            // safe to ignore and continue for this one\\n        } catch (Throwable e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(SEVERE, "Failed to shut down triggers", e);\\n            // save for later\\n            errors.add(e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(386, '"boolean isValidAuthority(String authority) {\\n        if (authority == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // check manual authority validation if specified\\n        if (authorityValidator != null && authorityValidator.isValid(authority)) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        // convert to ASCII if possible\\n        final String authorityASCII = DomainValidator.unicodeToASCII(authority);\\n\\n        Matcher authorityMatcher = AUTHORITY_PATTERN.matcher(authorityASCII);\\n        if (!authorityMatcher.matches()) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // We have to process IPV6 separately because that is parsed in a different group\\n        String ipv6 = authorityMatcher.group(PARSE_AUTHORITY_IPV6);\\n        if (ipv6 != null) {\\n            InetAddressValidator inetAddressValidator = InetAddressValidator.getInstance();\\n            if (!inetAddressValidator.isValidInet6Address(ipv6)) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            String hostLocation = authorityMatcher.group(PARSE_AUTHORITY_HOST_IP);\\n            // check if authority is hostname or IP address:\\n            // try a hostname first since that\'s much more likely\\n            if (!this.domainValidator.isValid(hostLocation)) {\\n                // try an IPv4 address\\n                InetAddressValidator inetAddressValidator = InetAddressValidator.getInstance();\\n                if (!inetAddressValidator.isValidInet4Address(hostLocation)) {\\n                    // isn\'t IPv4, so the URL is invalid\\n                    return false;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            String port = authorityMatcher.group(PARSE_AUTHORITY_PORT);\\n            if (port != null && port.length() > 0) {\\n                try {\\n                    int iPort = Integer.parseInt(port);\\n                    if (iPort < 0 || iPort > MAX_UNSIGNED_16_BIT_INT) {\\n                        return false;\\n                    }\\n                } catch (NumberFormatException nfe) {\\n                    return false; // this can happen for big numbers\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        String extra = authorityMatcher.group(PARSE_AUTHORITY_EXTRA);\\n        if (extra != null && extra.trim().length() > 0) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }"')]

[(106, '\'CronTabList create(@NonNull String format, Hash hash) {\\n        Vector<CronTab> r = new Vector<>();\\n        int lineNumber = 0;\\n        String timezone = null;\\n\\n        for (String line : format.split("\\\\\\\\r?\\\\\\\\n")) {\\n            lineNumber++;\\n            line = line.trim();\\n\\n            if (lineNumber == 1 && line.startsWith("TZ=")) {\\n                final String timezoneString = line.replace("TZ=", "");\\n                timezone = getValidTimezone(timezoneString);\\n                if (timezone != null) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "CRON with timezone {0}", timezone);\\n                } else {\\n                    throw new ANTLRException("Invalid or unsupported timezone \\\'" + timezoneString + "\\\'");\\n                }\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (line.isEmpty() || line.startsWith("#"))\\n                continue;   // ignorable line\\n            try {\\n                r.add(new CronTab(line, lineNumber, hash, timezone));\\n            } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {\\n                throw new ANTLRException(Messages.CronTabList_InvalidInput(line, e.getMessage()), e);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return new CronTabList(r);\\n    }\'')]

[(306, '\'int digest(String s) {\\n        try {\\n            MessageDigest messageDigest = createMessageDigest();\\n            messageDigest.update(s.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n            byte[] digest = messageDigest.digest();\\n\\n            // 16 bytes -> 4 bytes\\n            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {\\n                digest[i] ^= digest[i + 4] + digest[i + 8] + digest[i + 12];\\n            }\\n            return (b2i(digest[0]) << 24) | (b2i(digest[1]) << 16) | (b2i(digest[2]) << 8) | b2i(digest[3]);\\n        } catch (GeneralSecurityException e) {\\n            throw new RuntimeException("Could not generate SHA-256 hash", e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(235, '\'void updateComputerList(final boolean automaticAgentLaunch) {\\n        final ConcurrentMap<Node, Computer> computers = getComputerMap();\\n        final Set<Computer> old = new HashSet<>(computers.size());\\n        Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n            @Override\\n            public void run() {\\n                Map<String, Computer> byName = new HashMap<>();\\n                for (Computer c : computers.values()) {\\n                    old.add(c);\\n                    Node node = c.getNode();\\n                    if (node == null)\\n                        continue;   // this computer is gone\\n                    byName.put(node.getNodeName(), c);\\n                }\\n\\n                Set<Computer> used = new HashSet<>(old.size());\\n\\n                updateComputer(AbstractCIBase.this, byName, used, automaticAgentLaunch);\\n                for (Node s : getNodes()) {\\n                    long start = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n                    updateComputer(s, byName, used, automaticAgentLaunch);\\n                    if (LOG_STARTUP_PERFORMANCE && LOGGER.isLoggable(Level.FINE)) {\\n                        LOGGER.fine(String.format("Took %dms to update node %s",\\n                                System.currentTimeMillis() - start, s.getNodeName()));\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                // find out what computers are removed, and kill off all executors.\\n                // when all executors exit, it will be removed from the computers map.\\n                // so don\\\'t remove too quickly\\n                old.removeAll(used);\\n                // we need to start the process of reducing the executors on all computers as distinct\\n                // from the killing action which should not excessively use the Queue lock.\\n                for (Computer c : old) {\\n                    c.inflictMortalWound();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        });\\n        for (Computer c : old) {\\n            // when we get to here, the number of executors should be zero so this call should not need the Queue.lock\\n            killComputer(c);\\n        }\\n        getQueue().scheduleMaintenance();\\n        Listeners.notify(ComputerListener.class, false, ComputerListener::onConfigurationChange);\\n    }\'')]

[(1089, '"void removeExecutor(final Executor e) {\\n        final Runnable task = () -> {\\n            synchronized (Computer.this) {\\n                executors.remove(e);\\n                oneOffExecutors.remove(e);\\n                addNewExecutorIfNecessary();\\n                if (!isAlive()) {\\n                    AbstractCIBase ciBase = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n                    if (ciBase != null) { // TODO confirm safe to assume non-null and use getInstance()\\n                        ciBase.removeComputer(Computer.this);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        };\\n        if (!Queue.tryWithLock(task)) {\\n            // JENKINS-28840 if we couldn\'t get the lock push the operation to a separate thread to avoid deadlocks\\n            threadPoolForRemoting.submit(Queue.wrapWithLock(task));\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(332, '\'FileAndDescription getHomeDir(ServletContextEvent event) {\\n        // check the system property for the home directory first\\n        for (String name : HOME_NAMES) {\\n            String sysProp = SystemProperties.getString(name);\\n            if (sysProp != null)\\n                return new FileAndDescription(new File(sysProp.trim()), "SystemProperties.getProperty(\\\\"" + name + "\\\\")");\\n        }\\n\\n        // look at the env var next\\n        for (String name : HOME_NAMES) {\\n            String env = EnvVars.masterEnvVars.get(name);\\n            if (env != null)\\n                return new FileAndDescription(new File(env.trim()).getAbsoluteFile(), "EnvVars.masterEnvVars.get(\\\\"" + name + "\\\\")");\\n        }\\n\\n        // otherwise pick a place by ourselves\\n\\n        String root = event.getServletContext().getRealPath("/WEB-INF/workspace");\\n        if (root != null) {\\n            File ws = new File(root.trim());\\n            if (ws.exists())\\n                // Hudson <1.42 used to prefer this before ~/.hudson, so\\n                // check the existence and if it\\\'s there, use it.\\n                // otherwise if this is a new installation, prefer ~/.hudson\\n                return new FileAndDescription(ws, "getServletContext().getRealPath(\\\\"/WEB-INF/workspace\\\\")");\\n        }\\n\\n        File legacyHome = new File(new File(System.getProperty("user.home")), ".hudson");\\n        if (legacyHome.exists()) {\\n            return new FileAndDescription(legacyHome, "$user.home/.hudson"); // before rename, this is where it was stored\\n        }\\n\\n        File newHome = new File(new File(System.getProperty("user.home")), ".jenkins");\\n        return new FileAndDescription(newHome, "$user.home/.jenkins");\\n    }\'')]

[(362, '\'void load(PluginWrapper wrapper) throws IOException {\\n        // override the context classloader. This no longer makes sense,\\n        // but it is left for the backward compatibility\\n        ClassLoader old = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(wrapper.classLoader);\\n        try {\\n            String className = wrapper.getPluginClass();\\n            if (className == null) {\\n                // use the default dummy instance\\n                wrapper.setPlugin(new DummyImpl());\\n            } else {\\n                try {\\n                    Class<?> clazz = wrapper.classLoader.loadClass(className);\\n                    Object o = clazz.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();\\n                    if (!(o instanceof Plugin)) {\\n                        throw new IOException(className + " doesn\\\'t extend from hudson.Plugin");\\n                    }\\n                    wrapper.setPlugin((Plugin) o);\\n                } catch (LinkageError | ClassNotFoundException e) {\\n                    throw new IOException("Unable to load " + className + " from " + wrapper.getShortName(), e);\\n                } catch (NoSuchMethodException | InstantiationException | IllegalAccessException | InvocationTargetException e) {\\n                    throw new IOException("Unable to create instance of " + className + " from " + wrapper.getShortName(), e);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            // initialize plugin\\n            try {\\n                Plugin plugin = wrapper.getPluginOrFail();\\n                plugin.setServletContext(pluginManager.context);\\n                startPlugin(wrapper);\\n            } catch (Throwable t) {\\n                // gracefully handle any error in plugin.\\n                throw new IOException("Failed to initialize", t);\\n            }\\n        } finally {\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(old);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(274, '\'void initPageVariables(JellyContext context) {\\n        StaplerRequest currentRequest = Stapler.getCurrentRequest();\\n        currentRequest.getWebApp().getDispatchValidator().allowDispatch(currentRequest, Stapler.getCurrentResponse());\\n        String rootURL = currentRequest.getContextPath();\\n\\n        Functions h = new Functions();\\n        context.setVariable("h", h);\\n\\n\\n        // The path starts with a "/" character but does not end with a "/" character.\\n        context.setVariable("rootURL", rootURL);\\n\\n        /*\\n            load static resources from the path dedicated to a specific version.\\n            This "/static/VERSION/abc/def.ghi" path is interpreted by stapler to be\\n            the same thing as "/abc/def.ghi", but this avoids the stale cache\\n            problem when the user upgrades to new Jenkins. Stapler also sets a long\\n            future expiration dates for such static resources.\\n\\n            see https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Hyperlinks+in+HTML\\n         */\\n        context.setVariable("resURL", rootURL + getResourcePath());\\n        context.setVariable("imagesURL", rootURL + getResourcePath() + "/images");\\n        context.setVariable("divBasedFormLayout", true);\\n        context.setVariable("userAgent", currentRequest.getHeader("User-Agent"));\\n        IconSet.initPageVariables(context);\\n    }\'')]

[(1291, '"void setAgentProtocols(@NonNull Set<String> protocols) {\\n        Set<String> disabled = new TreeSet<>();\\n        Set<String> enabled = new TreeSet<>();\\n        for (AgentProtocol p : AgentProtocol.all()) {\\n            String name = p.getName();\\n            if (name != null && !p.isRequired()) {\\n                // we want to record the protocols where the admin has made a conscious decision\\n                // thus, if a protocol is opt-in, we record the admin enabling it\\n                // if a protocol is opt-out, we record the admin disabling it\\n                // We should not transition rapidly from opt-in -> opt-out -> opt-in\\n                // the scenario we want to have work is:\\n                // 1. We introduce a new protocol, it starts off as opt-in. Some admins decide to test and opt-in\\n                // 2. We decide that the protocol is ready for general use. It gets marked as opt-out. Any admins\\n                //    that took part in early testing now have their config switched to not mention the new protocol\\n                //    at all when they save their config as the protocol is now opt-out. Any admins that want to\\n                //    disable it can do so and will have their preference recorded.\\n                // 3. We decide that the protocol needs to be retired. It gets switched back to opt-in. At this point\\n                //    the initial opt-in admins, assuming they visited an upgrade to a controller with step 2, will\\n                //    have the protocol disabled for them. This is what we want. If they didn\'t upgrade to a controller\\n                //    with step 2, well there is not much we can do to differentiate them from somebody who is upgrading\\n                //    from a previous step 3 controller and had needed to keep the protocol turned on.\\n                //\\n                // What we should never do is flip-flop: opt-in -> opt-out -> opt-in -> opt-out as that will basically\\n                // clear any preference that an admin has set, but this should be ok as we only ever will be\\n                // adding new protocols and retiring old ones.\\n                if (p.isOptIn()) {\\n                    if (protocols.contains(name)) {\\n                        enabled.add(name);\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    if (!protocols.contains(name)) {\\n                        disabled.add(name);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        disabledAgentProtocols = disabled.isEmpty() ? null : new ArrayList<>(disabled);\\n        enabledAgentProtocols = enabled.isEmpty() ? null : new ArrayList<>(enabled);\\n        agentProtocols = null;\\n    }"')]

[(145, '\'void perform(Job<?, ?> job) throws IOException, InterruptedException {\\n        //Exceptions thrown by the deletion submethods are collated and reported\\n        Map<Run<?, ?>, Set<IOException>> exceptionMap = new HashMap<>();\\n\\n        LOGGER.log(FINE, "Running the log rotation for {0} with numToKeep={1} daysToKeep={2} artifactNumToKeep={3} artifactDaysToKeep={4}", new Object[] {job, numToKeep, daysToKeep, artifactNumToKeep, artifactDaysToKeep});\\n\\n        // always keep the last successful and the last stable builds\\n        Run lsb = job.getLastSuccessfulBuild();\\n        Run lstb = job.getLastStableBuild();\\n\\n        if (numToKeep != -1) {\\n            // Note that RunList.size is deprecated, and indeed here we are loading all the builds of the job.\\n            // However we would need to load the first numToKeep anyway, just to skip over them;\\n            // and we would need to load the rest anyway, to delete them.\\n            // (Using RunMap.headMap would not suffice, since we do not know if some recent builds have been deleted for other reasons,\\n            // so simply subtracting numToKeep from the currently last build number might cause us to delete too many.)\\n            RunList<? extends Run<?, ?>> builds = job.getBuilds();\\n            for (Run r : builds.subList(Math.min(builds.size(), numToKeep), builds.size())) {\\n                if (shouldKeepRun(r, lsb, lstb)) {\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                LOGGER.log(FINE, "{0} is to be removed", r);\\n                try { r.delete(); }\\n                catch (IOException ex) { exceptionMap.computeIfAbsent(r, key -> new HashSet<>()).add(ex); }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (daysToKeep != -1) {\\n            Calendar cal = new GregorianCalendar();\\n            cal.add(Calendar.DAY_OF_YEAR, -daysToKeep);\\n            Run r = job.getFirstBuild();\\n            while (r != null) {\\n                if (tooNew(r, cal)) {\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                if (!shouldKeepRun(r, lsb, lstb)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINE, "{0} is to be removed", r);\\n                    try { r.delete(); }\\n                    catch (IOException ex) { exceptionMap.computeIfAbsent(r, key -> new HashSet<>()).add(ex); }\\n                }\\n                r = r.getNextBuild();\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (artifactNumToKeep != null && artifactNumToKeep != -1) {\\n            RunList<? extends Run<?, ?>> builds = job.getBuilds();\\n            for (Run r : builds.subList(Math.min(builds.size(), artifactNumToKeep), builds.size())) {\\n                if (shouldKeepRun(r, lsb, lstb)) {\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                LOGGER.log(FINE, "{0} is to be purged of artifacts", r);\\n                try { r.deleteArtifacts(); }\\n                catch (IOException ex) { exceptionMap.computeIfAbsent(r, key -> new HashSet<>()).add(ex); }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (artifactDaysToKeep != null && artifactDaysToKeep != -1) {\\n            Calendar cal = new GregorianCalendar();\\n            cal.add(Calendar.DAY_OF_YEAR, -artifactDaysToKeep);\\n            Run r = job.getFirstBuild();\\n            while (r != null) {\\n                if (tooNew(r, cal)) {\\n                    break;\\n                }\\n                if (!shouldKeepRun(r, lsb, lstb)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(FINE, "{0} is to be purged of artifacts", r);\\n                    try { r.deleteArtifacts(); }\\n                    catch (IOException ex) { exceptionMap.computeIfAbsent(r, key -> new HashSet<>()).add(ex); }\\n                }\\n                r = r.getNextBuild();\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (!exceptionMap.isEmpty()) {\\n            //Collate all encountered exceptions into a single exception and throw that\\n            String msg = String.format(\\n                    "Failed to rotate logs for [%s]",\\n                    exceptionMap.keySet().stream().map(Object::toString).collect(Collectors.joining(", "))\\n            );\\n            throw new CompositeIOException(msg, exceptionMap.values().stream().flatMap(Collection::stream).collect(Collectors.toList()));\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(350, '\'void saveAndRemoveEntries(Predicate<Map.Entry<SaveableReference, VersionRange>> matchingPredicate) {\\n        /*\\n         * Note that there a race condition here: we acquire the lock and get localCopy which includes some\\n         * project (say); then we go through our loop and save that project; then someone POSTs a new\\n         * config.xml for the project with some old data, causing remove to be called and the project to be\\n         * added to data (in the new version); then we hit the end of this method and the project is removed\\n         * from data again, even though it again has old data.\\n         *\\n         * In practice this condition is extremely unlikely, and not a major problem even if it\\n         * does occur: just means the user will be prompted to discard less than they should have been (and\\n         * would see the warning again after next restart).\\n         */\\n        List<SaveableReference> removed = new ArrayList<>();\\n        for (Map.Entry<SaveableReference, VersionRange> entry : data.entrySet()) {\\n            if (matchingPredicate.test(entry)) {\\n                Saveable s = entry.getKey().get();\\n                if (s != null) {\\n                    try {\\n                        s.save();\\n                    } catch (Exception x) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "failed to save " + s, x);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n                removed.add(entry.getKey());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        data.keySet().removeAll(removed);\\n    }\'')]

[(211, '\'int getChunkSizeFromInputStream(final InputStream in)\\n      throws IOException {\\n\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        // States: 0=normal, 1=\\\\r was scanned, 2=inside quoted string, -1=end\\n        int state = 0;\\n        while (state != -1) {\\n        int b = in.read();\\n            if (b == -1) {\\n                throw new IOException("chunked stream ended unexpectedly");\\n            }\\n            switch (state) {\\n                case 0:\\n                    switch (b) {\\n                        case \\\'\\\\r\\\':\\n                            state = 1;\\n                            break;\\n                        case \\\'\\\\"\\\':\\n                            state = 2;\\n                            /* fall through */\\n                        default:\\n                            baos.write(b);\\n                    }\\n                    break;\\n\\n                case 1:\\n                    if (b == \\\'\\\\n\\\') {\\n                        state = -1;\\n                    } else {\\n                        // this was not CRLF\\n                        throw new IOException("Protocol violation: Unexpected"\\n                            + " single newline character in chunk size");\\n                    }\\n                    break;\\n\\n                case 2:\\n                    switch (b) {\\n                        case \\\'\\\\\\\\\\\':\\n                            b = in.read();\\n                            baos.write(b);\\n                            break;\\n                        case \\\'\\\\"\\\':\\n                            state = 0;\\n                            /* fall through */\\n                        default:\\n                            baos.write(b);\\n                    }\\n                    break;\\n                default: throw new RuntimeException("assertion failed");\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        //parse data\\n        String dataString = baos.toString(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII);\\n        int separator = dataString.indexOf(\\\';\\\');\\n        dataString = separator > 0\\n            ? dataString.substring(0, separator).trim()\\n            : dataString.trim();\\n\\n        int result;\\n        try {\\n            result = Integer.parseInt(dataString.trim(), 16);\\n        } catch (NumberFormatException e) {\\n            throw new IOException("Bad chunk size: " + dataString, e);\\n        }\\n        return result;\\n    }\'')]

[(52, '"boolean isInstalled(int major, int minor) {\\n        try {\\n            if (major == 4 && minor >= 5) {\\n                return isV45PlusInstalled(minor);\\n            } else if (major == 4 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV40Installed();\\n            } else if (major == 3 && minor == 5) {\\n                return isV35Installed();\\n            } else if (major == 3 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV35Installed() || isV30Installed();\\n            } else if (major == 2 && minor == 0) {\\n                return isV35Installed() || isV30Installed() || isV20Installed();\\n            } else {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n        } catch (JnaException e) {\\n            if (e.getErrorCode() == 2) {\\n                // thrown when openReadonly fails because the key doesn\'t exist.\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n            throw e;\\n        }\\n    }"')]

[(2152, '\'List<Future<UpdateCenter.UpdateCenterJob>> prevalidateConfig(InputStream configXml) throws IOException {\\n        Jenkins.get().checkPermission(Jenkins.ADMINISTER);\\n        List<Future<UpdateCenter.UpdateCenterJob>> jobs = new ArrayList<>();\\n        UpdateCenter uc = Jenkins.get().getUpdateCenter();\\n        // TODO call uc.updateAllSites() when available? perhaps not, since we should not block on network here\\n        for (Map.Entry<String, VersionNumber> requestedPlugin : parseRequestedPlugins(configXml).entrySet()) {\\n            PluginWrapper pw = getPlugin(requestedPlugin.getKey());\\n            if (pw == null) { // install new\\n                UpdateSite.Plugin toInstall = uc.getPlugin(requestedPlugin.getKey(), requestedPlugin.getValue());\\n                if (toInstall == null) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "No such plugin {0} to install", requestedPlugin.getKey());\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                logPluginWarnings(requestedPlugin, toInstall);\\n                jobs.add(toInstall.deploy(true));\\n            } else if (pw.isOlderThan(requestedPlugin.getValue())) { // upgrade\\n                UpdateSite.Plugin toInstall = uc.getPlugin(requestedPlugin.getKey(), requestedPlugin.getValue());\\n                if (toInstall == null) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "No such plugin {0} to upgrade", requestedPlugin.getKey());\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                if (!pw.isOlderThan(new VersionNumber(toInstall.version))) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "{0}@{1} is no newer than what we already have", new Object[] {toInstall.name, toInstall.version});\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n                logPluginWarnings(requestedPlugin, toInstall);\\n                if (!toInstall.isCompatibleWithInstalledVersion()) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(WARNING, "{0}@{1} is incompatible with the installed @{2}", new Object[] {toInstall.name, toInstall.version, pw.getVersion()});\\n                }\\n                jobs.add(toInstall.deploy(true)); // dynamicLoad=true => sure to throw RestartRequiredException, but at least message is nicer\\n            } // else already good\\n        }\\n        return jobs;\\n    }\'')]

[(238, '\'ConsoleNote readFrom(DataInputStream in) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\\n        try {\\n            byte[] preamble = new byte[PREAMBLE.length];\\n            in.readFully(preamble);\\n            if (!Arrays.equals(preamble, PREAMBLE))\\n                return null;    // not a valid preamble\\n\\n            byte[] mac;\\n            byte[] buf;\\n            try (DataInputStream decoded = new DataInputStream(Base64.getDecoder().wrap(in))) {\\n                int macSz = -decoded.readInt();\\n                int sz;\\n                if (macSz > 0) { // new format\\n                    mac = new byte[macSz];\\n                    decoded.readFully(mac);\\n                    sz = decoded.readInt();\\n                    if (sz < 0) {\\n                        throw new IOException("Corrupt stream");\\n                    }\\n                } else {\\n                    mac = null;\\n                    sz = -macSz;\\n                }\\n                buf = new byte[sz];\\n                decoded.readFully(buf);\\n            }\\n\\n            byte[] postamble = new byte[POSTAMBLE.length];\\n            in.readFully(postamble);\\n            if (!Arrays.equals(postamble, POSTAMBLE))\\n                return null;    // not a valid postamble\\n\\n            if (!INSECURE) {\\n                if (mac == null) {\\n                    throw new IOException("Refusing to deserialize unsigned note from an old log.");\\n                } else if (!MAC.checkMac(buf, mac)) {\\n                    throw new IOException("MAC mismatch");\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            Jenkins jenkins = Jenkins.getInstanceOrNull();\\n\\n            try (ObjectInputStream ois = new ObjectInputStreamEx(new GZIPInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(buf)),\\n                    jenkins != null ? jenkins.pluginManager.uberClassLoader : ConsoleNote.class.getClassLoader(),\\n                    ClassFilter.DEFAULT)) {\\n                return getConsoleNote(ois);\\n            }\\n        } catch (Error e) {\\n            // for example, bogus \\\'sz\\\' can result in OutOfMemoryError.\\n            // package that up as IOException so that the caller won\\\'t fatally die.\\n            throw new IOException(e);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(371, '\'void unmigrateBuildsDir(File builds) throws Exception {\\n        File mapFile = new File(builds, MAP_FILE);\\n        if (!mapFile.isFile()) {\\n            System.err.println(builds + " does not look to have been migrated yet; skipping");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n        for (File build : builds.listFiles()) {\\n            int number;\\n            try {\\n                number = Integer.parseInt(build.getName());\\n            } catch (NumberFormatException x) {\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            File buildXml = new File(build, "build.xml");\\n            if (!buildXml.isFile()) {\\n                System.err.println(buildXml + " did not exist");\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            String xml = Files.readString(Util.fileToPath(buildXml), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n            Matcher m = TIMESTAMP_ELT.matcher(xml);\\n            if (!m.find()) {\\n                System.err.println(buildXml + " did not contain <timestamp> as expected");\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n            long timestamp = Long.parseLong(m.group(1));\\n            String nl = m.group(2);\\n            xml = m.replaceFirst("  <number>" + number + "</number>" + nl);\\n            m = ID_ELT.matcher(xml);\\n            String id;\\n            if (m.find()) {\\n                id = m.group(1);\\n                xml = m.replaceFirst("");\\n            } else {\\n                // Post-migration build. We give it a new ID based on its timestamp.\\n                id = legacyIdFormatter.format(new Date(timestamp));\\n            }\\n            Files.writeString(Util.fileToPath(buildXml), xml, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n            if (!build.renameTo(new File(builds, id))) {\\n                System.err.println(build + " could not be renamed");\\n            }\\n            Util.createSymlink(builds, id, Integer.toString(number), StreamTaskListener.fromStderr());\\n        }\\n        Util.deleteFile(mapFile);\\n        System.err.println(builds + " has been restored to its original format");\\n    }\'')]

[(80, '\'void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, final FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        String uri = request instanceof HttpServletRequest ? ((HttpServletRequest) request).getRequestURI() : "?";\\n        Level level = UNINTERESTING_URIS.matcher(uri).find() ? Level.FINER : Level.FINE;\\n        LOGGER.log(level, () -> "starting filter on " + uri);\\n\\n        new FilterChain() {\\n            private int position = 0;\\n            // capture the array for thread-safety\\n            private final Filter[] filters = ChainedServletFilter.this.filters;\\n\\n            @Override\\n            public void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n                if (position == filters.length) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(level, () -> uri + " end: " + status());\\n                    chain.doFilter(request, response);\\n                } else {\\n                    Filter next = filters[position++];\\n                    try {\\n                        LOGGER.log(level, () -> uri + " @" + position + " " + next + " »");\\n                        next.doFilter(request, response, this);\\n                        LOGGER.log(level, () -> uri + " @" + position + " " + next + " « success: " + status());\\n                    } catch (IOException | ServletException | RuntimeException x) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(level, () -> uri + " @" + position + " " + next + " « " + x + ": " + status());\\n                        throw x;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            private int status() {\\n                return response instanceof HttpServletResponse ? ((HttpServletResponse) response).getStatus() : 0;\\n            }\\n        }.doFilter(request, response);\\n\\n    }\'')]

[(327, '\'String summarize(File dir) throws Exception {\\n        File[] kids = dir.listFiles();\\n        Map<String, String> m = new TreeMap<>();\\n        for (File kid : kids) {\\n            String notation;\\n            String symlink = Util.resolveSymlink(kid);\\n            if (symlink != null) {\\n                notation = "→" + symlink;\\n            } else if (kid.isFile()) {\\n                notation = "\\\'" + Files.readString(kid.toPath(), Charset.defaultCharset()) + "\\\'";\\n            } else if (kid.isDirectory()) {\\n                notation = summarize(kid);\\n            } else {\\n                notation = "?";\\n            }\\n            m.put(kid.getName(), notation);\\n        }\\n        return m.toString();\\n    }\'')]

[(2240, '\'Map<String, VersionNumber> parseRequestedPlugins(InputStream configXml) throws IOException {\\n        final Map<String, VersionNumber> requestedPlugins = new TreeMap<>();\\n        try {\\n            SAXParserFactory spf = SAXParserFactory.newInstance();\\n            spf.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);\\n            spf.setFeature(XMLConstants.FEATURE_SECURE_PROCESSING, true);\\n            spf.newSAXParser().parse(configXml, new DefaultHandler() {\\n                @Override public void startElement(String uri, String localName, String qName, Attributes attributes) throws SAXException {\\n                    String plugin = attributes.getValue("plugin");\\n                    if (plugin == null) {\\n                        return;\\n                    }\\n                    if (!plugin.matches("[^@]+@[^@]+")) {\\n                        throw new SAXException("Malformed plugin attribute: " + plugin);\\n                    }\\n                    int at = plugin.indexOf(\\\'@\\\');\\n                    String shortName = plugin.substring(0, at);\\n                    VersionNumber existing = requestedPlugins.get(shortName);\\n                    VersionNumber requested = new VersionNumber(plugin.substring(at + 1));\\n                    if (existing == null || existing.compareTo(requested) < 0) {\\n                        requestedPlugins.put(shortName, requested);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n                @Override public InputSource resolveEntity(String publicId, String systemId) throws IOException,\\n                        SAXException {\\n                    return RestrictiveEntityResolver.INSTANCE.resolveEntity(publicId, systemId);\\n                }\\n\\n            });\\n        } catch (SAXException x) {\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to parse XML", x);\\n        } catch (ParserConfigurationException e) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(e); // impossible since we don\\\'t tweak XMLParser\\n        }\\n        return requestedPlugins;\\n    }\'')]

[(772, '\'List<List<Path>> buildChildPaths(VirtualFile cur, Locale locale) throws IOException {\\n            List<List<Path>> r = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n            VirtualFile[] files = cur.list(getOpenOptions());\\n                Arrays.sort(files, new FileComparator(locale));\\n\\n                for (VirtualFile f : files) {\\n                    Path p = new Path(Util.rawEncode(f.getName()), f.getName(), f.isDirectory(), f.length(), f.canRead(), f.lastModified());\\n                    if (!f.isDirectory()) {\\n                        r.add(List.of(p));\\n                    } else {\\n                        // find all empty intermediate directory\\n                        List<Path> l = new ArrayList<>();\\n                        l.add(p);\\n                        String relPath = Util.rawEncode(f.getName());\\n                        while (true) {\\n                            // files that don\\\'t start with \\\'.\\\' qualify for \\\'meaningful files\\\', nor SCM related files\\n                            List<VirtualFile> sub = new ArrayList<>();\\n                            for (VirtualFile vf : f.list(getOpenOptions())) {\\n                                String name = vf.getName();\\n                                if (!name.startsWith(".") && !name.equals("CVS") && !name.equals(".svn")) {\\n                                    sub.add(vf);\\n                                }\\n                            }\\n                            if (sub.size() != 1 || !sub.get(0).isDirectory())\\n                                break;\\n                            f = sub.get(0);\\n                            relPath += \\\'/\\\' + Util.rawEncode(f.getName());\\n                            l.add(new Path(relPath, f.getName(), true, f.length(), f.canRead(), f.lastModified()));\\n                        }\\n                        r.add(l);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n\\n            return r;\\n    }\'')]
