[(127, "'void set(String format, int line, Hash hash, String timezone) {\\n        CrontabLexer lexer = new CrontabLexer(CharStreams.fromString(format));\\n        lexer.removeErrorListeners();\\n        lexer.addErrorListener(new JenkinsANTLRErrorListener());\\n        lexer.setLine(line);\\n        CrontabParser parser = new CrontabParser(new CommonTokenStream(lexer));\\n        parser.removeErrorListeners();\\n        parser.addErrorListener(new JenkinsANTLRErrorListener(parser::getErrorMessage));\\n        parser.setHash(hash);\\n        spec = format;\\n        specTimezone = timezone;\\n\\n        parser.startRule(this);\\n        if ((dayOfWeek & (1 << 7)) != 0) {\\n            dayOfWeek |= 1; // copy bit 7 over to bit 0\\n            dayOfWeek &= ~(1 << 7); // clear bit 7 or CalendarField#ceil will return an invalid value 7\\n        }\\n    }'")]

 try {\\n                session.handler = provider.handle(req, rsp, new Provider.Listener() {\\n                    private Object providerSession;\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void onWebSocketConnect(Object providerSession) {\\n                        this.providerSession = providerSession;\\n                        session.startPings();\\n                        session.opened();\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public Object getProviderSession() {\\n                        return providerSession;\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void onWebSocketClose(int statusCode, String reason) {\\n                        session.stopPings();\\n                        session.closed(statusCode, reason);\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void onWebSocketError(Throwable cause) {\\n                        if (cause instanceof ClosedChannelException) {\\n                            onWebSocketClose(0, cause.toString());\\n                        } else {\\n                            session.error(cause);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void onWebSocketBinary(byte[] payload, int offset, int length) {\\n                        try {\\n                            session.binary(payload, offset, length);\\n                        } catch (IOException x) {\\n                            session.error(x);\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void onWebSocketText(String message) {\\n                        try {\\n                            session.text(message);\\n                        } catch (IOException x) {\\n                            session.error(x);\\n                        }\\n [(124, '\'Channel forProcess(String name, ExecutorService execService, final Process proc, OutputStream header) throws IOException {\\n        final Thread thread = new StreamCopyThread(name + " stderr", proc.getErrorStream(), header);\\n        thread.start();\\n\\n        ChannelBuilder cb = new ChannelBuilder(name, execService) {\\n            @Override\\n            public Channel build(CommandTransport transport) throws IOException {\\n                return new Channel(this, transport) {\\n                    /**\\n                     * Kill the process when the channel is severed.\\n                     */\\n                    @Override\\n                    public synchronized void terminate(IOException e) {\\n                        super.terminate(e);\\n                        proc.destroy();\\n                        // the stderr copier should exit by itself\\n                    }\\n\\n                    @Override\\n                    public synchronized void join() throws InterruptedException {\\n                        super.join();\\n                        // wait for the child process to complete, too\\n                        proc.waitFor();\\n                        thread.join();\\n                    }\\n                };\\n            }\\n        };\\n        cb.withHeaderStream(header);\\n\\n        Executor executor = Executor.currentExecutor();\\n        Object context = executor != null ? executor.getOwner() : proc;\\n        for (ChannelConfigurator cc : ChannelConfigurator.all()) {\\n            cc.onChannelBuilding(cb, context);\\n        }\\n\\n        return cb.build(proc.getInputStream(), proc.getOutputStream());\\n    }\'')]

[(1779, "'Path createDirectories(@NonNull Path dir, FileAttribute<?>... attrs) throws IOException {\\n        dir = dir.toAbsolutePath();\\n\\n        Path parent;\\n        for (parent = dir.getParent(); parent != null; parent = parent.getParent()) {\\n            if (Files.exists(parent)) {\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        if (parent == null) {\\n            if (Files.isDirectory(dir)) {\\n                return dir;\\n            } else {\\n                try {\\n                    return Files.createDirectory(dir, attrs);\\n                } catch (FileAlreadyExistsException e) {\\n                    if (Files.isDirectory(dir)) {\\n                        // a concurrent caller won the race\\n                        return dir;\\n                    } else {\\n                        throw e;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        Path child = parent;\\n        for (Path name : parent.relativize(dir)) {\\n            child = child.resolve(name);\\n            if (!Files.isDirectory(child)) {\\n                try {\\n                    Files.createDirectory(child, attrs);\\n                } catch (FileAlreadyExistsException e) {\\n                    if (Files.isDirectory(child)) {\\n                        // a concurrent caller won the race\\n                    } else {\\n                        throw e;\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return dir;\\n    }'")]

[(127, '\'Resource _getConflict(ResourceList lhs, ResourceList rhs) {\\n        for (Map.Entry<Resource, Integer> r : lhs.write.entrySet()) {\\n            for (Resource l : rhs.all) {\\n                Integer v = rhs.write.get(l);\\n                if (v != null) // this is write/write conflict.\\n                    v += r.getValue();\\n                else // Otherwise set it to a very large value, since it\\\'s read/write conflict\\n                    v = MAX_INT;\\n                if (r.getKey().isCollidingWith(l, unbox(v))) {\\n                    LOGGER.info("Collision with " + r + " and " + l);\\n                    return r.getKey();\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }\'')]

[(83, '\'void visit(File file, String relativePath) throws IOException {\\n        if (Functions.isWindows())\\n            relativePath = relativePath.replace(\\\'\\\\\\\\\\\', \\\'/\\\');\\n\\n        BasicFileAttributes basicFileAttributes = Files.readAttributes(Util.fileToPath(file), BasicFileAttributes.class);\\n        if (basicFileAttributes.isDirectory())\\n            relativePath += \\\'/\\\';\\n        TarArchiveEntry te = new TarArchiveEntry(relativePath);\\n        int mode = IOUtils.mode(file);\\n        if (mode != -1)   te.setMode(mode);\\n        te.setModTime(basicFileAttributes.lastModifiedTime().toMillis());\\n        long size = 0;\\n\\n        if (!basicFileAttributes.isDirectory()) {\\n            size = basicFileAttributes.size();\\n            te.setSize(size);\\n        }\\n        tar.putArchiveEntry(te);\\n        try {\\n            if (!basicFileAttributes.isDirectory()) {\\n                // ensure we don\\\'t write more bytes than the declared when we created the entry\\n\\n                try (InputStream fin = Files.newInputStream(file.toPath());\\n                     BoundedInputStream in = new BoundedInputStream(fin, size)) {\\n                    // Separate try block not to wrap exception thrown while opening the input stream into an exception\\n                    // indicating a problem while writing\\n                    try {\\n                        int len;\\n                        while ((len = in.read(buf)) >= 0) {\\n                            tar.write(buf, 0, len);\\n                        }\\n                    } catch (IOException | InvalidPathException e) { // log the exception in any case\\n                        throw new IOException("Error writing to tar file from: " + file, e);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } finally { // always close the entry\\n            tar.closeArchiveEntry();\\n        }\\n        entriesWritten++;\\n    }\'')]

[(518, '\'Class determineType(HierarchicalStreamReader reader, boolean validField, Object result, String fieldName, Class definedInCls) {\\n        String classAttribute = reader.getAttribute(mapper.aliasForAttribute("class"));\\n        if (classAttribute != null) {\\n            Class specifiedType = mapper.realClass(classAttribute);\\n            Class fieldType = reflectionProvider.getFieldType(result, fieldName, definedInCls);\\n            if (fieldType.isAssignableFrom(specifiedType))\\n                // make sure that the specified type in XML is compatible with the field type.\\n                // this allows the code to evolve in more flexible way.\\n                return specifiedType;\\n        }\\n        if (!validField) {\\n            Class itemType = mapper.getItemTypeForItemFieldName(result.getClass(), fieldName);\\n            if (itemType != null) {\\n                return itemType;\\n            } else {\\n                return mapper.realClass(reader.getNodeName());\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            Class fieldType = reflectionProvider.getFieldType(result, fieldName, definedInCls);\\n            return mapper.defaultImplementationOf(fieldType);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(708, '\'void addDependencies(URL hpiResUrl, String fromPath, Set<URL> dependencySet) throws URISyntaxException, MalformedURLException {\\n        if (dependencySet.contains(hpiResUrl)) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        Manifest manifest = parsePluginManifest(hpiResUrl);\\n        String dependencySpec = manifest.getMainAttributes().getValue("Plugin-Dependencies");\\n        if (dependencySpec != null) {\\n            String[] dependencyTokens = dependencySpec.split(",");\\n            ServletContext context = Jenkins.get().servletContext;\\n\\n            for (String dependencyToken : dependencyTokens) {\\n                if (dependencyToken.endsWith(";resolution:=optional")) {\\n                    // ignore optional dependencies\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n\\n                String[] artifactIdVersionPair = dependencyToken.split(":");\\n                String artifactId = artifactIdVersionPair[0];\\n                VersionNumber dependencyVersion = new VersionNumber(artifactIdVersionPair[1]);\\n\\n                PluginManager manager = Jenkins.get().getPluginManager();\\n                VersionNumber installedVersion = manager.getPluginVersion(manager.rootDir, artifactId);\\n                if (installedVersion != null && !installedVersion.isOlderThan(dependencyVersion)) {\\n                    // Do not downgrade dependencies that are already installed.\\n                    continue;\\n                }\\n\\n                URL dependencyURL = context.getResource(fromPath + "/" + artifactId + ".hpi");\\n\\n                if (dependencyURL == null) {\\n                    // Maybe bundling has changed .jpi files\\n                    dependencyURL = context.getResource(fromPath + "/" + artifactId + ".jpi");\\n                }\\n\\n                if (dependencyURL != null) {\\n                    // And transitive deps...\\n                    addDependencies(dependencyURL, fromPath, dependencySet);\\n                    // And then add the current plugin\\n                    dependencySet.add(dependencyURL);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(373, "'Calendar ceil(Calendar cal) {\\n        Calendar twoYearsFuture = (Calendar) cal.clone();\\n        twoYearsFuture.add(Calendar.YEAR, 2);\\n        OUTER:\\n        while (true) {\\n            if (cal.compareTo(twoYearsFuture) > 0) {\\n                // we went too far into the future\\n                throw new RareOrImpossibleDateException();\\n            }\\n            for (CalendarField f : CalendarField.ADJUST_ORDER) {\\n                int cur = f.valueOf(cal);\\n                int next = f.ceil(this, cur);\\n                if (cur == next)  continue;   // this field is already in a good shape. move on to next\\n\\n                // we are modifying this field, so clear all the lower level fields\\n                for (CalendarField l = f.lowerField; l != null; l = l.lowerField)\\n                    l.clear(cal);\\n\\n                if (next < 0) {\\n                    // we need to roll over to the next field.\\n                    f.rollUp(cal, 1);\\n                    f.setTo(cal, f.first(this));\\n                    // since higher order field is affected by this, we need to restart from all over\\n                    continue OUTER;\\n                } else {\\n                    f.setTo(cal, next);\\n                    //check if value was actually set\\n                    if (f.valueOf(cal) != next) {\\n                        // we need to roll over to the next field.\\n                        f.rollUp(cal, 1);\\n                        f.setTo(cal, f.first(this));\\n                        // since higher order field is affected by this, we need to restart from all over\\n                        continue OUTER;\\n                    }\\n                    if (f.redoAdjustmentIfModified)\\n                        continue OUTER; // when we modify DAY_OF_MONTH and DAY_OF_WEEK, do it all over from the top\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return cal; // all fields adjusted\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(288, '\'Map<String, JSONObject> convertToTokenMap(Object tokenStoreData) {\\n        if (tokenStoreData == null) {\\n            // in case there are no token\\n            return Collections.emptyMap();\\n        } else if (tokenStoreData instanceof JSONObject) {\\n            // in case there is only one token\\n            JSONObject singleTokenData = (JSONObject) tokenStoreData;\\n            Map<String, JSONObject> result = new HashMap<>();\\n            addJSONTokenIntoMap(result, singleTokenData);\\n            return result;\\n        } else if (tokenStoreData instanceof JSONArray) {\\n            // in case there are multiple tokens\\n            JSONArray tokenArray = (JSONArray) tokenStoreData;\\n            Map<String, JSONObject> result = new HashMap<>();\\n            for (int i = 0; i < tokenArray.size(); i++) {\\n                JSONObject tokenData = tokenArray.getJSONObject(i);\\n                addJSONTokenIntoMap(result, tokenData);\\n            }\\n            return result;\\n        }\\n\\n        throw HttpResponses.error(400, "Unexpected class received for the token store information");\\n    }\'')]

see AuthenticationProcessingFilter2#successfulAuthentication for alternative\\n                apf.setSessionAuthenticationStrategy(new SessionFixationProtectionStrategy());\\n            }\\n            apf.setRememberMeServices(sc.rememberMe2);\\n            final AuthenticationSuccessHandler successHandler = new AuthenticationSuccessHandler();\\n            successHandler.setTargetUrlParameter("from");\\n            apf.setAuthenticationSuccessHandler(successHandler);\\n            apf.setAuthenticationFailureHandler(new SimpleUrlAuthenticationFailureHandler("/loginError"));\\n            filters.add(apf);\\n        }\\n        filters.add(new RememberMeAuthenticationFilter(sc.manager2, sc.rememberMe2));\\n        filters.addAll(commonFilters());\\n        return new ChainedServletFilter(filters);\\n    }\'')]

[(39, "'User isConnectingUsingApiToken(String username, String tokenValue) {\\n        User user = User.getById(username, false);\\n        if (user == null) {\\n            ApiTokenPropertyConfiguration apiTokenConfiguration = GlobalConfiguration.all().getInstance(ApiTokenPropertyConfiguration.class);\\n            if (apiTokenConfiguration.isTokenGenerationOnCreationEnabled()) {\\n                String generatedTokenOnCreation = Util.getDigestOf(ApiTokenProperty.API_KEY_SEED.mac(username));\\n                boolean areTokenEqual = MessageDigest.isEqual(\\n                        generatedTokenOnCreation.getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII),\\n                        tokenValue.getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII)\\n                );\\n                if (areTokenEqual) {\\n                    // directly return the user freshly created\\n                    // and no need to check its token as the generated token\\n                    // will be the same as the one we checked just above\\n                    return User.getById(username, true);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        } else {\\n            ApiTokenProperty t = user.getProperty(ApiTokenProperty.class);\\n            if (t != null && t.matchesPassword(tokenValue)) {\\n                return user;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return null;\\n    }'")]

[(92, '\'boolean isValidInet4Address(String inet4Address) {\\n        // verify that address conforms to generic IPv4 format\\n        String[] groups = ipv4Validator.match(inet4Address);\\n\\n        if (groups == null) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n\\n        // verify that address subgroups are legal\\n        for (String ipSegment : groups) {\\n            if (ipSegment == null || ipSegment.isEmpty()) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            int iIpSegment;\\n\\n            try {\\n                iIpSegment = Integer.parseInt(ipSegment);\\n            } catch (NumberFormatException e) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (iIpSegment > IPV4_MAX_OCTET_VALUE) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n            if (ipSegment.length() > 1 && ipSegment.startsWith("0")) {\\n                return false;\\n            }\\n\\n        }\\n\\n        return true;\\n    }\'')]

[(58, '\'void safeTransform(@NonNull Source source, @NonNull Result out) throws TransformerException,\\n            SAXException {\\n\\n        InputSource src = SAXSource.sourceToInputSource(source);\\n        if (src != null) {\\n            SAXTransformerFactory stFactory = (SAXTransformerFactory) TransformerFactory.newInstance();\\n            stFactory.setFeature(XMLConstants.FEATURE_SECURE_PROCESSING, true);\\n\\n            XMLReader xmlReader = XMLReaderFactory.createXMLReader();\\n            try {\\n                xmlReader.setFeature(FEATURE_HTTP_XML_ORG_SAX_FEATURES_EXTERNAL_GENERAL_ENTITIES, false);\\n            }\\n            catch (SAXException ignored) { /* ignored */ }\\n            try {\\n                xmlReader.setFeature(FEATURE_HTTP_XML_ORG_SAX_FEATURES_EXTERNAL_PARAMETER_ENTITIES, false);\\n            }\\n            catch (SAXException ignored) { /* ignored */ }\\n            // defend against XXE\\n            // the above features should strip out entities - however the feature may not be supported depending\\n            // on the xml implementation used and this is out of our control.\\n            // So add a fallback plan if all else fails.\\n            xmlReader.setEntityResolver(RestrictiveEntityResolver.INSTANCE);\\n            SAXSource saxSource = new SAXSource(xmlReader, src);\\n            _transform(saxSource, out);\\n        }\\n        else {\\n            // for some reason we could not convert source\\n            // this applies to DOMSource and StAXSource - and possibly 3rd party implementations...\\n            // a DOMSource can already be compromised as it is parsed by the time it gets to us.\\n            if (SystemProperties.getBoolean(DISABLED_PROPERTY_NAME)) {\\n                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING,  "XML external entity (XXE) prevention has been disabled by the system " +\\n                        "property {0}=true Your system may be vulnerable to XXE attacks.", DISABLED_PROPERTY_NAME);\\n                if (LOGGER.isLoggable(Level.FINE)) {\\n                    LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "Caller stack trace: ", new Exception("XXE Prevention caller history"));\\n                }\\n                _transform(source, out);\\n            }\\n            else {\\n                throw new TransformerException("Could not convert source of type " + source.getClass() + " and " +\\n                        "XXEPrevention is enabled.");\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(319, '\'String getRelativeNameFrom(String itemFullName, String groupFullName) {\\n        String[] itemFullNameA = itemFullName.isEmpty() ? MemoryReductionUtil.EMPTY_STRING_ARRAY : itemFullName.split("/");\\n        String[] groupFullNameA = groupFullName.isEmpty() ? MemoryReductionUtil.EMPTY_STRING_ARRAY : groupFullName.split("/");\\n        for (int i = 0; ; i++) {\\n            if (i == itemFullNameA.length) {\\n                if (i == groupFullNameA.length) {\\n                    // itemFullName and groupFullName are identical\\n                    return ".";\\n                } else {\\n                    // itemFullName is an ancestor of groupFullName; insert ../ for rest of groupFullName\\n                    StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\\n                    for (int j = 0; j < groupFullNameA.length - itemFullNameA.length; j++) {\\n                        if (j > 0) {\\n                            b.append(\\\'/\\\');\\n                        }\\n                        b.append("..");\\n                    }\\n                    return b.toString();\\n                }\\n            } else if (i == groupFullNameA.length) {\\n                // groupFullName is an ancestor of itemFullName; insert rest of itemFullName\\n                StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\\n                for (int j = i; j < itemFullNameA.length; j++) {\\n                    if (j > i) {\\n                        b.append(\\\'/\\\');\\n                    }\\n                    b.append(itemFullNameA[j]);\\n                }\\n                return b.toString();\\n            } else if (itemFullNameA[i].equals(groupFullNameA[i])) {\\n                // identical up to this point\\n                continue;\\n            } else {\\n                // first mismatch; insert ../ for rest of groupFullName, then rest of itemFullName\\n                StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\\n                for (int j = i; j < groupFullNameA.length; j++) {\\n                    if (j > i) {\\n                        b.append(\\\'/\\\');\\n                    }\\n                    b.append("..");\\n                }\\n                for (int j = i; [(945, '"String encode(String s, boolean[] map) {\\n        boolean escaped = false;\\n        StringBuilder out = null;\\n        CharsetEncoder enc = null;\\n        CharBuffer buf = null;\\n        char c;\\n        for (int i = 0, m = s.length(); i < m; i++) {\\n            int codePoint = Character.codePointAt(s, i);\\n            if ((codePoint & 0xffffff80) == 0) { // 1 byte\\n                c = s.charAt(i);\\n                if (c > 122 || map[c]) {\\n                    if (!escaped) {\\n                        out = new StringBuilder(i + (m - i) * 3);\\n                        out.append(s, 0, i);\\n                        escaped = true;\\n                    }\\n                    if (enc == null || buf == null) {\\n                        enc = StandardCharsets.UTF_8.newEncoder();\\n                        buf = CharBuffer.allocate(1);\\n                    }\\n                    // 1 char -> UTF8\\n                    buf.put(0, c);\\n                    buf.rewind();\\n                    try {\\n                        ByteBuffer bytes = enc.encode(buf);\\n                        while (bytes.hasRemaining()) {\\n                            byte b = bytes.get();\\n                            out.append(\'%\');\\n                            out.append(toDigit((b >> 4) & 0xF));\\n                            out.append(toDigit(b & 0xF));\\n                        }\\n                    } catch (CharacterCodingException ex) {\\n                    }\\n                } else if (escaped) {\\n                    out.append(c);\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                if (!escaped) {\\n                    out = new StringBuilder(i + (m - i) * 3);\\n                    out.append(s, 0, i);\\n                    escaped = true;\\n                }\\n\\n                byte[] bytes = new String(new int[] { codePoint }, 0, 1).getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n                for (byte aByte : bytes) {\\n                    out.append(\'%\');\\n                    out.append(toDigit((aByte >> 4) & 0xF));\\n                    out.append(toDigit(aByte & 0xF));\\n                }\\n\\n                if (Character.charCount(codePoint) > 1) {\\n                    i++; // we processed two characters\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return escaped ? out.toString() : s;\\n    }"')]

[(2231, '\'void denySymlink(File file, String root, OpenOption... openOptions) throws IOException {\\n        /* This should be checked right before the file is opened or otherwise traversed.\\n           If at all possible, it should also be checked immediately afterwards.\\n           This narrows any possible race conditions that may exist in weird situations,\\n           platforms, or implementations.\\n           newInputStreamDenyingSymlinkAsNeeded(...) demonstrates how this would be done.\\n\\n           This is useful for preventing symlink following on systems that don\\\'t support\\n           LinkOption.NOFOLLOW_LINK. [(233, "'boolean replaceNode(final Node oldOne, final @NonNull Node newOne) throws IOException {\\n        if (ENFORCE_NAME_RESTRICTIONS) {\\n            Jenkins.checkGoodName(newOne.getNodeName());\\n        }\\n\\n        if (oldOne == nodes.get(oldOne.getNodeName())) {\\n            // use the queue lock until Nodes has a way of directly modifying a single node.\\n            Queue.withLock(new Runnable() {\\n                @Override\\n                public void run() {\\n                    Nodes.this.nodes.remove(oldOne.getNodeName());\\n                    Nodes.this.nodes.put(newOne.getNodeName(), newOne);\\n                    jenkins.updateComputerList();\\n                    jenkins.trimLabels(oldOne, newOne);\\n                }\\n            });\\n            updateNode(newOne);\\n            if (!newOne.getNodeName().equals(oldOne.getNodeName())) {\\n                Util.deleteRecursive(new File(getNodesDir(), oldOne.getNodeName()));\\n            }\\n            NodeListener.fireOnUpdated(oldOne, newOne);\\n\\n            return true;\\n        } else {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n    }'")]

[(1221, "'int getUpstreamRelationship(AbstractProject that) {\\n        FingerprintAction f = getAction(FingerprintAction.class);\\n        if (f == null)     return -1;\\n\\n        int n = -1;\\n\\n        // look for fingerprints that point to the given project as the source, and merge them all\\n        for (Fingerprint e : f.getFingerprints().values()) {\\n            if (upstreamCulprits) {\\n                // With upstreamCulprits, we allow upstream relationships\\n                // from intermediate jobs\\n                Fingerprint.RangeSet rangeset = e.getRangeSet(that);\\n                if (!rangeset.isEmpty()) {\\n                    n = Math.max(n, rangeset.listNumbersReverse().iterator().next());\\n                }\\n            } else {\\n                BuildPtr o = e.getOriginal();\\n                if (o != null && o.belongsTo(that))\\n                    n = Math.max(n, o.getNumber());\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        return n;\\n    }'")]

[(3437, '\'FormValidation validateRelativePath(String value, boolean errorIfNotExist, boolean expectingFile) throws IOException {\\n        checkPermissionForValidate();\\n\\n        value = fixEmpty(value);\\n\\n        // none entered yet, or something is seriously wrong\\n        if (value == null) return FormValidation.ok();\\n\\n        // a common mistake is to use wildcard\\n        if (value.contains("*")) return FormValidation.error(Messages.FilePath_validateRelativePath_wildcardNotAllowed());\\n\\n        try {\\n            if (!exists())    // no base directory. can\\\'t check\\n                return FormValidation.ok();\\n\\n            FilePath path = child(value);\\n            if (path.exists()) {\\n                if (expectingFile) {\\n                    if (!path.isDirectory())\\n                        return FormValidation.ok();\\n                    else\\n                        return FormValidation.error(Messages.FilePath_validateRelativePath_notFile(value));\\n                } else {\\n                    if (path.isDirectory())\\n                        return FormValidation.ok();\\n                    else\\n                        return FormValidation.error(Messages.FilePath_validateRelativePath_notDirectory(value));\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            String msg = expectingFile ? Messages.FilePath_validateRelativePath_noSuchFile(value) :\\n                Messages.FilePath_validateRelativePath_noSuchDirectory(value);\\n            if (errorIfNotExist)     return FormValidation.error(msg);\\n            else                    return FormValidation.warning(msg);\\n        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\\n            return FormValidation.ok();\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(140, '\'void _doBuild(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp, @QueryParameter TimeDuration delay) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        if (delay == null)\\n            delay = new TimeDuration(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.convert(getJob().getQuietPeriod(), TimeUnit.SECONDS));\\n\\n\\n        List<ParameterValue> values = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        JSONObject formData = req.getSubmittedForm();\\n        Object parameter = formData.get("parameter");\\n        if (parameter != null) {\\n            JSONArray a = JSONArray.fromObject(parameter);\\n\\n            for (Object o : a) {\\n                JSONObject jo = (JSONObject) o;\\n                String name = jo.getString("name");\\n\\n                ParameterDefinition d = getParameterDefinition(name);\\n                if (d == null)\\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException("No such parameter definition: " + name);\\n                ParameterValue parameterValue = d.createValue(req, jo);\\n                if (parameterValue != null) {\\n                    values.add(parameterValue);\\n                } else {\\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Cannot retrieve the parameter value: " + name);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        WaitingItem item = Jenkins.get().getQueue().schedule(\\n                getJob(), delay.getTimeInSeconds(), new ParametersAction(values), new CauseAction(new Cause.UserIdCause()));\\n        if (item != null) {\\n            String url = formData.optString("redirectTo");\\n            if (url == null || !Util.isSafeToRedirectTo(url))   // avoid open redirect\\n                url = req.getContextPath() + \\\'/\\\' + item.getUrl();\\n            rsp.sendRedirect(formData.optInt("statusCode", SC_CREATED), url);\\n        } else\\n            // send the user back to the job top page.\\n            rsp.sendRedirect(".");\\n    }\'')]

[(129, '\'T get(@NonNull String key, boolean createIfNotExist, P createParams) throws IOException {\\n        while (true) {\\n            totalQuery.incrementAndGet();\\n            Object value = core.get(key);\\n\\n            if (value instanceof SoftReference) {\\n                SoftReference<T> wfp = (SoftReference<T>) value;\\n                T t = wfp.get();\\n                if (t != null) {\\n                    cacheHit.incrementAndGet();\\n                    return t;  // found it\\n                }\\n                weakRefLost.incrementAndGet();\\n            }\\n            if (value instanceof Loading) {\\n                // another thread is loading it. get the value from there.\\n                T t = ((Loading<T>) value).get();\\n                if (t != null || !createIfNotExist)\\n                    return t;   // found it (t!=null) or we are just \\\'get\\\' (!createIfNotExist)\\n            }\\n\\n            // the fingerprint doesn\\\'t seem to be loaded thus far, so let\\\'s load it now.\\n            // the care needs to be taken that other threads might be trying to do the same.\\n            Loading<T> l = new Loading<>();\\n            if (value == null ? core.putIfAbsent(key, l) != null : !core.replace(key, value, l)) {\\n                // the value has changed since then. another thread is attempting to do the same.\\n                // go back to square 1 and try it again.\\n                continue;\\n            }\\n\\n            T t = null;\\n            try {\\n                t = load(key);\\n                if (t == null && createIfNotExist) {\\n                    t = create(key, createParams);    // create the new data\\n                    if (t == null)\\n                        throw new IllegalStateException("Bug in the derived class"); // bug in the derived classes\\n                }\\n            } catch (IOException e) {\\n                loadFailure.incrementAndGet();\\n                throw e;\\n            } finally {\\n                // let other threads know that the value is available now.\\n                // when the original thread failed to load, this should set it to null.\\n                l.set(t);\\n            }\\n\\n            // the map needs to be updated to reflect the result of loading\\n            if (t != null)\\n                core.put(key, new SoftReference<>(t));\\n            else\\n                core.remove(key);\\n\\n            return t;\\n        }\\n\\n    }\'')]

[(243, '\'String loadFile(@NonNull File logfile, @NonNull Charset charset) throws IOException {\\n        // Note: Until charset handling is resolved (e.g. by implementing\\n        // https://issues.jenkins.io/browse/JENKINS-48923 ), this method\\n        // must be able to handle character encoding errors. We need to make\\n        // sure that in such cases, no CharacterCodingException is thrown.\\n        //\\n        // One approach that cannot be used is Files.newBufferedReader, which\\n        // creates its CharsetDecoder with the default behavior of reporting\\n        // malformed input and unmappable character errors. [(99, '\'void doXml(StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp,\\n                      @QueryParameter String xpath,\\n                      @QueryParameter String wrapper,\\n                      @QueryParameter String tree,\\n                      @QueryParameter int depth) throws IOException, ServletException {\\n        setHeaders(rsp);\\n\\n        String[] excludes = req.getParameterValues("exclude");\\n\\n        if (xpath == null && excludes == null) {\\n            // serve the whole thing\\n            rsp.serveExposedBean(req, bean, Flavor.XML);\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        StringWriter sw = new StringWriter();\\n\\n        // first write to String\\n        Model p = MODEL_BUILDER.get(bean.getClass());\\n        TreePruner pruner = tree != null ? new NamedPathPruner(tree) : new ByDepth(1 - depth);\\n        p.writeTo(bean, pruner, Flavor.XML.createDataWriter(bean, sw));\\n\\n        // apply XPath\\n        FilteredFunctionContext functionContext = new FilteredFunctionContext();\\n        Object result;\\n        try {\\n            Document dom = new SAXReader().read(new StringReader(sw.toString()));\\n            // apply exclusions\\n            if (excludes != null) {\\n                for (String exclude : excludes) {\\n                    XPath xExclude = dom.createXPath(exclude);\\n                    xExclude.setFunctionContext(functionContext);\\n                    List<org.dom4j.Node> list = xExclude.selectNodes(dom);\\n                    for (org.dom4j.Node n : list) {\\n                        Element parent = n.getParent();\\n                        if (parent != null)\\n                            parent.remove(n);\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n            if (xpath == null) {\\n                result = dom;\\n            } else {\\n                XPath comp = dom.createXPath(xpath);\\n                comp.setFunctionContext(functionContext);\\n                List list = comp.selectNodes(dom);\\n\\n                if (wrapper != null) {\\n                    // check if the wrapper is a valid entity name\\n                    // First position:  letter or underscore\\n                    // Other positions: \\\\w (letter, number, underscore), dash or dot\\n                    String validNameRE = "^[a-zA-Z_][\\\\\\\\w-\\\\\\\\.]*$";\\n\\n                    if (!wrapper.matches(validNameRE)) {\\n                        rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_BAD_REQUEST);\\n                        rsp.getWriter().print(Messages.Api_WrapperParamInvalid());\\n                        return;\\n                    }\\n\\n                    Element root = DocumentFactory.getInstance().createElement(wrapper);\\n                    for (Object o : list) {\\n                        if (o instanceof String) {\\n                            root.addText(o.toString());\\n                        } else {\\n                            root.add(((org.dom4j.Node) o).detach());\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                    result = root;\\n                } else if (list.isEmpty()) {\\n                    rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_NOT_FOUND);\\n                    rsp.getWriter().print(Messages.Api_NoXPathMatch(xpath));\\n                    return;\\n                } else if (list.size() > 1) {\\n                    rsp.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);\\n                    rsp.getWriter().print(Messages.Api_MultipleMatch(xpath, list.size()));\\n                    return;\\n                } else {\\n                    result = list.get(0);\\n                }\\n            }\\n\\n        } catch (DocumentException e) {\\n            LOGGER.log(Level.FINER, "Failed to do XPath/wrapper handling. XML is as follows:" + sw, e);\\n            throw new IOException("Failed to do XPath/wrapper handling. Turn on FINER logging to view XML.", e);\\n        }\\n\\n\\n        if (isSimpleOutput(result) && !permit(req)) {\\n            // simple output prohibited\\n            rsp.sendError(HttpURLConnection.HTTP_FORBIDDEN, "primitive XPath result sets forbidden; implement jenkins.security.SecureRequester");\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        // switch to gzipped output\\n        try (OutputStream o = rsp.getCompressedOutputStream(req)) {\\n            if (isSimpleOutput(result)) {\\n                // simple output allowed\\n                rsp.setContentType("text/plain;charset=UTF-8");\\n                String text = result instanceof CharacterData ? ((CharacterData) result).getText() : result.toString();\\n                o.write(text.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n                return;\\n            }\\n\\n            // otherwise XML\\n            rsp.setContentType("application/xml;charset=UTF-8");\\n            new XMLWriter(o).write(result);\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(457, '\'Map writeValueToImplicitCollection(UnmarshallingContext context, Object value, Map implicitCollections, Object result, String itemFieldName) {\\n        String fieldName = mapper.getFieldNameForItemTypeAndName(context.getRequiredType(), value.getClass(), itemFieldName);\\n        if (fieldName != null) {\\n            if (implicitCollections == null) {\\n                implicitCollections = new HashMap(); // lazy instantiation\\n            }\\n            Collection collection = (Collection) implicitCollections.get(fieldName);\\n            if (collection == null) {\\n                Class fieldType = mapper.defaultImplementationOf(reflectionProvider.getFieldType(result, fieldName, null));\\n                if (!Collection.class.isAssignableFrom(fieldType)) {\\n                    throw new ObjectAccessException("Field " + fieldName + " of " + result.getClass().getName() +\\n                            " is configured for an implicit Collection, but field is of type " + fieldType.getName());\\n                }\\n                if (pureJavaReflectionProvider == null) {\\n                    pureJavaReflectionProvider = new PureJavaReflectionProvider();\\n                }\\n                collection = (Collection) pureJavaReflectionProvider.newInstance(fieldType);\\n                reflectionProvider.writeField(result, fieldName, collection, null);\\n                implicitCollections.put(fieldName, collection);\\n            }\\n            collection.add(value);\\n        }\\n        return implicitCollections;\\n    }\'')]

[(255, '\'void checkTriggers(final Calendar cal) {\\n        Jenkins inst = Jenkins.get();\\n\\n        // Are we using synchronous polling?\\n        SCMTrigger.DescriptorImpl scmd = inst.getDescriptorByType(SCMTrigger.DescriptorImpl.class);\\n        if (scmd.synchronousPolling) {\\n            LOGGER.fine("using synchronous polling");\\n\\n            // Check that previous synchronous polling job is done to prevent piling up too many jobs\\n            if (previousSynchronousPolling == null || previousSynchronousPolling.isDone()) {\\n                // Process SCMTriggers in the order of dependencies. The polling job is submitted only if the previous job has\\n                // terminated.\\n                // FIXME allow to set a global crontab spec\\n                previousSynchronousPolling = scmd.getExecutor().submit(new DependencyRunner(new ProjectRunnable() {\\n                    @Override\\n                    public void run(AbstractProject p) {\\n                        for (Trigger t : (Collection<Trigger>) p.getTriggers().values()) {\\n                            if (t instanceof SCMTrigger) {\\n                                if (t.job != null) {\\n                                    LOGGER.fine("synchronously triggering SCMTrigger for project " + t.job.getName());\\n                                } else {\\n                                    LOGGER.fine("synchronously triggering SCMTrigger for unknown project");\\n                                }\\n                                t.run();\\n                            }\\n                        }\\n                    }\\n                }));\\n            } else {\\n                LOGGER.fine("synchronous polling has detected unfinished jobs, will not trigger additional jobs.");\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Process all triggers, except SCMTriggers when synchronousPolling is set\\n        for (TriggeredItem p : inst.allItems(TriggeredItem.class)) {\\n            LOGGER.finer(() -> "considering " + p);\\n            for (Trigger t : p.getTriggers().values()) {\\n                LOGGER.finer(() -> "found trigger " + t);\\n                if (!(p instanceof AbstractProject && t instanceof SCMTrigger && scmd.synchronousPolling)) {\\n                    if (t != null && t.spec != null && t.tabs != null) {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.FINE, "cron checking {0} with spec ‘{1}’", new Object[]{p, t.spec.trim()});\\n\\n                        if (t.tabs.check(cal)) {\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.CONFIG, "cron triggered {0}", p);\\n                            try {\\n                                long begin_time = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n                                if (t.job == null) {\\n                                    LOGGER.fine(() -> t + " not yet started on " + p + " but trying to run anyway");\\n                                }\\n                                t.run();\\n                                long end_time = System.currentTimeMillis();\\n                                if (end_time - begin_time > CRON_THRESHOLD * 1000) {\\n                                    TriggerDescriptor descriptor = t.getDescriptor();\\n                                    String name = descriptor.getDisplayName();\\n                                    final String msg = String.format("Trigger \\\'%s\\\' triggered by \\\'%s\\\' (%s) spent too much time (%s) in its execution, other timers could be delayed.",\\n                                            name, p.getFullDisplayName(), p.getFullName(), Util.getTimeSpanString(end_time - begin_time));\\n                                    LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, msg);\\n                                    SlowTriggerAdminMonitor.getInstance().report(descriptor.getClass(), p.getFullName(), end_time - begin_time);\\n                                }\\n                            } catch (Throwable e) {\\n                                // t.run() is a plugin, and some of them throw RuntimeException and other things.\\n                                // don\\\'t let that cancel the polling activity. report and move on.\\n                                LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, t.getClass().getName() + ".run() failed for " + p, e);\\n                            }\\n                        } else {\\n                            LOGGER.log(Level.FINER, "did not trigger {0}", p);\\n                        }\\n                    } else {\\n                        LOGGER.log(Level.WARNING, "The job {0} has a syntactically incorrect config and is missing the cron spec for a trigger", p.getFullName());\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\'')]

[(215, '"boolean verifySignature(Signature signature, String providedSignature) {\\n        // We can only make one call to Signature#verify here.\\n        // Since we need to potentially check two values (one decoded from hex, the other decoded from base64),\\n        // try hex first: It\'s almost certainly going to fail decoding if a base64 string was passed.\\n        // It is extremely unlikely for base64 strings to be a valid hex string.\\n        // This way, if it\'s base64, the #verify call will be skipped, and we continue with the #verify for decoded base64.\\n        // This approach might look unnecessarily clever, but short of having redundant Signature instances,\\n        // there doesn\'t seem to be a better approach for this.\\n        try {\\n            if (signature.verify(Hex.decodeHex(providedSignature.toCharArray()))) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        } catch (SignatureException | DecoderException ignore) {\\n            // ignore\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            if (signature.verify(Base64.getDecoder().decode(providedSignature))) {\\n                return true;\\n            }\\n        } catch (SignatureException | IllegalArgumentException ignore) {\\n            // ignore\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }"')]

[(64, '\'void reconnection(boolean webSocket) throws Throwable {\\n        AtomicBoolean canWork = new AtomicBoolean();\\n            rr.then(r -> {\\n                InboundAgentRule.Options.Builder builder = InboundAgentRule.Options.newBuilder().name("remote").secret();\\n                if (webSocket) {\\n                    builder.webSocket();\\n                }\\n                Slave s = inboundAgents.createAgent(r, builder.build());\\n                assertEquals(1, s.getChannel().call(new JVMCount()).intValue());\\n                while (logging.getMessages().stream().noneMatch(msg -> msg.contains("Effective SlaveRestarter on remote:"))) {\\n                    Thread.sleep(100);\\n                }\\n                // Likely true on Unix, likely false on Windows (not under winsw):\\n                canWork.set(logging.getMessages().stream().anyMatch(msg -> msg.contains("Effective SlaveRestarter on remote: [jenkins.slaves.restarter.")));\\n            });\\n            rr.then(r -> {\\n                DumbSlave s = (DumbSlave) r.jenkins.getNode("remote");\\n                r.waitOnline(s);\\n                try {\\n                    assertEquals(canWork.get() ? 1 : 2, s.getChannel().call(new JVMCount()).intValue());\\n                } finally {\\n                    inboundAgents.stop(r, s.getNodeName());\\n                }\\n            });\\n    }\'')]

[(172, "'String applyPatternRepeatedly(@NonNull Pattern pattern, @NonNull String filename,\\n                                  @NonNull Function<String, Character> converter) {\\n        StringBuilder id = new StringBuilder();\\n        int beginIndex = 0;\\n        Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(filename);\\n        while (matcher.find()) {\\n            String group = matcher.group();\\n            id.append(filename, beginIndex, matcher.start());\\n            id.append(converter.apply(group));\\n            beginIndex = matcher.end();\\n        }\\n        id.append(filename.substring(beginIndex));\\n        return id.toString();\\n    }'")]
